   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,217:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I learned the Concorde was designed back in the sixties. Aerodynamics have improved a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,247:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: great deal since then, with computational fluid dynamics. Engine efficiencies have improved
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,265:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: massively. Even if you just change the engines on the Concorde, you could double the range or
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,274:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: thereabouts. I thought, Well, what if we could figure out an efficient design that could make it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,276:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: economically competitive to have a supersonic aircraft? I started looking into it more and did the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,276:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: math on all of it.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,277:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,277:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我了解到协和飞机是在六十年代设计的。从那时起，空气动力学有了很大改进，有了计算流体动力学。发动机效率有了大幅提高。即使你只是更换协和飞机的发动机，你也可以将航程增加一倍左右。我想，好吧，如果我们能想出一个高效的设计，使超音速飞机在经济上具有竞争力呢？我开始更多地研究它，并对所有方面进行了计算。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,278:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,284:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  You can get super efficient and super fast when electric aircraft have vertical takeoff and
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,285:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: landing, and go supersonic. We could make a breakthrough aircraft several generations beyond what
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,285:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: currently exists.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,286:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,286:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  当电动飞机具有垂直起降并达到超音速时，你可以获得超高效率和超高速度。我们可以制造出比现有飞机先进几代的突破性飞机。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,287:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,288:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Diving into SpaceX and Tesla, I had to learn how to make hardware. I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,288:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,289:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: d never seen a CNC
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,290:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: machine or laid out carbon fiber. I didn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,290:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,301:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t know any of those things, but if you read books and talk to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,306:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: experts, you can pick them up quickly. I started going to the Palo Alto public library to read about
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,307:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: rocket engineering and started calling experts, asking to borrow their old engine manuals.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,308:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,308:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  深入 SpaceX 和特斯拉，我必须学习如何制造硬件。我从未见过数控机床或铺设碳纤维。我不知道这些事情，但如果你读书并与专家交谈，你可以快速学会它们。我开始去帕洛阿尔托公共图书馆阅读火箭工程方面的书籍，并开始打电话给专家，请求借阅他们的旧发动机手册。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,309:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,310:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Most people self-limit their ability to learn. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,310:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,311:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s pretty straightforward—just read books and
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,312:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: talk to people.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,312:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,313:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  大多数人自我限制他们的学习能力。这很简单——只要读书并与人交谈。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,313:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,315:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The physics background is helpful as the foundation. But in rocketry I am self-taught,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,315:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: meaning I don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,316:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,316:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t have an aerospace degree. I just read a lot of books and talked to a lot of people.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,317:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,318:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  物理学背景作为基础是有帮助的。但在火箭方面，我是自学成才，意思是我没有航空航天学位。我只是读了很多书并与很多人交谈。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,318:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,322:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Talk to people from different walks of life, in different industries, professions, and skills.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,322:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Try to learn as much as possible. Search for meaning.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,323:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,323:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  与来自不同行业、职业和技能的不同背景的人交谈。尽量多学习。寻找意义。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,324:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: THE VALUE OF ENGINEERING
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,325:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 工程的价值
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,325:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,325:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I spend 80 percent of my time on engineering.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,326:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,326:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我 80% 的时间都花在工程上。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,326:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Engineering Is Magic
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,327:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 工程是魔法
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,327:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,328:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Engineering is, for all intents and purposes, magic, and who wouldn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,328:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,329:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t want to be a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,329:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: magician?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,329:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,330:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  工程，就所有意图和目的而言，就是魔法，谁不想成为魔术师呢？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,330:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,330:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Q: What drew you to engineering?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,331:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,331:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  问：是什么吸引你从事工程？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,332:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,332:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I have a physics background and grew up in an engineering-centric household. I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,333:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,333:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: m still
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,334:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: more an engineer than anything else.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,334:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,335:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我有物理学背景，在一个以工程为中心的家庭中长大。我仍然更多是工程师而不是其他任何身份。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,335:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,340:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  My dad is an extremely talented electrical and mechanical engineer. We built model
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,341:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: airplanes and circuit boards together when I was a kid. He tutored me, and I didn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,341:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,352:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t even know it at
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,360:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the time. I also did things like make model rockets. In South Africa, there were no premade rockets.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,360:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: I had to go to the chemist to get the ingredients for rocket fuel, mix it, and put it in a pipe.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,361:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,361:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我父亲是一位极其有才华的电气和机械工程师。小时候我们一起制作模型飞机和电路板。他辅导我，我当时甚至不知道。我还做过制作模型火箭之类的事情。在南非，没有预制火箭。我必须去药剂师那里获取火箭燃料的成分，混合它，然后把它放进管子里。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,362:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,362:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  There were lots of 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,363:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,363:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: engineery
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,363:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,371:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  things around me. When I asked for an explanation, I got
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,373:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the true explanation of how things work. When I was a little kid, I was really scared of the dark. But
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,373:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: I came to understand 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,374:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,374:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: dark
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,375:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,377:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  just means the absence of photons in the visible wavelength—four hundred
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,378:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: to seven hundred nanometers. I thought, well it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,378:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,379:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s silly to be afraid of a lack of photons. Then I wasn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,379:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,380:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,380:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: afraid of the dark anymore.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,380:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,381:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我周围有很多
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,381:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,382:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 工程类
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,382:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,383:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 的东西。当我要求解释时，我得到了事物如何工作的真实解释。当我还是个小孩时，我真的很害怕黑暗。但我开始理解
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,383:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,383:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 黑暗
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,384:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,384:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 只是意味着可见波长（400 到 700 纳米）没有光子。我想，害怕缺乏光子是愚蠢的。然后我不再害怕黑暗了。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,385:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,389:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I was very technology oriented as a kid growing up in South Africa. With our first
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,390:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: computer came books to teach yourself programming. This was the coolest thing I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,390:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,394:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: d ever seen.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,395:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: When I was about twelve, I started programming and selling my own games to buy new games. I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,396:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: was hooked. I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,396:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,397:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: d spend money on better computers, Dungeons 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,397:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,398:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Dragons modules, and things like
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,399:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: that. I was nerdmaster3000.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,399:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,400:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我在南非长大时非常以技术为导向。我们的第一台电脑附带了自学编程的书籍。这是我见过的最酷的东西。大约十二岁时，我开始编程并出售自己的游戏来买新游戏。我上瘾了。我会花钱买更好的电脑、龙与地下城模组之类的东西。我是 nerdmaster3000。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,400:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,401:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I wasn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,401:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,405:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t that much of a loner, but I was quite bookish. I was reading all the time. I would
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,406:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: be reading, working on my computer, reading comics, that kind of thing.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,407:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,407:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我不是那么孤僻，但我相当书呆子。我一直在阅读。我会读书、用电脑工作、看漫画，类似的事情。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,408:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,408:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  When I was young, I wasn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,409:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,413:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t sure what I was going to do when I got older. I thought the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,414:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: idea of inventing things would be cool, because I read a quote from Arthur C. Clarke: 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,415:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,416:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: A
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,416:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: sufficiently advanced technology is indistinguishable from magic.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,417:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,417:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  That
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,418:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,418:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s really true.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,419:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,419:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  年轻时，我不确定长大后要做什么。我认为发明东西的想法会很酷，因为我读到亚瑟·C·克拉克的一句话：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,420:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,420:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 任何足够先进的技术都与魔法无异。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,421:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,421:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 这真的很对。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,421:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,422:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  If you go back three hundred years, you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,422:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,428:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: d be burned at the stake for things we take for
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,429:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: granted today. Being able to fly is crazy. Being able to see over long distances, communicate, and
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,430:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: instantly access all the world
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,430:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,435:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s information from almost anywhere on the earth. This would all be
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,436:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: considered magic in times past. It actually goes beyond that. Many things we take for granted today
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,437:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: weren
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,437:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,438:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t imagined in times past, even in the realm of magic.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,438:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,438:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  如果回到三百年前，你会因为今天我们视为理所当然的事情而被处以火刑。能够飞行是疯狂的。能够从长距离看东西、交流，并从地球上几乎任何地方立即访问世界上所有信息。这些在过去都会被视为魔法。实际上它超越了这一点。许多我们今天视为理所当然的事情在过去甚至没有在魔法领域被想象过。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,439:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,440:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I thought if I could advance technology, that would be like being a magician. That would
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,441:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: be really cool.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,441:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,441:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我想如果我能推进技术，那就像成为魔术师一样。那会很酷。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,442:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,447:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  At one point, I was thinking about doing physics as a career. But to really advance physics
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,448:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: these days, you need new data. Physics is fundamentally governed by the progress of engineering.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,448:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,448:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  曾经有一段时间，我在考虑将物理学作为职业。但现在要真正推进物理学，你需要新数据。物理学从根本上受工程进步的支配。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,449:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,449:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  There is always debate about, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,450:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,450:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Which is better, engineers or scientists? Aren
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,450:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,451:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t scientists
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,451:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: better? Wasn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,452:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,452:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t Einstein the smartest person?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,452:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,455:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Personally, I think engineering is better because
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,456:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: without engineering, you do not have any new data. You hit a limit.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,457:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,457:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  总是有关于
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,457:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,458:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 哪个更好，工程师还是科学家？科学家不是更好吗？爱因斯坦不是最聪明的人吗？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,458:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,458:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 的辩论。就我个人而言，我认为工程更好，因为没有工程，你就没有任何新数据。你遇到了极限。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,459:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,461:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  You can be smart within the context of the limits of the data you have, but unless you have
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,462:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: a way to get more data, you can
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,462:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,473:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t make progress. Galileo engineered the telescope, which allowed
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,477:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: him to see Jupiter had moons. If you want to advance civilization, you must address the limiting
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,478:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: factor. The limiting factor is the engineering. Therefore, you must address the engineering.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,479:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,479:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  你可以在你拥有的数据限制的范围内聪明，但除非你有办法获得更多数据，否则你无法取得进展。伽利略设计了望远镜，这使他能够看到木星有卫星。如果你想推进文明，你必须解决限制因素。限制因素是工程。因此，你必须解决工程问题。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,480:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,480:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I certainly admire the discoveries of the great scientists. They
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,481:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,482:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re creating a deeper
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,483:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: understanding of how the universe already works. That
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,483:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,484:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s cool—but the universe, in a way, already
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,485:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: knows that. They
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,485:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,485:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re discovering what already exists.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,486:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,486:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我当然钦佩伟大科学家的发现。他们正在创造对宇宙如何运作的更深入理解。这很酷——但宇宙在某种程度上已经知道了。他们在发现已经存在的东西。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,487:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,490:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Science is discovering the essential truths about what exists in the universe. Engineering is
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,490:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: about creating things that have never existed before.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,491:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,491:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  科学是发现关于宇宙中存在的事物的基本真理。工程是关于创造从未存在过的事物。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,492:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Engineering Wins Wars
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,493:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 工程赢得战争
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,493:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,494:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  In Sun Tzu
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,494:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,495:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s The Art of War, there is no chapter on technology. It is an interesting book I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,495:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,496:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ve read many times. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,496:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,497:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s packed with wisdom, but there should be a chapter saying: 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,498:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,500:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: If you have a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,501:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: decisive technological advantage, you can win with minimal casualties to your side.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,501:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,501:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,502:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  在孙子的《孙子兵法》中，没有关于技术的章节。这是一本我读过很多次的有趣的书。它充满了智慧，但应该有一章说：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,503:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,503:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 如果你有决定性的技术优势，你可以以最小的伤亡获胜。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,503:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,504:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,512:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Technology plays a much stronger role in war than is generally understood: technology
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,514:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: viewed in the broadest sense, including a better phalanx, or spears made of bronze, iron, or steel.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,515:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: These can be big differences.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,515:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,516:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  技术在战争中扮演的角色比通常理解的要强得多：从最广泛的意义上看待技术，包括更好的方阵，或由青铜、铁或钢制成的长矛。这些可能是巨大的差异。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,516:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,517:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The Romans won their wars through technology.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,518:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,518:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  罗马人通过技术赢得了战争。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,519:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,529:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  One of the advantages Romans had was good metallurgy. Their swords were martensitic
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,534:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: (an improvement over austenitic metallurgy), so they were stronger. The Romans were often
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,534:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: fighting opponents whose swords would basically bend over a Roman sword. If you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,535:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,536:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re in a sword
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,536:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: fight and your sword bends like a noodle…big disadvantage.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,537:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,537:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  罗马人拥有的优势之一是好冶金。他们的剑是马氏体的（优于奥氏体冶金），所以它们更坚固。罗马人经常与对手的剑基本上会在罗马剑上弯曲的对手作战。如果你在剑战中你的剑像面条一样弯曲……巨大的劣势。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,537:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,539:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The Romans were great engineers. Even things like building roads gave them a military
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,539:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: advantage. If you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,539:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,541:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re trying to march an army somewhere fast, roads beat the heck out of a small
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,541:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: winding path through the forest.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,542:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,542:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  罗马人是伟大的工程师。即使是修路这样的事情也给了他们军事优势。如果你想快速将军队行军到某地，道路胜过穿过森林的小蜿蜒小路。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,543:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,544:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  But when fighting outside the Roman empire, they sometimes lost their wars because of
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,544:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: their opponent
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,544:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,553:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s technology. When the Romans fought the Scythians, they did not have a good
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,556:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: counter to mounted war archers, especially if they got lured into flat terrain. They were pretty much
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,556:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: helpless against the technology of a mounted archer.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,557:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,557:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  但在罗马帝国之外作战时，他们有时会因为对手的技术而输掉战争。当罗马人与斯基泰人作战时，他们没有对付骑马战弓手的好方法，特别是如果他们被引诱到平坦地形时。他们对骑马弓箭手的技术几乎无能为力。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,558:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,558:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  When there
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,558:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,559:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s a rapid change in the rate of technology, engineering plays a pivotal role.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,559:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,560:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  当技术变化率快速时，工程发挥着关键作用。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,560:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,564:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  If there is a big difference in the technologies—even if the other side has more people, better
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,565:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: generals, and is smarter—the side with the advanced technology will win.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,565:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,565:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  如果技术存在巨大差异——即使对方有更多人、更好的将军、更聪明——拥有先进技术的一方将获胜。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,566:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,570:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The technology war of fighters and bombers during World War II is fascinating. The US
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,571:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: completely crushed it on bombers at the end of the war, but they didn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,571:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,576:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t start out that way. At the start
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,577:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: of World War II in the Pacific, entire US squadrons were sometimes shot down with zero Japanese
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,578:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: losses. A total KO.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,578:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,579:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  二战期间战斗机和轰炸机的技术战非常迷人。美国在战争结束时完全碾压了轰炸机，但他们开始时并非如此。在太平洋二战开始时，整个美国中队有时被击落而日本零损失。完全击倒。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,579:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,583:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The US fighters at the beginning of World War II were not good either. Their tactics were
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,583:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: terrible, the aircraft were terrible, and the training was incorrect, too.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,584:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,584:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  美国战斗机在二战开始时也不好。他们的战术很糟糕，飞机很糟糕，训练也不正确。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,585:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,585:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,585:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,592:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s interesting to see where they started out and how fast things innovated. There was
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,594:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: impressive design work by many countries: Japan, the US, Germany, UK, Russia, and others had
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,594:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: some impressive fighter designs.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,595:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,595:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  看看他们从哪里开始以及创新速度有多快是很有趣的。许多国家都有令人印象深刻的设计工作：日本、美国、德国、英国、俄罗斯和其他国家都有一些令人印象深刻的战斗机设计。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,596:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,605:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  It was a constant technological rock-paper-scissors game. One country would make a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,608:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: plane, another made a new plane to beat that one, then another country would make an even newer
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,609:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: plane. What really matters is the pace of innovation.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,609:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,610:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  这是一场持续的技术石头剪刀布游戏。一个国家制造一架飞机，另一个国家制造一架新飞机来击败它，然后另一个国家制造一架更新的飞机。真正重要的是创新速度。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,610:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,616:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  When the rate of change of technology is high enough, or there is a big technological
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,617:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: difference between one side and the other, then that technology dominates and you get a lopsided
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,618:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: victory.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,618:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,618:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  当技术变化率足够高，或一方与另一方之间存在巨大技术差异时，该技术占主导地位，你会获得一边倒的胜利。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,619:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,620:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Many books on the strategy of war actually don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,620:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,627:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t address technology, or do only in a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,630:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: tangential manner. But obviously, if there is an overwhelming technological advantage, that side
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,631:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: will win even if the odds are dramatically stacked against them.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,632:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,632:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  许多关于战争战略的书籍实际上没有涉及技术，或者只是以间接的方式涉及。但显然，如果有压倒性的技术优势，那一方将获胜，即使几率对他们极为不利。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,633:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,640:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  To use an extreme example (a limit case), if you can shoot lasers from space to any spot on
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,641:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the ground by just pointing at it, it would not matter if you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,641:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,643:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re fighting Julius Caesar, Heinz
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,643:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Guderian, or Napoleon. They just got lasered from space.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,644:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,644:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  举一个极端的例子（极限情况），如果你可以从太空向地面上任何地点发射激光，只需指向它，那么你是在与朱利叶斯·凯撒、海因茨·古德里安还是拿破仑作战都无关紧要。他们只是从太空被激光击中了。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,644:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,646:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Most battles in history, because technology moved slowly, were more about maneuvering,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,647:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: tactics, and strategy. But when there
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,647:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,653:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s technological discontinuity, it fundamentally changes the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,654:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: whole situation. Wars in the modern era are very much technology race wars. How fast can we
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,654:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: create new technology?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,655:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,655:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  历史上的大多数战役，因为技术移动缓慢，更多是关于机动、战术和战略。但当存在技术不连续时，它从根本上改变了整个局面。现代战争非常像是技术竞赛战争。我们能多快创造新技术？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,656:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,657:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The best example would be the nuclear bomb. Anyone who made nuclear bombs first,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,657:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: won. That
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,657:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,658:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s it. End of story.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,658:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,658:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  最好的例子是核弹。任何先制造出核弹的人就赢了。就是这样。故事结束。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,659:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,660:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  That was the reason for the US Manhattan Project. People think it was a government
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,660:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: project. I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,661:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,669:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: d like to emphasize that it was a creation of the physics community more than it was the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,672:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: government. The government supported it, but it was a decision and creation from the physics
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,672:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: community. Without them, it would not have happened.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,673:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,673:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  这就是美国曼哈顿计划的原因。人们认为它是一个政府项目。我想强调的是，它更多是物理学界的创造，而不是政府的。政府支持它，但它是物理学界的决定和创造。没有他们，它不会发生。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,673:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,674:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  They simply came to the conclusion that they couldn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,674:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,676:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t let Hitler have the bomb. So they
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,676:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: made it first to be certain of it.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,677:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,677:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  他们只是得出结论，不能让希特勒拥有核弹。所以他们先制造它以确保这一点。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,677:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,678:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  There isn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,678:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,679:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t a better example of a super weapon—anyone who gets it wins.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,679:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,680:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  没有比这更好的超级武器例子了——任何得到它的人就赢了。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,680:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,680:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Play to win, or don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,681:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,681:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t play at all.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,682:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,682:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  为了胜利而战，否则根本不要玩。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,682:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Engineering Creates Value
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,683:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 工程创造价值
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,683:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,687:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  My mind feels like a wild storm. I have a fountain of ideas. I have more ideas than I could
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,688:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: possibly execute. Innovation is not the problem. Execution is the problem.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,688:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,689:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我的头脑感觉像一场狂暴的风暴。我有创意的喷泉。我的想法比我能执行的多得多。创新不是问题。执行是问题。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,689:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,699:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  There is never a shortage of ideas. I find ideas to be somewhat trivial, but the execution of
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,703:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: good ideas is extremely difficult. Prototypes are easy; production is hard. Production and being cash
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,704:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: flow positive is excruciating pain. Product ideas are nearly irrelevant.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,704:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,705:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  想法从来不会短缺。我发现想法有些微不足道，但好想法的执行极其困难。原型很容易；生产很难。生产并实现正现金流是极度痛苦。产品想法几乎无关紧要。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,705:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,706:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  You only build value in a company if you do hard work to solve tough problems. That
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,706:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,707:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,708:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: why companies are valuable. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,708:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,709:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s why they should be valuable, and largely why they are.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,709:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,710:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  你只有在努力解决棘手问题时才能在公司中建立价值。这就是公司有价值的原因。这就是它们应该有价值的理由，也大致是它们有价值的原因。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,710:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,749:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Tesla is a hardcore technology company. We do serious engineering. We do real
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,776:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: manufacturing as well. We do hardcore manufacturing. Coils of aluminum and plastic pellets go into
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,791:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: one end of the factory and cars come out the other. We did all the vehicle engineering, all the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,797:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: powertrain engineering, all the software. The evidence for us solving hard engineering problems is
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,799:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: that Toyota, Daimler, and Mercedes buy electric powertrains from us. If it was easy, they would do
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,799:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: it.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,799:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,800:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  特斯拉是一家硬核技术公司。我们做严肃的工程。我们也做真正的制造。我们做硬核制造。铝卷和塑料颗粒从工厂一端进入，汽车从另一端出来。我们做了所有车辆工程、所有动力系统工程、所有软件。我们解决困难工程问题的证据是丰田、戴姆勒和奔驰从我们这里购买电动动力总成。如果这很容易，他们会自己做。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,800:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,801:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The idea of going to Mars is not hard; that
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,801:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,802:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s irrelevant. Getting to Mars is the hard part.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,802:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,802:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  去火星的想法并不难；那是无关紧要的。到达火星才是困难的部分。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,803:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: PART I 翻译完成 ✅
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,803:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: PART I: PURSUE PURPOSE（追求目标）
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,804:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  已全部翻译完成！
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,804:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 包含章节：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,804:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,805:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: LIVING A PURPOSEFUL LIFE（过有目标的生活）
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,806:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,807:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: THINK LIKE A PHYSICIST（像物理学家一样思考）
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,807:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,807:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: THE VALUE OF ENGINEERING（工程的价值）
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,808:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 下一条消息继续翻译 PART II: ULTRA HARDCORE WORK（极限硬核工作）
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,809:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: PART II: ULTRA HARDCORE WORK
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,809:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 第二部分：极限硬核工作
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,809:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,812:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  To those who quietly help advance the causes we mutually believe in, knowing advancing
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,812:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the cause is the only reward: thank you.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,813:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,813:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  致那些默默帮助我们共同信念的事业前进的人，知道推进事业是唯一的回报：谢谢你们。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,814:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: WHAT IT TAKES
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,814:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 成功所需的条件
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,815:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,815:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  If conventional thinking makes your mission impossible, then unconventional thinking is
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,816:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: necessary.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,816:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,817:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  如果传统思维让你的任务变得不可能，那么非常规思维就是必要的。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,817:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Take Responsibility
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,818:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 承担责任
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,818:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,819:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I am CEO of these companies because I feel I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,819:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,820:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: m responsible for them, not because it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,820:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,821:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,821:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: best thing for my quality of life.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,822:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,822:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我是这些公司的 CEO，因为我觉得我对它们负有责任，不是因为这对我的生活质量是最好的。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,823:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,825:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I want to emphasize that sometimes—in fact, most of the time—I get way too much credit or
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,825:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: attention for what I do. I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,826:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,829:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: m just the visible element. The reason these companies are successful is
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,830:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: because we have extremely talented people at all levels making it happen.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,831:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,831:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我想强调的是，有时——事实上，大多数时候——我因我所做的事情获得了太多的赞誉或关注。我只是可见的元素。这些公司成功的原因是因为我们在各个层面都有极其有才华的人让它实现。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,832:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,832:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I didn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,833:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,847:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t expect to be CEO of these big companies. It just sort of happened that way. It was
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,853:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: never my intent to run Tesla. Running two companies is quite a burden. Sometimes when people
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,854:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: think of being a CEO, they imagine granting themselves lots of vacation and doing fun things. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,854:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: doesn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,855:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,856:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t work that way. What you actually get as CEO is a distillation of the worst things going on in
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,856:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the company.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,856:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,857:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我没想过会成为这些大公司的 CEO。只是碰巧变成了那样。我从未打算经营特斯拉。经营两家公司是相当大的负担。有时当人们想到成为 CEO 时，他们想象给自己很多假期和做有趣的事情。不是那样的。作为 CEO 你实际得到的是公司发生的最糟糕事情的浓缩。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,857:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,858:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Particularly, if you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,858:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,859:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re the CEO, you work on all the worst problems in the company. There
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,859:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,864:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s no point in spending time on things that are going right, so you only spend time on things that are going wrong. Specifically, the things other people can
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,865:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,865:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t fix. The most pernicious and painful problems.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,865:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,866:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  特别是，如果你是 CEO，你处理公司所有最糟糕的问题。花时间在做对的事情上没有意义，所以你只花时间在出错的事情上。具体来说，是其他人无法解决的问题。最有害和最痛苦的问题。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,866:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,867:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Q: How do you manage through failure?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,867:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,867:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  问：你如何度过失败？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,868:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,875:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Managing through big failures is painful and difficult. It feels terrible. The company looks
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,876:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: at me to rally them, so I do. But I feel terrible. Failure is a punch in the gut. Even when you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,876:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,878:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ve got a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,879:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: lot of smart people working super hard to minimize the probability of failure, it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,879:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,880:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s still there. And it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,880:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,880:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,881:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: quite significant.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,881:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,882:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  度过重大失败是痛苦和困难的。感觉很糟糕。公司指望我来鼓舞他们，所以我这样做。但我感觉很糟糕。失败是对肠胃的一拳。即使你有很多聪明人超级努力地工作以最小化失败的概率，它仍然存在。而且相当显著。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,882:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,883:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Given the options, I prefer to learn from success.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,883:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,883:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  在有选择的情况下，我更喜欢从成功中学习。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,884:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Earn Deep Understanding
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,885:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 获得深入理解
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,885:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,891:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I wanted to know how the universe works and how the economy works. So, I studied
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,892:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: physics and economics. You need to be able to bring a lot of people together to create something. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,893:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,894:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,895:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: difficult to do something as just an individual, especially for a significant technology.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,896:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,896:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我想知道宇宙如何运作以及经济如何运作。所以，我学习了物理学和经济学。你需要能够把很多人聚集在一起来创造一些东西。作为个人很难做一些事情，特别是对于重大技术。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,897:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,897:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I was concerned if I didn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,898:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,900:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t study business I would be forced to work for someone who did,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,900:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: because they would know special things I didn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,901:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,901:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t know. I didn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,902:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,903:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t like the sound of that, so I made sure
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,903:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: I knew those things, too.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,904:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,904:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我担心如果我不学习商业，我就会被强迫为学习过商业的人工作，因为他们会知道一些我不知道的特殊事情。我不喜欢那样，所以我确保我也知道那些事情。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,905:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,923:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Physics gave me the basics, a good analytical framework. Physics was rigorous, and we
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,932:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: learned a lot of math. Later, I was in an advanced securities analysis class in the business school,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,934:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: and they were teaching people matrix math. I realized if you can do physics math, then business
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,934:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: math is super easy.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,935:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,935:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  物理学给了我基础知识，一个很好的分析框架。物理学很严谨，我们学了很多数学。后来，我在商学院上了一门高级证券分析课，他们在教人们矩阵数学。我意识到如果你能做物理学数学，那么商业数学就超级简单。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,936:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,938:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  My goals were to engineer products by having a feel for the physics and to never work for
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,938:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: a boss with a business degree.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,939:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,939:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我的目标是通过对物理学的感觉来设计产品，并且永远不为拥有商业学位的老板工作。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,940:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,946:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  One reason SpaceX could move so quickly is I made both the engineering decisions and
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,948:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the spending decisions together in one brain. In most companies, those decisions require at least two
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,948:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: different people.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,949:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,949:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  SpaceX 能够如此快速行动的一个原因是我在一个大脑中同时做出工程决策和支出决策。在大多数公司，这些决策需要至少两个不同的人。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,950:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,950:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  There
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,951:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,951:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s some engineering guy who
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,952:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,954:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s trying to convince a finance guy that this money
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,955:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: should be spent. But the finance guy doesn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,955:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,956:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t understand engineering, so he can
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,956:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,958:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t tell if this is a good
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,958:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: way to spend money or not. Plus, they may not trust each other. I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,959:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,962:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: m making the engineering and
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,962:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: spending decisions together with all the information in one place. My brain trusts itself.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,963:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,963:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  有个工程人员试图说服财务人员这笔钱应该花。但财务人员不懂工程，所以他无法判断这是否是花钱的好方法。而且，他们可能互不信任。我在一个地方拥有所有信息，同时做出工程和支出决策。我的大脑信任它自己。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,964:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,964:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,964:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,965:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: m head engineer, chief designer, and CEO at SpaceX, so I don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,965:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,966:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t have to cave to some
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,967:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: money guy. I encounter CEOs who don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,967:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,967:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t know the details of their technology, and that
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,968:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,968:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s ridiculous
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,968:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: to me.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,969:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,969:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我是 SpaceX 的首席工程师、首席设计师和 CEO，所以我不必向某个财务人员屈服。我遇到过不知道技术细节的 CEO，这对我来说很荒谬。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,970:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,970:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  To make the right decisions, you need to understand something at a detailed level.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,971:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,971:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  要做出正确的决策，你需要在细节层面上理解某事。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,972:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Sleep on the Factory Floor
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,972:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 睡在工厂地板上
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,973:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,973:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,973:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,977:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ve done many many stretches of one-hundred-hour weeks—true one-hundred-hour weeks,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,978:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: sleeping roughly six hours per day. I would not recommend that. That
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,978:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,979:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s for emergencies, not all the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,979:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: time.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,980:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,980:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我做过很多很多段每周一百小时的工作——真正的一百小时周，每天大约睡六小时。我不推荐那样。那是为了紧急情况，不是一直如此。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,980:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,981:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  During difficult times at Tesla I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,981:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,983:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ve had to do it, and sometimes at the beginning of my
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,984:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: earliest startups I did that. I wouldn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,984:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,986:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t leave the office. I would sleep under my desk and work seven
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,986:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: days a week. Sometimes it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,986:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,987:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s necessary for success, or to avoid failure.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,987:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,988:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  在特斯拉困难时期我不得不这样做，有时在我最早的创业初期我也那样做。我不会离开办公室。我会睡在办公桌下，每周工作七天。有时这对成功是必要的，或者为了避免失败。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,988:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,994:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Tesla is pretty far up there in terms of work ethic, anywhere in the world. The Tesla work
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,995:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ethic is substantially greater than any other large car or manufacturing company in the US, that I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,996:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,996:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: m
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,997:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: aware of.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,997:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,997:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  特斯拉在职业道德方面相当靠前，在世界上任何地方都是如此。据我所知，特斯拉的职业道德远超过美国任何其他大型汽车或制造公司。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:51,998:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,008:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  If there was a crisis situation, I slept on the floor. Most of the time I did not sleep in a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,012:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: conference room because people could not see me in the conference room—I slept on the floor in the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,012:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: factory. Otherwise how would people know? They wouldn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,013:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,015:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t. Seeing is believing. I slept on the floor
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,016:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: outside the conference room so they could see I was there.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,016:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,017:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  如果有危机情况，我睡在地板上。大多数时候我不睡在会议室，因为人们在会议室看不到我——我睡在工厂的地板上。否则人们怎么会知道？他们不会。眼见为实。我睡在会议室外的地板上，这样他们就能看到我在那里。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,017:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,030:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  When the team is being asked to work super hard, I have to be right there with them and
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,034:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: they have to see it. If I fall asleep in the middle of the factory floor at four in the morning and wake
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,035:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: up four hours later, they see that. They are like, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,035:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,036:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: If the CEO is willing to take that level of pain, I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,037:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: can do it too.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,037:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,038:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,038:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  当团队被要求超级努力地工作时，我必须和他们在一起，他们必须看到。如果我在凌晨四点睡在工厂地板中间，四小时后醒来，他们会看到。他们会想，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,039:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,039:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 如果 CEO 愿意承受那种程度的痛苦，我也能做到。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,040:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,040:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,044:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  It was a world of hurt. I would wake up smelling like oil and iron filings. It was rough. But
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,044:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: I was asking people to really go all out. I can
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,045:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,045:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t expect them to go all out if I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,046:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,046:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: m not doing the same.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,047:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,047:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  那是一个痛苦的世界。我醒来时身上有油和铁屑的味道。很艰难。但我要求人们真正全力以赴。如果我不这样做，我就不能期望他们全力以赴。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,048:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Frontline Leadership
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,049:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 一线领导力
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,049:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,063:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Think about war. Do you want the general in some ivory tower or on the front lines? The
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,069:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: troops fight harder if they see the general on the front lines. Nobody bleeds for the prince in the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,070:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: palace. Get out there on the front line. Show them that you care and that you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,070:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,071:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re not in some plush
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,071:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: office somewhere.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,071:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,072:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  想想战争。你想要将军在象牙塔里还是在一线？如果士兵看到将军在一线，他们会更努力地战斗。没有人会为宫殿里的王子流血。到一线去。向他们表明你关心，你不在某个舒适的办公室里。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,072:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,074:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  If they see the general out on the battlefield, the troops are going to be motivated.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,074:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Wherever Napoleon was, that
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,074:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,075:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s where his armies would be at their best. Even if I don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,075:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,076:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t do anything
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,076:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: but show up, they
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,077:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,077:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ll look at me and know I wasn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,077:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,078:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t spending all night partying.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,078:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,079:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  如果他们看到将军在战场上，士兵们会受到鼓舞。拿破仑在哪里，他的军队就会在哪里表现最好。即使我什么都不做只是出现，他们会看着我，知道我没有整夜派对。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,079:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,079:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Never ask your troops to do something you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,080:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,083:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re not willing to do. Whatever the people at the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,084:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: front lines are doing, I try to do it at least a few times myself.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,084:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,084:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  永远不要要求你的士兵做你不愿意做的事情。一线人员在做什么，我尽量自己至少做几次。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,085:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,086:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  It is my firm belief that the separation of the workplace into 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,086:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,086:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: executives
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,087:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,087:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  and 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,087:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,088:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: employees
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,088:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,095:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,100:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: does not create a good working environment. We want to create a system of equality without
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,101:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: artificial barriers, so someone can start as a trainee and one day lead the entire company.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,101:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,101:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我坚信将工作场所分为
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,102:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,102:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 高管
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,102:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,103:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 和
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,103:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,103:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 员工
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,104:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,104:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 不会创造良好的工作环境。我们想创造一个平等的制度，没有人为障碍，这样有人可以从实习生开始，有一天领导整个公司。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,105:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,137:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  This is why we eliminate all special privileges of executives. Everyone has equal access to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,157:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: parking, eating at the same tables, and there are no management offices. I am convinced that
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,167:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: managers should work at the forefront, in the same work environment as the entire team. Even
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,169:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: though I run a company, I still do not have my own office and often move my workplace to the most
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,170:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: challenging area in the factory.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,170:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,171:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  这就是为什么我们消除高管的所有特殊特权。每个人都有平等的停车权限，在同一张桌子吃饭，没有管理办公室。我坚信管理者应该在最前沿工作，与整个团队在相同的工作环境中。即使我经营一家公司，我仍然没有自己的办公室，经常把我的工作场所搬到工厂最具挑战性的区域。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,171:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,175:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Managers should always take care of their team before they take care of themselves. The
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,176:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: supervisor is there to serve his team, not the other way round.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,177:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,177:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  管理者应该总是在照顾自己之前先照顾他们的团队。主管在那里服务他的团队，而不是相反。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,178:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,190:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  All technical managers must have hands-on experience. For example, managers of
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,196:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: software teams must spend at least 20 percent of their time coding. Solar roof managers must spend
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,197:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: time on the roofs doing installations. Otherwise, they are like a cavalry leader who can
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,197:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,198:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t ride a horse
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,198:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: or a general who can
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,199:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,199:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t use a sword.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,200:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,200:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  所有技术管理者必须有实践经验。例如，软件团队的管理者必须花费至少 20% 的时间编码。太阳能屋顶管理者必须花时间在屋顶上做安装。否则，他们就像不会骑马的骑兵领袖或不会用剑的将军。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,201:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,202:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Always be smashing your ego. Internalize responsibility. Whether you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,202:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,203:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re a CEO or any
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,204:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: other role, do whatever it takes to succeed.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,204:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,205:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  永远要粉碎你的自我。内化责任。无论你是 CEO 还是任何其他角色，做任何需要的事情来成功。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,205:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,207:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  A major failure mode is a high ego-to-ability ratio. If your ego-to-ability ratio gets too
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,207:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: high, then you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,208:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,208:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ve broken the feedback loop to reality.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,209:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,210:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  一个主要的失败模式是高自我与能力比率。如果你的自我与能力比率变得太高，那么你就破坏了对现实的反馈循环。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,210:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,211:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  In AI terms, you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,211:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,215:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ll break your reinforcement learning (RL) loop. You want to have a strong
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,215:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: RL loop, which means internalizing responsibility and minimizing ego.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,216:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,217:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  用 AI 术语来说，你会破坏你的强化学习（RL）循环。你想要有一个强大的 RL 循环，这意味着内化责任和最小化自我。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,217:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,218:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Do whatever the task is, whether grand or humble.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,218:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,219:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  做任何任务，无论是宏伟还是卑微。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,220:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Adversity Forges Strength
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,220:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 逆境锻造力量
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,221:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,221:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  There is a great quote from Winston Churchill: 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,222:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,222:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: If you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,223:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,223:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re going through hell, keep going.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,223:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,224:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,224:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  温斯顿·丘吉尔有一句名言：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,224:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,225:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 如果你正在经历地狱，继续前进。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,225:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,225:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,226:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Q: Do you think overcoming challenges is something innate in your personality?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,226:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,227:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  问：你认为克服挑战是你性格中固有的东西吗？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,227:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,229:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I was driven as a kid, very willful. One story I remember: At age six, I was grounded for
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,229:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: some reason. I don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,229:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,230:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t remember why, but I felt it was unjust. I really wanted to go to my cousin
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,230:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,232:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,232:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: birthday party. I escaped from my nanny and walked across the city.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,233:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,233:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我小时候很有动力，非常任性。我记得一个故事：六岁时，我因为某种原因被禁足。我不记得为什么，但我觉得这不公正。我真的很想去参加我表哥的生日派对。我从保姆那里逃出来，穿过了城市。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,234:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,242:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I was just learning to read, so I could barely read the road signs. This was foolish, and
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,245:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: something terrible could have happened. But I was so determined I walked clear across the capital
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,246:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: city of South Africa at six years old.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,246:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,247:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我刚刚学习阅读，所以我几乎看不懂路标。这很愚蠢，可能发生可怕的事情。但我如此决心，六岁时我走遍了南非首都。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,247:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,263:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  It was ten or twelve miles, much farther than I realized, and it took me about four hours.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,269:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: As my mom was leaving the party with my brother and sister, she saw me walking down the road
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,270:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: and freaked out. So I climbed a tree and refused to come down until she promised not to punish me.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,270:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,271:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  那是十到十二英里，比我意识到的远得多，花了我大约四个小时。当我妈妈带着我的兄弟姐妹离开派对时，她看到我走在路上，吓坏了。所以我爬上一棵树，拒绝下来，直到她答应不惩罚我。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,271:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,272:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I seem to have a high, innate drive, and that
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,272:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,273:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s been true even since I was a little kid.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,273:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,274:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我似乎有很高的先天驱动力，这从我小时候就是如此。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,274:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,275:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  When I was five or six, I thought I was insane. It became clear other people
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,275:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,276:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s minds weren
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,276:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,277:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t exploding with ideas all the time. I felt strange. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,278:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,279:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s hard to turn it off. It might sound great when it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,280:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: is on. But what if it doesn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,280:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,281:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t turn off? It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,281:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,282:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s like a never-ending explosion.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,282:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,283:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  当我五六岁时，我以为我疯了。很明显其他人的头脑不会一直充满想法。我感觉很奇怪。很难关掉它。当它开启时可能听起来很棒。但如果它不关闭呢？这就像一场永无止境的爆炸。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,283:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,286:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I was the youngest kid in my grade, so I was quite small. I was kind of a smart aleck, too.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,286:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: It was a recipe for disaster. I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,287:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,289:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: d get called every name in the book and beaten up. Being small and
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,289:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: having violent bullies is a bad situation.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,290:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,290:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我是年级里最小的孩子，所以我很小。我也有点自作聪明。这是灾难的配方。我会被骂遍所有难听的话并被殴打。个子小又有暴力的霸凌者是个糟糕的情况。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,291:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,291:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  There was a level of violence in my childhood that wouldn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,292:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,305:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t be tolerated in any American
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,313:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: school. It was like Lord of the Flies. There were a couple of gangs that were pretty evil, and I was
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,315:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: one of their chosen victims. Partly because I stuck up for another kid they were relentless on, that
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,316:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: made me a target.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,316:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,317:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我童年时期有一定程度的暴力，这在美国任何学校都不会被容忍。这就像《蝇王》。有几个相当邪恶的帮派，我是他们选定的受害者之一。部分因为我保护另一个被他们无情对待的孩子，这让我成为了目标。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,317:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,319:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The place where I grew up in South Africa was very violent. Fighting was normal, it was
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,320:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: part of the culture. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,320:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,321:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ll certainly toughen you up; that
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,321:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,322:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s for sure. I was in a lot of fights I didn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,322:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,326:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t want
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,328:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: to be in. I got beaten up really badly in a few of them. I was in real hardcore street fights, from about
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,328:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: six to sixteen.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,329:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,330:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我在南非长大的地方非常暴力。打架是正常的，它是文化的一部分。这肯定会让你变得坚强；这是肯定的。我参加了很多我不想参加的打架。其中有几次我被打得很惨。我经历了真正的硬核街头斗殴，从大约六岁到十六岁。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,330:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,331:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I was almost beaten to death—within an inch of my life at one point.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,331:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,332:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我几乎被打死——有一次只差一英寸就死了。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,332:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,335:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I got to a reasonably good size around fifteen, and around sixteen they stopped trying to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,335:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: beat me up, because it didn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,336:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,336:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t work out so well for them anymore.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,336:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,337:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我在十五岁左右长得相当壮实，大约十六岁时他们不再试图打我，因为那对他们来说不再那么顺利了。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,337:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,337:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  People say they
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,338:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,340:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re worried about the damage of words. People worried about words have
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,340:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: never been punched in the face. Once you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,341:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,341:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ve been punched in the face, real hard, right on the nose—you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,341:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,342:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ll take any words over that.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,342:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,343:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  人们说他们担心言语的伤害。担心言语的人从未被打过脸。一旦你被狠狠地打在脸上，正好打在鼻子上——你会选择任何言语而不是那个。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,343:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,344:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Adversity shaped me. My pain threshold became very high.
