   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,418:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  如果你不吃玻璃，你就不会成功。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,419:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,420:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Q: How do you keep your focus on the big picture when you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,420:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,421:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re constantly faced with being
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,422:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: bankrupt in a month?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,422:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,423:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  问：当你不断面临一个月内破产时，你如何保持对大局的关注？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,423:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,424:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  A very small percentage of mental energy is spent on the big picture. You know where you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,425:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,425:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re generally heading, and the actual path is going to be a zigzag in that direction. You
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,426:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,428:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re trying not
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,429:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: to deviate too far from the path you want to be on, but you have to, to some degree.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,429:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,430:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  只有很小比例的精神精力花在大局上。你知道你大致要去哪里，实际路径会是在那个方向上的之字形。你试图不偏离你想走的路太远，但你必须在某种程度上这样做。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,430:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,450:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Failure is not good. Failure is bad. But if something is important enough, then you do it,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,459:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: even though the risk of failure is high. My advice for somebody who wants to start a company: Bear
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,461:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: in mind, the most likely outcome is failure. Reconcile yourself to that strong possibility, and only if
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,462:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: you still feel compelled to, do it.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,462:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,463:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  失败不好。失败是坏事。但如果某事足够重要，那么你就去做，即使失败的风险很高。我对想创办公司的人的建议：记住，最可能的结果是失败。让自己接受那种强烈的可能性，只有如果你仍然感到有冲动，才去做。
