   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,466:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re not gonna die of exposure—really, what
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,467:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,467:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s the worst
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,468:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: that could happen?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,468:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,468:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  话虽如此，许多人过于害怕创办公司。最坏的情况是什么？你不会饿死；你不会冻死——真的，最坏的情况是什么？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,469:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: BUILDING EXCEPTIONAL TEAMS
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,469:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 打造卓越团队
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,470:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,473:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The most important thing is to attract great people. Whether you are creating a company or
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,474:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: joining a company, find an amazing group that you really respect.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,474:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,475:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  最重要的是吸引优秀的人。无论你是在创建公司还是加入公司，找到一个你真正尊敬的惊人团队。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,475:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: A Group with a Goal
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,476:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 有目标的团队
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,476:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,477:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  A company is just a bunch of people coming together to create a product or service. There
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,477:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,478:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s no such thing as 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,478:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,479:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: a business,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,479:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,480:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  just a group pursuing a goal.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,480:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,480:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  公司只是一群人聚在一起创造产品或服务。没有
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,481:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,481:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 企业
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,482:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,482:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 这种东西，只是一个追求目标的群体。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,482:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,487:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  How talented and hardworking that group is, and the degree to which they are focused
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,488:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: cohesively in a good direction, will determine the success of the company. If you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,488:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,489:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re creating a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,489:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: company, or if you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,490:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,490:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re joining a company, the most important thing is to attract great people.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,491:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,491:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  这个团队有多么有才华和勤奋，以及他们在多大程度上凝聚在一个好的方向上，将决定公司的成功。如果你在创建公司，或者如果你在加入公司，最重要的是吸引优秀的人。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,492:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,494:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  A company is essentially a cybernetic collective of people and machines. This collective is
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,494:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: far smarter than an individual.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,495:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,495:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  公司本质上是一个人和机器的控制论集体。这个集体远比个人聪明。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,496:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,496:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  That
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,497:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,498:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s what a company is, and there are different levels of complexity in the way
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,498:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: companies are formed.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,499:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,499:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  这就是公司是什么，公司形成的方式有不同层次的复杂性。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,500:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,500:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Obviously, one person can
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,501:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,502:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t build a whole rocket, engines, launchpad, and everything. That
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,502:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,512:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s impossible. We have thousands of people at SpaceX. By piecing it out to different people and
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,516:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: using our collection of computers, tools, and machines we can make lots of rockets, launch them
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,517:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: into orbit, dock with the International Space Station, and more.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,517:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,518:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  显然，一个人不能建造整个火箭、发动机、发射台和所有东西。那是不可能的。我们在 SpaceX 有数千人。通过将其分配给不同的人并使用我们的计算机、工具和机器集合，我们可以制造很多火箭，将它们发射到轨道上，与国际空间站对接，等等。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,518:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,525:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  People sometimes forget a company is just a group of people gathered together to make
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,526:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: products for fellow human beings. As long as they make great products, the company will have great
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,526:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: value.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,526:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,527:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  人们有时会忘记公司只是一群人聚集在一起为其他人类制造产品。只要他们制造出伟大的产品，公司就会有巨大的价值。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,527:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,535:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  To create a company, you have to convince others to join you in your effort. You have to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,537:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: convince them there is a reasonable chance of success and if there is success, the reward will be
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,537:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: commensurate with the effort.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,537:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,538:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  要创建公司，你必须说服其他人加入你的努力。你必须说服他们有一个合理的成功机会，如果有成功，回报将与努力相称。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,538:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,538:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  If you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,539:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,540:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re going to create a company, the first thing you should try to do is create a working
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,540:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: prototype.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,540:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,541:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  如果你要创建公司，你应该尝试做的第一件事是创建一个可工作的原型。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,541:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,550:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  When starting a company, create a demonstration, a mock-up, or a sketch. This helps
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,552:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: people envision it. Try to get to that point as soon as possible, then iterate to make it as real as
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,552:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: possible as fast as possible.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,553:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,553:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  创办公司时，创建一个演示、模型或草图。这有助于人们设想它。尽快达到那个点，然后迭代使其尽可能真实、尽可能快。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,554:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,554:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  It doesn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,554:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,559:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t sink in for people until you actually have a physical object they can use. Even
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,559:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: when you can show something works on paper, and the calculations are clear, it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,560:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,560:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s not the same.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,560:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,561:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  直到你真正有一个他们可以使用的实物，人们才会理解。即使你能在纸上展示某些东西可行，计算也很清楚，但这是不一样的。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,561:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,564:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Anything can look good on PowerPoint. If you have an actual demonstration, even in
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,565:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: primitive form, it is much more effective in convincing people.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,565:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,566:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  任何事情在 PowerPoint 上看起来都可以很好。如果你有一个实际的演示，即使是原始形式，它在说服人们方面也要有效得多。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,566:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,567:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Fundamentally, if you don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,567:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,568:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t have a compelling product at a compelling price, you don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,568:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,569:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,569:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: have a great company.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,569:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,570:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  从根本上说，如果你没有一个在价格上有吸引力的引人注目的产品，你就没有一家伟大的公司。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,570:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Create a Culture of Builders
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,571:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 创造建造者文化
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,571:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,573:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I consider one of my core responsibilities as CEO is to have an environment where great
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,573:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: engineers can flourish.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,574:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,574:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我认为我作为 CEO 的核心职责之一是创造一个让优秀工程师能够茁壮成长的环境。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,575:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,575:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,576:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,578:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t think I manage smart people; they manage themselves. If someone is smart and
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,579:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: talented, they can go anywhere and do anything, anytime.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,579:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,580:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我不认为我管理聪明人；他们管理自己。如果有人聪明且有才华，他们可以随时去任何地方做任何事情。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,580:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,581:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I say, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,581:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,582:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Look, this is the goal we
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,582:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,583:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re after. Do you agree with this goal? If you do, then let
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,583:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,584:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,584:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: try to get it done.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,585:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,585:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,586:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我说，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,586:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,587:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 看，这就是我们追求的目标。你同意这个目标吗？如果同意，那么让我们努力完成它。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,587:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,588:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,588:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,588:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,589:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ll provide my opinion along the way. But it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,589:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,591:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s rare for me to actually insist on a particular
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,592:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: thing. Once in a while I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,592:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,592:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ll say, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,593:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,597:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: You have to trust me on this one. We have to do this, and if it turns
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,598:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: out to be a bad decision, we can all hold it against me in the future.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,598:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,599:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,599:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我会在此过程中提供我的意见。但我很少真正坚持某件特定的事情。偶尔我会说，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,600:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,600:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 这件事你必须相信我。我们必须这样做，如果结果证明这是一个糟糕的决定，我们将来都可以怪我。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,601:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,601:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,609:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Another important principle: You want everyone to be able to think like the chief engineer.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,610:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: They need to understand the system at a high level, well enough to know when they are making a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,611:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: bad optimization.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,611:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,611:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  另一个重要原则：你希望每个人都能够像首席工程师一样思考。他们需要在高层次上理解系统，足够好地知道他们何时在做糟糕的优化。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,612:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,616:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Since a company is a group of people assembled to create a product or service, the ability
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,617:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: to attract and motivate great people is critical to the success of a company. That
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,618:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,619:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s the purpose of a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,619:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: company. People sometimes forget this elementary truth.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,620:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,620:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  由于公司是一群聚集在一起创造产品或服务的人，吸引和激励优秀人才的能力对公司的成功至关重要。这就是公司的目的。人们有时会忘记这个基本真理。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,620:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,621:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  If you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,621:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,635:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re able to get talented, hard-working people to join the company, work together, and
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,641:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: have a relentless sense of perfection toward a common goal, you will end up with a great product. If
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,641:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: you have a great product, lots of people will buy it, and the company will be successful.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,642:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,642:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  如果你能够让有才华、勤奋的人加入公司，一起工作，并对共同目标有不懈的完美追求，你最终会得到一个伟大的产品。如果你有一个伟大的产品，很多人会购买它，公司就会成功。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,642:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,643:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  That
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,643:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,653:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s why our most important consideration is recruiting the best people. The output of
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,657:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: any company is the vector sum of the people within it. If we attract the most talented people over
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,657:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: time and our direction is correctly aligned, we will prevail.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,658:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,658:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  这就是为什么我们最重要的考虑是招聘最优秀的人。任何公司的产出都是其中人员的矢量和。如果我们随着时间的推移吸引最有才华的人，并且我们的方向正确对齐，我们将获胜。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,658:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,660:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  A small group of technically strong people will always beat a large group of moderately
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,660:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: strong people.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,660:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,661:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  一小群技术强大的人总是会击败一大群中等强大的人。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,661:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,672:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  What you see at SpaceX is the result of an incredible team. Supertalented people who work
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,676:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: like crazy to advance technology. They make this happen. My role is to make sure they have an
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,676:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: environment where their talents can come to the fore. I can
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,677:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,678:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t tell you how honored and grateful I am
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,679:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: to work with such a great team.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,679:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,680:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  你在 SpaceX 看到的是令人难以置信的团队的结果。超级有才华的人疯狂地工作以推进技术。他们让这成为现实。我的角色是确保他们有一个能让他们的才能脱颖而出的环境。我无法告诉你与这样伟大的团队一起工作我感到多么荣幸和感激。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,680:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,681:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Do everything you can to gather great people.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,681:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,681:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  尽一切努力聚集优秀的人。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,682:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,683:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Many companies suppress their talented, driven engineers. Some are suppressed by being
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,684:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: so comfortable they don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,684:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,690:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t produce much. There are a few places in Silicon Valley with good
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,692:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: engineers—but what are they producing? The output of that engineering talent seems low, though maybe
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,693:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: they are enjoying themselves.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,693:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,694:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  许多公司压制他们有才华、有动力的工程师。有些人因为太舒适而被压制，他们产出不多。硅谷有几个地方有好的工程师——但他们在生产什么？那些工程人才的产出似乎很低，尽管也许他们很享受。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,694:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,695:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Tesla is not like that. We
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,695:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,695:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re demanding. You
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,696:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,696:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re going to get a lot done and it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,697:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,697:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s going to be
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,698:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: cool work, but it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,698:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,699:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s not going to be easy. At Tesla, a superb engineer
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,699:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,700:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s talents are used to a greater
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,701:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: degree than anywhere else.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,701:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,702:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  特斯拉不是那样的。我们要求很高。你会完成很多工作，这会很酷，但不会容易。在特斯拉，优秀工程师的才能比在任何其他地方都得到更大程度的发挥。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,702:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,705:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Tesla has been like a whole series of startups. So far almost all have been quite successful,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,705:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: so we must be doing something right.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,706:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,706:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  特斯拉就像一系列初创公司。到目前为止，几乎所有都相当成功，所以我们一定在做一些正确的事情。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,707:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,707:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Only exceptional performance constitutes a passing grade.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,708:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,708:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  只有卓越的表现才算及格。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,709:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Recruit for Exceptional Ability
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,710:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 招聘非凡能力
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,710:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,711:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  When hiring, I look for evidence of exceptional ability, or at least exceptional aspiration.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,711:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,712:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  招聘时，我寻找非凡能力的证据，或者至少非凡的抱负。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,712:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,713:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Sometimes these things get messed up in recruiting. I sometimes wonder, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,713:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,714:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: If Nikola Tesla
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,715:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: applied to Tesla, would we even give him an interview?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,715:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,716:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,716:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,716:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s not clear. They might say, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,717:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,718:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: This guy
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,718:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: came from some weird college in Eastern Europe, he
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,719:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,719:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s got some odd mannerisms, we don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,719:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,720:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t know if
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,721:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: we should give him an interview.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,721:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,721:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I worry that
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,722:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,722:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s what we
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,722:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,723:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: d do. Our response should be, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,723:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,724:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Man,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,724:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Nikola Tesla, this kid
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,724:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,725:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s super smart. What does he want? We
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,725:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,726:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ll pay him anything
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,726:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: !
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,726:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,727:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,727:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  有时这些事情在招聘中会搞砸。我有时会想，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,728:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,728:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 如果尼古拉·特斯拉申请特斯拉，我们会给他面试机会吗？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,728:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,729:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 这不清楚。他们可能会说，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,729:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,729:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 这家伙来自东欧某个奇怪的大学，他有一些奇怪的举止，我们不知道是否应该给他面试。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,730:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,730:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 我担心我们会那样做。我们的反应应该是，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,731:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,731:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 天哪，尼古拉·特斯拉，这家伙超级聪明。他想要什么？我们愿意付他任何报酬！
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,731:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,732:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,734:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I always ask my teams to give a lot of thought to who should join. I recommend paying
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,734:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: close attention to people who haven
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,735:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,738:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t completed their grad or even undergrad, but are obviously
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,738:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: brilliant. Better to have them join before they achieve a breakthrough.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,739:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,739:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我总是要求我的团队认真思考谁应该加入。我建议密切关注那些没有完成研究生甚至本科，但显然很聪明的人。最好在他们取得突破之前让他们加入。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,740:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,740:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  You
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,741:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,743:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ve got to be willing to recruit hard for excellent people. When I was interviewing
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,744:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Bülent Altan for SpaceX, I told him, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,744:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,744:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: I heard you don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,745:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,748:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t want to move to Los Angeles because your
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,749:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: wife works for Google in San Francisco. Well, I just talked to Larry Page, and they
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,749:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,751:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re going to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,752:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: transfer your wife down to LA. So what are you going to do now?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,752:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,753:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  He said he would come work for
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,754:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: SpaceX.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,754:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,754:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  你必须愿意努力招聘优秀的人。当我为 SpaceX 面试布伦特·阿尔坦时，我告诉他，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,755:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,755:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 我听说你不想搬到洛杉矶，因为你的妻子在旧金山为谷歌工作。好吧，我刚刚和拉里·佩奇谈过，他们会把你的妻子调到洛杉矶。那你现在要做什么？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,756:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,756:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 他说他会来为 SpaceX 工作。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,757:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,760:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I have a great ability to tell if someone is a good engineer or not. And I am good at
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,761:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: optimizing the efficiency of an engineering team. It helps that I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,762:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,762:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: m quite good at engineering in
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,763:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: general.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,763:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,764:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我有很强的能力判断某人是否是好的工程师。我擅长优化工程团队的效率。一般来说，我很擅长工程，这很有帮助。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,764:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,771:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  In interviews, I ask people to tell me the story of their career and some of the tougher
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,773:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: problems they dealt with, how they dealt with those, and how they made decisions at key transition
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,773:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: points. Usually that
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,774:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,775:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s enough for me to get a good gut feeling about someone. What I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,775:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,777:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: m really
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,778:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: looking for is evidence of exceptional ability. Did they face difficult problems and overcome them?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,779:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,780:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  在面试中，我要求人们告诉我他们职业生涯的故事以及他们处理的一些更棘手的问题，他们如何处理这些问题，以及他们如何在关键转折点做出决策。通常这足以让我对某人有一个好的直觉。我真正寻找的是非凡能力的证据。他们是否面临困难问题并克服了它们？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,780:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,781:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Usually the person who had to struggle with the problem really understands it and they don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,781:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,782:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t forget if it was difficult. Ask them detailed questions about it, and they
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,783:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,785:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ll know the answers. A
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,786:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: person who was not responsible for that accomplishment will not know the details.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,786:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,787:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  通常，不得不与问题斗争的人真正理解它，他们不会忘记是否困难。问他们关于它的详细问题，他们会知道答案。一个不对该成就负责的人不会知道细节。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,788:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Retain Only Special Forces
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,788:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 只保留特种部队
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,789:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,793:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I worked very hard to collect the right expertise when starting SpaceX. I tried hard to find
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,794:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: a great chief engineer for the rocket, but good chief engineers wouldn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,794:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,801:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t join and there is no point in
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,805:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: hiring the bad ones. I ended up being chief engineer of the rocket. If I could have found somebody
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,806:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: better, maybe we would have had fewer than three failures.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,806:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,807:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  创办 SpaceX 时，我非常努力地收集正确的专业知识。我努力想为火箭找到一位伟大的首席工程师，但好的首席工程师不愿意加入，雇佣差的也没有意义。我最终成为了火箭的首席工程师。如果我能找到更好的人，也许我们的失败会少于三次。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,808:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,809:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Wherever the smartest, most driven people are choosing to work, that company is going to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,809:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: win.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,810:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,810:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  无论最聪明、最有动力的人选择在哪里工作，那家公司都会获胜。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,811:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,812:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  My philosophy for companies in the startup phase is a 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,812:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,813:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Special Forces
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,813:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,814:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  approach. The
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,815:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: minimum passing grade is excellent. I believe that
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,815:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,815:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s the culture companies need to have if they
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,816:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,816:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,816:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: going to become successful.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,817:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,817:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我对初创阶段公司的理念是
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,817:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,818:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 特种部队
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,818:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,818:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 方法。最低及格分数是优秀。我相信这是公司要想成功必须拥有的文化。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,819:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,819:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Q: Is building great teams and products just a question of being well funded?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,820:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,820:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  问：打造伟大团队和产品只是资金充足的问题吗？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,820:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,821:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,821:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,822:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s not like if we just had more money we could spend it effectively on R
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,822:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,822:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: D. That
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,823:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,825:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s not
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,827:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: how it works. If there was a factory producing excellent engineers, that would be true. Except this
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,827:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: factory doesn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,827:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,828:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t exist. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,828:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,831:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s incredibly difficult to find the right talent, integrate them into an
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,832:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: organization, and have it work effectively. Money is not the constraint.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,832:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,833:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  不是像如果我们有更多钱就能有效地花在研发上那样。不是那样运作的。如果有一个工厂生产优秀工程师，那会是真的。但这个工厂不存在。找到合适的人才，将他们整合到组织中，并使其有效运作是极其困难的。钱不是限制。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,833:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,834:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  There are only a small number of excellent people, and they
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,834:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,841:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re hard to find. Engineers
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,844:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: especially. At the end of the day, the competitiveness of any company is a function of the most
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,844:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: talented and driven people. That is the team that
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,845:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,845:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s going to win.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,846:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,846:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  只有少数优秀的人，他们很难找到。尤其是工程师。归根结底，任何公司的竞争力都是最有才华和最有动力的人的函数。那就是会获胜的团队。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,846:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,847:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The fundamental limitation is exceptional engineers. There are not that many.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,848:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,848:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  根本限制是卓越的工程师。没有那么多。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,848:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,853:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Having a strong sense of purpose will attract the very best talent in the world. If the work
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,854:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: is enjoyable, the financial rewards are good, and the product will change the world—that
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,854:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,855:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s a pretty
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,856:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: powerful set of motivators.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,856:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,856:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  拥有强烈的目标感将吸引世界上最优秀的人才。如果工作令人愉快，财务回报丰厚，产品将改变世界——这是一套非常强大的激励因素。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,857:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,857:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,858:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,863:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ve made several hiring decisions where I valued intellect over heart and I think that was a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,864:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: mistake. I have tried to adjust accordingly. It matters whether somebody is a good person.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,864:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,865:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我曾做过几次招聘决定，我看重智力胜过品格，我认为那是个错误。我试图相应地调整。某人是否是好人很重要。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,865:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,866:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  One test for assessing someone
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,866:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,873:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s character is to look at the character of their friends and
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,876:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: associates. While people can put up a mask themselves for their character, their friends and
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,876:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: associates will not. You can judge a person
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,877:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,880:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s character by their associates and to some degree by
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,881:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: their enemies. If evil people hate you, you might be doing something right.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,881:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,882:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  评估某人品格的一个测试是看他们的朋友和同事的品格。虽然人们可以为自己的品格戴上面具，但他们的朋友和同事不会。你可以通过一个人的同事来判断他的品格，在某种程度上也可以通过他的敌人。如果邪恶的人恨你，你可能在做一些正确的事情。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,882:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,884:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  When hiring, look for people with the right attitude. Skills can be taught. Attitude changes
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,885:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: require a brain transplant.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,885:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,886:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  招聘时，寻找态度正确的人。技能可以教授。态度改变需要大脑移植。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,886:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Feedback over Feelings
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,887:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 反馈胜过感受
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,887:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,888:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Physics does not care about hurt feelings. It cares about whether you got the rocket right.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,889:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,889:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  物理学不在乎受伤的感情。它在乎你是否把火箭做对了。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,890:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,890:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  All bad news should be given loudly and often. Good news can be said quietly and once.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,891:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,891:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  所有坏消息都应该大声且经常地传达。好消息可以安静地说一次。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,892:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,905:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I give people hardcore feedback, but I try to always focus on the substance of the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,913:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: discussion. I try to criticize the action, not the person. We all make mistakes. What matters is
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,914:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: whether a person has a good feedback loop, can seek criticism from others, and can improve.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,914:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,915:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我给人们硬核的反馈，但我尽量总是关注讨论的实质。我尽量批评行为，而不是人。我们都会犯错。重要的是一个人是否有良好的反馈循环，能否寻求他人的批评，并能否改进。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,915:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,915:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,916:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,916:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s not your job to make people on your team love you. In fact, that
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,916:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,918:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s counterproductive. I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,919:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: had a manager who would not fire anyone. I told him, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,919:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,919:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: You can
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,919:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,921:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t tell people they have to get their
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,921:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: shit together, and when they don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,921:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,922:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t get their shit together—nothing happens to them.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,922:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,922:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,923:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  让你的团队成员爱你不是你的工作。事实上，那会适得其反。我有一个经理不愿意解雇任何人。我告诉他，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,923:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,924:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 你不能告诉人们他们必须振作起来，而当他们没有振作起来时——对他们没有任何后果。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,924:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,924:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,925:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Camaraderie is dangerous. It makes it hard for people to challenge each other
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,925:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,929:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s work.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,930:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: There is a tendency to not want to throw a colleague under the bus. That needs to be avoided.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,931:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Wanting to be everyone
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,931:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,941:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s friend leads you to care too much about the emotions of the individual in
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,945:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: front of you rather than caring about the success of the whole enterprise. Focusing on that one
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,945:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: individual can lead to a far greater number of people being hurt.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,946:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,946:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  友情是危险的。它使人们难以挑战彼此的工作。有一种倾向是不想把同事推到车下。这需要避免。想成为每个人的朋友会导致你过于关心面前个人的情绪，而不是关心整个企业的成功。专注于那一个人可能导致更多的人受到伤害。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,947:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,947:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I think it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,947:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,948:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s a real weakness to want to be liked. A real weakness. And I do not have that.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,949:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,949:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我认为想被喜欢是一个真正的弱点。一个真正的弱点。而我没有那个。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,949:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: DESIGNING THE ORGANIZATION
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,950:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 设计组织
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,950:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,951:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  It must be okay for people to talk directly and make the right thing happen.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,952:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,952:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  人们必须能够直接交谈并让正确的事情发生。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,952:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Remove Organizational Boundaries
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,953:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 消除组织边界
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,953:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,954:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  In any product, you can see the errors in the organization
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,954:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,955:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s structure. They will manifest
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,956:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: themselves in the product.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,956:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,957:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  在任何产品中，你都能看到组织结构中的错误。它们会在产品中表现出来。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,957:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,961:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  A major source of issues is poor communication between departments. The way to solve
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,961:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: this is to allow free flow of information between all levels.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,962:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,962:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  问题的一个主要来源是部门之间沟通不畅。解决这个问题的方法是允许信息在所有层级之间自由流动。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,963:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,980:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  There are two schools of thought about how information should flow within companies.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,993:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The most common way is chain of command. That means you always flow communication through
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,996:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: your manager. The problem with this approach is that, while it serves to enhance the power of the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,997:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: manager, it fails to serve the company.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,997:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,998:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  关于信息如何在公司内部流动有两种思想流派。最常见的方式是指挥链。这意味着你总是通过你的经理进行沟通。这种方法的问题是，虽然它有助于增强经理的权力，但它不能为公司服务。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:52,998:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,028:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  If, in order to get something done between departments, an individual contributor has to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,043:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: talk to their manager, who talks to a director, who talks to a VP, who talks to another VP, who talks
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,050:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: to a director, who talks to a manager, who talks to someone doing the actual work, then superdumb
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,050:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: things will happen. Then the info has to flow back the other way again. This is incredibly dumb.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,051:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,052:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  如果为了在部门之间完成某事，一个个人贡献者必须与他们的经理交谈，经理与总监交谈，总监与副总裁交谈，副总裁与另一个副总裁交谈，另一个副总裁与总监交谈，总监与经理交谈，经理与做实际工作的人交谈，那么超级愚蠢的事情会发生。然后信息必须再以相反的方式流回。这非常愚蠢。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,052:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,069:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Problems get solved quickly when a person just talks to a person in another department and
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,077:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: makes the right thing happen. Anyone can and should talk to anyone else according to what they
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,078:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: think is the fastest way to solve a problem for the benefit of the whole company. You can talk to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,079:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: your manager
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,079:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,081:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s manager without his permission. You can talk directly to a VP in another
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,081:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: department. You can talk to me.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,081:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,082:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  当一个人只是与另一个部门的人交谈并让正确的事情发生时，问题会迅速解决。任何人都可以且应该与其他任何人交谈，按照他们认为对整个公司最有利的最快方式解决问题。你可以在没有经理许可的情况下与你经理的经理交谈。你可以直接与另一个部门的副总裁交谈。你可以与我交谈。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,082:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,084:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Communication should travel via the shortest path necessary to get the job done, not
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,084:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: through the 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,084:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,085:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: chain of command.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,085:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,085:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,086:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  沟通应该通过完成工作所需的最短路径进行，而不是通过
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,086:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,086:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 指挥链
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,087:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,087:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,087:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,088:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Any manager who attempts to enforce 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,088:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,089:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: chain of command
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,089:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,091:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  communication will soon find
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,092:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: themselves working elsewhere. You can talk to anyone without anyone else
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,092:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,099:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s permission. Moreover,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,103:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: you should consider yourself obligated to do so until the right thing happens. Always view yourself
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,103:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: as working for the good of the company and never your department.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,104:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,104:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  任何试图强制执行
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,104:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,105:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 指挥链
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,105:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,105:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 沟通的经理很快就会发现自己要在其他地方工作了。你可以在没有其他人许可的情况下与任何人交谈。此外，你应该认为自己有义务这样做，直到正确的事情发生。始终将自己视为为公司利益工作，而不是为你的部门工作。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,106:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,134:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  How can it possibly help Tesla for departments to erect barriers between themselves or see
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,150:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: their success as relative within the company instead of collective? We are all in the same boat.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,158:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Managers should work hard to ensure they are not creating silos within the company that create an
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,159:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: us-versus-them mentality or impede communication in any way. This is a natural tendency and
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,160:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: needs to be actively fought.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,160:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,161:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  部门之间树立壁垒或将他们的成功视为公司内部相对而非集体，怎么可能帮助特斯拉？我们都在同一条船上。管理者应该努力确保他们不在公司内部制造孤岛，从而产生我们对他们的 mentality 或以任何方式阻碍沟通。这是一种自然倾向，需要积极抵制。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,161:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,162:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The point is ensuring we execute ultrafast and well.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,162:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,163:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  重点是确保我们超快速且良好地执行。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,163:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,164:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Q: How do boundaries between departments affect product development?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,164:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,165:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  问：部门之间的边界如何影响产品开发？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,165:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,166:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  You can see the organizational boundaries in the product. You
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,166:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,167:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ll often get a box in a box.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,167:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: You realize, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,168:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,168:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Why is this thing in two boxes?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,168:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,171:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Turns out, because both teams thought they needed
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,172:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: an enclosure, the product ends up with an enclosure in an enclosure.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,172:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,173:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  你可以在产品中看到组织边界。你经常会得到一个盒子里的盒子。你意识到，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,173:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,174:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 为什么这个东西在两个盒子里？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,174:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,174:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 结果是，因为两个团队都认为他们需要一个外壳，产品最终变成了外壳里的外壳。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,175:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,177:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  One case from the Tesla Model 3: The battery pack had a top enclosure and the car also
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,178:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: has an underbody, right above it. What
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,178:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,179:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s the point of that? That doesn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,179:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,183:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t make any sense, but because
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,183:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: one team enclosed the battery pack and another team wanted to have an enclosed body, it happened.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,184:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,185:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  特斯拉 Model 3 的一个案例：电池组有一个顶部外壳，汽车也有一个底部车身，就在它上面。那有什么意义？这没有任何意义，但因为一个团队封闭了电池组，另一个团队想要有一个封闭的车身，它就发生了。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,185:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,186:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  It makes sense from an individual team
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,186:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,187:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s perspective, but you don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,187:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,188:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t need a cover on the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,188:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: battery—there
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,189:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,190:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s a car on top of it. Putting the cover on the battery pack adds mass and cost, so it should
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,190:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: be deleted.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,191:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,191:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  从单个团队的角度来看是有意义的，但你不需要在电池上加盖——上面有一辆车。在电池组上加盖增加了质量和成本，所以应该删除它。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,192:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,192:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Find the design necessity of every part and every process.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,193:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,193:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  找出每个部件和每个过程的设计必要性。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,194:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,207:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Occasionally something seems necessary at the design level but turns out unnecessary in
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,213:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: manufacturing. Connect designers and manufacturers to make sure they communicate often. The
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,214:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: people on the assembly line should be able to immediately grab a designer or engineer and say, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,215:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,215:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: WHY DID YOU MAKE IT THIS WAY
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,216:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: !
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,216:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,217:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,217:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,218:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  偶尔有些东西在设计层面看起来必要，但在制造中却不必要。连接设计师和制造商，确保他们经常沟通。装配线上的人应该能够立即抓住设计师或工程师说，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,218:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,219:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 你为什么这样设计！
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,219:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,220:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,221:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  If your hand is on a stove and it gets hot, you pull it right off. But if it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,221:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,222:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s someone else
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,222:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,224:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,225:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: hand on the stove, it will take you longer to do something about it.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,225:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,226:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  如果你的手在炉子上，它变热了，你会立刻拿开。但如果是别人的手在炉子上，你需要更长时间才能做些什么。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,226:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,239:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  You cannot separate design, engineering, and manufacturing. They need to be together
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,245:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: because you are going to make mistakes. You want to identify and fix those mistakes today, right
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,245:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: now. And if you separate them, the mistakes will fester. Let the manufacturers put the designers
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,246:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,246:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,246:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: hands on the stove too.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,247:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,247:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  你不能将设计、工程和制造分开。他们需要在一起，因为你会犯错。你想今天、现在就识别并修复这些错误。如果你分开它们，错误会恶化。让制造商也把设计师的手放在炉子上。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,247:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,248:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Whenever there are problems to solve, don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,248:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,250:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t just meet with your managers. Do a skip level,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,251:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: where you meet with the level right below your managers.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,251:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,252:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  每当有问题要解决时，不要只与你的经理会面。进行跨级会面，与你经理下面的级别会面。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,252:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,253:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Physically go to where the problem is, immediately.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,253:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,253:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  亲自去问题所在的地方，立即。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,254:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,254:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  One of my rules is 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,254:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,255:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Go as close to the source as possible.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,255:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,256:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  We were trying to determine
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,256:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: how thick Starship
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,257:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,257:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s walls should be. Rather than only talking to the company
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,258:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,265:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s executives, I talked
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,269:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: to some of the workers actually doing the welding. I asked what they thought was safe. The line
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,270:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: workers thought the tank walls could get as thin as 4.8 millimeters.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,270:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,270:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我的一个规则是
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,271:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,271:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 尽可能接近源头
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,272:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,272:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 。我们试图确定星舰的墙壁应该有多厚。我没有只与公司高管交谈，而是与一些实际进行焊接的工人交谈。我问他们认为什么是安全的。流水线工人认为罐壁可以薄至 4.8 毫米。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,273:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,273:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,273:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,274:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: What about four?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,274:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,275:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I asked. 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,275:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,276:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: That would make us pretty nervous,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,276:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,277:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  the workers replied. 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,277:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,277:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Okay,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,278:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,278:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I said, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,279:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,279:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Let
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,279:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,280:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s try four millimeters.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,280:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,281:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  It worked.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,281:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,281:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,282:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,282:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 四毫米怎么样？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,283:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,283:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 我问。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,283:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,284:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 那会让我们很紧张，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,284:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,285:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 工人们回答。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,285:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,285:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 好吧，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,286:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,286:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 我说，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,287:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,287:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 让我们试试四毫米。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,287:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,288:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 它奏效了。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,288:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Simple Communication
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,289:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 简单沟通
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,289:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,290:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,290:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,293:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t use acronyms or nonsense words for objects, software, or processes. In general,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,294:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: anything that requires an explanation inhibits communication. We don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,295:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,296:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t want people to have to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,296:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: memorize a glossary just to function.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,297:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,298:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  不要对物体、软件或过程使用首字母缩略词或无意义的词。一般来说，任何需要解释的事情都会阻碍沟通。我们不希望人们必须记住一个词汇表才能工作。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,298:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,305:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I noticed a creeping tendency to use made-up acronyms at SpaceX and Tesla. Excessive
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,308:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: use of made-up acronyms is a significant impediment to communication, and keeping
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,309:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: communication clear as we grow is incredibly important.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,309:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,310:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我注意到 SpaceX 和特斯拉有一种逐渐使用编造的首字母缩略词的倾向。过度使用编造的首字母缩略词是沟通的重大障碍，随着我们成长保持沟通清晰非常重要。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,310:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,321:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  A few acronyms here and there may not seem so bad, but if a thousand people are making
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,325:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: these up, over time the result will be a huge glossary that we have to issue to new employees. No
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,326:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: one actually remembers all these acronyms, and people don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,326:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,327:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t want to seem dumb in a meeting, so
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,328:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: they just sit there in ignorance.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,329:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,329:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  这里那里几个首字母缩略词可能看起来不那么糟糕，但如果一千个人在编造这些，随着时间的推移，结果将是一个我们必须发给新员工的巨大词汇表。没有人真正记得所有这些首字母缩略词，人们不想在会议上显得愚蠢，所以他们只是无知地坐在那里。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,330:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,341:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I told people the acronyms needed to stop immediately or I would take drastic action.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,345:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Unless an acronym is approved by me, it should not enter the SpaceX glossary. If there is an existing
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,346:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: acronym that cannot reasonably be justified, it should be eliminated.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,346:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,347:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我告诉人们首字母缩略词需要立即停止，否则我会采取严厉行动。除非首字母缩略词经过我批准，否则不应进入 SpaceX 词汇表。如果存在无法合理解释的首字母缩略词，应该消除它。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,347:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,383:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The key test for an acronym is to ask whether it helps or hurts communication. An
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,406:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: acronym that most engineers outside of SpaceX already know, such as GUI (graphical user
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,418:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: interface), is fine to use. It is also okay to use a few acronyms or contractions every now and again,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,422:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: assuming I have approved them. For example, we use MVac and M9 instead of Merlin 1C-Vacuum
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,422:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: or Merlin 1C-Sea Level. But they need to be kept to a minimum.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,423:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,424:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  首字母缩略词的关键测试是问它是帮助还是阻碍沟通。SpaceX 之外的大多数工程师已经知道的首字母缩略词，如 GUI（图形用户界面），可以使用。偶尔使用几个首字母缩略词或缩写也可以，假设我已经批准了它们。例如，我们使用 MVac 和 M9 而不是 Merlin 1C-Vacuum 或 Merlin 1C-Sea Level。但它们需要保持在最低限度。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,424:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,425:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The most simple, straightforward, low-ego terms are generally best. You want to close the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,426:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: loop on reality hard.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,426:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,426:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  最简单、直接、低自我的术语通常最好。你想努力关闭现实循环。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,427:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Innovation Needs Permission to Fail
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,427:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 创新需要失败的许可
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,428:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,428:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Failure is essentially irrelevant unless it is catastrophic.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,429:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,429:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  失败本质上无关紧要，除非它是灾难性的。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,430:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,430:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  You have to always look at the incentive structure of an organization and ask, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,431:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,431:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Is that
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,432:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: organization properly incentivizing innovation?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,432:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,432:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  We
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,433:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,438:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re looking for any possible action that can
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,439:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: improve the probability of success, no matter how small. Whether that comes from an intern, me, or
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,440:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: anyone else doesn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,440:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,440:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t matter.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,441:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,441:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  你必须始终查看组织的激励结构并问，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,442:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,442:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 该组织是否适当激励创新？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,442:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,443:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 我们正在寻找任何可能提高成功概率的行动，无论多么小。无论这来自实习生、我还是其他任何人都没关系。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,443:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,444:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  When trying new things, you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,444:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,446:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ve got to have some acceptance of failure…failure must be an
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,447:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: option. If failure is not an option, it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,447:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,450:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s going to result in extremely conservative choices and you may
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,451:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: get something even worse than lack of innovation—things may go backward.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,451:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,452:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  尝试新事物时，你必须对失败有一定的接受度……失败必须是一个选项。如果失败不是一个选项，它将导致极其保守的选择，你可能会得到比缺乏创新更糟糕的东西——事情可能会倒退。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,452:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,453:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  When we had early failures in the SpaceX flights, I didn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,453:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,457:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t fire anyone responsible for those
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,459:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: particular causes of failure. They could have made better decisions, but they were smart and
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,460:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: hardworking. It just wouldn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,460:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,461:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t have been fair in that situation. Letting people go is only fair if they
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,461:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: can
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,462:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,462:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t get themselves motivated around the core mission or they
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,463:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,463:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re really not giving it everything they
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,464:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: can.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,464:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,465:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  当我们在 SpaceX 早期飞行中遇到失败时，我没有解雇那些对特定失败原因负责的人。他们本可以做出更好的决定，但他们聪明且勤奋。在这种情况下解雇他们是不公平的。只有当人们无法围绕核心任务激励自己或他们真的没有尽最大努力时，解雇他们才是公平的。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,465:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,466:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,466:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,468:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s important to create an environment that fosters innovation, and you want to let it evolve
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,469:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: in a Darwinian way. You don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,469:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,472:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t want to pick one technology or path and decide that it will win,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,473:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: because it may not be the best option. Let things evolve.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,473:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,474:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  创造一个培养创新的环境很重要，你想让它以达尔文式的方式进化。你不想选择一种技术或路径并决定它会获胜，因为它可能不是最好的选择。让事情自然进化。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,474:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,475:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  With innovation and new technology, you don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,475:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,476:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t know what the path is—there
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,476:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,477:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s no map. By
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,478:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: nature it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,478:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,479:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s unknown, which means you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,479:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,480:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re going to make false moves. It must be culturally acceptable
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,481:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: to make false moves.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,481:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,482:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  对于创新和新技术，你不知道路径是什么——没有地图。本质上它是未知的，这意味着你会做出错误的举动。在文化上必须接受做出错误举动。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,482:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,483:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  So to provide support for innovation, make sure the penalty for failure is low. You don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,484:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,485:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,485:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: want the response to failure to be too punitive. That
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,486:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,486:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s one of the keys to Silicon Valley
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,487:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,488:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s success.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,488:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: There are many founders who
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,489:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,492:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ve built successful companies after a previous company failed. They
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,492:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: quickly reconstituted. People left and joined other companies. That
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,493:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,493:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s critical.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,494:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,494:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  因此，为了支持创新，确保失败的惩罚很低。你不希望对失败的反应过于惩罚性。这是硅谷成功的关键之一。有许多创始人在前一家公司失败后建立了成功的公司。他们迅速重组。人们离开并加入其他公司。这很关键。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,495:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,497:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  If you punish people too much for failure, then they will respond accordingly, and the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,498:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: innovation you get will be incremental. Nobody
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,499:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,505:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s going to try anything bold for fear of getting fired
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,508:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: or being punished in some way. If you expect innovation, the compensation structure must reflect
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,509:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: that. The risk-reward must favor taking bold moves.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,510:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,510:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  如果你因失败而过多惩罚人们，那么他们会相应地回应，你得到的创新将是渐进式的。没有人会尝试任何大胆的事情，因为害怕被解雇或以某种方式受到惩罚。如果你期望创新，薪酬结构必须反映这一点。风险回报必须有利于采取大胆行动。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,511:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,511:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Failure is a side effect of iteration. I once told a discouraged engineer, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,512:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,512:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: If you can
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,512:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,514:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t tell me
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,515:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the four ways you fucked something up before you got it right, you weren
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,515:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,515:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t the one doing the real
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,516:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: work.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,516:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,516:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,517:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  失败是迭代的副作用。我曾经告诉一位沮丧的工程师，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,517:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,517:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 如果你不能告诉我你在做对之前搞砸的四件事，那你就不是真正做工作的人。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,518:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,518:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,518:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  If we
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,519:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,519:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re not occasionally blowing up an engine on the test stand, we
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,520:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,520:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re not trying hard
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,520:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: enough.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,521:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,521:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  如果我们不是偶尔在测试台上炸毁发动机，我们就没有足够努力。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,521:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,522:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Q: Why is it so hard to predict what will work and what won
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,522:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,523:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,523:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,523:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  问：为什么如此难以预测什么会成功什么不会？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,524:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,524:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  We do as much as we can on the ground and in simulations, but a lot of factors can
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,525:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,527:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t be
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,528:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: simulated. A design might work in simulation or the test stand, but not in a real flight. There
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,528:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,531:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s no
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,533:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: test stand that can test a rocket at 17,000 mph, doing six Gs in every different orientation. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,534:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,534:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s not
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,535:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: possible.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,535:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,536:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我们在地面和模拟中尽可能多地做，但很多因素无法模拟。设计可能在模拟或测试台中有效，但在实际飞行中无效。没有测试台可以在 17,000 英里/小时的速度下测试火箭，在每个不同方向承受 6G。这是不可能的。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,536:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,542:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  After we fly a mission, hundreds of changes take place. Not a few. Hundreds. If you go to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,543:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: a detailed level across the ship, booster, and engines, there might be thousands of changes between
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,544:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: flights. I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,544:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,545:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: m just talking hardware here; software changes even more.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,545:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,546:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  在我们执行一次飞行任务后，会发生数百次变更。不是几个。数百个。如果你详细查看飞船、助推器和发动机，飞行之间可能有数千次变更。我只是在说硬件；软件变更更多。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,546:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,579:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Many are small, but a small change could be a big deal. The first issues you find are
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,600:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: fundamental design flaws that would make success impossible. Some issues vary. They make
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,610:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: success possible sometimes, but not every time. Maybe a design will blow up only once in a while.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,614:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Things that work only sometimes can throw you off. Just because it worked once does not mean it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,614:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: will work again, because the combination of factors isn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,615:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,619:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t the same. It requires a lot of flights to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,619:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: figure out which issues cause one in ten failures and which cause one in one hundred failures.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,620:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,620:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  许多是小的，但小的变更可能是大事。你发现的第一个问题是基本设计缺陷，会使成功变得不可能。一些问题会变化。它们有时使成功成为可能，但不是每次。也许设计只会偶尔爆炸。只有时有时无的事情会让你迷失。仅仅因为它成功过一次并不意味着它会再次成功，因为因素的组合不一样。需要很多次飞行才能找出哪些问题导致十分之一的失败，哪些导致百分之一的失败。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,621:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,623:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  You will lose. It will hurt the first fifty times. When you get used to losing, you will play
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,623:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: each game with less emotion.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,624:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,624:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  你会输。前五十次会很痛。当你习惯失败后，你会以更少的情绪玩每场游戏。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,625:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Simplicity Wins
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,625:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 简单获胜
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,626:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,627:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Never use a cruise missile to kill a fly; just use a flyswatter.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,627:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,628:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  永远不要用巡航导弹杀苍蝇；只用苍蝇拍。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,628:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,636:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Every decision we made in early SpaceX designs has been with simplicity in mind.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,639:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Simplicity both improves reliability and reduces cost. Fewer components means fewer components
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,640:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: to buy and fewer components that can go wrong.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,640:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,641:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我们在早期 SpaceX 设计中做出的每个决定都考虑到简单性。简单性既提高可靠性又降低成本。更少的部件意味着更少的部件需要购买，更少的部件可能出错。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,641:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,650:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The number of lines of code is not a figure of merit. I consider a large number of lines of
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,652:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: code to be bad, not good. I would award one point for adding a line of code and two points for
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,653:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: deleting a line of code.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,653:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,654:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  代码行数不是优点的指标。我认为大量代码行是坏的，不是好的。我会为添加一行代码奖励一分，为删除一行代码奖励两分。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,655:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,655:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  In general, always pick common sense as your guide. If following a 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,655:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,656:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: company rule
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,656:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,660:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  is
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,661:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: obviously ridiculous in a particular situation, such that it would make for a great Dilbert cartoon,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,662:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: then the rule should change.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,662:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,663:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  一般来说，总是选择常识作为你的指南。如果在特定情况下遵循
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,663:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,663:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 公司规则
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,663:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,664:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 显然很荒谬，以至于可以成为一幅伟大的迪尔伯特漫画，那么规则应该改变。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,664:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,665:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Simplicity is our mantra. It creates both reliability and low cost.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,665:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,666:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  简单是我们的座右铭。它既创造可靠性又创造低成本。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,666:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,666:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Q: What are the benefits of simplicity at scale?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,667:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,667:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  问：规模化的简单性有什么好处？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,668:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,669:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  At Tesla, the Model 3 body线 in Fremont was only ever meant to make five thousand cars a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,669:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: week, and it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,670:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,671:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s now doing seven thousand. We achieved that by removing things. We had been doing
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,672:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: a lot of foolish things. We
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,672:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,674:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ve changed some of the designs and made them simpler and easier to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,675:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: build. Simplicity comes from hundreds of little changes.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,675:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,676:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  在特斯拉，弗里蒙特的 Model 3 车身线原本只计划每周生产五千辆车，现在达到七千辆。我们通过移除东西实现了这一点。我们一直做了很多愚蠢的事情。我们改变了一些设计，使它们更简单、更容易建造。简单来自数百个小改变。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,676:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,688:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Being able to get 40 percent more output from the same manufacturing line makes a big
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,692:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: difference. It also reduces the marginal cost of production and improves the quality of the car. This
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,693:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: is the result of a ton of hard work by a lot of people.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,693:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,694:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  能够从同一条生产线获得 40% 更多的产出会产生巨大影响。它还降低了生产的边际成本并提高了汽车质量。这是很多人大量辛勤工作的结果。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,694:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,695:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  For three months I was at the gigafactory trying to help fix battery production. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,695:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,697:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s a lot of
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,697:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: little things. I look at every tiny part of each process and ask, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,698:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,698:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Is this process necessary?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,699:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,699:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,699:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  有三个月我在超级工厂试图帮助修复电池生产。这是很多小事情。我查看每个过程的每个微小部分并问，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,700:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,700:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 这个过程必要吗？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,701:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,701:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,702:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The best part is no part. The best process is no process.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,702:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,702:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  最好的部件是没有部件。最好的过程是没有过程。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,703:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,717:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  For example, a robot would put a car frame on a turntable. The turntable would rotate and
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,724:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: then another robot would pick it up. The problem was the turntable would sometimes break down.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,725:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: So, we eliminated the turntable. With a robot-to-robot handoff, we had one less step, less equipment,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,725:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: and didn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,726:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,726:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t have turntable breakage to consider. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,727:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,727:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s a lot of this really simple stuff, but a thousand
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,728:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: times.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,728:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,729:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  例如，机器人会将车架放在转盘上。转盘会旋转，然后另一个机器人会拿起它。问题是转盘有时会故障。所以，我们消除了转盘。通过机器人到机器人的交接，我们少了一步，少了设备，也不必考虑转盘故障。这是很多非常简单的东西，但重复一千次。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,729:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,730:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,730:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,731:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s a lot of minimizing things that can go wrong and maximizing the efficiency of the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,732:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: simple things.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,732:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,733:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  这是很多最小化可能出错的事情并最大化简单事情的效率。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,733:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,733:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  If you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,734:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,737:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ve got a whole bunch of separate parts and each of them has a given tolerance—even if
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,738:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: that tolerance is tight, like 0.2 millimeter tolerance—but if you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,738:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,739:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ve got fifty parts…you have to multiply the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,740:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: variances together. You
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,740:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,741:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ll end up with a huge variance between cars. That
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,741:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,742:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s one of the reasons it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,742:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,744:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,744:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: better to combine parts rather than have more individual parts.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,745:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,745:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  如果你有一大堆单独的部件，每个部件都有一定的公差——即使那个公差很紧，比如 0.2 毫米公差——但如果你有五十个部件……你必须将方差相乘。你最终会在汽车之间产生巨大的差异。这是最好合并部件而不是拥有更多单独部件的原因之一。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,746:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,747:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  In the Model 3 engineering, there were a lot of right answers to the wrong questions.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,747:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,748:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  在 Model 3 工程中，有很多对错误问题的正确答案。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,748:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,749:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Fifty different times for fifty different parts, an engineer would ask, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,749:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,750:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: What
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,750:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,751:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s the best
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,752:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: material to make this part out of?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,752:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,754:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Of course, they would get fifty different answers. They were all
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,755:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: true individually, but not true collectively.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,755:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,756:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  五十次针对五十个不同部件，工程师会问，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,756:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,757:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 用什么材料制造这个部件最好？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,757:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,757:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 当然，他们会得到五十个不同的答案。它们单独看都是真的，但集体看不是真的。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,758:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,760:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  When you try to join all these parts made of dissimilar metals, there are many issues. You
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,761:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: need better sealant to prevent galvanic corrosion. You
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,761:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,765:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ve got to join some with rivets, some with
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,766:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: spot welds, some with resin, or resin and spot welds. Then it looks like a Frankenstein situation all
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,767:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: together.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,767:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,767:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  当你试图连接所有这些由不同金属制成的部件时，有很多问题。你需要更好的密封剂来防止电偶腐蚀。你必须用铆钉连接一些，用点焊连接一些，用树脂连接一些，或树脂和点焊。然后它看起来像一个弗兰肯斯坦的情况。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,768:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,768:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,768:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,782:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s way better to have a single piece, casted. Then you have no gaps, no sealant, no
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,788:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: dissimilar metals. You can reduce the size of the body shop in the factory dramatically. Having the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,788:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: rear body cast for Model Y allowed us to reduce the body shop by 30 percent.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,789:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,789:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  最好有一个单一的铸件。这样你就没有缝隙，没有密封剂，没有不同金属。你可以大幅减少工厂车身车间的规模。为 Model Y 铸造后车身使我们能够将车身车间减少 30%。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,790:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,790:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  There
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,790:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,799:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s roughly a thousand robots on the Model 3 body line. Which, by the way, is not a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,801:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: figure of merit. We got rid of three hundred robots by switching to rear body casting. When we
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,802:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: change the front body to casting, we
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,802:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,803:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ll get rid of another three hundred robots. You want fewer
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,803:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: things, not more.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,804:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,804:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Model 3 车身线上大约有一千个机器人。顺便说一句，这不是优点的指标。我们通过切换到后车身铸造摆脱了三百个机器人。当我们把前车身改为铸造时，我们将再摆脱三百个机器人。你想要更少的东西，而不是更多。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,805:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,805:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,805:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,806:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s easy to say 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,806:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,807:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: simplify,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,807:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,807:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  but it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,808:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,808:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s very difficult to do it.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,808:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,809:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  说
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,809:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,810:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 简化
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,810:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,810:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 很容易，但做起来非常困难。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,811:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The Algorithm
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,811:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 算法
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,812:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,812:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I became a broken record on The Algorithm. But it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,813:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,813:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s helpful to say it to an annoying
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,814:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: degree.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,814:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,815:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我对算法成了一个破唱片。但说到烦人的程度是有帮助的。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,815:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,817:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I have everyone at my companies rigorously implement a five-step process for
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,818:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: engineering. I call it The Algorithm. I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,818:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,819:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ll list the steps, then explain. The order is very important.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,820:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,820:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我让我公司的每个人都严格实施一个五步工程流程。我称之为算法。我会列出步骤，然后解释。顺序非常重要。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,821:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,823:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  1. Make your requirements less dumb. 2. Try very hard to delete the part or process. 3.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,824:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Simplify or optimize. 4. Accelerate. 5. Automate.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,824:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,825:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  1. 让你的要求不那么愚蠢。2. 非常努力地删除部件或过程。3. 简化或优化。4. 加速。5. 自动化。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,825:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,826:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Q: Why is the order of the steps so important?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,826:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,827:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  问：为什么步骤的顺序如此重要？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,827:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,828:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,828:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,831:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ve personally made the mistake of going backward—on all five steps—multiple times. Many
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,832:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: things at Tesla were automated, accelerated, simplified, and then deleted.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,833:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,833:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我个人曾犯过倒退的错误——在所有五个步骤上——多次。特斯拉的许多事情被自动化、加速、简化，然后被删除。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,834:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,838:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  One example was fiberglass mats on top of the battery pack. At one point I was basically
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,839:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: living on the battery pack production line, because it was choking the entire car
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,840:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,853:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s production. The
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,863:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: first mistake was trying to fix the automation to make the robot better, to make it move faster on a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,866:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: shorter path. We increased the rate by 20 percent, then 100 percent. Then, we tried to optimize the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,867:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: use of glue and the drying speed.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,867:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,868:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  一个例子是电池组顶部的玻璃纤维垫。有一段时间我基本上住在电池组生产线上，因为它扼住了整辆车的生产。第一个错误是试图修复自动化以使机器人更好，使它在更短的路径上移动更快。我们将速率提高了 20%，然后 100%。然后，我们试图优化胶水的使用和干燥速度。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,868:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,871:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Automating was a mistake, then accelerating was a mistake, then optimizing was a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,872:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: mistake. Finally, I asked the battery safety team, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,873:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,873:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: What the hell are these mats for? Fire protection?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,873:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,874:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,874:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: They said, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,874:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,874:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: No, they
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,875:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,875:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re for noise and vibration.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,875:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,876:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,876:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  自动化是个错误，然后加速是个错误，然后优化是个错误。最后，我问电池安全团队，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,876:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,877:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 这些垫子到底是干什么的？防火吗？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,877:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,877:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 他们说，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,878:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,878:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 不，它们是用于噪音和振动的。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,878:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,879:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,879:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I said, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,879:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,880:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: But…you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,880:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,880:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re the battery team.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,881:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,881:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  So I asked the noise vibration analysis team, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,881:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,882:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: What
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,882:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,882:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,883:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: mat for?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,883:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,884:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  They said fire safety. It was like being in a Dilbert cartoon. I feel like I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,884:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,885:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: m in a Dilbert
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,885:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: cartoon quite frequently.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,886:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,886:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我说，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,886:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,887:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 但……你们是电池团队。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,887:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,887:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 所以我问噪音振动分析团队，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,888:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,888:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 垫子是干什么的？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,888:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,889:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 他们说防火安全。这就像在迪尔伯特漫画里一样。我觉得我经常在迪尔伯特漫画里。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,889:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,902:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  So we ran a test: a car with and without the fiberglass mats and a microphone in both. No
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,907:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: one could tell the difference. So, we deleted the part (the mats), which deleted a step that required
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,908:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: two million dollars of robotics, because it was just a big pile of nonsense.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,908:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,909:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  所以我们做了一个测试：一辆有玻璃纤维垫的车和一辆没有的车，两辆车都有麦克风。没人能分辨出区别。所以，我们删除了部件（垫子），这删除了一个需要两百万美元机器人的步骤，因为它只是一大堆废话。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,909:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,910:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Q: Can you walk me through the steps?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,910:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,911:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  问：你能带我 walkthrough 这些步骤吗？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,911:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,920:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The first step is to question the requirements, and make your requirements less dumb. You
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,923:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: have to start there, because otherwise you could get the perfect answer to the wrong question. This
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,923:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: step makes the question the least wrong possible.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,924:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,924:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  第一步是质疑要求，让你的要求不那么愚蠢。你必须从那里开始，否则你可能会得到对错误问题的完美答案。这一步使问题尽可能少错。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,925:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,928:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Your requirements are definitely dumb. It does not matter who gave them to you.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,928:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Requirements from smart people are the most dangerous, because you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,929:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,932:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re less likely to question
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,933:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: them. Always question requirements, even if it came from me. Everyone is wrong some of the time.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,933:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,934:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  你的要求肯定是愚蠢的。谁给你的不重要。来自聪明人的要求最危险，因为你不太可能质疑它们。总是质疑要求，即使它来自我。每个人都有错的时候。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,934:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,935:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Whatever requirements or constraints you do have must come from a person, not a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,936:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: department. You can
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,936:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,949:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t actually ask a department. You have to be able to ask a person, and the person
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,955:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: putting forth the requirement must take responsibility for that requirement. Otherwise, you could
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,956:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: have a requirement made up by an intern two years ago off the cuff, or someone who isn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,956:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,958:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t even at
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,959:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the company anymore. You must know the name of the real person who made every requirement.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,959:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,960:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  你无论有什么要求或约束都必须来自一个人，而不是一个部门。你不能真正问一个部门。你必须能够问一个人，提出要求的人必须对该要求负责。否则，你可能有一个两年前实习生随口编造的要求，或者一个甚至不在公司的人的要求。你必须知道提出每个要求的真实人物的姓名。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,961:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,961:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Many times we
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,961:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,971:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ve had dumb requirements, dug into them, and discovered no one currently
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,974:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: working in that department agrees with the requirement. These things are often way more silly than
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,975:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: you think. So step one is make your requirements less dumb.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,976:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,976:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  很多时候我们有愚蠢的要求，深入研究它们，发现目前在该部门工作没有人同意该要求。这些事情通常比你想象的更愚蠢。所以第一步是让你的要求不那么愚蠢。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,977:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,979:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Step two: Try very hard to delete the part or process. It sounds obvious, but people often
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,979:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: forget to try deleting something entirely.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,980:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,980:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  第二步：非常努力地删除部件或过程。这听起来很明显，但人们经常忘记尝试完全删除某些东西。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,981:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,981:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  If you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,982:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,983:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re not adding deleted things back in 10 percent of the time, you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,983:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,984:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re clearly not
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,985:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: deleting enough. Somewhat illogically, people often feel they
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,986:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,989:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ve succeeded if they are not forced to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,990:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: put anything back in. But actually they have failed in a different way, because they
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,990:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,991:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ve been overly
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,992:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: conservative and have left things in there that shouldn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,993:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,993:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t be.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,994:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,994:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  如果你没有 10% 的时间把删除的东西加回来，你显然删除得不够。有些不合逻辑的是，人们经常觉得如果没有被迫把任何东西加回来就是成功了。但实际上他们以另一种方式失败了，因为他们过于保守，留下了不应该存在的东西。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,995:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,996:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The bias tends to be very strong for adding this part or process step 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,996:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,997:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: just in case we need it.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,997:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,998:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  But you can make 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,998:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,999:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: just in case
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:53,999:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,000:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  arguments for many, many, many things.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,000:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,001:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  添加这个部件或过程步骤的偏见往往很强，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,001:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,002:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 以防我们需要它
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,002:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,003:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 。但你可以为很多很多很多事情提出
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,003:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,004:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 以防万一
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,004:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,005:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 的论点。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,005:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,011:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  People tend to remember, with sometimes a jarring level of pain, when they deleted
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,012:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: something they later needed. They overcorrect, and put too much stuff in there, which
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,013:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: overcomplicates things.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,013:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,014:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  人们倾向于记住，有时带着令人震惊的痛苦程度，当他们删除了后来需要的东西时。他们过度纠正，放了太多东西在里面，这使事情过于复杂。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,014:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,014:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I tell them this in advance: 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,015:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,015:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Look, we
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,015:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,017:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re deliberately going to delete more than we should.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,017:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Some of the things we delete, we
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,018:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,018:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re going to put back in. At least one in ten things, we
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,018:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,019:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re going to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,019:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: add back in.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,020:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,020:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  People get a little shook by that. But if you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,020:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,024:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re so conservative in deleting that you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,024:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: never have to put anything back in, you obviously have a lot of stuff that isn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,025:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,025:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t needed. So, you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,025:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,026:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ve got
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,026:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: to overcorrect for that tendency.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,027:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,027:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我提前告诉他们：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,027:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,028:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 看，我们故意要删除比我们应得的更多。我们删除的一些东西，我们会放回去。至少十分之一的东西，我们会加回来。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,028:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,028:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 人们对此有点动摇。但如果你在删除方面如此保守以至于你从不必把任何东西放回去，你显然有很多不需要的东西。所以，你必须过度纠正这种倾向。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,029:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,029:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  At SpaceX, I would tell the team, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,030:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,030:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: We are on a deletion rampage
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,031:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: !
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,031:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: !
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,034:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Nothing is sacred. We
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,036:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: will delete any remotely questionable tubes, sensors, manifolds, etc. tonight. Please go ultrahardcore
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,037:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: on deletion and simplification.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,037:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,037:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  We put immense effort into reducing mass.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,038:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,038:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  在 SpaceX，我会告诉团队，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,039:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,039:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 我们处于删除狂潮中！！没有什么神圣的。今晚我们将删除任何稍微可疑的管道、传感器、歧管等。请在删除和简化方面超级硬核。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,039:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,040:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 我们投入巨大努力减少质量。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,040:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,040:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  There
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,041:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,052:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s a recursive factor to mass. If you add an extra ton of heat shielding, you also need
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,056:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: more fuel to get it to orbit, and you need more fuel to deorbit, and you need more fuel to land it.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,057:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Also the structure now has more load on it, because it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,057:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,061:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s carrying an extra ton of heat shield. This
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,061:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: applies to any given ton. Adding each ton is almost like adding two tons when it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,062:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,062:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s fully considered.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,063:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: We
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,063:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,064:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ve calculated it to be around a 1.8 recursion factor, but we
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,064:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,069:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re probably forgetting something that
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,070:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: gets us closer to two. Every one ton of mass begets an extra ton. That is why it is very important to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,070:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: delete.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,071:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,072:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  质量有一个递归因子。如果你增加一吨额外的隔热层，你也需要更多燃料将其送入轨道，你需要更多燃料使其脱离轨道，你需要更多燃料着陆。此外，结构现在有更多负荷，因为它承载了额外一吨的隔热层。这适用于任何给定的一吨。当充分考虑时，添加每一吨几乎就像添加两吨。我们计算它大约是 1.8 的递归因子，但我们可能忘记了一些让我们更接近二的东西。每一吨质量会产生额外一吨。这就是为什么删除非常重要。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,072:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,074:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Recapping so far: Step one, make your requirements less dumb. Step two, try hard to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,074:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: delete the part or process.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,075:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,075:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  到目前为止回顾：第一步，让你的要求不那么愚蠢。第二步，努力删除部件或过程。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,076:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,079:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Then, once you have deleted as much as you can, the third step is to simplify or optimize.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,080:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The third step. The third step. Not the first step. Why?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,080:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,081:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  然后，一旦你尽可能删除了，第三步是简化或优化。第三步。第三步。不是第一步。为什么？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,081:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,082:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The most common mistake of smart engineers is to optimize a thing that should not exist.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,083:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,083:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  聪明工程师最常见的错误是优化一个不应该存在的东西。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,084:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,084:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Everyone was trained in high school and college to answer the question in front of them. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,085:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,085:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s convergent logic. You can
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,086:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,086:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t tell the professor, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,087:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,087:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Your question is dumb.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,088:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,090:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  You have to answer the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,091:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: question. Without knowing it, almost everyone has this mental straightjacket on. They
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,091:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,093:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ll work on
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,093:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: optimizing a thing that should simply not exist.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,094:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,094:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  每个人在高中和大学都被训练回答面前的问题。这是收敛逻辑。你不能告诉教授，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,095:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,095:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 你的问题很愚蠢。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,096:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,096:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 你必须回答问题。不知不觉中，几乎每个人都有这个精神枷锁。他们会致力于优化一个根本不应该存在的东西。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,097:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,098:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Then, and only then, step four: accelerate cycle time. Once you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,098:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,099:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re moving in the right
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,100:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: direction, and moving efficiently…you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,100:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,101:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re moving too slow. Go faster. You can always make things go
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,101:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: faster.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,102:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,103:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  然后，只有那时，第四步：加速周期时间。一旦你朝着正确的方向移动，并且高效地移动……你移动得太慢了。更快。你总是可以让事情变得更快。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,103:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,110:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  But, do not go faster until you have worked on the other three things first. I mistakenly
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,112:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: spent a lot of time accelerating processes that I later realized should have been deleted. Speeding up
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,112:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: something that shouldn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,113:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,114:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t exist is absurd. If you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,114:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,115:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re digging your grave, don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,115:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,116:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t dig it faster. Stop
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,116:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: digging.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,117:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,118:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  但是，在你先完成其他三件事之前不要更快。我错误地花了很多时间加速我后来意识到应该被删除的过程。加速不应该存在的东西是荒谬的。如果你在挖自己的坟墓，不要挖得更快。停止挖掘。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,118:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,138:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Step five, the final step, is to automate. The big mistake I made in the Tesla factories in
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,147:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Nevada and Fremont was trying to automate every step too early. To fix that, we had to tear
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,149:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: hundreds of expensive robots out of the production line. We put a hole in the side of the building
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,150:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: just to remove all that equipment.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,150:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,151:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  第五步，最后一步，是自动化。我在内华达和弗里蒙特的特斯拉工厂犯的大错误是过早尝试自动化每个步骤。为了解决这个问题，我们不得不从生产线上拆掉数百个昂贵的机器人。我们在大楼侧面开了一个洞，只是为了移除所有那些设备。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,151:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,154:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Always wait until the end of designing a process—after you have questioned all the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,154:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: requirements and deleted unnecessary parts—before you introduce automation.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,155:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,155:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  总是等到设计过程的最后——在你质疑了所有要求并删除了不必要的部件之后——再引入自动化。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,155:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: MANIACAL URGENCY
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,156:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 疯狂紧迫感
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,156:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,157:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  A maniacal sense of urgency is our operating principle.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,157:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,158:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  疯狂的紧迫感是我们的运营原则。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,158:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,158:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,159:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t Waste Time
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,159:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 不要浪费时间
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,160:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,162:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Excessive meetings are the blight of big companies and almost always get worse over time.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,163:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Get rid of all large meetings, unless you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,163:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,164:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re certain they are providing value to the whole audience, in
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,165:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: which case, keep them short.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,165:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,166:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  过多的会议是大公司的祸害，几乎总是随着时间的推移变得更糟。摆脱所有大型会议，除非你确定它们为整个受众提供价值，在这种情况下，保持它们简短。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,166:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,170:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Also get rid of frequent meetings, unless you are dealing with an extremely urgent matter.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,171:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Meeting frequency should drop rapidly once the urgent matter is resolved.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,171:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,171:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  还要摆脱频繁的会议，除非你正在处理极其紧急的事情。一旦紧急事项得到解决，会议频率应迅速下降。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,172:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,173:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Walk out of a meeting or drop off a call as soon as it is obvious you aren
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,177:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,179:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t adding value. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,180:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: is not rude to leave; it is rude to make someone stay and waste their time.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,180:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,180:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  一旦很明显你没有增加价值，就走出会议或挂断电话。离开不是粗鲁；让某人留下来浪费他们的时间才是粗鲁。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,181:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Speed Is Both Offense and Defense
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,181:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 速度既是进攻也是防守
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,182:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,182:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The only true currency is time.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,183:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,183:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  唯一真正的货币是时间。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,184:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,202:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The best offense and defense is speed. The SR-71 Blackbird is a military plane with almost
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,212:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: no defense except acceleration. It was never shot down. Not even once. Over three thousand missiles
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,214:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: were shot at the SR-71 Blackbird and none hit. All it did was go faster. The power of speed is
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,214:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: underappreciated as a competitive factor.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,215:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,220:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  最好的进攻和防守是速度。SR-71 黑鸟是一架军用飞机，除了加速外几乎没有防御。它从未被击落。一次也没有。超过三千枚导弹向 SR-71 黑鸟发射，没有一枚击中。它所做的只是更快。速度作为竞争因素的力量被低估了。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,223:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,230:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The real way you actually achieve intellectual property (IP) protection is by innovating
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,231:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: fast. If your rate of innovation is high, then you don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,231:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,234:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t need to worry about protecting the IP because
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,234:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: other companies will be copying something you did years ago. That
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,235:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,237:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s fine. Just make sure your rate
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,237:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: of innovation is fast. Speed of innovation is what matters.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,238:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,239:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  你实际实现知识产权（IP）保护的真正方式是快速创新。如果你的创新率高，那么你不需要担心保护 IP，因为其他公司会复制你几年前做的事情。没关系。只要确保你的创新速度快。创新速度才是重要的。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,239:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,261:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  We obviously cannot compete with the big car companies in size, so we must do so with
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,272:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: intelligence and agility. A factory moving at twice the speed of another factory is basically
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,276:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: equivalent to two factories. The company will succeed if it can do with one factory what takes other
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,277:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: companies two, three, or four factories. We try to think, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,277:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,279:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: How can we make each factory produce
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,280:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: what would normally require five or even ten factories?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,280:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,280:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,281:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我们显然不能在规模上与大汽车公司竞争，所以我们必须用智慧和敏捷性来竞争。以两倍于另一个工厂的速度移动的工厂基本上相当于两个工厂。如果公司能够用一个工厂完成其他公司需要两、三或四个工厂的事情，它就会成功。我们试图思考，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,281:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,281:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 我们如何让每个工厂生产通常需要五个甚至十个工厂的东西？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,282:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,282:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,283:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I have a running triage of what I do at each company, constantly thinking, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,283:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,284:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: What is the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,284:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: most useful thing I could do?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,285:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,285:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,285:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我对我在每家公司做的事情有一个持续的分诊，不断思考，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,286:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,286:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 我能做的最有用的事情是什么？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,286:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,287:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,308:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  In early SpaceX, I told the team everything we did was a function of our burn rate. We
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,318:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: were burning through a hundred thousand dollars per day. In the same way, I expected the revenue
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,320:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: in ten years to be ten million dollars a day. Every day we were slower to achieve our goals was a day
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,321:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: of missing out on that revenue.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,321:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,322:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  在早期的 SpaceX，我告诉团队我们做的一切都是燃烧率的函数。我们每天燃烧十万美元。同样，我预计十年后的收入是每天一千万美元。我们每天越慢实现目标，就是错过那收入的一天。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,322:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,332:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  You need to be a vector, not just a scalar. That means you need to go at high speed in the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,334:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: right direction. No company will always be going in the right direction all the time—so you have to do
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,335:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: course corrections, like a guided missile.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,335:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,336:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  你需要成为一个向量，而不仅仅是一个标量。这意味着你需要以高速向正确的方向前进。没有公司会一直朝着正确的方向前进——所以你必须进行航向修正，就像制导导弹一样。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,336:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,361:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I try to work as much as possible—to the edge of sanity. Every good hour or even minute of
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,373:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: thinking about Tesla and SpaceX has such a big effect on the company. It makes sleeping difficult.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,378:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Tesla is getting to the point where every high-quality minute of thinking has a million-dollar impact.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,379:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: That is insane. If Tesla is doing $2 billion a week in revenue, that
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,379:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,382:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s about $300 million a day, seven
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,383:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: days a week. There are many instances where a half-hour meeting improved the company
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,383:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,384:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s financial
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,384:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: outcome by $100 million.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,385:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,386:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我尽量尽可能多地工作——到理智的边缘。每一小时甚至每一分钟思考特斯拉和 SpaceX 对公司都有如此大的影响。这使得睡觉变得困难。特斯拉正达到每个高质量分钟的思考都有百万美元影响的地步。这太疯狂了。如果特斯拉每周收入 20 亿美元，那大约是每天 3 亿美元，一周七天。有很多例子表明，半小时的会议将公司的财务成果提高了 1 亿美元。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,386:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Do Things in Parallel
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,387:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 并行做事
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,387:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,390:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Everything is measured in terms of time. What is the time risk associated with something?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,390:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The one thing you cannot replace is time.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,391:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,391:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  一切都用时间来衡量。与某事相关的时间风险是什么？你无法替代的一件事是时间。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,392:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,415:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  For PayPal, we needed to establish a lot of back-office relationships to attach various data
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,427:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: sources. The credit card system for processing credit cards, the Federal Reserve System for doing
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,431:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: electronic funds transfers, the various fraud databases to run fraud checks. There was a lot we had to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,432:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: interface with, and it took a while to set all that up.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,433:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,433:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  对于 PayPal，我们需要建立很多后台关系来连接各种数据源。处理信用卡的信用卡系统、进行电子资金转账的美联储系统、运行欺诈检查的各种欺诈数据库。我们有很多需要对接的，设置所有这些东西花了一些时间。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,434:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,443:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  But by doing them all in parallel, it all came together simultaneously. Developing the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,445:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: software and having it ready for the general public coincided with us concluding deals with the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,446:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: outside vendors. All that took about a year.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,447:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,447:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  但通过并行做所有这些事情，它们同时汇聚在一起。开发软件并准备好向公众发布与我们与外部供应商达成协议同时进行。所有这一切花了大约一年时间。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,448:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,448:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Avoid serialized dependencies. A lot of things have a 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,449:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,449:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: gestation period
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,450:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,461:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  and there is
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,469:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: nothing you can do to accelerate it. If you can have all those things gestating in parallel, that will
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,472:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: substantially accelerate your overall timeline. People tend to serialize too much. Put as many
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,473:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: gestating elements in parallel as possible.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,473:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,473:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  避免序列化依赖。很多事情都有
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,474:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,474:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 孕育期
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,474:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,475:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ，你无法加速它。如果你能让所有这些事情并行孕育，这将大大加速你的整体时间表。人们倾向于过多地序列化。尽可能多地将孕育元素并行放置。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,475:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,475:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  If a timeline is long, it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,476:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,476:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s wrong.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,476:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,477:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  如果时间表很长，那就是错的。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,477:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Break Down the 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,478:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,478:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Impossible
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,478:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,479:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 分解
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,479:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,479:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 不可能
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,480:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,480:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,488:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The general principles of first-principle thinking apply to software, hardware, anything
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,490:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: really. Often, we were told something was impossible, but once we broke it down into its constituent
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,490:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: elements, we could solve those.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,491:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,491:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  第一性原理思维的一般原则适用于软件、硬件，任何事物。通常，我们被告知某事是不可能的，但一旦我们将其分解为其组成元素，我们就能解决这些问题。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,492:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,523:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  For xAI in 2024, we were trying to build a training supercluster (a giant network of
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,542:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: computers to train an AI model). We went to the various suppliers and said we needed one hundred
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,552:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: thousand H100s (superpowerful computer chips) to be able to train coherently. Their estimates for
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,555:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: how long it would take to complete that were eighteen to twenty-four months. Well, we needed to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,555:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: get that done in six months or we wouldn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,556:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,556:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t be competitive.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,556:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,557:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  对于 2024 年的 xAI，我们试图建立一个训练超级集群（一个巨大的计算机网络来训练 AI 模型）。我们去找各种供应商，说我们需要十万个 H100（超级强大的计算机芯片）才能进行连贯训练。他们对完成这件事需要多长时间的估计是十八到二十四个月。好吧，我们需要在六个月内完成，否则我们就没有竞争力。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,558:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,558:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  So, we broke that down. We need a building; we need power; we need cooling.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,559:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,559:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  所以，我们分解了它。我们需要一栋建筑；我们需要电力；我们需要冷却。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,559:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,560:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  We didn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,560:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,571:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t have enough time to build a building from scratch. So, we found a factory in
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,576:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Memphis that was no longer in use. The input power was 15 megawatts and we needed 150
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,577:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: megawatts. So, we rented generators and put them along one side of the building.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,577:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,578:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我们没有足够的时间从头开始建造一栋建筑。所以，我们在孟菲斯找到了一家不再使用的工厂。输入功率是 15 兆瓦，我们需要 150 兆瓦。所以，我们租用了发电机，把它们放在大楼的一侧。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,578:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,582:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Then, we needed cooling. So, we rented about a quarter of the mobile cooling capacity of
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,583:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the US and put the chillers on the other side of the building.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,583:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,583:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  然后，我们需要冷却。所以，我们租用了美国大约四分之一的移动冷却能力，把冷却器放在大楼的另一侧。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,584:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,584:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  That didn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,585:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,589:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t fully solve the problem because the power variations during training are very
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,590:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: big. Power can drop by 50 percent in 100 milliseconds, which the generators can
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,590:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,595:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t keep up with. So
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,598:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: then we added Tesla megapacks and modified the software in the megapacks to be able to smooth
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,599:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: out the power variation during the training run.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,599:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,600:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  这并没有完全解决问题，因为训练期间的功率变化非常大。功率可以在 100 毫秒内下降 50%，发电机跟不上。所以我们添加了特斯拉 Megapack，并修改了 Megapack 中的软件，以便能够在训练运行期间平滑功率变化。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,600:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,614:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Then there were a bunch of networking challenges. Networking cables for one hundred
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,620:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: thousand GPUs (graphics processing units) are very, very difficult. We ran the networking team to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,621:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: do the cabling in four shifts, 24/7. I was sleeping in the data center and doing cabling myself.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,621:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,622:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  然后有一堆网络挑战。十万个 GPU（图形处理单元）的网络电缆非常非常困难。我们让网络团队分四班，24/7 进行布线。我睡在数据中心，自己布线。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,622:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,628:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Now called Colossus, it is currently the largest AI training platform in the world. It was
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,629:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: constructed in 122 days. Ninety-two days later, it had been doubled to two hundred thousand GPUs.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,629:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,630:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  现在称为 Colossus，它是目前世界上最大的 AI 训练平台。它在 122 天内建成。92 天后，它已经翻倍到二十万个 GPU。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,630:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Set Aggressive Timelines
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,631:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 设定激进的时间表
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,631:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,632:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I often tell the Tesla team: 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,632:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,633:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,633:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,634:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s okay to scrap equipment or money. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,634:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,634:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s not okay to scrap
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,635:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: time.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,635:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,635:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,636:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我经常告诉特斯拉团队：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,636:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,636:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 报废设备或金钱是可以的。报废时间是不可以的。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,637:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,637:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,640:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  When I was interviewing for a vice president of machining, I explained I was paying for
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,641:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: everything at SpaceX out of pocket. I asked him, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,641:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,641:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: What
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,642:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,642:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s the cheapest you would work for?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,642:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,647:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  He
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,649:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: haggled, and eventually we agreed. Ten minutes later, I gave him a contract. This was a Saturday at
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,650:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 5:00 p.m. He started working that night.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,650:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,651:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  当我面试加工副总裁时，我解释我在 SpaceX 自掏腰包支付一切。我问他，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,651:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,651:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 你愿意为多少最低薪酬工作？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,652:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,652:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 他讨价还价，最终我们达成了协议。十分钟后，我给了他一份合同。那是一个星期六下午 5 点。他当晚就开始工作了。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,652:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,653:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Q: Do you deliberately make aggressive prediction timelines to drive people to be
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,654:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ambitious?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,654:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,655:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  问：你故意制定激进的预测时间表来推动人们雄心勃勃吗？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,655:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,656:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  For internal timelines, we set the most aggressive timelines we can. I do this because there
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,656:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,657:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s a kind of 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,657:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,657:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: law of gaseous expansion
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,658:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,658:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  for schedules. Whatever time you set, it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,659:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,659:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s not going to be less
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,660:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: than that. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,660:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,661:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s rare that something will ever get done faster than the schedule.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,661:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,662:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  对于内部时间表，我们设定我们能设定的最激进的时间表。我这样做是因为时间表有一种
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,662:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,662:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 气体膨胀定律
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,663:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,663:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 。无论你设定什么时间，都不会少于那个时间。很少有事情会比时间表更快完成。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,664:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,664:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  When I cite a schedule, it is actually the schedule I think is true. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,665:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,669:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s not some fake
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,670:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: schedule I made up. It may be delusional—that is entirely possible, and that has happened from time to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,671:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: time. But it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,671:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,672:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s never some knowingly fake deadline, ever.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,672:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,673:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  当我引用一个时间表时，它实际上是我认为真实的时间表。这不是我编造的假时间表。它可能是妄想的——这完全可能，而且时不时发生过。但它从来不是明知故犯的假截止日期，从来没有。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,673:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,689:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I want to emphasize that some dates are not dates that will actually be met. For example,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,697:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the initial release date for the Model 3 at Tesla was an impossible date because there are seven
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,698:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: thousand unique components in the Model 3, and our deadline assumed all of them would arrive on
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,699:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: time. That won
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,699:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,700:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t happen. But, it was a date for us to hold ourselves (internally) and our suppliers to.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,700:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,701:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我想强调，有些日期不是实际会实现的日期。例如，特斯拉 Model 3 的初始发布日期是一个不可能的日期，因为 Model 3 有七千个独特组件，我们的截止日期假设它们都能按时到达。那不会发生。但是，那是我们用来约束自己（内部）和供应商的日期。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,702:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,702:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I do have a habit of being optimistic with schedules.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,703:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,703:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我确实有对时间表乐观的习惯。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,704:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,704:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  When I give estimates about our production, it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,705:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,737:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s guesswork. Especially guesses about
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,762:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: exponential curves. In exponential growth, the difference a year or two makes to an outcome is
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,775:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: enormous. We got a lot of criticism for the number of cars we delivered in 2017. The area under the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,779:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: curve of production in 2017 was quite small because it was the beginning of an exponential ramp,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,780:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: but once that growth got going, the area under the curve was enormous. That
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,781:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,782:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s why people were so
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,783:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: shocked. I kept trying to say this, but people don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,783:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,784:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t understand what exponential means.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,784:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,785:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  当我给出关于我们产量的估计时，那是猜测。尤其是关于指数曲线的猜测。在指数增长中，一两年对结果的差异是巨大的。我们因 2017 年交付的汽车数量而受到很多批评。2017 年生产曲线下的面积相当小，因为它是指数增长的开始，但一旦增长开始，曲线下的面积是巨大的。这就是为什么人们如此震惊。我一直试图这样说，但人们不理解指数是什么意思。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,786:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,790:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  In 2018, we doubled our global fleet, cumulatively. We made and delivered about as many
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,791:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: cars as we had in our entire history. Most people thought it wasn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,791:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,792:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t possible. If you predicted linear
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,793:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: growth, it wouldn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,793:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,794:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t seem possible.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,794:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,795:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  2018 年，我们的全球车队累计翻了一番。我们制造和交付的汽车数量与我们整个历史中的数量差不多。大多数人认为这是不可能的。如果你预测线性增长，它似乎不可能。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,795:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,803:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  But when making estimates involving exponential growth, small changes in the calendar
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,806:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: breakpoint have enormous percentage differences in outcome. The time difference is small, but the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,808:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: percentage difference in the outcome is enormous.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,809:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,810:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  但在进行涉及指数增长的估计时，日历断点的小变化会导致结果的巨大百分比差异。时间差异很小，但结果的百分比差异巨大。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,810:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,812:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  As far as our predictions are concerned, the media tends to report all the wrong ones and
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,813:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ignore all the correct ones. I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,814:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,819:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ve had a long career in multiple industries. If you list just my sins, I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,819:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: sound like the worst person on Earth. But if you put those in the context of what I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,819:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,820:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ve done right, it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,820:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: makes much more sense.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,821:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,821:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  就我们的预测而言，媒体倾向于报道所有错误的预测，忽略所有正确的预测。我在多个行业有很长的职业生涯。如果你只列出我的罪过，我听起来像地球上最糟糕的人。但如果你把这些放在我做对的事情的背景下，这就更有意义了。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,822:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,822:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,822:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,823:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t want to blow your mind, but I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,823:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,823:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: m not always right.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,824:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,824:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我不想让你震惊，但我并不总是对的。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,824:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,827:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The longer you do anything, the more mistakes you will make, cumulatively. If you sum
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,827:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: up just the mistakes, it sounds like I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,828:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,828:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: m the worst predictor ever, which is not the case.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,829:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,829:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  你做任何事情的时间越长，你犯的错误就越多，累积起来。如果你只总结错误，听起来我是有史以来最糟糕的预测者，事实并非如此。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,829:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,830:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Some of them happen sooner or later, but they do tend to come true. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,830:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,836:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s rare they do not
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,838:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: come true eventually. For radical technology predictions, the point is not that it was a few years late,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,839:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: but that it happened at all. That
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,839:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,840:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s the more important part.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,840:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,840:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  其中一些迟早会发生，但它们确实倾向于实现。它们最终不实现的情况很少见。对于激进的技术预测，重点不是它晚了几 年，而是它确实发生了。那是更重要的部分。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,841:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,841:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I may be a little optimistic, but I always deliver.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,842:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,842:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我可能有点乐观，但我总是兑现承诺。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,843:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: WE MUST MAKE STUFF
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,843:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 我们必须制造东西
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,844:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,844:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Manufacturing is underrated. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,844:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,845:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s hard.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,845:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,846:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  制造被低估了。它很难。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,846:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: PART III: BUILDING COMPANIES
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,847:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 第三部分：创建公司
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,847:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,848:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Q: What fuels your creativity?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,848:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,848:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  问：什么激发你的创造力？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,849:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,849:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Pressure. Necessity.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,850:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,850:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  压力。必要性。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,851:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: WE MUST MAKE STUFF (continued)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,851:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 我们必须制造东西（续）
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,852:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The Real Work
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,852:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 真正的工作
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,852:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,853:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Some people have an absurd view of the economy as a magic thing that just produces stuff.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,854:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,854:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  有些人对经济有一种荒谬的看法，认为它是一个能自动生产东西的魔法。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,855:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,857:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  They think goods and services magically come from somewhere, and if somebody has
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,857:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: more stuff than somebody else, it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,858:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,858:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s because they took more from this magic source of stuff.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,859:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,859:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  他们认为商品和服务神奇地从某个地方来，如果有人比别人有更多东西，那是因为他们从这个魔法来源拿了更多。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,859:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,860:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Now, let me break it to the fools out there. If we don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,860:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,860:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t make stuff, there
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,861:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,861:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s no stuff. If we
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,861:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,862:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,862:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t grow the food, process the food, and transport the food…there
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,863:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,864:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s no food. Medical treatments,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,864:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: getting your teeth fixed, everything. There
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,865:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,865:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s no stuff if we don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,865:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,866:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t make stuff.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,866:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,866:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  现在，让我告诉那些愚蠢的人。如果我们不制造东西，就没有东西。如果我们不种植食物、加工食物、运输食物……就没有食物。医疗、补牙、一切。如果我们不制造东西，就没有东西。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,867:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,872:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Some people have become detached from reality. This notion that the government can just
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,872:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: send checks out to everybody and everything will be fine is not true—obviously. You can
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,873:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,874:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t just legislate
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,874:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: money to solve things. If you don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,875:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,875:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t make stuff, there is no stuff. The whole machine could grind to a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,876:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: halt.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,876:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,877:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  有些人已经脱离了现实。这种认为政府可以给每个人寄支票一切就会好起来的想法是不对的——显然。你不能仅仅通过立法印钱来解决问题。如果你不制造东西，就没有东西。整个机器可能会停止运转。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,877:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,877:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Technological progress is not inevitable. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,878:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,879:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s not some kind of abstract concept. Humans
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,879:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: make technology. If we don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,880:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,880:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t do it, it will not happen.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,881:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,881:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  技术进步不是必然的。它不是某种抽象概念。人类创造技术。如果我们不做，它就不会发生。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,882:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,882:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Somebody has to do the real work.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,882:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,883:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  必须有人做真正的工作。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,883:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,884:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  There
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,884:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,895:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s an overallocation of talent in finance and law, especially in the United States. Too
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,899:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: many smart people go into finance and law. This is both a compliment and a criticism. We should
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,900:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: have fewer people doing law and finance and more people making stuff.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,900:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,901:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  金融和法律领域人才过剩，特别是在美国。太多聪明人进入金融和法律。这既是赞美也是批评。我们应该有更少的人从事法律和金融，更多的人制造东西。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,901:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,902:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Manufacturing used to be highly valued in the United States. These days it hasn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,902:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,904:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t been as
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,905:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: much, which I think is wrong. Making cars is an honest day
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,905:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,905:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s living, that
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,906:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,909:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s for sure. Making anything
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,910:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: or providing a valuable service like good entertainment, good information—these are valuable things to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,910:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: do.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,911:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,911:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  制造业在美国曾经受到高度重视。这些天来没有那么多了，我认为这是错误的。制造汽车是诚实的谋生方式，这是肯定的。制造任何东西或提供有价值的服务，如好的娱乐、好的信息——这些都是有价值的事情。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,912:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,912:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,913:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,913:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ve got mad respect for the makers of things.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,914:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,914:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我对制造东西的人非常尊敬。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,915:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The Factory Is the Product
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,915:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 工厂就是产品
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,916:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,917:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The biggest epiphany I had building Tesla is what really matters is the machine that builds
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,918:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the machines—the factory.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,918:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,919:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我在建造特斯拉过程中最大的顿悟是真正重要的是制造机器的机器——工厂。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,919:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,929:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  To accelerate a sustainable future, Tesla had to scale up production volume as quickly as
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,932:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: possible. That is why Tesla engineering transitioned to focus heavily on designing the machine that
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,933:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: makes the machines—turning the factory itself into the product.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,933:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,934:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  为了加速可持续的未来，特斯拉必须尽快扩大生产规模。这就是为什么特斯拉工程转变为专注于设计制造机器的机器——将工厂本身变成产品。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,935:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,940:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  A first-principles physics analysis of automotive production suggests that somewhere
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,942:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: between a fivefold to tenfold improvement is achievable by version three on a roughly two-year
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,942:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: iteration cycle.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,943:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,943:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  对汽车生产的第一性原理物理分析表明，在大约两年的迭代周期内，到第三版可以实现五倍到十倍的改进。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,944:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,944:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Tesla believes strongly in making things. Apple and Google do not. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,945:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,949:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s a philosophical
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,951:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: difference. We believe that manufacturing technology is itself subject to a tremendous amount of
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,952:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: innovation. In fact, we believe there
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,952:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,967:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s more potential for innovation in manufacturing than in the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,976:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: design of a car—by a long shot. This is just a philosophical difference. Perhaps we are wrong. But we
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,978:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: believe in manufacturing, and a company that values manufacturing as highly as we do will attract
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,978:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the best minds in manufacturing.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,978:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,979:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  特斯拉坚信制造东西。苹果和谷歌不这样认为。这是一个哲学差异。我们相信制造技术本身会受到大量创新的影响。事实上，我们认为制造业的创新潜力比汽车设计大得多——远远超过。这只是哲学差异。也许我们错了。但我们相信制造业，一家像我们一样重视制造业的公司将吸引制造业最优秀的人才。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,979:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,982:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Our success or failure will not be because of competition. It will be our capability to make
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,983:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: a high-quality product at a price people can afford.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,983:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,984:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我们的成功或失败不会是因为竞争。而是我们能否以人们负担得起的价格制造高质量产品。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,984:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,984:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  You
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,985:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,986:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ve got this giant factory, a cybernetic collective with ten thousand things going wrong
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,986:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: and you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,987:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,987:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ve got to solve them all. Fast. If you don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,987:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,988:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t solve problems fast enough, the factory doesn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,988:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,990:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,990:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: go. A big factory burns a huge amount of money every minute you aren
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,991:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,991:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t making a product.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,991:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,992:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  你有一个巨大的工厂，一个控制论集体，有一万件事出错，你必须全部解决。快速。如果你不能足够快地解决问题，工厂就无法运转。每一分钟你不生产产品，大工厂就会燃烧大量资金。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,992:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Attack the Constraint
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,993:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 攻击限制因素
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,993:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,994:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Designing a rocket is trivial.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,994:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,995:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  设计火箭是微不足道的。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:54,995:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,001:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  There are tons of books you can read, and if you can understand equations, you can design
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,002:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: a rocket. Real easy. But making even one of these things and getting it to orbit is very hard.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,003:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,003:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  有成吨的书你可以读，如果你能理解方程，你就能设计火箭。很容易。但制造其中一个并将其送入轨道非常困难。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,004:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,004:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,004:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,005:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s the same thing for cars. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,005:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,006:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s easy to make a car prototype; it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,006:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,007:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s hard to do car production.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,007:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,008:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  汽车也是一样。制造汽车原型很容易；进行汽车生产很难。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,008:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,009:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  This is underappreciated. People think there is a 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,009:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,010:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: eureka
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,010:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,011:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  moment where you come up
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,012:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: with an idea and that
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,012:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,013:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s it. They believe design is the hard part and production is just making copies.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,013:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: That
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,014:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,014:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s completely false.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,015:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,015:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  这被低估了。人们认为有一个
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,016:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,016:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 尤里卡
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,016:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,017:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 时刻，你想出一个想法就完了。他们认为设计是困难的部分，生产只是复制。这完全错误。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,017:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,021:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  At Tesla, we learned a valuable lesson. The production line will move as fast as the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,022:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: slowest and least lucky part of the entire production line. Let
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,022:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,026:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s say there are ten thousand things that
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,027:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: have to go right for production to work. If you have 9,999 things working and one that isn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,027:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,028:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t, that sets
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,028:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the production rate.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,029:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,030:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  在特斯拉，我们学到了宝贵的教训。生产线的速度将取决于整个生产线中最慢和最不走运的部分。假设有上万件事必须正确才能让生产运转。如果你有 9,999 件事正常工作，有一件不正常，那就决定了生产率。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,030:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,043:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Things move as fast as the least lucky or least competent supplier. Any natural disaster you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,049:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: care to name has happened to our suppliers. A supplier had a factory burn down. An earthquake. A
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,049:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: tsunami. Massive hail. A tornado. A ship sank. A shoot-out at the Mexican border. I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,050:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,051:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: m not kidding.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,051:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: That delayed trunk carpet.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,052:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,052:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  事情的速度取决于最不走运或最无能的供应商。任何你能想到的自然灾害都发生在我们的供应商身上。一个供应商的工厂被烧毁。地震。海啸。大冰雹。龙卷风。一艘船沉没。墨西哥边境的枪战。我不是开玩笑。那延迟了后备箱地毯。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,053:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,063:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  So when scaling SpaceX, we spent ten to one hundred times more effort on designing the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,067:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: manufacturing system than on designing the Raptor engine. We built the rockets first and the factory
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,068:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: later, because building the production system is the harder thing.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,068:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,069:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  所以在扩大 SpaceX 规模时，我们在设计制造系统上花费的精力是设计猛禽发动机的十到一百倍。我们先建造火箭，后建造工厂，因为建造生产系统是更困难的事情。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,069:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,085:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Design is overrated, and manufacturing is underrated. There is 1,000 percent, maybe
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,093:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 10,000 percent more work that goes into the production system than the product itself. Especially for
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,095:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: a product with new technology. The difficulty of manufacturing is proportionate to the amount of
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,095:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: new technology in the product.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,096:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,096:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  设计被高估了，制造被低估了。生产系统比产品本身多 1000%，可能 10000% 的工作量。特别是对于有新技术的产品。制造难度与产品中新技术的数量成正比。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,096:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Manufacturing Is the Moat
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,097:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 制造是护城河
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,097:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,106:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Two things define manufacturing competitiveness: economies of scale and technology. If
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,108:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: you maximize your level of technology and maximize your level of scale, this is obviously going to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,108:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: be the most competitive situation. That
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,109:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,109:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s why plants are so freaking giant.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,110:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,110:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  两件事定义制造竞争力：规模经济和技术。如果你最大化你的技术水平和规模水平，这显然是最具竞争力的情况。这就是为什么工厂如此巨大。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,110:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,133:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Our plant in Texas starts from actual rail cars of raw materials coming in. We form the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,144:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: battery cell and the battery pack, build the motor, and cast the parts. We also have introduced a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,147:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: major innovation, which is to cast the entire front third and rear third of the car as a single piece. I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,148:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: got this idea from toy cars. I wondered, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,148:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,149:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Toys are cheap
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,149:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: !
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,149:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  How do they make toys?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,150:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,150:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,151:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,151:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: They just cast
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,151:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: them.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,152:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,152:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I was like, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,152:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,153:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Well, can you build a casting machine big enough for a car?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,153:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,154:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  They said, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,154:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,155:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: No one
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,155:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ever has.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,155:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,156:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,156:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,157:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Are we breaking any laws of physics?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,157:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,157:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,158:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,158:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: No…
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,159:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,159:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,159:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,160:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Well, let
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,160:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,161:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s just ask them.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,161:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,165:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  There were six
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,167:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: major casting machine suppliers in the world at the time. Five of them said no and the sixth said
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,167:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: maybe. I said, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,168:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,168:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,169:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,169:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ll take that as a yes.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,169:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,170:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,170:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我们在德克萨斯州的工厂从实际的原材料铁路车厢开始。我们制造电池单元和电池组，建造电机，铸造部件。我们还引入了一项重大创新，即将汽车的前三分之一和后三分之一整体铸造成一个部件。我从玩具车上得到这个想法。我想，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,171:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,171:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 玩具很便宜！他们如何制造玩具？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,172:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,172:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,173:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 他们只是铸造它们。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,173:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,173:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 我想，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,174:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,174:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 好吧，你能建造一台足够大的铸造机来铸造汽车吗？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,175:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,175:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 他们说，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,175:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,176:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 从来没有人这样做过。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,176:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,177:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,177:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 我们违反任何物理定律吗？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,178:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,178:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,178:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 不……
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,179:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,179:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,180:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 好吧，让我们问问他们。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,180:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,181:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 当时世界上有六家主要的铸造机供应商。其中五家说不，第六家说可能。我说，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,181:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,182:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 我就当那是同意了。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,182:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,182:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,184:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Prototypes are easy and fun. Reaching volume production with a reliable product at an
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,185:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: affordable price is excruciatingly difficult.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,186:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,186:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  原型很容易也很有趣。以负担得起的价格实现可靠产品的批量生产极其困难。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,187:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: BECOMING A FOUNDER
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,187:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 成为创始人
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,188:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,189:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  You want to embark on something where success is certain to be one of the possible
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,189:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: outcomes.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,190:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,190:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  你想开始一件事，其中成功肯定是可能的结果之一。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,191:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,192:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Q: What was the path to starting your first company?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,192:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,193:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  问：你创办第一家公司的路径是什么？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,193:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,201:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Growing up in South Africa, it seemed like a lot of the advanced technology was being
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,203:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: produced in America and Silicon Valley, especially. I wanted to go where I could be involved in the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,204:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: creation of new technology. That
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,204:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,207:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s what took me first to Canada (because I could get citizenship in
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,208:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Canada through my mom) and then ultimately to the US.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,208:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,209:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  在南非长大，似乎很多先进技术都在美国，特别是硅谷生产。我想去一个我可以参与创造新技术的地方。这就是我先去加拿大（因为我可以通过我妈妈获得加拿大公民身份）然后最终去美国的原因。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,209:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,215:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  When I was seventeen, I got my Canadian passport. Three weeks later I was in Canada. I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,216:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: left South Africa and landed in Montreal. I arrived with a backpack, a suitcase of books, and $2,000.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,217:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,217:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  十七岁时，我拿到了加拿大护照。三周后我就在加拿大了。我离开南非，降落在蒙特利尔。我带着一个背包、一箱书和 2000 美元到达。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,218:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,221:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I stayed in a youth hostel for a few days, then bought a bus ticket for one hundred bucks to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,222:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: go across the country, making stops along the way.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,222:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,222:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我在青年旅社住了几天，然后花一百美元买了一张巴士票穿越全国，沿途停靠。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,223:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,223:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I managed to get to Swift Current in Saskatchewan. My cousin
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,224:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,230:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s son had a wheat farm
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,233:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: where I worked for about six weeks, as I turned eighteen. We did a barn raising, cleared out the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,234:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: wheat bins and grain silos, and worked the vegetable patch.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,234:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,234:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我设法到达了萨斯喀彻温省的斯威夫特卡伦特。我表哥的儿子有一个小麦农场，我在那里工作了大约六周，当时我刚满十八岁。我们建谷仓、清理小麦仓和谷仓，并在菜园工作。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,235:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,243:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Then I got back on the bus and went to Vancouver. I had a half-uncle there in the lumber
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,246:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: industry. I ended up working at a lumber mill chainsawing logs and cleaning out the pulp boiler.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,246:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: That might be the hardest job I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,246:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,251:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ve had. You had to crawl through this little tunnel in a hazmat suit
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,252:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: and then shovel this steaming sand and mush out of the boilers to clean them out. There
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,252:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,253:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s only one
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,254:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: entrance or exit, a little tunnel. If you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,254:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,262:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re claustrophobic, it would be real bad. It did not seem safe.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,265:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: But it was the highest-paying job at the employment office. Other jobs were under eight dollars an
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,266:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: hour, and this one was eighteen dollars an hour.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,266:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,267:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  然后我回到巴士上去了温哥华。我在那里有个半叔叔在木材行业。我最终在一家锯木厂用电锯锯木头和清理纸浆锅炉。那可能是我做过的最艰难的工作。你必须穿着防护服爬过这个小隧道，然后把锅炉里的蒸汽沙子和糊状物铲出来清理干净。只有一个入口或出口，一个小隧道。如果你有幽闭恐惧症，那就很糟糕了。这看起来不安全。但那是就业办公室薪水最高的工作。其他工作每小时不到八美元，这份工作是每小时十八美元。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,267:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,269:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I worked there as a lumberjack doing odd jobs for a few months. Then I applied for
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,269:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: college, and went to Queen
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,270:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,271:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s University in Kingston. I was there for a couple years before applying
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,271:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: to UPenn. I didn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,272:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,272:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t think I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,272:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,273:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: d be able to go because I was paying my own way through university. That
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,273:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,276:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s not too hard in Canada because tuition is highly subsidized, but in the US college is more expensive.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,276:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,277:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我在那里当伐木工做了几个月的零工。然后我申请了大学，去了金斯顿的女王大学。我在那里待了几年，然后申请了宾夕法尼亚大学。我认为我去不了，因为我自己支付大学费用。这在加拿大不太难，因为学费有大量补贴，但在美国大学更贵。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,277:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,279:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I paid my own way through college and dropped out of Stanford grad school with $110K
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,279:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: in college debt.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,280:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,280:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我自己支付大学费用，从斯坦福研究生院退学时背负着 11 万美元的大学债务。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,281:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,316:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Physics and computer science were always my two best subjects, because I wanted to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,339:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: figure out the nature of the universe. I thought I might do physics at a particle accelerator, banging
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,351:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: particles together to see what happens in a research facility. Then, the supercollider got canceled in
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,355:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the US, and I realized I could study for years to work at a collider, and then the government could
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,356:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: arbitrarily cancel it. Decision made: I could not do that.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,356:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,357:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  物理学和计算机科学一直是我最好的两门学科，因为我想弄清楚宇宙的本质。我想我可能会在粒子加速器做物理学，在研究设施中将粒子碰撞在一起看会发生什么。然后，超级对撞机在美国被取消了，我意识到我可能会学习多年在对撞机工作，然后政府可以随意取消它。决定已定：我不能那样做。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,357:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,358:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Q: How did you decide to leave your PhD program and start your first company?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,358:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,359:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  问：你如何决定离开博士项目并创办你的第一家公司？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,359:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,378:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Because of my interest in electric cars as a college student, I took an internship at a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,387:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: company that made high-energy-density capacitors. My intent was to get a PhD in energy storage
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,390:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: solutions for electric vehicles. I was going to Stanford to study material science and the physics of
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,391:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: high-energy-density capacitors for use in electric vehicles.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,391:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,392:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  由于我作为大学生对电动汽车的兴趣，我在一家制造高密度电容器的公司实习。我的意图是获得电动汽车储能解决方案的博士学位。我要去斯坦福学习材料科学和高密度电容器的物理学，用于电动汽车。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,392:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,393:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  But, I wasn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,393:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,396:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t sure if my work during that PhD would actually be useful. I was concerned it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,396:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: could be academically useful but not practically useful.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,397:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,397:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  但是，我不确定我在博士期间的工作是否真的有用。我担心它可能在学术上有用但在实践中无用。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,398:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,400:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Success on an academic level would have been quite likely. I could publish a paper, but
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,400:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: most papers are pretty useless.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,401:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,401:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  在学术层面成功是相当可能的。我可以发表论文，但大多数论文都很无用。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,402:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,403:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Once in a while you get something spectacular but it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,403:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,420:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s pretty rare. How many PhD papers
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,432:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: are actually used by someone, ever? Percentagewise, not many. You add a leaf to the tree of
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,437:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: knowledge, but that leaf could be saying, Nope, not possible. This is not good enough technology to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,437:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: be used in an electric vehicle. There goes seven years of my life.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,438:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,438:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  偶尔你会得到一些惊人的东西，但这很罕见。有多少博士论文真的被人使用过？按百分比，不多。你为知识之树添加了一片叶子，但那片叶子可能在说，不，不可能。这不够好的技术不能用于电动汽车。我七年的生命就这样没了。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,439:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,442:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Not that I cared about the PhD, actually. I just needed a lab. I could spend years working in
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,443:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: a lab and maybe the technology would work…or maybe it wouldn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,443:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,444:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,444:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,444:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  其实我不是在乎博士学位。我只是需要一个实验室。我可能会花几年时间在实验室工作，也许技术会成功……也许不会。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,445:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,445:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I was not sure success was even a possibility. I thought maybe it was, but I wasn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,446:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,446:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t sure.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,446:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,447:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我不确定成功是否有可能。我想也许有，但我不确定。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,448:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,449:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Then the internet started taking off. It was clear to me the internet was happening in 1995,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,452:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: although most people weren
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,452:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,464:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t aware of it then. I was pretty sure success was one of the possible
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,469:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: outcomes for an internet company. I knew watching the internet get built while doing a PhD would
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,470:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: be frustrating. I decided to put graduate school on hold and start an internet company.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,470:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,471:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  然后互联网开始起飞。我很清楚互联网在 1995 年正在发生，尽管当时大多数人没有意识到。我相当确定成功是互联网公司的可能结果之一。我知道在做博士时看着互联网建立会令人沮丧。我决定把研究生院搁置一边，创办一家互联网公司。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,471:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,472:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I thought I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,472:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,477:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: d be able to come back to electric vehicles. I figured electric vehicle technology
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,477:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: and energy storage technology would have a natural progression, and that ended up happening.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,478:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,478:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我想我能够回到电动汽车。我认为电动汽车技术和储能技术会有一个自然的发展，结果确实如此。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,479:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,488:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  In 1995, it was not obvious you could make any money on the internet. Until Netscape
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,492:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: went public in late 1995, nobody thought you could make a valuable internet company. Now it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,492:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: seems obvious. But back then, it was not at all.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,493:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,493:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  1995 年，很明显你不能在互联网上赚钱。直到网景在 1995 年末上市，没有人认为你可以创建一家有价值的互联网公司。现在这似乎很明显。但那时，完全不是这样。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,494:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,498:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Humanity was effectively becoming a superorganism, qualitatively different from what it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,499:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: had been before. I wanted to be part of that. I wanted to help build humanity
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,500:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,500:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s nervous system.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,500:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,501:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  人类实际上正在成为一个超级有机体，与以前有质的不同。我想成为其中的一部分。我想帮助建立人类的神经系统。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,501:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,503:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The internet turned out to be a good idea for my first company because software is a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,504:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: low-capital endeavor. I didn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,504:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,505:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t have any money, and had a bunch of student debt. You don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,505:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,507:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t need a lot
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,508:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: of tooling and equipment to get started. Software you can just write by yourself. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,508:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,511:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s not capital
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,511:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: intensive. Starting something software-related as your first company is much, much easier.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,512:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,512:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  互联网结果是我第一家公司的一个好主意，因为软件是低资本的努力。我没有任何钱，还有一堆学生债务。你不需要很多工具和设备就可以开始。软件你可以自己写。它不是资本密集型的。以软件相关的东西作为你的第一家公司要容易得多。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,513:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Starting Zip2
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,514:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 创办 Zip2
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,514:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,515:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  When we first started Zip2, our ambitions were quite low: make enough money to pay rent.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,515:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,516:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  当我们刚开始 Zip2 时，我们的野心很低：赚足够的钱付房租。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,516:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,517:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Q: When did you start your first company?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,517:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,518:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  问：你什么时候开始你的第一家公司？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,519:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,520:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Starting a company was not actually the first thing I tried. I tried to get a job at Netscape,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,520:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: but they didn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,521:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,522:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t reply to my emails. So I went to hang out in the lobby at Netscape. I didn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,522:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,524:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t know who
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,524:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: to talk to, and I was too shy to talk to anyone. I figured, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,525:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,525:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: If I can
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,526:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,526:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t get a job, I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,527:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,527:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ll just try writing my
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,528:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: own software.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,528:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,529:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,529:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  创办公司实际上不是我尝试的第一件事。我试图在网景找到工作，但他们没有回复我的电子邮件。所以我去网景的大厅闲逛。我不知道该和谁说话，我太害羞了不敢和任何人说话。我想，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,530:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,530:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 如果我找不到工作，我就自己写软件。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,531:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,531:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,532:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  It wasn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,532:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,534:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t actually from the desire to start a company. I just wanted to be part of building the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,535:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: internet in some way. Since I couldn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,535:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,536:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t get a job at an internet company, I had to start one myself.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,536:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,536:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  实际上不是出于创办公司的愿望。我只是想以某种方式参与建设互联网。由于我无法在互联网公司找到工作，我不得不自己创办一家。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,537:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,537:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I wanted to try to build something useful, but I didn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,538:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,540:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t think I would build anything
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,541:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: particularly great. Probabilistically, greatness seemed unlikely, but I wanted to at least try.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,541:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,542:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我想尝试建造一些有用的东西，但我不认为我会建造任何特别伟大的东西。从概率上讲，伟大似乎不太可能，但我至少想试试。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,542:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,560:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  We started off building maps, directions, and classified ads. It was, to the best of my
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,568:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: knowledge, the first map and directions on the internet. There may still be some patents—or maybe they
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,570:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: lapsed at this point. (Note from Eric: there is, patent #5944769.) The whole initial code base I wrote
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,570:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: myself because there wasn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,570:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,571:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t anyone else. It was just me.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,571:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,572:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我们开始制作地图、方向和分类广告。据我所知，这是互联网上的第一个地图和方向。可能还有一些专利——或者也许它们现在已经失效了。（埃里克的注释：有，专利号 5944769。）整个初始代码库我自己写的，因为没有其他人。只有我。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,572:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,583:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I was twenty-four at the time and only had a few thousand dollars saved. I convinced my
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,586:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: brother to join, and he brought about five thousand dollars, which was a lot for us. For the first few
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,587:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: months, we only had one computer. When the website wasn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,587:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,600:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t working, it was because I was
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,609:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: compiling code. The website was up during the day; I was coding at night, seven days a week, all
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,611:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the time. We more or less squatted in the office because the landlord was always out of the country,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,611:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: and nobody was using it.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,612:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,612:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我当时二十四岁，只存了几千美元。我说服我弟弟加入，他带了大约五千美元，这对我们来说很多。在最初的几个月里，我们只有一台电脑。当网站不工作时，是因为我在编译代码。网站白天运行；我晚上编码，一周七天，一直如此。我们或多或少 squatting 在办公室里，因为房东总是在国外，没有人用它。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,613:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,613:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Soon, there were six of us. Me, my brother, a friend of my mom
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,614:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,615:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s, and three salespeople
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,616:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: we hired on contingency by putting an ad in the newspaper.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,616:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,617:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  很快，我们有六个人。我、我弟弟、我妈妈的一个朋友，以及我们通过报纸广告雇佣的三个销售人员。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,617:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,618:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Things were pretty tough in the early going. I didn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,618:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,620:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t have any money. In fact, I had
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,620:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: negative money because of a huge student debt. I couldn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,621:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,640:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t afford an apartment and an office, so I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,653:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: rented an office because that was cheaper. I slept on the futon at the office and showered at the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,657:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: YMCA. I briefly had a girlfriend in that period and to stay with me, she had to sleep in the office. I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,658:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: was in the best shape—every day a workout, shower, and you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,658:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,659:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re good to go
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,659:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: !
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,659:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,660:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  早期的事情相当艰难。我没有任何钱。事实上，我有负钱，因为巨额学生债务。我买不起公寓和办公室，所以我租了一间办公室，因为那更便宜。我睡在办公室的蒲团上，在基督教青年会洗澡。那段时间我短暂有一个女朋友，为了和我在一起，她不得不睡在办公室里。我状态最好——每天锻炼、洗澡，就可以出发了！
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,661:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,687:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  There was a small internet service provider on the floor below us, so we drilled a hole
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,703:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: through the floor and connected a modem cable. That got us our internet connection for one hundred
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,709:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: bucks a month. We had a tiny revenue stream, but an absurdly tiny burn rate. We actually had more
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,710:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: revenue than we had expenses. When we talked to VCs (venture capitalists), we could say we were
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,711:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: profitable.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,711:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,712:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我们楼下有一家小型互联网服务提供商，所以我们在地板上钻了一个洞，连接了一根调制解调器电缆。这让我们以每月一百美元的价格获得了互联网连接。我们有很小的收入流，但燃烧率小得荒谬。我们实际上收入比支出多。当我们与风险投资家交谈时，我们可以说我们是盈利的。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,712:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,713:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Most venture capitalists wouldn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,713:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,714:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t take a meeting with us, though. They said, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,714:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,715:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Who
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,715:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,716:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s made
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,717:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: money on the internet? No one. Okay, pass.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,717:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,718:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,718:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  不过，大多数风险投资家不愿与我们会面。他们说，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,718:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,719:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 谁在互联网上赚到钱了？没有人。好吧，跳过。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,719:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,720:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,732:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  There was a lot more interest in the internet following the Netscape IPO (initial public
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,737:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: offering). Our software was more impressive by then, too. Mohr Davidow Ventures (a VC firm)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,738:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: invested $3 million for 60 percent of the company, which we thought was crazy. They
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,738:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,746:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re going to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,751:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: give us money for nothing? They must be mad. It seemed insane to give us so much money for a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,752:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: company that consisted of six people at the time. But it worked out well for them.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,753:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,753:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  网景首次公开募股后，人们对互联网的兴趣大增。那时我们的软件也更令人印象深刻。Mohr Davidow Ventures（一家风险投资公司）投资 300 万美元购买公司 60% 的股份，我们认为这很疯狂。他们会白给我们钱？他们一定疯了。给我们这么多钱换取当时只有六个人的公司似乎很疯狂。但这对他们来说效果很好。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,754:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,755:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Q: How did the original idea for Zip2 come about?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,755:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,756:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  问：Zip2 的最初想法是如何产生的？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,756:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,779:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  We needed to build something that would earn money quickly. We thought the media
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,792:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: industry would need help converting their content from print to electronic, and they clearly had
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,796:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: money. If we could help them move to the internet, maybe we could generate revenue. There was no
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,797:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: advertising revenue on the internet at the time. That was the basis of Zip2.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,797:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,798:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我们需要建造一些能快速赚钱的东西。我们认为媒体行业需要帮助将他们的内容从印刷转换为电子，他们显然有钱。如果我们能帮助他们转向互联网，也许我们可以产生收入。当时互联网上没有广告收入。这就是 Zip2 的基础。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,798:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,814:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  We hired a lot more people and wrote software to bring newspapers online. Knight Ridder,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,821:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: New York Times Company, and Hearst all became investors and customers. And at one point, Zip2
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,823:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: was responsible for a significant section of the New York Times Company website. I got to know
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,823:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the media industry well.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,823:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,824:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我们雇佣了更多的人，编写软件将报纸上线。骑士里德、纽约时报公司和赫斯特都成为投资者和客户。在某个时候，Zip2 负责纽约时报公司网站的重要部分。我很好地了解了媒体行业。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,824:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,835:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The challenge was too much control by the existing media companies. They had too many
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,839:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: board seats and too much voting control over Zip2. They kept trying to push the company in
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,840:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: directions that made no sense. We actually had good software—comparable to Yahoo
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,840:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: !
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,844:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  or Excite at the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,846:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: time. It was all being forced through media companies, who would not fully use it. We built the best
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,846:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: technology, but it wasn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,847:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,847:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t being deployed properly.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,848:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,848:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  挑战是现有媒体公司的控制太多。他们有太多的董事会席位和对 Zip2 的太多投票控制权。他们不断试图将公司推向毫无意义的方向。我们实际上有很好的软件——当时可与雅虎或 Excite 相媲美。它都被迫通过媒体公司，他们不会充分利用它。我们建造了最好的技术，但它没有被正确部署。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,849:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,849:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,849:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,853:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s a bit like building F-22 fighter jets and selling them to people who roll them down the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,853:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: hill at each other. Not the way to use the technology
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,853:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: !
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,854:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,854:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  这有点像建造 F-22 战斗机，然后卖给互相从山上滚下来的人。这不是使用技术的方式！
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,855:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,855:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  That
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,855:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,856:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s when I realized you want to sell your products straight to the end consumer. If you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,857:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,858:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ve got great technology, go directly to the end consumer. Don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,858:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,859:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t sell it to some bonehead legacy
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,859:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: company that doesn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,860:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,860:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t understand how to use it.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,861:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,861:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  那时我意识到你想直接把产品卖给最终消费者。如果你有很好的技术，直接去最终消费者。不要把它卖给一些不懂如何使用它的愚蠢传统公司。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,861:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,868:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Fortunately, Compaq came along. We had the opportunity to sell Zip2 to Compaq in early
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,869:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 1999 and accepted that offer. It was a little over $300 million in cash. Cash is a currency I highly
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,870:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: recommend.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,870:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,871:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  幸运的是，康柏出现了。我们在 1999 年初有机会将 Zip2 出售给康柏，并接受了那个报价。那是超过 3 亿美元的现金。现金是我强烈推荐的货币。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,871:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,875:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  To this day, that moment astonishes me. At the time I was living in a house with four
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,876:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: housemates. Literally, a check came in my mailbox. I was like, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,876:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,877:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: This is insane. What if somebody…? I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,877:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: mean, I guess they
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,878:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,878:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: d have trouble cashing it?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,879:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,880:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Seems like a weird way to send money. My bank
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,881:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: account went from $5,000 to $21,005,000.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,881:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,882:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  直到今天，那一刻仍然让我惊讶。当时我和四个室友住在一所房子里。真的，一张支票出现在我的邮箱里。我想，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,882:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,883:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 这太疯狂了。如果有人……？我的意思是，我想他们兑现会有困难？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,883:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,884:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 这似乎是一种奇怪的汇款方式。我的银行账户从 5000 美元变成了 21,005,000 美元。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,884:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,885:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Immediately after the sale, I didn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,885:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,893:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t take any time off. I still had to pay taxes, then I ended
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,896:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: up putting almost all of that into X.com (which became PayPal). This was early 1999, and there
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,898:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: were a lot of opportunities remaining on the internet.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,899:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,899:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  出售后，我没有休息。我仍然需要纳税，然后我最终把几乎所有钱都投入了 X.com（后来成为 PayPal）。这是 1999 年初，互联网上还有很多机会。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,900:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,900:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,901:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,901:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ve always wanted to push my chips back on the table or play the next level of the game. I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,902:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,902:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: m not good at sitting back.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,903:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,903:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我一直想把筹码推回桌上或玩游戏的下一级。我不擅长袖手旁观。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,904:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Going All In, Again (Zip2 Earnings into PayPal)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,905:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 再次全力以赴（Zip2 收益投入 PayPal）
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,905:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,906:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  It was frustrating.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,906:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,907:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  这令人沮丧。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,907:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,911:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  We built incredible technology at Zip2, and it had not been used. I wanted to build another
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,912:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: internet company to show technology can be extremely effective when used properly.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,912:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,912:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我们在 Zip2 建造了令人难以置信的技术，但它没有被使用。我想再建一家互联网公司，以表明技术如果正确使用可以非常有效。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,913:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,916:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I felt like we had our wings clipped somewhat with Zip2. I wanted to avoid being
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,917:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: constrained by our customers like that, and go direct-to-consumer. That
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,917:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,917:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s what motivated me to start
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,918:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: PayPal.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,918:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,918:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我觉得我们在 Zip2 的翅膀被剪掉了。我想避免像那样受到客户的限制，直接面向消费者。这就是我创办 PayPal 的动机。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,919:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,919:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Q: How did you come up with the idea for PayPal?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,920:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,920:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  问：你是如何想出 PayPal 的想法的？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,920:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,933:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I thought, What was essentially digital? What exists in the form of information, but is not
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,938:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: high bandwidth? In 1999, most people still had modems, so video was not really feasible. Money is
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,939:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: low bandwidth and mostly digital. What can we do to make money work better?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,939:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,939:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我想，本质上是数字的是什么？什么以信息形式存在，但不是高带宽？1999 年，大多数人仍然有调制解调器，所以视频不太可行。钱是低带宽且主要是数字的。我们能做什么让钱更好地工作？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,940:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,942:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Money is like a database for guiding people to decide what they should do. You can think
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,943:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: of banks as a set of databases.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,943:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,943:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  钱就像一个数据库，指导人们决定他们应该做什么。你可以把银行看作一组数据库。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,944:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,949:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The 1990s financial infrastructure was a bunch of ancient mainframes, running ancient
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,950:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: code, doing batch processing with poor security, and a series of heterogeneous databases. A
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,951:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: herky-jerky frickin
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,951:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,952:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  monstrosity.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,952:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,952:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  1990 年代的金融基础设施是一堆古老的大型机，运行古老的代码，进行安全性差的批处理，以及一系列异构数据库。一个颠簸的该死的怪物。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,953:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,956:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  From an information theory standpoint, finance would be much better if it could be
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,957:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: real-time, secure, and fast. Essentially just one real-time database. Let
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,957:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,958:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s try to build that.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,958:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,959:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  从信息论的角度来看，如果金融能够实时、安全和快速，会好得多。基本上就是一个实时数据库。让我们试着建造那个。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,959:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,960:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Q: Can you explain the PayPal idea from an information theory perspective?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,960:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,961:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  问：你能从信息论角度解释 PayPal 的想法吗？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,961:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,967:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Think of money as information. People often think money has power in and of itself. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,968:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: does not. Money is just information. Money is a database for resource allocation across time and
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,969:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: space.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,969:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,969:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  把金钱看作信息。人们经常认为金钱本身有权力。它没有。金钱只是信息。金钱是一个跨时间和空间资源配置的数据库。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,970:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,970:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Let
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,971:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,973:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s try thinking in the limit, as I explained before. If you are stranded on a tropical island
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,973:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: with a trillion dollars, it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,974:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,975:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s useless. On the island there are no resources to allocate, except yourself, so
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,975:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: money doesn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,976:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,976:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t help. If you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,977:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,978:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re stranded with no food, all the Bitcoin in the world will not stop you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,978:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: from starving.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,979:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,979:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  让我们尝试用极限思维，正如我之前解释的。如果你被困在热带岛屿上，有一万亿美元，那是无用的。在岛上没有资源可分配，除了你自己，所以钱没有帮助。如果你被困没有食物，世界上所有的比特币都不会阻止你挨饿。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,980:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,984:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  You need something to create ratios of value between products and services. In an
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,984:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: economy, you have a massive number of products and services. You can
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,985:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:55,995:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t trade for everything. That
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,002:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: would be extremely unwieldy. You need something to create the ratio of exchange between goods
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,003:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: and services. You also need something that allows us to shift obligations across time, like debt and
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,004:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: equity.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,004:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,005:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  你需要一些东西来创建产品和服务之间的价值比率。在经济中，你有大量的产品和服务。你不能交换所有东西。那将非常笨重。你需要一些东西来创建商品和服务之间的交换比率。你还需要一些东西让我们能够跨时间转移义务，如债务和股权。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,006:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,010:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The quality of money as a system is a function of different variables. Just like an internet
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,010:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: connection, you want high bandwidth, low latency, and few errors.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,011:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,011:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  金钱作为系统的质量是不同变量的函数。就像互联网连接一样，你想要高带宽、低延迟和少错误。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,012:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,028:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  What PayPal really did was help improve the bandwidth—the speed at which money could
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,036:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: move. Instead of mailing checks back and forth, you could do real-time exchange of money online.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,037:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Sellers could then ship items immediately instead of waiting for a check and then for the bank to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,037:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: clear it.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,038:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,038:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  PayPal 真正做的是帮助提高带宽——金钱可以移动的速度。你可以在线实时交换金钱，而不是来回邮寄支票。卖家可以立即发货，而不是等待支票然后等待银行清算。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,039:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,040:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  We should look at currencies from an information theory standpoint. Whichever has least
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,041:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: error and latency will win.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,041:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,042:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我们应该从信息论的角度看待货币。错误和延迟最少的将获胜。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,042:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,043:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  That
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,043:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,045:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s what X.com originally was. I thought we should try to do all the financial things as
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,046:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: well—not just payments. I still think that
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,046:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,047:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s what PayPal should have done, but whatever. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,047:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,048:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s water under
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,048:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the bridge at this point.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,048:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,049:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  这就是 X.com 最初的样子。我想我们也应该尝试做所有金融事情——不仅仅是支付。我仍然认为那是 PayPal 应该做的，但无论如何。这已经是过去式了。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,049:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,054:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I rolled most of my Zip2 money into X.com, investing $12.5 million. In 1999, Sequoia
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,054:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: invested in X.com, buying $5 million in shares, and Mike Moritz joined the company
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,055:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,056:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s board. When
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,057:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Moritz invested, he said we should hire a CEO. I said, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,057:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,058:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Great, I don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,058:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,058:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t want to be CEO.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,059:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,059:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I had no
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,060:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: desire to be a CEO. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,060:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,061:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s a lot of chores…being CEO sucks. He also told me, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,061:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,063:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Dude, you should not invest
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,063:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: basically everything except your house and car in your startup.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,064:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,064:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,065:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我把大部分 Zip2 的钱投入 X.com，投资 1250 万美元。1999 年，红杉资本投资 X.com，购买 500 万美元的股份，迈克·莫里茨加入了公司董事会。当莫里茨投资时，他说我们应该雇佣一位 CEO。我说，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,065:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,066:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 太好了，我不想当 CEO。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,066:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,066:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 我没有当 CEO 的愿望。当 CEO 有很多杂事……当 CEO 很糟糕。他还告诉我，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,067:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,067:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 伙计，你不应该除了房子和车之外把所有东西都投资到你的初创公司。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,068:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,068:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,069:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I kept the chips on the table.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,069:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,069:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我把筹码留在桌上。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,070:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Listen Well, Correct Fast
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,071:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 好好倾听，快速纠正
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,071:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,076:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The initial thought with X.com was to create a conglomeration of financial services, so you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,079:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: have one place where all your financial service needs could be seamlessly integrated and work
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,080:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: smoothly.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,080:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,081:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  X.com 最初的想法是创建一个金融服务集团，这样你就有一个地方可以无缝集成所有你的金融服务需求并顺利工作。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,081:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,082:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  We had a little feature: payments through email. When we showed the system to someone,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,082:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: we
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,083:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,084:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: d show the hard part first: the conglomeration of financial services. Nobody was interested.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,084:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,085:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我们有一个小功能：通过电子邮件支付。当我们向某人展示系统时，我们会先展示困难的部分：金融服务集团。没有人感兴趣。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,085:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,088:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Then we showed people email payments, which were relatively easy to build, and
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,089:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: everybody was interested. So, we focused on email payments. That
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,089:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,090:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s what really got PayPal to take
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,090:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: off.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,091:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,092:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  然后我们向人们展示电子邮件支付，这相对容易构建，每个人都感兴趣。所以，我们专注于电子邮件支付。这才是真正让 PayPal 起飞的原因。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,092:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,092:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,093:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,094:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s important to take feedback from your environment. If we hadn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,094:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,096:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t responded to what
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,096:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: people said, we probably would not have been successful. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,097:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,102:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s important to look for things like that,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,103:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: focus on them, and correct your prior assumptions. You want to close those loops as quickly and
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,104:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: clearly as possible.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,104:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,105:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  从环境中获取反馈很重要。如果我们没有回应人们所说的，我们可能不会成功。重要的是寻找这样的事情，专注于它们，并纠正你之前的假设。你想尽可能快速和清晰地关闭这些循环。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,105:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,106:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,106:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,108:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: m trying to create an accurate mental model of reality. If I have a wrong view on
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,108:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: something, or if there
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,109:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,109:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s a nuanced improvement that can be made, I say, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,109:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,111:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: I used to think this, which
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,111:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: turned out to be wrong—thank goodness I don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,111:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,112:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t have that wrong belief anymore.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,112:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,112:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,113:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我试图创建一个准确的现实心理模型。如果我对某事有错误的看法，或者如果有细微的改进可以做，我会说，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,113:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,114:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 我曾经这样想，结果证明是错的——感谢上帝我不再有那个错误的信念了。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,114:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,114:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,115:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,115:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,115:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: m a huge believer in taking feedback.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,116:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,116:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我非常相信接受反馈。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,116:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,128:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  We took a similar approach with PayPal that worked at Zip2, which was to have a small
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,132:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: group of very talented people, and keep it small. PayPal had maybe thirty engineers for a system
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,132:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: which I would say is more sophisticated than the Federal Reserve clearing system.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,133:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,133:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我们对 PayPal 采用了与 Zip2 类似的行之有效的方法，就是拥有一小群非常有才华的人，并保持小规模。PayPal 大约有三十名工程师，用于一个我认为比美联储清算系统更复杂的系统。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,134:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,137:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Both Zip2 and PayPal operated like Silicon Valley startups. Pretty flat hierarchy,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,138:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: everybody had a similar desk, and anyone could talk to anyone.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,138:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,138:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Zip2 和 PayPal 都像硅谷初创公司一样运营。相当扁平的层级，每个人都有类似的办公桌，任何人都可以和任何人交谈。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,139:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,139:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  We had a philosophy of 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,140:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,140:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: best idea wins
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,140:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,147:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  as opposed to the person proposing the idea
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,150:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: winning because of who they are. Even though there were times when I thought that should have
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,151:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: been the way to go. Everyone was an equity stakeholder.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,151:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,152:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我们的理念是
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,152:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,152:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 最好的想法获胜
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,153:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,153:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ，而不是提出想法的人因为他们的身份而获胜。尽管有时我认为那应该是前进的方式。每个人都是股权利益相关者。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,154:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,154:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  If there were two options, and one wasn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,155:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,164:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t obviously better than the other, rather than spend
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,168:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: time trying to pick which one was slightly better, we would just pick one and go. Sometimes we
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,169:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: were wrong and picked the suboptimal path, but at least we moved fast.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,169:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,170:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  如果有两个选项，一个并不明显优于另一个，与其花时间试图选择哪个稍微好一点，我们只会选择一个然后继续。有时我们错了，选择了次优路径，但至少我们移动得快。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,170:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,171:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Better to pick a path and keep moving than just vacillate endlessly on a decision.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,171:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,172:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  最好选择一条路并继续前进，而不是在一个决定上无休止地摇摆不定。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,172:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,174:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  We were focused on building the best product we possibly could. Both Zip2 and PayPal
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,175:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: were product-focused companies. We didn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,175:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,184:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t worry too much about intellectual property paperwork.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,189:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: We were incredibly obsessive about building the best possible customer experience. That was a far
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,189:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: more effective selling tool than having a giant sales force or marketing gimmicks.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,190:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,191:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我们专注于建造我们能建造的最好的产品。Zip2 和 PayPal 都是以产品为中心的公司。我们不太担心知识产权文书工作。我们非常痴迷于建造最好的客户体验。那是一个比拥有庞大的销售团队或营销噱头更有效的销售工具。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,191:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,192:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Pay close attention to negative feedback, and solicit it, particularly from friends. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,192:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,194:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,195:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: incredibly helpful. This may sound like simple advice, but hardly anyone does it.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,195:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,196:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  密切关注负面反馈，并征求它，特别是来自朋友的。这非常有帮助。这听起来像是简单的建议，但几乎没有人这样做。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,196:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Unite and Conquer
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,197:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 团结并征服
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,197:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,198:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  What matters to me is winning, and not in a small way.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,199:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,199:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  对我来说重要的是获胜，而且不是小胜。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,200:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,216:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Around the same time I was starting X, another company formed called Confinity, which
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,224:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: was Peter Thiel, Max Levchin, Luke Nosek, David Sacks, Ken Howery, etc. At X.com, we had
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,226:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Jeremy Stoppelman, who created Yelp, and Roelof Botha, who went on to run Sequoia. Both
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,227:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: companies had a crazy amount of talent.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,227:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,228:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  大约在我创办 X 的同时，另一家公司成立了，名为 Confinity，成员是彼得·蒂尔、马克斯·列夫琴、卢克·诺塞克、大卫·萨克斯、肯·豪厄里等。在 X.com，我们有创建 Yelp 的杰里米·斯托普尔曼，以及后来经营红杉资本的罗洛夫·博塔。两家公司都有疯狂的才华。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,229:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,249:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Confinity started as a PalmPilot cryptography company, back when you could
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,261:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: communicate through the infrared port of a PalmPilot. Then they evolved in the direction of
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,265:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: payments as well. We were both in Palo Alto, a block away from each other—at one point, even in the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,266:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: same building. We were competing with each other like maniacs.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,266:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,267:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Confinity 最初是一家 PalmPilot 加密公司，那时你可以通过 PalmPilot 的红外端口进行通信。然后他们也向支付方向发展。我们都在帕洛阿尔托，相隔一个街区——在某个时候，甚至在同一栋楼里。我们像疯子一样互相竞争。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,267:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,268:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Finally, we had coffee on University Avenue and said, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,268:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,269:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Hey, why don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,269:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,270:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t we just combine
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,270:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: our efforts? Otherwise we
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,271:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,271:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re gonna bludgeon each other to death.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,271:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,273:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  We knew we had to get that deal
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,274:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: done fast or we were both gonna die.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,274:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,274:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  最后，我们在大学大道喝咖啡，说，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,275:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,275:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 嘿，我们为什么不联合我们的努力？否则我们会互相打死。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,275:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,276:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 我们知道我们必须快速完成那笔交易，否则我们都会死。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,276:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,281:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  So we merged Confinity with X.com and raised $100 million in three weeks during March
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,282:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: of 2000. About a year later, we changed the company name to the product name, PayPal.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,282:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,283:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  所以我们将 Confinity 与 X.com 合并，并在 2000 年 3 月的三周内筹集了 1 亿美元。大约一年后，我们将公司名称改为产品名称 PayPal。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,283:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,288:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  We went from starting a company to fourteen months later merging and having a valuation
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,289:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: of $500 million in March of 2000. It felt so sudden, like, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,289:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,289:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: This is completely ridiculous.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,290:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,290:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,291:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我们从创办公司到十四个月后合并，在 2000 年 3 月估值达到 5 亿美元。感觉如此突然，就像，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,291:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,292:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 这完全荒谬。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,292:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,292:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,295:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  In April 2000, the market went into freefall. The challenge was keeping the company alive
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,295:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: for the next two years.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,296:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,296:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  2000 年 4 月，市场陷入自由落体。挑战是让公司在接下来的两年里保持生存。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,297:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,298:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  There was a lot of drama; it was a turbulent period. I didn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,298:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,298:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t expect PayPal
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,299:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,307:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s growth rate to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,313:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: be what it was, and that created major problems. After the first month of the website being active,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,314:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: we had one hundred thousand customers. It was nutty. We definitely did not anticipate that.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,314:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,315:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  有很多戏剧性；那是一个动荡时期。我没有预料到 PayPal 的增长率会是这样，这造成了重大问题。在网站活跃的第一个月后，我们有十万客户。这很疯狂。我们绝对没有预料到。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,316:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,316:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Q: What made PayPal
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,317:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,317:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s growth rate so dramatic?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,318:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,318:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  问：是什么让 PayPal 的增长率如此惊人？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,319:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,343:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  PayPal was a perfect case for viral marketing. Like Hotmail, one customer would be like a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,356:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: salesperson for you, bringing other customers. Customers would send money to a friend and bring
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,361:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: that friend into the network. We had this exponential growth, where the more customers we had, the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,362:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: faster it grew. It was like bacteria in a petri dish, following an S-curve.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,362:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,363:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  PayPal 是病毒式营销的完美案例。像 Hotmail 一样，一个客户就像你的销售人员，带来其他客户。客户会向朋友汇款，并把那个朋友带入网络。我们有这种指数增长，客户越多，增长越快。这就像培养皿中的细菌，遵循 S 曲线。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,364:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,382:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  We started off first by offering people twenty dollars if they opened an account and twenty
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,391:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: dollars if they referred anyone. Then we dropped it to ten dollars. Then we dropped it to five dollars.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,392:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: As the network got bigger and bigger, the value of the network itself exceeded any sort of carrot that
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,393:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: we could offer.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,393:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,394:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我们开始时提供二十美元，如果他们开设账户，再提供二十美元，如果他们推荐任何人。然后我们降到十美元。然后我们降到五美元。随着网络越来越大，网络本身的价值超过了我们能提供的任何胡萝卜。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,394:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,400:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  We probably spent $60 or $70 million in incentives to build that network. That seems like
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,401:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: a lot, but it built a very valuable network. The relative cost depends on your scale. That
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,401:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,402:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s a peanut to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,402:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Google.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,402:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,403:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我们可能花费了 6000 万或 7000 万美元的激励来建立那个网络。这似乎很多，但它建立了一个非常有价值的网络。相对成本取决于你的规模。这对谷歌来说是小菜一碟。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,404:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,405:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Q: Leading through that kind of growth seems very challenging. How did you manage it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,405:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: all?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,406:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,406:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  问：领导这种增长似乎非常有挑战性。你是如何管理这一切的？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,407:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,415:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I ran PayPal for about the first two years of its existence. We launched after year one, and
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,416:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: by the end of year two we had a million customers. It gives you a sense for how fast things can
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,417:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: grow. We didn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,417:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,418:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t have a sales force, VP of sales, or VP of marketing and we didn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,418:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,419:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t spend any money
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,419:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: on advertising.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,420:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,420:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我经营 PayPal 大约前两年。我们在第一年后推出，到第二年底我们有一百万客户。这让你感受到事情可以增长多快。我们没有销售团队、销售副总裁或营销副总裁，我们也没有花任何钱做广告。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,421:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,421:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  It wasn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,421:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,423:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t easy, because we still had some bugs in the software. Even if the bug only occurs
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,424:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: one in one thousand times, that
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,424:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,424:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s still a thousand angry customers shouting, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,425:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,425:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Where is my money
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,425:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: !
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,426:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,426:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,426:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,427:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  这不容易，因为我们的软件仍然有一些漏洞。即使漏洞只发生千分之一，那仍然是一千个愤怒的客户大喊，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,427:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,427:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 我的钱在哪里！？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,428:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,428:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,453:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  We had a customer service office on University Avenue in Palo Alto with five people.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,468:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: When something went wrong, customer service phones would explode. We had many challenges.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,475:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Various financial regulatory agencies were trying to shut us down. The FTC was trying to shut us
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,476:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: down. Visa, MasterCard, and eBay were all trying to have us shut down. There were a lot of battles.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,476:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,477:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我们在帕洛阿尔托大学大道有一个客户服务办公室，有五个人。当出现问题时，客服电话会爆炸。我们有很多挑战。各种金融监管机构试图关闭我们。联邦贸易委员会试图关闭我们。Visa、万事达卡和 eBay 都试图让我们关闭。有很多战斗。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,477:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,478:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  It was a close call. We came close to dying in 2000 and 2001.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,478:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,479:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  那是千钧一发。我们在 2000 年和 2001 年差点死掉。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,479:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: From Exile to Exit
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,480:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 从流放至退出
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,480:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,481:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I was away for two weeks and the management team decided I wasn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,481:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,484:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t the right guy to run
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,485:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the company. Instead of fighting during a critical time, I thought it was best to concede.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,485:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,486:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我离开了两周，管理团队认为我不是经营公司的合适人选。我认为在关键时刻战斗不如让步。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,486:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,486:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,487:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,510:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s not a good idea to leave the office when there are a lot of major things underway that
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,523:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: are causing people a great deal of stress. I left for a trip, a combination of needing to raise money
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,526:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: and I had gotten married earlier that year and had not had a vacation or honeymoon. It was kind of a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,527:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: combined financing trip and honeymoon. Also not a great idea.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,528:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,528:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  当有很多重大事情正在进行，给人们带来很大压力时，离开办公室不是个好主意。我去旅行了，一方面需要筹集资金，另一方面我那年早些时候结婚了，还没有度假或蜜月。这有点像融资旅行和蜜月结合。也不是个好主意。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,529:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,546:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I got removed as CEO of PayPal because I wanted to do a bunch of things that seemed
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,554:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: extremely risky. I think they would have worked out, but at a time when companies were dropping
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,555:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: like flies, I was proposing we do all these things that sound risky—it was much too scary for the rest of
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,556:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the team.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,556:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,557:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我被解除 PayPal CEO 的职务，因为我想做一些看起来非常冒险的事情。我认为它们会成功，但在公司像苍蝇一样倒闭的时候，我提议我们做所有这些听起来冒险的事情——这对其他团队成员来说太可怕了。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,557:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,558:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I didn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,558:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,568:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t agree with their conclusion, but I understood why they took the action they did.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,572:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Peter, Max, David, and the other guys are smart people with the right motivations. They did what
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,573:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: they thought was right, for the right reasons. The reasons weren
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,573:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,574:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t valid in my opinion but it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,574:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,575:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s hard to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,576:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: argue with the ultimate outcome, which was positive.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,576:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,577:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我不同意他们的结论，但我理解他们为什么采取那样的行动。彼得、马克斯、大卫和其他人是聪明人，动机正确。他们出于正确的原因做了他们认为正确的事情。我认为这些理由不成立，但很难反驳最终的结果，那是积极的。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,577:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,586:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  It would be easy to be bitter and hate them forever, but the better course of action is to turn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,588:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the other cheek. I put a lot of effort into making things good between us, and they became good. I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,589:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: invested in some of Peter
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,589:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,593:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s companies, including Founders Fund, which is made up primarily of
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,594:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: former PayPal people. Peter, who replaced me as CEO, later invested in SpaceX.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,594:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,595:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  很容易心怀怨恨并永远恨他们，但更好的做法是宽容。我花了很多努力让我们之间的关系变好，它们确实变好了。我投资了彼得的一些公司，包括创始人基金，主要由前 PayPal 人员组成。彼得，他接替我当 CEO，后来投资了 SpaceX。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,595:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,596:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Life is too short for long-term grudges.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,596:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,597:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  生命太短，不适合长期怀恨。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,597:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,598:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Q: What was the exit like?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,599:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,599:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  问：退出是什么感觉？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,599:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,617:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  In about February of 2002, PayPal went public. I think we were the only internet company
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,626:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: to go public in the first part of 2002. It went reasonably well, although I can imagine we set a record
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,627:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: on SEC rewrites. This was right around the time of Enron and other corporate scandals, so they put
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,628:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: us through the wringer.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,628:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,629:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  大约在 2002 年 2 月，PayPal 上市了。我想我们是 2002 年上半年唯一上市的互联网公司。进展相当顺利，虽然我可以想象我们在 SEC 重写方面创下了纪录。这正好是安然和其他公司丑闻的时候，所以他们把我们折腾了一番。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,629:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,629:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  It was a tough, long-running battle between PayPal and eBay
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,630:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,663:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s payment system, and it was
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,690:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: certainly challenging. There were times it felt like trying to win a land war in Asia. They got to set
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,703:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the ground rules. It was like trying to beat Microsoft inside their own operating system. It took a lot
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,707:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: of effort to beat eBay in their own system. One of the long-term risks for PayPal was eBay would
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,708:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: one day prevail. One way to retire that risk was to sell to eBay.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,708:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,709:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  PayPal 和 eBay 的支付系统之间是一场艰难、持久的战斗，确实很有挑战性。有时感觉就像试图在亚洲打赢一场陆地战争。他们可以制定基本规则。这就像试图在他们自己的操作系统内击败微软。在他们自己的系统内击败 eBay 需要很多努力。PayPal 的长期风险之一是 eBay 有一天会获胜。消除该风险的一种方法是卖给 eBay。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,709:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,710:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  In October 2002, we struck a deal to sell PayPal to eBay for about $4.5 billion.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,710:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,711:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  2002 年 10 月，我们达成了一项协议，以约 45 亿美元将 PayPal 出售给 eBay。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,711:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,720:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I could go and buy one of the islands of the Bahamas and turn it into my personal fiefdom,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,721:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: but I am much more interested in trying to build and create a new company. I haven
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,721:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,722:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t spent my
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,722:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: winnings. I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,722:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,723:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: m going to put almost all of it back into a new game.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,723:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,724:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我可以去买巴哈马的一个岛屿，把它变成我的个人领地，但我更有兴趣尝试建立和创造一家新公司。我没有花掉我的赢利。我要把几乎所有钱都投入一个新游戏。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,724:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: BUILDING TESLA
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,725:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 建造特斯拉
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,725:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,733:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Accelerating the removal of hydrocarbons from the crust and placing them in the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,736:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: atmosphere is unwise. This is one of the biggest problems of the twenty-first century. Hopefully this
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,737:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: transition to sustainable energy occurs before it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,737:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,737:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s too late.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,738:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,738:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  加速从地壳中移除碳氢化合物并将它们放入大气中是不明智的。这是二十一世纪最大的问题之一。希望向可持续能源的过渡在太晚之前发生。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,739:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The Mission to Protect the Planet
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,739:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 保护地球的使命
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,740:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,740:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  There
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,741:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,741:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s no way we can conserve our way to a good future. We have to make energy
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,742:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: sustainable.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,742:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,743:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我们无法通过节约走向美好的未来。我们必须让能源可持续。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,743:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,744:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Q: Why is the mission of Tesla so important to you?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,744:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,745:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  问：为什么特斯拉的使命对你如此重要？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,745:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,751:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The overarching purpose of Tesla is to help expedite the move from a mine-and-burn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,753:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: hydrocarbon economy toward a solar-electric economy, which I believe to be the primary, but not
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,754:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: exclusive, sustainable solution.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,754:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,755:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  特斯拉的总体目标是帮助加快从开采和燃烧碳氢化合物经济向太阳能经济的转变，我认为这是主要的但不是唯一的可持续解决方案。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,755:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,758:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Energy output is the foundation of the economy, just like sunlight is the foundation of the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,758:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ecosystem. To a first approximation, a country
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,759:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,760:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s goods and services production will be proportionate
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,760:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: to its energy output.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,761:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,761:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  能源产出是经济的基础，就像阳光是生态系统的基础一样。粗略地说，一个国家的商品和服务生产将与其能源产出成正比。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,762:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,780:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  By definition, we must at some point achieve a sustainable energy economy or we will run
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,790:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: out of fossil fuels to burn and civilization will collapse. Given that we must get off fossil fuels
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,793:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: anyway, and that virtually all scientists agree dramatically increasing atmospheric and oceanic
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,794:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: carbon levels is insane…the faster we achieve sustainability, the better.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,794:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,795:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  根据定义，我们必须在某个时候实现可持续能源经济，否则我们将耗尽可燃烧的化石燃料，文明将崩溃。鉴于我们无论如何都必须摆脱化石燃料，而且几乎所有科学家都同意大幅增加大气和海洋碳水平是疯狂的……我们实现可持续性的速度越快越好。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,795:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,795:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,796:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,796:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t have any fundamental dislike of hydrocarbons. I simply look at the future and say, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,797:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,797:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: What is the thing that will actually work?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,798:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,798:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Using a nonrenewable resource obviously will not work.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,798:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,799:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我对碳氢化合物没有任何根本性的厌恶。我只是展望未来并说，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,799:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,800:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 什么才是真正有效的东西？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,800:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,800:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 使用不可再生资源显然行不通。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,801:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,803:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  There are time extensions on the game, but the game is going to end eventually. That
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,804:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: should be obvious. If we rely on nonrenewables, it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,804:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,805:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s like we
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,805:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,809:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re stuck in a room where the oxygen is
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,810:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: gradually depleting. We want to get out of that room. The sooner we get out of that room, the better.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,810:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,811:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  游戏有时间延长，但游戏最终会结束。那应该是显而易见的。如果我们依赖不可再生能源，就像我们被困在一个氧气逐渐耗尽的房间里。我们想离开那个房间。我们越早离开那个房间越好。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,811:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,812:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Q: How do you respond to people who don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,812:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,813:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t see the problem with extraction?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,813:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,813:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  问：你如何回应那些看不到开采问题的人？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,814:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,827:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  It is dangerous to be extracting vast quantities of hydrocarbons from deep within the earth
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,832:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: and putting them in the atmosphere. Sooner or later, something bad will happen. There are a lot of
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,833:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: people, particularly in the US, who are vehemently against electric cars and sustainable energy. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,833:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,834:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,835:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: quite difficult to reason with them.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,835:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,836:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  从地球深处开采大量碳氢化合物并将它们放入大气中是危险的。迟早会发生一些不好的事情。有很多人，特别是在美国，强烈反对电动汽车和可持续能源。很难与他们讲道理。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,836:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,836:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  They
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,837:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,837:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ll say, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,838:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,838:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Well, some scientists don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,838:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,839:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t think climate change is a problem.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,839:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,840:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,840:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  他们会说，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,840:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,841:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 嗯，一些科学家不认为气候变化是个问题。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,841:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,842:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,842:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  You can find some small number of people that will disagree with anything.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,843:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,843:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  你可以找到少数人会不同意任何事情。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,844:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,844:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  This reminds me of the tobacco industry. For the longest time you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,845:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,846:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: d see ads where they
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,846:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: claimed tobacco was healthy for you. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,847:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,847:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s hard to believe these days, but it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,848:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,848:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s true.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,849:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,849:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  这让我想起烟草行业。很长一段时间你会看到广告声称烟草对你健康。现在很难相信，但这是真的。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,850:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,852:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  There were reports where there seemed to be a correlation between lung cancer and
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,853:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: smoking, but tobacco companies would say, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,853:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,854:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Our scientists have conducted experiments and they
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,855:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: show no relation at all
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,855:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: !
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,856:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,856:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,857:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,857:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s complete nonsense.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,858:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,858:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  有报告显示肺癌和吸烟之间似乎存在相关性，但烟草公司会说，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,858:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,859:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 我们的科学家进行了实验，他们显示完全没有关系！
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,859:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,860:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 这完全是胡说八道。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,860:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,861:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Almost any reasonable scientist would say, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,861:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,864:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Yes, of course smoking causes lung cancer
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,864:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: and all sorts of other bad things. Not definitively but it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,865:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,865:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s extremely likely.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,866:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,867:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Yet the tobacco industry
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,867:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: would still say, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,868:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,868:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Scientists disagree
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,869:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: !
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,869:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,870:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  because 1 or 2 percent of the scientific community didn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,870:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,871:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t feel
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,871:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: that way.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,872:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,872:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  几乎任何合理的科学家都会说，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,873:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,873:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 是的，当然吸烟会导致肺癌和各种其他坏事。不是绝对但极有可能。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,874:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,874:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 然而烟草行业仍然会说，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,875:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,875:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 科学家有分歧！
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,876:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,876:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 因为 1% 或 2% 的科学界不那样认为。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,877:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,877:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The public just hears 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,878:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,878:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Scientists disagree
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,879:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: !
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,879:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,880:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  rather than 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,880:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,882:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 99 percent of scientists think the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,882:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: other 1 percent are stupid.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,883:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,883:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,884:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  公众只听到
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,884:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,885:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 科学家有分歧！
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,885:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,886:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 而不是
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,886:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,887:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 99% 的科学家认为另外 1% 是愚蠢的。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,887:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,888:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,888:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The question isn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,889:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,889:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,890:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,891:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Can you prove we
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,891:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,892:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re making the planet warmer?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,892:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,893:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  but, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,893:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,894:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Can you prove
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,894:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: we
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,895:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,895:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re not?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,896:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,896:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  And you can
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,897:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,898:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,898:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,899:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  问题不是，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,899:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,899:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 你能证明我们正在让地球变暖吗？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,900:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,900:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 而是，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,900:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,901:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 你能证明我们没有吗？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,901:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,901:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 你不能。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,901:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,902:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  It makes me mad when smart, ethical scientists are accused of publishing climate papers
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,903:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: for 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,903:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,903:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: grant money.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,904:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,910:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  They earn peanuts compared to their other opportunities and give that up to help
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,911:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the world. But their accusers earn billions by slowing down the growth of clean energy. Who is
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,911:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: more credible?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,912:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,912:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  当聪明、有道德的科学家被指控为了
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,912:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,913:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 资助资金
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,913:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,913:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 发表气候论文时，我很生气。与其他机会相比，他们赚的是 peanuts，放弃那些来帮助世界。但他们的指控者通过减缓清洁能源的增长赚取数十亿。谁更可信？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,914:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,914:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  People often believe things inversely proportional to the evidence. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,915:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,916:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s so strange. Given a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,917:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: set of possible explanations, why pick the one that
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,917:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,917:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s least likely?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,918:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,918:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  人们经常相信与证据成反比的事情。这很奇怪。给定一组可能的解释，为什么选择最不可能的？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,918:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,919:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Q: So it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,919:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,920:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s not too late to turn things around?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,920:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,920:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  问：所以扭转局面还为时不晚吗？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,921:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,945:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Humanity will solve sustainable energy if we continue to push hard. The future is bright
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,957:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: for cheap, abundant energy. It will be possible to use that energy to pull carbon out of the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,962:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: atmosphere. It takes a lot of energy to do that carbon capture, because putting it into the atmosphere
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,963:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: releases energy. To pull it out, you need to use a lot of energy.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,963:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,964:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  如果我们继续努力，人类将解决可持续能源问题。廉价、丰富能源的未来是光明的。将有可能利用那种能量从大气中吸收碳。进行碳捕获需要大量能量，因为将其放入大气中会释放能量。要将其拉出，你需要使用大量能量。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,964:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,965:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  But if we
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,965:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,970:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ve got a lot of sustainable energy from wind and solar, we can sequester carbon.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,971:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: We can reverse the CO2 parts per million of the atmosphere and oceans and restore the climate.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,971:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,972:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  但如果我们有大量来自风能和太阳能的可持续能源，我们可以隔离碳。我们可以逆转大气和海洋中的二氧化碳百万分比，并恢复气候。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,972:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,973:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I donated $100 million to a prize for the best carbon capture technology.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,973:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,974:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我捐赠了 1 亿美元作为最佳碳捕获技术的奖金。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,974:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,975:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  We can create as much fresh water as we want. Earth is mostly water. We should call Earth
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,976:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,976:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,976:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Water.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,977:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,977:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,977:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,978:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s 70 percent water by surface area. We just happen to be on the small bit that
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,979:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,981:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s land. With
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,981:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: energy, we can turn ocean water into fresh water or irrigation water at low cost.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,982:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,982:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我们可以创造任意多的淡水。地球大部分是水。我们应该称地球为
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,983:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,983:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 水球
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,984:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,984:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 。按表面积计算，它 70% 是水。我们只是碰巧在那一小块陆地上。有了能源，我们可以低成本地将海水变成淡水或灌溉水。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,985:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,985:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  When you burn fossil fuels, there
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:56,986:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,001:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s all these side reactions and toxic gasses of various
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,009:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: kinds. A lot of little particulates that are bad for your lungs. All sorts of bad things are happening,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,011:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: which will go away with sustainable energy. The sky will be cleaner and quieter. The future is going
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,012:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: to be good.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,012:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,013:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  当你燃烧化石燃料时，会有所有这些副反应和各种有毒气体。很多对肺部有害的小颗粒。各种坏事正在发生，随着可持续能源它们将消失。天空将更清洁、更安静。未来将是美好的。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,013:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,017:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The purpose of Tesla was, and remains, accelerating the use of sustainable energy, so we
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,018:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: can imagine far into the future and life is still good. That
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,018:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,019:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s what 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,019:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,020:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: sustainable
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,020:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,020:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  means. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,021:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,022:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s not some
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,022:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: silly hippie thing—it matters for everyone.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,023:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,023:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  特斯拉的目的过去是，现在仍然是，加速可持续能源的使用，这样我们可以想象遥远的未来，生活仍然美好。这就是
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,024:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,024:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 可持续
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,025:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,025:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 的意思。这不是什么愚蠢的嬉皮士东西——它对每个人都很重要。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,026:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Going All In, Again (PayPal Earnings into Tesla)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,027:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 再次全力以赴（PayPal 收益投入特斯拉）
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,027:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,028:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  When you have a big technology change, it tends to come from new companies.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,029:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,029:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  当你有重大技术变革时，它往往来自新公司。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,030:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,032:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  A lot of entrepreneurial talent and financing goes to the internet. Other sectors like
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,032:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: automotive, solar, and space don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,033:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,035:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t see new entrants. Not a lot of entrepreneurs go into those areas,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,036:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: and not a lot of capital goes into those startups.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,037:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,037:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  很多创业人才和资金流向互联网。其他行业如汽车、太阳能和太空没有新进入者。没有很多创业者进入这些领域，也没有很多资金流入那些初创公司。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,038:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,039:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  This is a problem because innovation tends to come from new entrants to an industry. This
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,039:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: is Schumpeter
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,039:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,040:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s idea of creative destruction. In an oligopoly, no one is forced to innovate.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,040:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,041:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  这是个问题，因为创新往往来自行业的新进入者。这是熊彼特的创造性破坏理念。在寡头垄断中，没有人被迫创新。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,041:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,043:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  New entrants drive innovation more than anything, which is why I have devoted my efforts
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,044:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: to building new companies in those industries.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,044:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,045:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  新进入者比任何其他东西都更能推动创新，这就是为什么我致力于在这些行业建立新公司。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,045:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,053:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  These industries require quite a bit of capital to get going. My proceeds from PayPal after
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,055:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: tax were about $180 million. I thought I would allocate half to SpaceX, Tesla, and SolarCity. I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,056:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: thought that should be fine. I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,056:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,057:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: d have $90 million left, and that
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,057:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,057:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s…a lot, you know?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,058:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,058:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  这些行业需要相当多的资金才能启动。我从 PayPal 获得的税后收益大约是 1.8 亿美元。我想我会将一半分配给 SpaceX、特斯拉和 SolarCity。我想那应该没问题。我还剩下 9000 万美元，那是……很多，你知道吗？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,059:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,067:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  But things cost more and took longer than I thought. Each one ended up costing double
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,070:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: what I expected. I thought SpaceX would need $50 million. Tesla, I thought, would need $25
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,071:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: million, maybe $30 million. SolarCity…actually went really well.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,071:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,072:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  但事情花费的比我想象的更多，耗时也更长。每个最终花费都是我预期的两倍。我以为 SpaceX 需要 5000 万美元。特斯拉，我认为，需要 2500 万美元，也许 3000 万美元。SolarCity……实际上进展非常顺利。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,072:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,077:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I ended up putting $10 million into Solar City, $70 million into Tesla, and $100 million
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,078:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: into SpaceX. I literally had to borrow money for rent. It was a close call.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,078:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,079:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我最终向 Solar City 投入了 1000 万美元，向特斯拉投入了 7000 万美元，向 SpaceX 投入了 1 亿美元。我真的不得不借钱付房租。那是千钧一发。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,079:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Building the First Prototype
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,080:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 建造第一个原型
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,080:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,086:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I first realized all vehicles would be electric in the early nineties, way before Tesla started.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,087:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: I was studying physics in my sophomore year in college; it was obvious to me even then.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,087:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,088:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我首先在九十年代初意识到所有车辆都将是电动的，远在特斯拉开始之前。我大二时正在学习物理学；那时对我来说就很明显了。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,088:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,121:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Getting the timing right was important. Lithium-ion batteries were the critical
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,140:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: breakthrough needed for compelling electric cars. I knew it became possible to start Tesla because
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,150:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: we went from the energy density of lead acid batteries to lithium-ion batteries—about a 4x energy
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,153:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: density improvement. If you had a sixty-mile range with a lead-acid battery, you would have about
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,154:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: one-hundred-forty-mile range with lithium-ion for the same weight.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,154:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,155:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  把握正确的时机很重要。锂离子电池是引人注目的电动汽车所需的关键突破。我知道开始特斯拉变得可能，因为我们从铅酸电池的能量密度转向锂离子电池——大约 4 倍的能量密度改进。如果你用铅酸电池有 60 英里的续航里程，用锂离子电池相同重量下你将有大约 140 英里的续航里程。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,155:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,171:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  A company called AC Propulsion had built a prototype, which had similar specs to what
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,178:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: we eventually brought to market as the first Tesla Roadster. It was cool to see it in action, working. I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,179:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: tried hard to convince those guys to commercialize their car but they just did not want to do it.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,179:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,180:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  一家名为 AC Propulsion 的公司已经建造了一个原型，其规格与我们最终作为第一辆特斯拉 Roadster 推向市场的规格相似。看到它实际运行很酷。我努力说服那些家伙将他们的汽车商业化，但他们就是不想这样做。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,181:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,181:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The car they wanted to make was like an electric Scion. I told them, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,182:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,182:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: You guys, nobody
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,183:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,186:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,187:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: gonna pay $70,000 for an electric Scion. This is not gonna work. You will sell like fourteen of these
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,187:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: things.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,188:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,188:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,189:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  他们想制造的汽车就像电动 Scion。我告诉他们，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,189:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,190:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 伙计们，没有人会花 7 万美元买一辆电动 Scion。这行不通。你们只会卖出大约十四辆这种东西。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,190:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,190:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,191:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Though I also said, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,191:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,194:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Even though I think this is the dumbest idea ever, I will fund one tenth
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,195:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: of it if you can find nine other people.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,195:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,195:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,196:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  虽然我也说，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,196:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,197:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 即使我认为这是有史以来最愚蠢的想法，如果你能找到其他九个人，我将资助其中的十分之一。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,197:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,198:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,199:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I thought it would fail, but at least it was something. They didn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,199:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,200:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t actually get it off the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,201:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ground. Eventually I said, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,201:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,201:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: If you guys are not going to commercialize this, do you mind if I do?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,202:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,202:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,202:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我以为它会失败，但至少它是某种东西。他们实际上没有让它起步。最终我说，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,203:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,203:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 如果你们不打算将这个商业化，你们介意我来做吗？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,203:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,204:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,204:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  We made so many mistakes in the beginning of Tesla. Almost every decision we made was
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,205:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: wrong.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,205:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,206:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我们在特斯拉初期犯了太多错误。我们做的几乎每个决定都是错的。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,206:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,207:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The founding principles of Tesla were basically completely wrong. The premise was, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,207:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,207:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,208:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,208:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,208:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: not gonna be that hard
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,209:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: !
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,209:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  We
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,209:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,210:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ll take the Lotus Elise, a nice lightweight car, and we
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,210:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,211:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ll take AC
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,211:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Propulsion
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,211:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,212:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s drive unit technology, put 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,212:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,213:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: er together, and we
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,213:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,213:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ll have an electric car
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,214:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: !
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,214:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,214:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,215:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ll be great
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,215:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: !
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,215:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,216:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,216:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  特斯拉的创始原则基本上完全错误。前提是，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,216:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,217:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 不会那么难！我们将采用莲花 Elise，一款不错的轻型汽车，我们将采用 AC Propulsion 的驱动单元技术，把它们组装在一起，我们就有一辆电动汽车！那会很棒！
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,217:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,218:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,229:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Except the AC Propulsion technology could not be industrialized. It was handcrafted
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,234:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: electronics. In hot or cold weather, it would respond differently or not at all. It was impossible to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,234:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: scale this technology. You could only have finicky, individually made, superexpensive prototypes.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,235:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,235:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  除了 AC Propulsion 技术无法工业化。它是手工制作的电子产品。在炎热或寒冷的天气下，它的反应会不同或根本没有反应。不可能规模化这项技术。你只能拥有挑剔的、单独制造的、超级昂贵的原型。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,236:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,237:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I remember in the early days giving a test ride to Larry Page and Sergey Brin, whom I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,237:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,242:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ve
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,246:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: known for a long time. There was some bug in the system and, damn it, the car would only go ten
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,247:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: miles an hour. I was in the passenger seat saying, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,247:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,248:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Guys, I swear, it goes a lot faster than this.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,248:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,248:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,249:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我记得在早期给拉里·佩奇和谢尔盖·布林试驾，我认识他们很久了。系统中有一些漏洞，该死的，车只能以每小时 10 英里的速度行驶。我坐在副驾驶座上说，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,249:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,250:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 伙计们，我发誓，它的速度比这快得多。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,250:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,251:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,251:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  They were kind enough to put a little investment into the company, despite the world
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,252:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,252:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,253:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: worst demo.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,253:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,253:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  他们很好心地向公司投入了一点投资，尽管有世界上最糟糕的演示。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,254:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,261:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  It was just a flat-out burning dumpster fire of stupidity. One example: The chassis had to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,262:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: be redesigned to fit the battery pack and became 40 percent heavier. This invalidated the crash
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,263:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: testing Lotus had done.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,263:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,264:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  这完全是一场愚蠢的燃烧垃圾场大火。一个例子：底盘必须重新设计以适应电池组，变得重了 40%。这使莲花所做的碰撞测试无效。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,264:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,286:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  We ended up using none of the AC Propulsion technology. Something that looks cool and
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,299:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: works as an individual prototype does not necessarily scale. Eventually maybe 7 percent of the parts
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,303:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: of the original Tesla Roadster were common with the Lotus Elise. It would have been much smarter
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,304:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: to start with a clean-sheet design and not try to modify something else.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,304:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,305:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我们最终没有使用任何 AC Propulsion 技术。看起来酷且作为单独原型有效的东西不一定能规模化。最终，也许原始特斯拉 Roadster 的 7% 的部件与莲花 Elise 通用。从空白设计开始而不是试图修改其他东西会明智得多。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,306:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,311:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I was going to start an electric vehicle (EV) company with JB Straubel based on the AC
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,312:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Propulsion prototype. When I asked AC Propulsion if it was okay to do that, they said, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,313:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,315:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: There are
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,316:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: some other people who want to create an EV company; would you like to join forces with them?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,317:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,317:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,318:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: said, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,318:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,319:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: OK.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,319:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,324:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  That was a huge mistake. JB and I should have just started the company ourselves. My
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,325:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: default inclination is to start things from scratch, even more so after this experience.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,325:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,326:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我本打算与 JB·斯特劳贝尔基于 AC Propulsion 原型创办一家电动汽车公司。当我问 AC Propulsion 是否可以这样做时，他们说，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,326:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,327:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 还有一些人想创办一家电动汽车公司；你想和他们合作吗？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,327:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,328:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 我说，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,328:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,329:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 好的。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,329:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,330:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 那是一个巨大的错误。JB 和我应该自己创办公司。我的默认倾向是从头开始做事，在这次经历之后更是如此。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,330:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,334:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The most important thing is to start somewhere, be prepared to question your assumptions,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,334:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: fix what you did wrong, and adapt to reality.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,335:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,335:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  最重要的是从某个地方开始，准备好质疑你的假设，修正你做错的事情，并适应现实。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,336:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Becoming Tesla
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,337:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,337:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s CEO
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,338:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 成为特斯拉 CEO
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,338:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,356:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The actual error was me trying to have my cake and eat it too: I just wanted to work on the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,364:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: technology and the product. I thought someone else could be the CEO and run the business, because
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,366:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: I just like working on technology, product, and design. I was also doing SpaceX at the time, and our
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,366:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: rockets were exploding.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,367:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,367:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  实际的错误是我试图鱼与熊掌兼得：我只想专注于技术和产品。我以为其他人可以当 CEO 并经营业务，因为我只喜欢从事技术、产品和设计工作。我当时也在做 SpaceX，我们的火箭正在爆炸。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,367:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,381:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I had always wanted to build an electric car company. I thought this is how I could have
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,386:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: my cake and eat it too. That was a huge mistake and fundamentally a moral error. When I joined,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,387:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: there were no employees. There was no intellectual property. There was no prototype, no nothing.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,387:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,388:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我一直想建立一家电动汽车公司。我想这就是我如何鱼与熊掌兼得的方式。那是一个巨大的错误，根本上是一个道德错误。当我加入时，没有员工。没有知识产权。没有原型，什么都没有。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,388:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,391:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I had provided about 95 percent of the money for Tesla, so I could become CEO anytime I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,392:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: wanted. And in the end, I had to frickin
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,392:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,392:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  become CEO of Tesla. I didn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,393:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,394:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t want to be, but it was either
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,395:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: that or the company was going to die.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,395:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,396:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我提供了特斯拉大约 95% 的资金，所以我可以随时成为 CEO。最终，我他妈的不得不成为特斯拉的 CEO。我不想成为，但那是要么那样要么公司就会死。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,396:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,398:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I never wanted to be a CEO, but I learned you could not truly be the chief technology or
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,399:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: product officer unless you were the CEO.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,399:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,400:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我从不想成为 CEO，但我了解到你不能真正成为首席技术或产品官，除非你是 CEO。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,400:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,401:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Being CEO of two startups at the same time was not appealing. It shouldn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,401:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,403:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t be appealing,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,404:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: by the way, for anyone thinking it was a good idea. It was a terrible idea.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,405:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,405:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  同时担任两家初创公司的 CEO 并不吸引人。顺便说一句，对任何认为这是个好主意的人来说，它不应该有吸引力。那是一个糟糕的主意。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,405:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,406:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  If you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,406:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,407:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re a CEO of a company, the chore level is high, and if you don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,407:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,409:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t do your chores then
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,410:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the company goes to hell. Frankly, I hate doing chores—who doesn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,410:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,410:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t? There
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,411:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,412:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s a whole bunch of
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,412:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: personnel and legal issues: things I don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,413:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,413:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t find enjoyable to work on, but if I don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,414:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,415:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t work on them, the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,416:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: company suffers. The sheer volume of work is insane.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,416:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,417:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  如果你是一家公司的 CEO，杂事水平很高，如果你不做你的杂事，公司就会下地狱。坦率地说，我讨厌做杂事——谁不讨厌？有一大堆人事和法律问题：我不喜欢做的事情，但如果我不做，公司就会受苦。工作量简直是疯狂的。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,417:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,419:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The perception of me as a businessperson is fine, but my time is spent almost entirely with
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,420:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the engineering team. I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,420:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,421:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: m a physics guy, an engineer. I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,421:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,424:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: d prefer to be working on products. I do the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,425:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: business stuff because you have to do the business stuff. If you don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,425:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,427:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t do the business stuff,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,428:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: somebody else could do it for you and then you could be in trouble.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,429:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,429:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  把我看作商人的看法没问题，但我的时间几乎全部花在工程团队上。我是个物理学人，工程师。我更愿意从事产品工作。我做商业事情是因为你必须做商业事情。如果你不做商业事情，别人可以为你做，然后你可能会有麻烦。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,430:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,431:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I have a habit of biting off more than I can chew and just sitting there with chipmunk
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,431:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: cheeks.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,432:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,432:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我有一个习惯，就是贪多嚼不烂，然后坐在那里像花栗鼠一样鼓着腮帮子。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,433:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Sequenced Strategy of Tesla
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,433:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 特斯拉的序列策略
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,434:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,455:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Tesla is focused on making electric cars more affordable, which is tough. You need high
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,466:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: volume to make cars affordable. When we started, other car companies made a lot more cars, so they
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,470:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: got much better economies of scale. As we build more cars in higher volume, we make electric cars
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,471:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: available to a wider range of people at lower cost.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,471:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,472:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  特斯拉专注于让电动汽车更负担得起，这很难。你需要高产量才能让汽车负担得起。当我们开始时，其他汽车公司制造了更多的汽车，所以他们获得了更好的规模经济。当我们以更高的产量制造更多汽车时，我们以更低的成本让更广泛的人可以使用电动汽车。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,472:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,480:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The first version of a product has both a new-technology problem and a low-volume
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,481:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: problem. You want to make your mistakes at a small scale, work the bugs out of the system, then
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,482:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: reach for scale.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,482:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,483:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  产品的第一个版本既有新技术问题又有低产量问题。你想在小规模上犯错误，解决系统中的漏洞，然后达到规模。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,483:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,486:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  With a new product, the first thing engineers try to do is make it work. After you make it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,486:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: work, then you optimize and optimize and optimize.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,486:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,487:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  对于新产品，工程师试图做的第一件事是让它工作。在你让它工作之后，然后你优化、优化、再优化。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,487:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,494:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The master plan was: 1. Build a sports car. 2. Use that money to build an affordable car. 3.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,496:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Use that money to build an even more affordable car. (While doing above, also provide
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,497:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: zero-emission electric power generation options.)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,497:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,498:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  总体规划是：1. 建造一辆跑车。2. 用那笔钱建造一辆负担得起的汽车。3. 用那笔钱建造一辆更负担得起的汽车。（在做上述事情的同时，还提供零排放发电选项。）
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,498:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,502:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  We had to start off with step one, because it was all I could afford with what I made from
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,502:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: PayPal. I thought our chances of success were so low, I didn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,503:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,503:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t want to risk anyone
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,503:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,504:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s funds but my
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,504:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: own in the beginning.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,505:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,505:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我们必须从第一步开始，因为那是我用 PayPal 赚的钱所能负担的全部。我认为我们的成功几率很低，一开始我不想冒险用任何人的资金，除了我自己的。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,506:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,507:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The list of successful car startups is short. The number of American car companies that
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,507:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: haven
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,507:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,510:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t gone bankrupt is a grand total of two: Ford and Tesla. Starting a car company is idiotic, and
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,510:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: an electric car company is idiocy squared.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,511:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,511:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  成功汽车初创公司的名单很短。没有破产的美国汽车公司总数只有两家：福特和特斯拉。创办汽车公司是愚蠢的，电动汽车公司是平方愚蠢。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,511:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,512:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The idea is to drive to mass market as rapidly as possible, at the pace technology matures.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,513:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,513:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  想法是尽可能快地推向大众市场，以技术成熟的速度。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,513:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,516:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  As a little startup building a car, there was no way we could afford a giant plant to make
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,517:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: hundreds of thousands of cars a year. That
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,517:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,519:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s the kind of volume you need to make cheap cars, and
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,520:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: that plant would cost a billion dollars we didn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,520:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,520:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t have.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,521:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,521:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  作为一个建造汽车的小型初创公司，我们不可能负担得起一个每年制造数十万辆汽车的巨大工厂。那是制造便宜汽车所需的产量，那个工厂将花费我们是没有的 10 亿美元。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,522:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,531:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Our first car was a sports car, not because we think the world lacks a sports car, but
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,533:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: because it was the right entry point for the market. If you have a new technology, the right place to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,534:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: enter is high unit-cost, low unit-volume.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,534:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,535:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我们的第一辆车是跑车，不是因为我们认为世界缺少跑车，而是因为那是市场的正确切入点。如果你有新技术，正确的进入地点是高单位成本、低单位产量。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,535:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,559:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  A low-volume car means a much smaller, simpler factory with most things done by hand.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,573:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Without economies of scale, anything we built would be expensive whether it was an economy
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,578:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: sedan or a sports car. Some people would be prepared to pay a high price for a sports car. No one
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,579:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: would pay $100K for an electric Honda Civic, no matter how cool it looked.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,579:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,580:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  低产量汽车意味着一个更小、更简单的工厂，大部分事情都是手工完成的。没有规模经济，我们建造的任何东西都会很昂贵，无论是经济型轿车还是跑车。有些人愿意为跑车支付高价。没有人会为一辆电动本田思域支付 10 万美元，无论它看起来多酷。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,580:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,581:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  When a new cell phone or a new laptop comes out, they tend to be expensive at first,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,582:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: because they
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,582:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,584:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re figuring out the issues and it takes time to optimize. Over time, with scale, that new
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,585:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: technology becomes cheaper and cheaper.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,585:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,586:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  当新手机或新笔记本电脑推出时，它们一开始往往很贵，因为他们正在解决问题，需要时间来优化。随着时间的推移，随着规模，那项新技术变得越来越便宜。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,586:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,604:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  That is the unique and important thing Tesla accomplished. It is not the design of an
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,613:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: electric vehicle, an electric vehicle prototype, or even low-volume production of a car. The hard part
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,616:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: is not creating a prototype or going into limited production. There have been hundreds of car
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,617:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: startups over the years that got that far.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,617:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,618:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  这是特斯拉完成的独特而重要的事情。它不是电动汽车的设计、电动汽车原型，甚至不是汽车的低产量生产。困难的部分不是创建原型或进入有限生产。多年来有数百家汽车初创公司达到了那个程度。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,618:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,633:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The difficult thing—which has not been accomplished by an American car company in one
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,640:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: hundred years—is reaching volume production without going bankrupt. That is the actual hard thing.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,642:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The last American car company to reach volume production without going bankrupt was Chrysler.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,643:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: That was in the 1920s.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,643:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,644:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  困难的事情——一百年来美国汽车公司没有完成的——是在不破产的情况下达到批量生产。那是真正的困难事情。上一家在不破产的情况下达到批量生产的美国汽车公司是克莱斯勒。那是在 1920 年代。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,644:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Keeping Tesla Alive
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,644:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 维持特斯拉生存
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,645:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,647:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Tesla is alive by the skin of its teeth. So is SpaceX. If things had gone a little bit the other
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,647:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: way, both companies would be dead.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,648:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,648:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  特斯拉勉强存活。SpaceX 也是。如果事情稍有不同，两家公司都会死掉。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,649:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,649:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Man, this was grim. I thought this was going to turn into a tale of warning for hubris.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,650:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,650:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  天哪，这很严峻。我以为这将变成一个傲慢的警告故事。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,650:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,675:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  In 2008, SolarCity made a deal with Morgan Stanley, and Morgan Stanley had to renege
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,688:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: on the deal because they themselves were running out of money. For a while it looked like all three
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,692:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: companies were going to die. I was also going through a divorce. In addition to all that, I was getting
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,692:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: dumped on, massively, in the press. That was definitely a low point.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,693:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,693:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  2008 年，SolarCity 与摩根士丹利达成了一项协议，摩根士丹利不得不违背协议，因为他们自己资金不足。有一段时间看起来三家公司都要死掉。我也正在经历离婚。除此之外，我在媒体上被大量抨击。那绝对是一个低点。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,694:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,696:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  In the midst of this, I faced one of the most difficult choices of my whole life. Tesla and
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,697:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: SpaceX were both on the brink of bankruptcy.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,697:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,698:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  在这其中，我面临了我一生中最艰难的选择之一。特斯拉和 SpaceX 都处于破产边缘。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,698:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,708:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I had maybe $30 million or $40 million left. I had two choices: I could put it all into one
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,711:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: company, and the other would definitely die. I could split it between Tesla and SpaceX—but if I split it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,711:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: between the two, they both might die.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,712:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,712:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我大约还剩下 3000 万或 4000 万美元。我有两个选择：我可以把所有钱投入一家公司，另一家肯定会死。我可以在特斯拉和 SpaceX 之间分配——但如果我在两者之间分配，它们可能都会死。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,713:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,714:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  When you put your blood, sweat, and tears into creating something, building something
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,714:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: important—it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,715:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,715:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s like a child. Which one will I let starve to death? I couldn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,716:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,717:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t bring myself to do it. So, I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,717:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: split the money between the two.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,718:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,718:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  当你投入心血、汗水和泪水创造某物，建造重要的东西——它就像一个孩子。我会让哪一个饿死？我无法让自己这样做。所以，我把钱分给了两家公司。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,719:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,751:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Trying to raise money for a startup electric car company in 2008 while GM was going
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,772:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: bankrupt was difficult, to say the least. Eventually a subset of the previous investors came in, which
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,781:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: included Antonio Gracias, Steve Jurvetson, and Aaron Price, all whom I hold a debt of gratitude to.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,783:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: They said they would invest as much as I put in, so I put in everything. All the money I had left.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,784:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Literally everything. I didn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,784:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,785:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t have a house. I was staying in Jeff Skoll
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,785:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,786:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s spare bedroom.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,786:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,787:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  2008 年通用汽车破产时为一家初创电动汽车公司筹集资金至少可以说是困难的。最终一部分之前的投资者进来了，包括安东尼奥·格拉西亚斯、史蒂夫·尤尔韦特森和亚伦·普赖斯，我都欠他们人情。他们说他们会投入和我投入一样多的钱，所以我投入了一切。我剩下的所有钱。真的一切。我没有房子。我住在杰夫·斯科尔的备用卧室里。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,787:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,789:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (Note from Eric: At this point, Steve Jurvetson might interject with this context about
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,789:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: entrepreneurial heroism. 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,790:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,829:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Elon wrote a check for the entire remainder of his personal wealth to save
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,855:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the company, covering payroll during Christmas when no one else would. The economy was in a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,870:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: bad situation. Goldman just failed a private offering. It was the middle of the financial crisis. Tesla
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,876:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: did not look appealing, either. There was no DOE loan. There was no Daimler deal. The car had a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,877:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: negative gross margin. Oh, and the largest shareholder was pissed off, going AWOL. It was ugly.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,877:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,878:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: )
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,878:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,879:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  （埃里克的注释：此时，史蒂夫·尤尔韦特森可能会插入这段关于创业英雄主义的背景。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,879:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,880:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 埃隆开了一张他个人财富全部剩余部分的支票来拯救公司，在圣诞节期间支付工资，而其他人都不愿意。经济状况糟糕。高盛刚刚私募发行失败。那是金融危机的中期。特斯拉看起来也没有吸引力。没有能源部贷款。没有戴姆勒交易。汽车有负的毛利率。哦，最大的股东生气了，擅自离岗。这很丑陋。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,880:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,881:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ）
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,881:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,885:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  We closed that round at 6:00 p.m. on Christmas Eve 2008. It was the last hour of the last
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,886:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: day possible. We would have bounced payroll two days after Christmas.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,886:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,887:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我们在 2008 年平安夜下午 6 点完成了那一轮融资。那是最后可能的最后一天的最后一小时。我们将在圣诞节后两天无法支付工资。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,887:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,913:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Eventually, Daimler executives came to visit. They showed up expecting a PowerPoint.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,927:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: While they were on their way over, we dropped a Roadster motor and battery into a Smart Car and
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,932:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: let them drive it. They were shocked when it hit 60 mph in four seconds. Daimler ended up investing
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,933:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: $50 million. If Daimler had not invested in Tesla at that time, we would have died.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,933:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,934:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  最终，戴姆勒高管来访问。他们出现时期待一个 PowerPoint。在他们来的路上，我们将 Roadster 电机和电池放入一辆 Smart 车，让他们驾驶。当它在四秒内达到 60 英里/小时时，他们很震惊。戴姆勒最终投资了 5000 万美元。如果戴姆勒当时没有投资特斯拉，我们会死掉。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,934:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,935:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,935:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,938:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s definitely stressful when death is inches from your face, trying to eat your face off—like
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,938:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: right there and the foam is spattering on you.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,939:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,939:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  当死亡离你只有几英寸，试图吞噬你的脸——就像在那里，泡沫溅在你身上时，绝对有压力。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,939:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,940:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  For a while all I could think was, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,940:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,941:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: We need to live. How do we live?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,941:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,941:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,942:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  有一段时间我唯一能想的是，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,942:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,942:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 我们需要活下去。我们如何活下去？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,943:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,943:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,944:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  At both SpaceX and Tesla in 2008, if we
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,944:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,945:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: d paid our suppliers on time we would have gone
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,945:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: bankrupt immediately.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,945:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,946:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  2008 年在 SpaceX 和特斯拉，如果我们按时支付供应商，我们会立即破产。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,946:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The Edge of Sanity
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,947:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 理智的边缘
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,947:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,948:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Q: How do you prioritize with so many things going on at once?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,948:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,949:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  问：当有这么多事情同时发生时，你如何确定优先级？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,949:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,950:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Prioritizing has usually been out of desperation, not selection. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,950:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,951:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s not, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,951:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,951:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Oh, let
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,952:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,953:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s sit back
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,954:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: and leisurely decide how we shall spend these resources.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,954:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,954:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,955:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,955:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,955:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,956:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: This isn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,956:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,957:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t working, if we don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,957:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,958:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t make
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,958:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: it work, we
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,958:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,959:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re gonna go bankrupt, so we better make it work.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,959:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,960:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,960:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  确定优先级通常是出于绝望，而不是选择。不是，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,961:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,961:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 哦，让我们坐下来悠闲地决定我们如何花费这些资源。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,961:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,962:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 而是，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,962:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,963:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 这行不通，如果我们不让它行不通，我们会破产，所以我们最好让它行得通。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,963:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,964:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,978:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  We messed up almost every aspect of the Model 3 production line. There were so many
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,984:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: mistakes, the entire company had to be devoted to fixing them. We took everyone off every other
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,984:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: project—we all started working on the Model 3. We had to make it work or there wouldn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,985:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,985:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t be any more
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,986:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Tesla.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,986:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,987:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我们搞砸了 Model 3 生产线的几乎每个方面。有太多错误，整个公司都必须致力于修复它们。我们把所有人从其他项目中撤出——我们都开始致力于 Model 3。我们必须让它行得通，否则就不会再有特斯拉了。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,987:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,993:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  There was no choice. We had to get to high-volume production. It was a chicken-and-egg
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,993:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: situation. You can
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,994:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,995:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t make the car at an affordable price unless you have high volume. Without high
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,996:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: volume, you can
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,996:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,997:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t sell at an affordable price. So what do you do?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,997:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,998:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  没有选择。我们必须达到高产量。这是一个鸡和蛋的情况。除非你有高产量，否则你无法以负担得起的价格制造汽车。没有高产量，你就无法以负担得起的价格销售。那么你做什么？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,998:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:57,999:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  You take a giant flying leap at high volume and hope you can grab a cliff ledge with your
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,000:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: fingertips.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,000:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,001:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  你在高产量上进行一次巨大的飞跃，希望你的指尖能抓住悬崖边缘。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,001:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,002:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I felt like Indiana Jones running through the temple. There
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,003:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,008:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s a huge boulder chasing you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,010:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: and you need to jump across a giant pit in the ground. If you slow down, the boulder will crush you,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,010:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: and if you don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,011:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,011:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t make the leap, you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,012:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,012:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ll die in the pit. That
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,013:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,013:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s prioritizing.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,014:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,014:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我感觉像印第安纳·琼斯在寺庙里奔跑。有一个巨大的巨石追赶你，你需要跳过地上的一个巨大坑。如果你慢下来，巨石会压碎你，如果你不跳跃，你会死在坑里。这就是确定优先级。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,015:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,016:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Q: How did you motivate the team to do whatever it takes?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,016:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,017:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  问：你如何激励团队不惜一切代价？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,017:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,020:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I told them we had to go ultrahardcore. They had to prepare for a level of intensity greater
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,020:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: than anything they had experienced before.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,021:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,021:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我告诉他们我们必须超级硬核。他们必须准备好比他们以前经历过的任何强度都更高的强度水平。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,021:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,045:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I lived in the Fremont and Nevada factories for three years fixing that production line,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,057:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: running around like a maniac through every part of that factory, living with the team. I slept on the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,060:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: floor so the team going through a hard time could see me on the floor and know I was not in some
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,061:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ivory tower. Whatever pain they experienced, I had more.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,061:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,062:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我在弗里蒙特和内华达工厂住了三年，修复那条生产线，像疯子一样在工厂的每个部分跑来跑去，与团队生活在一起。我睡在地板上，这样经历困难的团队可以看到我在地板上，知道我不在某个象牙塔里。无论他们经历什么痛苦，我都有更多。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,062:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,062:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I worked to the edge of sanity. There wasn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,063:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,067:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t any other way to make it work but three years
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,068:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: of hell. From 2017 to 2019, I experienced the longest period of excruciating pain in my life. There
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,069:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: wasn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,069:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,074:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t any other way, and we still barely made it. We were on the ragged edge of bankruptcy the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,075:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: entire time. Three years of pain, but it had to be done or Tesla would be dead.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,076:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,076:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我工作到理智的边缘。没有其他方法让它行得通，除了三年的地狱。从 2017 年到 2019 年，我经历了我一生中最长的极度痛苦时期。没有其他方法，我们仍然勉强成功。我们一直处于破产的边缘。三年的痛苦，但必须这样做，否则特斯拉就会死掉。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,076:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,081:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  At this point, I think I know more about manufacturing than anyone currently alive on
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,082:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Earth. I can tell you how every damn part in that car is made. That
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,082:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,083:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s what happens when you live in
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,083:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the factory for three years.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,084:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,084:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  在这一点上，我认为我比地球上任何活着的人都更了解制造。我可以告诉你那辆车里的每个该死的部件是如何制造的。那就是当你在工厂里住了三年会发生的事情。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,085:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: A Whole New Kind of Car Company
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,085:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 一种全新的汽车公司
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,086:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,087:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Ultimately, what we induce other companies to do will have a greater impact than the cars
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,088:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: we make ourselves.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,088:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,089:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  最终，我们促使其他公司做的事情将比我们自己制造的汽车产生更大的影响。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,089:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,090:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Q: A Tesla is a very different product, but how different is Tesla as a company from a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,091:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: traditional auto company?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,091:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,092:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  问：特斯拉是一个非常不同的产品，但作为一家公司，特斯拉与传统汽车公司有多不同？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,092:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,107:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  A typical car company manages a supply chain, assembles vehicles, and sends them to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,114:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: dealers. They might make the engine, but most of the actual technology development and parts
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,115:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: manufacturing is done by suppliers. Most of the vehicle software is done by suppliers too. The
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,115:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: amount of 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,116:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,116:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: real work
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,117:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,118:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  done by car companies like GM or Ford is not as much as you think. They
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,118:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,118:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,119:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t do sales or service either; dealerships do.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,119:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,120:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  典型的汽车公司管理供应链，组装车辆，并将它们发送给经销商。他们可能制造发动机，但大部分实际技术开发和部件制造都是由供应商完成的。大部分车辆软件也由供应商完成。像通用或福特这样的汽车公司做的
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,121:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,121:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 真正工作
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,121:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,122:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 没有你想象的那么多。他们也不做销售或服务；经销商做。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,122:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,123:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  At Tesla, we do our own sales and service. We don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,123:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,140:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t have dealerships. I have made it a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,150:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: principle within Tesla that we should never attempt to make service a profit center. It does not seem
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,153:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: right to me when companies make a profit off customers when their product breaks. The best way to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,154:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: experience service is, of course, to not need service.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,154:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,155:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  在特斯拉，我们自己做销售和服务。我们没有经销商。我在特斯拉内部制定了一个原则，我们永远不应该试图让服务成为利润中心。当公司的产品坏了时从客户身上赚钱，这对我来说似乎不对。体验服务的最佳方式当然是不需要服务。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,156:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,156:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  If we charge for something, it is not because we want to make things more expensive; it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,157:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,157:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,158:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: because we can
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,158:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,159:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t figure out how to make it less expensive.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,160:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,160:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  如果我们对某事收费，不是因为我们想让事情更贵；而是因为我们无法找出如何让它更便宜。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,161:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,161:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  There
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,162:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,164:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s a lot of vertical integration at Tesla. We make the battery pack, the power
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,164:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: electronics, and the drivetrain ourselves. We
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,165:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,174:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re vertically integrated because the pace we needed to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,179:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: move was much faster than the supply chain could move. To the degree you rely on the legacy
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,179:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: supply chain, you inherit the legacy constraints—including their speed, costs, and technology.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,180:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,180:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  特斯拉有很多垂直整合。我们自己制造电池组、电力电子和动力总成。我们是垂直整合的，因为我们需要移动的速度比供应链可以移动的速度快得多。在你依赖传统供应链的程度上，你继承了传统限制——包括它们的速度、成本和技术。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,181:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,189:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  We do car insurance now, too. Car insurance is a bigger deal than it may seem. A lot of
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,192:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: people are paying 30–40 percent as much as their car lease payment for insurance. The car insurance
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,192:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: industry is incredibly inefficient because they
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,192:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,196:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ve got all these middlemen, from the insurance agent
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,197:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: all the way to the final reinsurer. There are a half dozen companies each taking a cut.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,197:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,198:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我们现在也做汽车保险。汽车保险比它看起来更重要。很多人支付的保险费是他们汽车租赁付款的 30-40%。汽车保险行业效率极低，因为他们有所有这些中间人，从保险代理人到最终再保险人。有半打公司各分一杯羹。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,198:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,199:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Insurance is driven by statistics, so even if you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,199:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,200:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re a good driver at twenty years old, it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,200:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,213:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,225:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: extremely expensive. Tesla allows for real-time insurance based on how you actually drive the car.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,229:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: If you drive the car in a safer way, you pay lower insurance. Our insurance is based on how you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,230:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: drive, not how people who fit your demographic have driven historically.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,230:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,230:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  保险由统计数据驱动，所以即使你在二十岁时是个好司机，它也非常昂贵。特斯拉允许根据你实际驾驶汽车的方式进行实时保险。如果你以更安全的方 式驾驶汽车，你支付更低的保险费。我们的保险基于你如何驾驶，而不是历史上符合你人口统计数据的人如何驾驶。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,231:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,249:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Tesla is as much a software company as a hardware company. The software in a Tesla
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,258:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: operates the car, the screen, the charging…all developed by us. Then, Tesla built an autopilot AI team
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,260:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: from scratch, the best real-world AI team on Earth. We also built a chip team too, because the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,261:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: hardware we could buy wasn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,261:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,262:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t capable of running our AI software.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,262:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,262:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  特斯拉既是一家软件公司也是一家硬件公司。特斯拉中的软件操作汽车、屏幕、充电……都由我们开发。然后，特斯拉从零开始建立了一个自动驾驶 AI 团队，地球上最好的现实世界 AI 团队。我们还建立了一个芯片团队，因为我们可以购买的硬件无法运行我们的 AI 软件。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,263:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,264:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Q: How important is the look and design of the cars?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,264:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,264:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  问：汽车的外观和设计有多重要？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,265:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,265:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The value of beauty and inspiration is underrated, no question.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,266:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,266:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  美丽和灵感的价值被低估了，毫无疑问。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,267:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,275:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  If you want to make something beautiful, you must trigger whatever fundamental aesthetic
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,278:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: algorithms there are. Our brains have some intrinsic elements that represent beauty, which trigger
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,279:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the emotion of appreciation of beauty in our mind.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,279:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,280:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  如果你想制造一些美丽的东西，你必须触发任何基本的美学算法。我们的大脑有一些代表美丽的内在元素，这些元素触发我们心中对美的欣赏情感。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,280:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,282:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I think these are relatively consistent among people. Not completely. Not everyone likes
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,283:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: exactly the same thing, but there
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,283:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,284:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s a lot of commonality. It is important to combine aesthetic design
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,285:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: with functionality.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,285:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,286:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我认为这些在人们中相对一致。不完全。不是每个人都喜欢完全相同的东西，但有很多共性。将美学设计与功能性结合起来很重要。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,286:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,339:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  What was hard about the Model S and Model X was to combine aesthetics and utility, to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,373:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: balance the two. You can make a car look good by giving it certain proportions—making it low and slim.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,392:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: But if you do that, the utility is significantly affected. The big challenge is trying to figure out how
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,399:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: to get five adults plus two kids in a seven-seater with high utility and keep it looking good. To make
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,400:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: a sports car look good is relatively easy. But to make a sedan or an SUV look good is quite difficult.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,400:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,401:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Model S 和 Model X 的困难之处是结合美学和实用性，平衡两者。你可以通过给它某些比例——让它低而瘦——让汽车看起来不错。但如果你这样做，实用性会受到显著影响。最大的挑战是试图找出如何在七座车中容纳五个成人加两个孩子，具有高实用性，并保持它看起来不错。让跑车看起来不错相对容易。但让轿车或 SUV 看起来不错相当困难。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,402:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,404:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Another incredibly important design principle is to have it feel bigger on the inside than it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,404:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: looks on the outside. That
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,405:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,405:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s also a hard thing to do.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,406:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,406:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  另一个极其重要的设计原则是让内部感觉比外部看起来更大。那也是一件困难的事情。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,407:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,407:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Most people don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,408:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,424:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t consciously notice the small details, but they do subconsciously. Your
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,432:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: mind takes in an overall impression. You know if something is appealing or not, even though you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,434:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: may not be able to point out exactly why. That sense is a summation of many details. Most of us
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,435:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: experience this as 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,435:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,436:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: that
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,436:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
