   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,438:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: that
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,439:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,439:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s beautiful,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,440:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,440:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  or 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,441:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,441:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: wow, that
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,442:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,442:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s elegant,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,443:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,443:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  but can
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,444:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,444:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t break down
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,445:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: why.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,445:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,446:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  大多数人不会 consciously 注意到小细节，但他们确实下意识地注意到。你的大脑接收一个整体印象。你知道某事是否有吸引力，即使你可能无法准确指出为什么。那种感觉是许多细节的总和。我们大多数人将其体验为
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,446:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,447:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 那很丑，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,447:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,447:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 或
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,448:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,448:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 那很美，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,448:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,448:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 或
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,449:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,449:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 哇，那很优雅，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,449:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,450:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 但无法分解为什么。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,450:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,450:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  You can train yourself. You can make yourself pay attention to 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,451:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,451:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: why.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,451:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,454:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  You can learn to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,455:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: bring subconscious awareness into conscious awareness. Look closely and carefully. Look at each
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,455:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: object
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,456:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,456:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s geometry.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,456:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,457:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  你可以训练自己。你可以让自己注意
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,457:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,457:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 为什么。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,458:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,458:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 你可以学习将潜意识意识带入显意识。仔细仔细地看。看每个物体的几何形状。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,458:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,472:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Pay attention to the little details. Train yourself to notice them. Notice the nuances of
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,478:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: design, shape, form, function, and the way it looks in different lights. Anyone can do this, although
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,479:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: it is a double-edged sword, because then you always notice all the little things. Now when
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,480:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: something
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,480:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,481:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s off—even a little thing—it drives me bananas.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,481:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,481:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  注意小细节。训练自己注意到它们。注意设计、形状、形式、功能的细微差别，以及它在不同光线下的外观。任何人都可以做到这一点，尽管这是一把双刃剑，因为那样你总是注意到所有小事情。现在当某些事情不对劲时——即使是一件小事——它也会让我发疯。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,482:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,482:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  If you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,483:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,483:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re trying to make a perfect product, attention to detail is essential.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,484:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,484:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  如果你试图制造一个完美的产品，注意细节是必不可少的。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,484:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Give People More for Less
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,485:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 以更少的钱给人们更多
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,485:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,486:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Revolutionizing industries is not for the faint of heart.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,486:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,487:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  革命化行业不适合胆小的人。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,487:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,488:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Q: How do you think about iterating through products to reach a mass market?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,488:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,489:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  问：你如何通过产品迭代达到大众市场？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,489:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,494:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The nature of new technology adoption tends to follow an S-curve. People underpredict it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,495:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: in the beginning, because they tend to extrapolate trends in a straight line. Then they
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,495:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,500:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ll overpredict it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,503:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: at the midpoint during massive growth. It will take longer than people think at the midpoint, but
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,504:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: much shorter than people think at the beginning.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,504:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,505:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  新技术采用的性质往往遵循 S 曲线。人们在开始时低估它，因为他们倾向于以直线推断趋势。然后他们会在大规模增长的中点高估它。在中点花费的时间比人们想象的要长，但在开始时比人们想象的要短得多。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,505:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,524:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  One way to look at technology is like rendering an image in successive levels of detail.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,532:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The first layer of the image is very blurry and things are out of place. Then with the next pass, it gets
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,533:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: a bit more defined and things start to shift into place. And you do another pass and another pass, and
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,534:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: eventually it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,534:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,537:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s refined and actually works. It generally takes three major iterations of any major new
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,537:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: technology to have it work really, really well.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,538:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,538:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  看待技术的一种方式就像以连续的细节层次渲染图像。图像的第一层非常模糊，东西错位。然后在下一遍，它变得更加清晰，东西开始到位。然后你再做一遍又一遍，最终它被完善并实际工作。任何重大新技术通常需要三次重大迭代才能使其真正、真正地工作。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,539:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,543:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Progress comes from design and technology improvements as well as scale. Look at the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,544:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: earliest cell phones. In the original Wall Street movie in 1987, the guy
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,544:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,557:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s walking down the beach
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,567:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: with a giant phone, carrying a briefcase to power it. It had like thirty minutes of battery life. Without
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,569:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: technology improvements, no amount of money or scale could have made that phone affordable. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,570:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: took a lot of engineering and design iterations.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,571:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,571:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  进步来自设计和技术改进以及规模。看看最早的手机。在 1987 年的原版《华尔街》电影中，那个家伙带着一个巨大的手机走在海滩上，带着一个公文包为它供电。它只有大约三十分钟的电池寿命。没有技术进步，再多的钱或规模都无法让那部手机负担得起。它需要很多工程和设计迭代。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,572:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,591:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  In the early days of cell phones, laptops, and gasoline cars, they were considered toys for
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,600:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: rich people. You need to go through this phase of having an expensive car available to few in order
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,603:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: to build the low-cost car available to many. The first version is simply about making the new
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,603:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: technology work. Then, you work to optimize.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,604:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,604:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  在手机、笔记本电脑和汽油车的早期，它们被认为是富人的玩具。你需要经历这个阶段，让少数人可以使用昂贵的汽车，以便建造许多人可以使用的低成本汽车。第一个版本只是关于让新技术工作。然后，你努力优化。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,605:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,605:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  We
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,606:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,624:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re probably on the thirtieth version of a cell phone, and with each successive design
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,633:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: iteration we add more capability. We integrate more parts and figure out better ways to produce it so
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,636:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: it gets both better and cheaper. Progress in any new technology takes multiple versions and a large
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,636:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: production volume to make it affordable.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,636:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,637:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我们可能在手机的第三十个版本上，每个连续的设计迭代我们增加更多功能。我们集成更多部件，找出更好的生产方法，这样它变得更好更便宜。任何新技术的进步需要多个版本和大量生产量才能使其负担得起。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,637:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,652:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Air travel used to be accessible to only a few people. It was insanely expensive and
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,659:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: dangerous. Now it is common to fly. The first TVs were rare and expensive. Then big, flat-screen
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,661:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: plasma TVs used to be extremely expensive. Now, you can buy an amazing flat-screen plasma for
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,661:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: two hundred bucks. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,662:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,662:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s amazing.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,662:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,663:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  航空旅行过去只有少数人可以使用。它非常昂贵和危险。现在飞行很常见。第一批电视很稀有且昂贵。然后大的平板等离子电视曾经非常昂贵。现在，你可以花 200 美元买一个惊人的平板等离子。这很惊人。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,663:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,674:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  This is also true for electric cars. The strategy for Tesla was to enter at the high end of the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,678:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: market with the Roadster, where customers are prepared to pay a premium. Then move as fast as
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,678:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: possible to higher volume and lower prices with each successive model.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,679:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,679:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  这也适用于电动汽车。特斯拉的策略是以 Roadster 进入市场高端，那里的客户准备支付溢价。然后随着每个后续车型尽可能快地转向更高产量和更低价格。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,679:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,685:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The Model S was a sporty four-door family car at roughly half the price point of the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,686:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Roadster. Then the Model 3 was even more affordable. All free cash flow was plowed back into R
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,686:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,693:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: D to drive down costs and bring the next products to market as fast as possible. When someone bought the Tesla Roadster, they were helping pay for development of the low-cost family car.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,693:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,694:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Model S 是一款运动型四门家庭轿车，价格约为 Roadster 的一半。然后 Model 3 更负担得起。所有自由现金流都投入研发以降低成本，并尽快将下一代产品推向市场。当有人购买特斯拉 Roadster 时，他们在帮助支付低成本家庭轿车的开发费用。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,694:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,695:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Q: Any other unique aspects about Tesla
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,695:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,696:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s product philosophy?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,696:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,697:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  问：关于特斯拉的产品哲学还有其他独特方面吗？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,697:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,698:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Focus on signal over noise. A lot of companies get confused. They spend a lot of money on
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,699:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: things that don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,699:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,706:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t actually make the product better. At Tesla, we put all the money into research and
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,707:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: development, manufacturing, and design to try and make the cars as good as possible. For any
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,708:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: company, ask, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,708:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,708:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Are the efforts we
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,709:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,709:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re expending resulting in a better product or service?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,710:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,710:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  If they
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,711:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,711:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,712:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: not, stop those efforts.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,712:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,712:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  专注于信号而非噪音。很多公司感到困惑。他们花很多钱在实际上不能让产品更好的事情上。在特斯拉，我们把所有钱都投入研发、制造和设计，试图让汽车尽可能好。对于任何公司，问，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,713:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,713:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 我们付出的努力是否导致更好的产品或服务？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,714:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,714:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 如果不是，停止那些努力。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,714:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,723:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Also, go for extreme levels of precision. One of the examples we use at Tesla is LEGO
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,726:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: blocks. LEGO is super precise. The press-fit comes down to a quarter millimeter or less, and each
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,726:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: one is exactly the same. LEGO doesn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,727:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,727:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t work if the press-fit is too soft or too hard. If it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,728:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,728:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s too soft, the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,729:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: press-and-click won
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,729:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,730:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t stick; if it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,730:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,731:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s too hard, you can
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,731:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,733:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t get it on. They can make something that is a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,733:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: tiny fraction of a millimeter accurate and it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,734:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,735:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s a low-cost plastic toy. If LEGO can be that precise, so
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,735:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: can a car.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,736:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,736:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  此外，追求极端的精度水平。我们在特斯拉使用的一个例子是乐高积木。乐高超级精确。压配合精度达到四分之一毫米或更少，每个都完全相同。如果压配合太软或太硬，乐高就不起作用。如果太软，压合不会粘住；如果太硬，你无法安装。他们可以制造出精度为毫米的微小分数的东西，它是一个低成本塑料玩具。如果乐高可以那么精确，汽车也可以。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,737:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The Battle of Public Perception
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,738:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 公众认知的战斗
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,738:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,744:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  It should puzzle you that a Tesla crash resulting in a broken ankle is front-page news, yet
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,745:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the many thousands of people who die in US auto accidents each year get almost no coverage.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,745:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,746:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  这应该让你困惑，特斯拉撞车导致脚踝骨折是头版新闻，然而每年在美国汽车事故中死亡的数千人几乎没有报道。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,746:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,748:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Q: How do you stay positive when faced with public attacks and misrepresentation,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,749:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: without becoming resentful or cynical?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,749:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,750:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  问：当你面临公众攻击和歪曲时，如何保持积极，而不变得怨恨或愤世嫉俗？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,751:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,752:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  It does get me down at times. It makes me sad. But at some point you realize these attacks
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,753:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: are by people who don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,754:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,756:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t know you and their goal is to generate clicks. If you can detach yourself
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,757:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: emotionally (which is not easy) and say, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,757:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,758:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: This person does not know me. They
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,758:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,758:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re just writing to get
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,759:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: clicks
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,759:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,759:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  then it doesn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,760:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,760:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t hurt as much.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,760:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,761:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  有时这确实让我沮丧。它让我伤心。但在某个时候你意识到这些攻击来自不了解你的人，他们的目标是产生点击量。如果你能在情感上超脱自己（这不容易）并说，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,761:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,761:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 这个人不了解我。他们只是为了获得点击量而写作
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,762:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,762:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 那么它就不会那么伤人。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,762:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,763:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  It also helps to stay focused on our mission. Tesla
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,763:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,765:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s motivation remains to make electric
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,766:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: transport as affordable as possible. That informs all our actions.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,766:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,767:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  保持专注于我们的使命也有帮助。特斯拉的动机仍然是让电动交通尽可能负担得起。这指导我们所有的行动。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,767:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,777:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  We put all our money and effort into trying to make the product as compelling as possible.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,780:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The way to sell any product is through word of mouth. The key is to have a product people love.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,780:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: People will talk about the things they love.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,781:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,781:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我们把所有钱和精力都投入试图让产品尽可能有吸引力。销售任何产品的方式是通过口碑。关键是拥有一个人们喜爱的产品。人们会谈论他们喜爱的东西。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,782:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,782:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  That generates real word of mouth, and that
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,783:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,783:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s how our sales have grown. We
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,783:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,789:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re not
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,793:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: spending money on advertising, public relations, or endorsements. Anyone who buys our car bought
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,794:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: it because they like the car, not their impression of the car.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,794:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,795:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  这产生了真正的口碑，这就是我们的销售增长的方式。我们不花钱在广告、公共关系或代言上。任何购买我们汽车的人购买它是因为他们喜欢这辆车，而不是他们对这辆车的印象。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,795:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,796:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Tesla does not advertise or pay for endorsements. Instead, we use that money to make the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,797:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: product great.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,797:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,797:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  特斯拉不做广告或支付代言费。相反，我们用那笔钱让产品变得伟大。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,798:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,804:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  There are over a million internal combustion engine car fires per year resulting in
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,805:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: thousands of deaths, but one Tesla car fire with no injuries gets the biggest headlines. Why the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,806:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: double standard?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,806:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,806:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  每年有超过一百万起内燃机汽车火灾，导致数千人死亡，但一起没有受伤的特斯拉汽车火灾却获得最大的头条新闻。为什么双重标准？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,807:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,809:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The problem is journalists are under constant pressure to get maximum clicks. They either
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,810:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: earn advertising dollars or get fired. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,810:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,811:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s a tricky situation, since Tesla doesn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,811:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,813:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t advertise and fossil
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,813:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: fuel companies and legacy car companies are among the world
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,814:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,814:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s biggest advertisers.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,814:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,815:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  问题是记者一直处于获得最大点击量的压力下。他们要么赚取广告费，要么被解雇。这是一个棘手的情况，因为特斯拉不做广告，而化石燃料公司和传统汽车公司是世界上最大的广告商之一。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,815:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,829:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Regulators tend to pay a disproportionate amount of attention to whatever is in the press.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,834:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: This is an objective fact. And Tesla generates a lot of press. In the United States, there are about
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,835:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: forty thousand automotive deaths per year. But if there are four in a Tesla, they
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,835:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,837:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ll probably receive a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,837:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: thousand times more press than any other incident.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,838:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,838:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  监管机构倾向于对媒体上的任何事情给予不成比例的关注。这是一个客观事实。特斯拉产生大量媒体报道。在美国，每年约有四万起汽车死亡事故。但如果有四起发生在特斯拉，它们可能会获得比其他任何事故多一千倍的媒体报道。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,839:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,839:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The reality is a Tesla, like most electric cars, is over 500 percent
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,840:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,840:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  现实是特斯拉，像大多数电动汽车一样，超过 500%
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,841:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: BUILDING SPACEX
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,842:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 建造 SpaceX
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,842:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,845:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Building mass-market electric cars was inevitable. It would have happened without me.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,845:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: But becoming a space-faring civilization is not inevitable.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,846:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,846:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  建造大众市场电动汽车是不可避免的。没有我也会发生。但成为一个太空航行文明不是不可避免的。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,847:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: THE ONLY ONE CRAZY ENOUGH FOR SPACE
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,848:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 唯一疯狂到足以进入太空的人
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,848:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,849:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,849:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,849:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ve always been optimistic. If I wasn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,850:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,850:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t optimistic, I wouldn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,851:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,852:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t be attempting all these crazy
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,852:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: things. I must be pathologically optimistic, I suppose.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,853:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,853:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我一直很乐观。如果我不乐观，我就不会尝试所有这些疯狂的事情。我想我一定是病态地乐观。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,854:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,857:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The origin of SpaceX was trying to figure out why we had not sent anyone to Mars. The
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,858:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: obvious next step after Apollo was to send people to Mars.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,858:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,858:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  SpaceX 的起源是试图找出为什么我们没有送任何人去火星。阿波罗之后明显的下一步是送人去火星。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,859:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,859:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Every year I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,859:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,860:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: d look at the NASA website, and there didn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,860:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,880:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t seem to be a date for it. We were
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,894:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: able to go to the moon in 1969. Our last mission to the moon was in 1972. Now here we are half a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,899:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: century later and we still have not gone back to the moon. It would be extremely tragic if Apollo
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,899:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: was the high-water mark for humanity, if the moon was as far as we got.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,900:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,900:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  每年我都会看 NASA 的网站，似乎没有日期。我们能够在 1969 年去月球。我们最后一次登月任务是在 1972 年。现在半个世纪过去了，我们仍然没有回到月球。如果阿波罗是人类的高水位标记，如果月球是我们到达的最远的地方，那将极其悲惨。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,901:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,908:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The space shuttle could only take people to low earth orbit. Then the space shuttle retired,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,909:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: and the United States could take no one to orbit. The trend was dwindling down to nothing. Does
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,910:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: this mean we
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,910:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,911:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ve peaked as a civilization?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,911:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,912:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  航天飞机只能将人送入低地球轨道。然后航天飞机退役了，美国无法送任何人进入轨道。趋势逐渐减少到零。这是否意味着我们作为文明已经达到了顶峰？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,912:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,922:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  If you had asked people in 1969 what the world would look like in fifty years, they would
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,925:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: have expected a base on the moon and some people visiting Mars. Maybe even a base on Mars.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,926:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: They would expect orbiting space hotels and other awesome stuff.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,926:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,927:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  如果你在 1969 年问人们五十年后世界会是什么样子，他们会预期月球上有一个基地，一些人访问火星。甚至可能火星上有一个基地。他们会预期轨道太空酒店和其他惊人的东西。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,927:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,928:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  If you told them, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,928:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,929:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Well, we have a device smaller than a deck of cards with access to all
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,929:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the world
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,930:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,933:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s information, and you can talk to anyone instantly on planet Earth. But the United States
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,933:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: will not be able to send anyone to orbit,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,934:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,934:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  they would have called bullshit. 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,935:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,936:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: You have all of that, and
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,936:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: nothing is happening in space?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,937:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: !
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,937:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,937:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,938:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  如果你告诉他们，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,938:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,939:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 好吧，我们有一个比一副扑克牌还小的设备，可以访问世界上所有的信息，你可以立即与地球上的任何人交谈。但美国将无法送任何人进入轨道，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,939:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,940:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 他们会说是胡扯。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,940:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,940:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 你有所有这些，太空中什么都没有发生？！
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,941:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,941:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,942:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  After we sold PayPal in 2001, I was trying to figure out why.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,942:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,943:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  2001 年我们出售 PayPal 后，我试图找出原因。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,943:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,944:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The original idea for SpaceX wasn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,944:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,945:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t to create a company. It was to figure out why we hadn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,946:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,947:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t sent people to Mars. I thought maybe we
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,947:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,949:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: d lost the will to explore. I thought we had to create the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,949:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: will to explore. But that was wrong.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,950:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,950:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  SpaceX 最初的想法不是创建一家公司。而是找出为什么我们没有送人去火星。我想也许我们失去了探索的意志。我想我们必须创造探索的意志。但那是错的。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,951:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,952:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  We have not lost the will to explore; people just did not think there was a way forward. If
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,953:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: people don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,953:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,954:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t think there
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,954:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,955:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s a way, then they won
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,955:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,956:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t continuously bash their head against the wall for
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,956:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: progress.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,957:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,958:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我们没有失去探索的意志；人们只是认为没有前进的道路。如果人们认为没有路，那么他们就不会为了进步而不断地用头撞墙。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,958:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,959:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  There must be things to inspire us—that make you proud to be a member of humanity.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,959:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,960:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  必须有事情激励我们——让你为成为人类的一员而感到自豪。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,960:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,972:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The Apollo moon landing was an example of that. Only a handful of people went to the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,976:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: moon—and yet actually we all went to the moon. We went with them vicariously. We shared in that
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,977:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: adventure. No one would say that was a bad idea—that Apollo wasn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,977:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,978:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t great. We need more of those.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,978:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,979:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  阿波罗登月就是一个例子。只有少数人去了月球——但实际上我们都去了月球。我们间接地和他们一起去了。我们分享了那次冒险。没有人会说那是一个坏主意——阿波罗不伟大。我们需要更多那样的事情。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,980:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,981:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The United States is a distillation of the human spirit of exploration. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,981:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,982:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s fundamental to the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,983:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: psyche. Once people realized, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,983:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,984:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: There is a way to do this,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,984:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,984:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  we got a lot of support.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,985:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,985:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  美国是人类探索精神的蒸馏。它对心灵是根本的。一旦人们意识到，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,985:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,986:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 有办法做到这一点，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,986:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,986:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 我们得到了很多支持。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,987:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: I EXPECTED TO LOSE EVERYTHING
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,987:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 我预计会失去一切
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,988:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,988:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  When something is important enough, you do it even if the odds are not in your favor.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,989:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,989:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  当某事足够重要时，即使几率对你不利，你也要去做。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,989:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,991:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  When I started them, I guessed both SpaceX and Tesla each had a probability of less than
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,991:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 10 percent to succeed.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,992:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,992:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  当我创办它们时，我猜测 SpaceX 和特斯拉各自成功的概率都小于 10%。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,993:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,993:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,993:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,994:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t look at ideas and ask, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,994:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,995:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: What is the rank-ordered list of best business opportunities
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,996:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: from a financial standpoint?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,996:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,998:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I look for problems that are important to fix for people now and for the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,998:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: future to be good.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,998:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,999:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我不会看着想法并问，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,999:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:58,999:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 从财务角度来看，最佳商业机会的排序列表是什么？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,000:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,000:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 我寻找对现在和未来都很重要的需要解决的问题。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,001:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,009:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  If one were to do a risk-adjusted rate of return estimate on opportunities, building rockets
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,011:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: and building cars would be pretty close to the bottom of the list. They would be the dumbest things
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,011:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: you could possibly do.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,011:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,012:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  如果一个人对机会进行风险调整后回报率估计，建造火箭和建造汽车将接近列表底部。那将是你可能做的最愚蠢的事情。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,012:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,013:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Company stock value is not a metric by which I judge my own achievements.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,014:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,014:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  公司股票价值不是我判断自己成就的指标。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,014:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,027:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I had a lot of friends try to talk me out of starting a rocket company, because they thought
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,031:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: it was crazy. Everyone thought it was a crazy idea. Some people had actually tried to start rocket
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,032:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: companies before and failed. They tried to talk me out of it too.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,032:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,033:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我有很多朋友试图说服我不要创办火箭公司，因为他们认为这很疯狂。每个人都认为这是一个疯狂的想法。有些人以前实际上试图创办火箭公司并失败了。他们也试图说服我不要这样做。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,033:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,035:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  One good friend compiled a bunch of footage of rocket failures and forced me to watch it.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,035:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: I said, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,035:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,036:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,036:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,037:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ve seen them all already.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,037:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,038:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,038:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  一个好朋友编译了一堆火箭失败的视频，强迫我看。我说，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,038:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,039:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 我已经都看过了。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,039:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,040:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,043:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I think these people misunderstood my premise. When I started SpaceX, it was not with the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,044:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: expectation of success. I thought the most likely outcome was failure.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,044:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,045:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我想这些人误解了我的前提。当我创办 SpaceX 时，并没有期望成功。我认为最可能的结果是失败。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,045:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,046:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Their premise for talking me out of it was, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,046:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,047:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: You
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,047:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,048:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re going to lose the money you invest.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,048:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,049:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,049:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: replied, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,050:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,050:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Well, that was my expectation anyway, so I don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,051:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,051:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t really mind
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,052:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: !
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,052:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,053:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,053:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  他们说服我的前提是，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,053:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,054:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 你会失去你投资的钱。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,054:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,055:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 我回答说，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,055:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,056:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 好吧，反正那是我的预期，所以我真的不介意！
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,056:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,057:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,057:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I mean, I mind losing money, but it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,058:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,061:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s not like I was trying to figure out the rank-ordered
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,062:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: best way to invest my money and on that basis chose space. I didn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,062:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,063:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t think, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,063:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,064:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: I could do real estate, or
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,065:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: invest in shoemaking, and—whoa
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,065:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: !
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,066:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Space has the highest ROI
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,066:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: !
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,067:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,067:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  That was not my premise.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,068:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,068:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我的意思是，我在意亏钱，但这不是说我试图找出投资我的钱的排序最佳方式，并在此基础上选择太空。我没有想，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,069:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,069:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 我可以做房地产，或投资制鞋业，然后——哇！太空有最高的投资回报率！
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,070:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,070:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 那不是我的前提。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,071:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,082:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  There have been many times where I expected to lose everything. Who starts a car
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,087:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: company and a rocket company expecting them to succeed? Certainly not me. I thought they both
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,088:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: had a low chance of success, less than 10 percent. Maybe 1 percent, I don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,089:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,089:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t know. Frankly, I wasn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,090:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,090:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,091:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: wrong.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,091:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,092:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  有很多次我预计会失去一切。谁会创办一家汽车公司和一家火箭公司并期望它们成功？肯定不是我。我认为它们成功的几率都很低，低于 10%。也许 1%，我不知道。坦率地说，我没说错。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,092:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,093:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  We must be optimistic. There
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,093:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,094:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s no point in being pessimistic. It just doesn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,094:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,094:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t help. My
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,095:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: theory is you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,095:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,096:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: d rather be optimistic and wrong about the future than pessimistic and right. If you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,096:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,096:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,097:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: pessimistic, you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,097:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,097:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re going to be miserable. Might as well enjoy the journey.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,098:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,098:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我们必须乐观。悲观没有意义。这只是没有帮助。我的理论是你宁愿对未来乐观而错，也不要悲观而对。如果你悲观，你会很痛苦。不如享受旅程。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,099:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,099:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Q: How did you go about creating belief and support for the Mars mission?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,100:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,100:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  问：你如何为火星任务创造信念和支持？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,100:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,101:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  If you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,101:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,102:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re trying to convince the public to do something, you have to think about what will
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,102:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: excite people.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,103:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,103:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  如果你试图说服公众做某事，你必须考虑什么会激发人们。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,104:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,107:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  What message are we going to try to convey? What will people respond to? What would I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,107:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: respond to if I was an objective member of the public?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,108:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,108:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我们要试图传达什么信息？人们会对什么做出反应？如果我是一个客观的公众成员，我会对什么做出反应？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,109:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,111:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I thought we could send a small greenhouse to the surface of Mars, with seeds and a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,112:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: nutrient gel to hydrate the seeds upon landing.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,112:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,112:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我想我们可以送一个小温室到火星表面，带有种子和营养凝胶，在着陆时给种子浇水。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,113:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,119:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The greenhouse mission would be the first life on another planet, as far as we knew. The
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,120:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: farthest life had ever traveled. We would have a great picture of green plants on a red background.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,120:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: That
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,121:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,121:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s the money shot. People tend to respond to precedents and superlatives.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,122:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,122:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  据我们所知，温室任务将是另一个星球上的第一个生命。生命曾经到达的最远的地方。我们将有一张绿色植物在红色背景上的精彩照片。那是关键镜头。人们倾向于对先例和最高级做出反应。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,123:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,127:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I thought getting a greenhouse on Mars would get people excited about sending humans
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,127:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: there. My original goal was to get the public excited, to get NASA
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,128:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,129:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s budget increased to get a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,129:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: mission to Mars funded.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,129:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,130:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我认为在火星上建立一个温室会让人们对送人去那里感到兴奋。我最初的目标是让公众兴奋起来，让 NASA 的预算增加，为火星任务提供资金。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,130:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,145:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I was willing to spend half the money I got from PayPal, so $90 million, on this mission
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,152:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: with no expectation of return. This was just something important to accomplish. If I spent $90
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,153:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: million to get NASA a bigger budget, which resulted in us going to Mars, that would be a good
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,154:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: outcome.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,154:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,155:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我愿意花我从 PayPal 获得的一半资金，即 9000 万美元，用于这个任务，不期望回报。这只是一项重要的成就。如果我花了 9000 万美元让 NASA 获得更大的预算，从而导致我们去火星，那将是一个好的结果。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,155:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,163:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Also, I was trying to figure out if I could afford to build a spacecraft. I wanted to budget
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,164:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: for two missions because if we only did one and it failed, it might actually deter people from trying
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,165:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: in the future.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,165:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,166:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  此外，我试图找出我是否能负担得起建造一艘航天器。我想为两次任务做预算，因为如果我们只做一次而失败了，它实际上可能会阻止人们将来尝试。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,166:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,168:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I was able to get the cost of the spacecraft, communications, and the little greenhouse
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,169:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: down. But the one thing I couldn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,169:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,181:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t compress was the cost to launch. There were only a few options,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,185:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: and the US options were way too expensive. I ended up going to Russia three times to try to buy the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,186:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: biggest intercontinental ballistic missile (ICBM) in the Russian nuclear fleet. That didn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,186:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,187:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t work out.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,187:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,188:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我能够降低航天器、通信和小温室的成本。但我无法压缩的一件事是发射成本。只有几个选项，美国的选项太贵了。我最终去了俄罗斯三次，试图购买俄罗斯核舰队中最大的洲际弹道导弹（ICBM）。那没有成功。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,188:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,203:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  In doing this, I realized what we really need to do is improve the technology of space
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,210:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: transportation. I wanted to hold out hope that humans could be a space-faring civilization, out there
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,211:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: among the stars. There was no chance of that unless a new company was started to create
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,211:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: revolutionary rockets.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,212:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,212:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  在这样做时，我意识到我们真正需要做的是改进太空运输技术。我想保持希望，人类可以成为一个太空航行文明，在群星之中。除非创办一家新公司来创造革命性火箭，否则没有机会。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,213:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,213:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  If a startup didn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,214:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,214:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t do something to advance rocket technology, it wouldn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,214:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,215:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t happen. Either it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,215:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,216:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s coming from a startup or it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,216:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,219:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s not happening at all. A small chance of success is better than no
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,220:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: chance of success. So I started SpaceX in mid-2002, expecting to fail.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,220:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,220:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  如果初创公司不做一些事情来推进火箭技术，它就不会发生。要么来自初创公司，要么根本不会发生。小的成功机会比没有成功机会好。所以我在 2002 年年中创办了 SpaceX，预计会失败。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,221:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,221:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Q: Why did you decide to fund SpaceX yourself?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,222:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,222:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  问：你为什么决定自己资助 SpaceX？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,222:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,233:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  After PayPal was sold, I started debating between working on solar, electric cars, or space.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,237:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: I figured space would be the least likely to succeed, so least likely to attract other entrepreneurs.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,237:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Nobody else was crazy enough to do space. I thought I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,237:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,238:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: d better work on space first.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,238:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,239:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  PayPal 出售后，我开始在太阳能、电动汽车或太空之间辩论。我认为太空最不可能成功，所以最不可能吸引其他创业者。没有其他人疯狂到足以做太空。我想我最好先从事太空工作。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,239:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,261:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  My first idea, the greenhouse mission, would have a 100 percent chance of losing all the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,274:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: money associated with it. If anything, starting a rocket company had less than a 100 percent chance
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,278:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: of losing all the money associated with it. From my perspective, it was actually less risky than the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,278:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: first idea, which was just paying to send the greenhouse to Mars.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,279:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,279:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我的第一个想法，温室任务，将有 100% 的几率失去与之相关的所有资金。如果说有什么的话，创办一家火箭公司有不到 100% 的几率失去与之相关的所有资金。从我的角度来看，它实际上比第一个想法风险更小，第一个想法只是支付将温室送到火星的费用。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,280:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,280:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The likeliest outcome is I will lose all my money. But what
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,281:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,282:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s the alternative? No progress
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,282:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: in space exploration? We
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,283:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,283:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ve got to give this a shot, or we
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,283:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,284:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re stuck on Earth forever.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,284:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,285:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  最可能的结果是我会失去所有的钱。但替代方案是什么？太空探索没有进展？我们必须试一试，否则我们将永远被困在地球上。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,285:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,286:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I would not recommend a space company to first-time entrepreneurs. Space is advanced
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,287:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: entrepreneuring. You
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,287:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,289:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re better off starting something that requires little capital first. Space is
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,289:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: definitely a high-capital effort.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,290:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,290:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我不建议首次创业者创办太空公司。太空是高级创业。你最好先开始一些需要很少资本的事情。太空绝对是一项高资本努力。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,290:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,291:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,291:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,292:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: m a big believer in this: Don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,292:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,293:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t ask investors to invest their money if you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,293:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,294:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re not prepared to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,294:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: invest your money. It doesn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,295:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,296:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t seem right to me to ask other people to invest if you don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,296:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,296:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t also invest. I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,297:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,298:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: d rather lose my money than any of my friends
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,298:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,299:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  money or investors
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,299:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,300:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  money.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,300:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,301:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我非常相信这一点：如果你不准备投资自己的钱，就不要要求投资者投资他们的钱。如果你自己不投资，却要求其他人投资，这对我来说似乎不对。我宁愿失去我的钱，也不愿失去我朋友的钱或投资者的钱。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,301:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,302:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I didn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,302:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,305:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t even seek investor funding for the first three rounds of SpaceX because the first
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,305:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: thing investors want to ask you is, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,306:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,307:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Tell us about prior successes in this field. What can we compare
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,307:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: this to?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,308:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,309:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  When you have about zero in the success category and a cemetery full of failures, they
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,309:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,311:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,312:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: not too keen. Rockets are pretty far out of the comfort zone of most venture capitalists.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,313:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,313:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我甚至在 SpaceX 的前三轮都没有寻求投资者资金，因为投资者想问你的第一件事是，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,314:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,314:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 告诉我们这个领域以前的成功。我们可以把这个和什么比较？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,315:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,315:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 当你在成功类别中大约为零，失败类别中有一个墓地时，他们不太热衷。火箭相当远离大多数风险投资家的舒适区。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,316:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,328:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  We were able to get venture funding after we demonstrated we were almost able to get to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,333:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: orbit. Credit goes to Founders Fund, my compatriots from PayPal: Peter Thiel, Luke Nosek, Ken
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,333:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Howery, and the guys. They invested before we got to orbit, so credit to them.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,334:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,335:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  在我们证明我们几乎能够进入轨道后，我们获得了风险投资。功劳归于创始人基金，我在 PayPal 的同胞：彼得·蒂尔、卢克·诺塞克、肯·豪厄里和伙计们。他们在我们进入轨道之前投资，所以功劳归于他们。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,335:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,337:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Rockets are hard. I had never made physical stuff before SpaceX, let alone rockets. I had to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,338:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: show I could actually make stuff.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,339:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,339:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  火箭很难。在 SpaceX 之前，我从未制造过实物，更不用说火箭了。我必须证明我实际上可以制造东西。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,340:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,358:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Once we started building a space launch company, I predicated the strategic plan on a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,366:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: known market, something I know for a fact exists: the need to put small- to medium-sized satellites
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,368:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: into orbit. We served that need initially. With that as a base of revenue, we could eventually move
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,369:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: into the human transportation market.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,370:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,371:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  一旦我们开始建造一家太空发射公司，我就将战略计划基于一个已知的市场，我知道确实存在的东西：将中小型卫星送入轨道的需求。我们最初满足了这一需求。以此为收入基础，我们最终可以进入人类运输市场。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,371:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,377:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  First, we built an orbital launch vehicle. A high mass-efficiency launch vehicle targeted to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,378:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: solving the satellite delivery market. Our approach was to make this a solid, sound business from the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,379:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: beginning.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,379:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,379:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  首先，我们建造了一辆轨道发射车。一辆高质量效率的发射车，旨在解决卫星交付市场。我们的方法是从一开始就使其成为稳固、健全的业务。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,380:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,405:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The long-term aims of the company were always human transportation. But I think the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,420:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: smart strategy was to first go for cargo delivery, putting satellites into orbit. Our eventual upgrade
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,427:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: path was to build Starship, the successor to Saturn V rocket, a superheavy-lift vehicle that could be
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,427:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: used for setting up a moon base or doing a Mars mission. That is our holy grail objective.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,428:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,428:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  公司的长期目标一直是人类运输。但我认为明智的策略是首先进行货物交付，将卫星送入轨道。我们最终的升级路径是建造星舰，土星 V 火箭的继任者，一种超重型运载工具，可用于建立月球基地或执行火星任务。那是我们的圣杯目标。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,429:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ROCKETS FROM FIRST PRINCIPLES
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,429:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 从第一性原理出发的火箭
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,430:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,431:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I was trying to figure out if there was something fundamentally superexpensive about
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,431:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: rockets.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,431:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,432:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我试图找出火箭是否有本质上超级昂贵的东西。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,432:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,433:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Q: How did you determine whether your vision for SpaceX had the potential to succeed?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,433:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,434:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  问：你如何确定你对 SpaceX 的愿景是否有成功潜力？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,434:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,435:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  How could the Russians build low-cost rockets? It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,435:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,442:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s not like we drive Russian cars, fly
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,445:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Russian planes, or have Russian kitchen appliances. The US is a pretty competitive place, and we
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,445:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: should be able to build a cost-efficient launch vehicle.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,446:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,446:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  俄罗斯人如何建造低成本火箭？这不是说我们开俄罗斯汽车，坐俄罗斯飞机，或有俄罗斯厨房电器。美国是一个竞争激烈的地方，我们应该能够建造一个成本效益高的发射车。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,447:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,447:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I started reading quite a bit about rockets, trying to understand why they
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,448:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,448:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re so friggin
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,449:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,454:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,457:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: expensive. It used to be $60 million to build the Delta II. Now, a Delta II costs $100 million to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,457:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: make. Crazy number. Delta II is a relatively small rocket
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,458:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: !
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,459:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The bigger rockets are anywhere from
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,459:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: $200 to $400 million.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,460:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,460:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我开始读了很多关于火箭的书，试图理解为什么它们他妈的这么贵。过去建造 Delta II 需要 6000 万美元。现在，Delta II 的制造成本为 1 亿美元。疯狂的数字。Delta II 是一个相对较小的火箭！较大的火箭从 2 亿到 4 亿美元不等。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,461:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,461:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I was pretty mad, and when I get mad I try to reframe the problem.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,462:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,462:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我很生气，当我生气时，我试图重新构建问题。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,463:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,464:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I looked at the suppliers NASA had been relying on. With suppliers like Boeing and
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,464:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Lockheed, you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,465:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,465:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re screwed.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,466:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,466:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我看了 NASA 一直依赖的供应商。使用像波音和洛克希德这样的供应商，你完蛋了。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,467:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,475:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  One problem with those big aerospace firms is incredible aversion to risk. Even if better
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,478:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: technology is available, they still use legacy components, often ones that were developed in the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,479:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 1960s. Everyone is trying to optimize their ass-covering.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,479:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,480:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  那些大型航空航天公司的一个问题是对风险的难以置信的厌恶。即使有更好的技术可用，他们仍然使用传统组件，通常是那些在 1960 年代开发的。每个人都在试图优化他们的屁股覆盖。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,481:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,481:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Second, there
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,481:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,482:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s a tendency in big aerospace companies to outsource everything. That
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,483:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,503:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s been
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,521:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: trendy in many industries, but aerospace has done it to a ridiculous degree. They outsource to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,531:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: subcontractors, and then the subcontractors outsource to sub-subcontractors, and so on. You have to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,533:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: go four or five layers down to find somebody actually doing real work—cutting metal, shaping atoms.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,534:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Every level above that tacks on cost—it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,534:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,535:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s overhead to the fifth power. I began to understand why things
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,536:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: were so expensive.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,537:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,537:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  其次，大型航空航天公司有一种外包一切的趋势。这在许多行业都很流行，但航空航天已经做到了荒谬的程度。他们外包给分包商，然后分包商外包给次级分包商，依此类推。你必须向下走四到五层才能找到真正做实际工作的人——切割金属、塑造原子。上面的每一层都增加了成本——这是五次方的开销。我开始理解为什么东西这么贵。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,538:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,538:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Boeing and Lockheed just want their cost-plus gravy trains. When you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,539:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,540:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ve had success for
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,540:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: too long, you lose the desire to take risks. We can
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,541:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,542:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t get to Mars with that system. They have an
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,543:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: incentive to never finish the job.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,543:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,543:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  波音和洛克希德只想要他们的成本加成 gravy 火车。当你成功太久，你就失去了冒险的欲望。我们无法用那个系统到达火星。他们有动力永远不完成工作。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,544:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,544:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  There wasn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,544:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,554:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t really a good reason for rockets to be so expensive. Rockets could be a lot
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,558:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: cheaper even if they were still expendable. But, if one could make them reusable, like airplanes, then
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,559:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the cost of rocketry and space travel would both drop dramatically.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,559:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,559:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  火箭如此昂贵并没有真正的好理由。即使火箭仍然是一次性的，它们也可以便宜得多。但是，如果能让它们像飞机一样可重复使用，那么火箭和太空旅行的成本都会大幅下降。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,560:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,576:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I put together a feasibility study with a team of engineers who were involved in all major
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,583:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: launch vehicle developments over the last thirty years. We met over a number of Saturdays in early
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,584:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 2001 to find the smartest way to approach launch cost and reliability, and we came up with a default
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,584:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: design.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,585:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,585:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我与一个参与了过去三十年所有主要运载火箭开发的工程师团队一起进行了一项可行性研究。我们在 2001 年初的几个星期六会面，找出处理发射成本和可靠性的最聪明方法，我们想出了一个默认设计。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,586:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,594:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  It was fortunate timing. The feasibility study finished around the time we agreed to sell
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,596:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: PayPal to eBay. So coincidently with that sale, I moved down to Los Angeles, the biggest
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,597:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: concentration of aerospace talent in the world.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,597:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,598:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  时机很幸运。可行性研究在我们同意将 PayPal 出售给 eBay 时完成。所以与那次出售巧合的是，我搬到了洛杉矶，那是世界上最大的航空航天人才集中地。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,598:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,599:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Q: Did people give you a hard time for this? It seems like a lot of people were saying 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,599:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,601:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Elon is a software guy. Why is he working on hardware?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,601:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,601:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,602:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  问：人们为此为难你了吗？似乎很多人都在说
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,602:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,603:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 埃隆是个软件人。他为什么在做硬件？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,603:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,603:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,604:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  One hundred percent. A lot of the press from that time is still online. They kept calling me
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,605:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: an 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,605:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,606:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: internet guy
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,606:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,607:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  attempting to build a rocket company. We got ridiculed quite a bit.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,607:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,608:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  百分之百。当时的很多媒体报道仍然在线。他们一直称我为试图建立火箭公司的
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,608:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,608:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 互联网人
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,609:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,609:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 。我们被嘲笑了很多。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,610:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,610:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  It does sound absurd. 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,611:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,611:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Internet guy starts rocket company
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,611:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,612:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  doesn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,612:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,613:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t sound like a recipe for
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,614:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: success, frankly, so I don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,614:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,615:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t hold it against them. It does sound improbable, and I agreed. It was
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,616:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: improbable.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,616:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,616:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  这听起来确实荒谬。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,617:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,617:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 互联网人创办火箭公司
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,618:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,618:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 听起来不像成功的秘诀，坦率地说，所以我不怪他们。这听起来确实不太可能，我同意。那确实不太可能。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,619:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,619:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I didn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,620:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,620:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t study rocket science but have picked it up along the way.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,621:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,621:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我没有学习火箭科学，但一路上学会了。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,622:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,622:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I didn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,623:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,624:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t really know how to start a rocket company. The first three launches failed. I did not
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,624:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: hit the bull
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,625:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,625:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s-eye.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,626:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,626:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我真的不知道如何创办火箭公司。前三次发射都失败了。我没有击中靶心。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,627:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: KEEPING SPACEX ALIVE
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,627:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 维持 SpaceX 生存
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,628:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,629:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  SpaceX is in this for the long haul and, come hell or high water, we are going to make this
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,630:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: work.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,630:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,631:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  SpaceX 是为了长期而努力，无论遇到什么困难，我们都要让它成功。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,631:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,632:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I thought if we couldn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,632:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,633:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t get to orbit within three failures, we deserved to die. That was my
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,634:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: going-in proposition.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,634:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,634:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我想如果我们在三次失败内无法进入轨道，我们就该死。那是我的初始命题。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,635:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,648:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  In 2006, our first rocket landed a couple hundred yards away from the launch site in tiny
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,653:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: fragments. The second attempt failed too. But, we got further each time. In 2008, we had the third
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,654:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: failure in a row of the Falcon rocket. I had only budgeted for three attempts.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,654:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,654:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  2006 年，我们的第一枚火箭以微小碎片的形式降落在离发射场几百码的地方。第二次尝试也失败了。但是，我们每次都走得更远。2008 年，我们连续第三次猎鹰火箭失败。我只预算了三次尝试。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,655:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,655:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  That
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,655:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,659:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s when I split all the money I had left between Tesla and SpaceX. It was enough to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,659:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: afford a fourth launch at SpaceX, if we moved super fast.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,660:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,660:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  就在那时，我把剩下的所有钱分给了特斯拉和 SpaceX。这足以支付 SpaceX 的第四次发射，如果我们超级快地行动。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,661:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,661:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I collected everyone in the conference room and said, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,661:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,664:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: We have one last rocket. Get your
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,665:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: shit together, go back to the island, and launch it. You have six weeks.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,665:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,665:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,666:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我把所有人召集到会议室说，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,666:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,667:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 我们有最后一枚火箭。振作起来，回到岛上，发射它。你有六周时间。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,667:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,667:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,668:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Here was my email to the team: 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,668:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,679:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: There should be absolutely zero question that SpaceX
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,685:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: will prevail in reaching orbit and demonstrating reliable space transport. For my part, I will never
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,686:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: give up and I mean never. Thank you for your hard work. Now, on to flight four.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,686:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,686:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,687:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  这是我给团队的电子邮件：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,687:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,688:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  SpaceX 将在进入轨道和展示可靠太空运输方面取得胜利，这绝对没有任何疑问。就我而言，我永远不会放弃，我是说永远。感谢你的辛勤工作。现在，进入第四次飞行。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,688:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,689:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,689:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  If we didn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,689:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,690:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t succeed, we would be pointed to as a reason people shouldn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,690:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,692:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t even try these
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,692:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: things. We must do whatever is necessary to keep going.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,693:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,693:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  如果我们不成功，我们将被指出作为人们甚至不应该尝试这些事情的理由。我们必须做任何必要的事情来继续前进。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,694:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,694:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,695:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,695:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t ever give up. I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,695:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,696:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: d have to be dead or completely incapacitated.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,696:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,697:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我从不放弃。我必须是死了或完全丧失能力。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,697:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,699:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  It was an interesting exercise in karma. After I got ousted by the PayPal coup leaders, I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,699:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: could have said 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,700:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,700:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: You guys suck,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,701:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,701:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  but I didn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,701:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,702:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t. If I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,702:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,703:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: d done that, Founders Fund wouldn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,703:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,706:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t have come
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,707:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: through with an investment in SpaceX in 2008 and the company would be dead. Karma may be real.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,707:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,708:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  这是一个有趣的因果报应练习。在我被 PayPal 政变领导者赶下台后，我本可以说
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,708:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,709:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 你们这些家伙很烂，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,709:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,710:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 但我没有。如果我那样做了，创始人基金就不会在 2008 年投资 SpaceX，公司就会死掉。因果报应可能是真的。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,710:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,711:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  If the fourth launch hadn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,711:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,715:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t worked, that would have been curtains. I had no money left. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,716:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: was a pretty close thing. We would have joined the graveyard of prior rocket startups.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,716:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,717:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  如果第四次发射没有成功，那就完了。我没有剩下的钱了。那是相当接近的事情。我们将加入先前火箭初创公司的墓地。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,717:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,722:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I thought the odds of the fourth launch working were better than 50 percent. There was just
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,723:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: a little change in the thrust transient of the first-stage engine we couldn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,723:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,725:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t see on the ground. That
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,725:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: made the difference. Fortunately, the fourth SpaceX launch worked.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,726:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,727:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我认为第四次发射成功的几率超过 50%。第一级发动机的推力瞬变有一点变化，我们在地面上看不到。那就是区别。幸运的是，第四次 SpaceX 发射成功了。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,727:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,728:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  We almost went down as the company that made it to orbit, then died.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,728:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,729:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我们差点成为进入轨道然后死掉的公司。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,729:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,730:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  When it worked, my cortisol levels were clinically high. I couldn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,731:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,733:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t feel celebratory. There
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,733:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: was no jubilation. I was too stressed. Getting to orbit meant, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,734:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,734:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Okay, we
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,735:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,735:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re not going to die today.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,736:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,736:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,736:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: We
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,737:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,737:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ll live a little bit longer. I just felt relief.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,738:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,738:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  当它成功时，我的皮质醇水平临床高。我无法感到庆祝。没有欢欣鼓舞。我太有压力了。进入轨道意味着，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,739:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,739:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 好吧，我们今天不会死。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,740:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,740:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 我们会活得更久一点。我只是感到解脱。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,741:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,744:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  But it was short-lived. We were still in a tough position. It was not like we had customers
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,744:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: lined up. Even the fourth launch working wasn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,745:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,746:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t enough to succeed. We also needed a big contract
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,747:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: to keep us alive.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,747:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,748:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  但那是短暂的。我们仍然处于艰难的境地。不像我们有客户排队。即使第四次发射成功也不足以成功。我们还需要一份大合同来维持生存。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,748:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: LANDING NASA CONTRACTS
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,748:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 获得 NASA 合同
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,749:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,753:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  After the successful launch, as I was scrambling to fundraise for Tesla in 2008, NASA
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,754:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: called out of the blue to tell me SpaceX had won a contract. I couldn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,754:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,755:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t believe it. I screamed, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,755:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,755:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,756:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: LOVE NASA. YOU GUYS ROCK,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,756:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,758:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  then hung up. I called our president, Gwynne Shotwell, and
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,759:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: told her to immediately sign whatever deal NASA offered.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,759:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,760:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  成功发射后，当我在 2008 年为特斯拉筹款时，NASA 突然打电话告诉我 SpaceX 赢得了一份合同。我不敢相信。我尖叫道，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,760:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,760:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 我爱 NASA。你们太棒了，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,761:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,761:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 然后挂断了电话。我打电话给我们的总裁格温·肖特韦尔，告诉她立即签署 NASA 提供的任何协议。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,762:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,762:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  It felt like I had been blindfolded and taken out to the firing squad. Then they yelled, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,763:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,763:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Fire
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,763:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,764:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,764:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: and the guns just went 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,764:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,765:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: click.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,765:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,767:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  No bullets. Then they let me free. Sure, I was glad to be alive. But I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,767:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: was still pretty fucking nervous.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,768:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,768:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  感觉就像我被蒙上眼睛，被带到行刑队。然后他们喊道，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,768:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,769:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 开火
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,769:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,769:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ，枪只是
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,770:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,770:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 咔嗒
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,771:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,771:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 一声。没有子弹。然后他们让我自由。当然，我很高兴还活着。但我仍然他妈的很紧张。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,771:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,772:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  My estimate of success was not far off. We just made it by the skin of our teeth.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,772:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,773:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我对成功的估计相差不远。我们只是勉强成功。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,773:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,777:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  We had developed the Dragon spacecraft somewhat opportunistically. NASA announced
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,777:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: they were going to retire the space shuttle, and they didn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,778:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,792:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t have the budget to develop a new vehicle
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,800:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: with cargo transport capability to the space station. They put it out to bid for the first time in NASA
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,802:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: history. It was quite a big step, and we were lucky enough to win one of those contracts. Then, the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,802:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: other company wasn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,803:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,805:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t able to execute, and SpaceX ended up being the primary means of
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,806:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: transporting cargo to and from the space station.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,806:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,807:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我们在某种程度上机会主义地开发了龙飞船。NASA 宣布他们将退役航天飞机，他们没有预算开发具有货运能力的新航天器到空间站。他们在 NASA 历史上首次公开招标。这是相当大的一步，我们足够幸运赢得了其中一份合同。然后，另一家公司无法执行，SpaceX 最终成为向空间站运输货物的主要手段。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,807:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,810:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Our rocket ended up costing around $6 million, super low compared to other rockets in
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,810:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: that class, which were about $25 million. We
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,811:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,814:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re about a quarter of the price of Boeing or Lockheed.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,815:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Once it was reusable, payload delivery could be two orders of magnitude cheaper.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,815:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,816:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我们的火箭最终花费约 600 万美元，与该级别的其他火箭相比超低，那些火箭约为 2500 万美元。我们大约是波音或洛克希德价格的四分之一。一旦可重复使用，有效载荷交付可以便宜两个数量级。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,816:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,818:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  After we did the first two space station resupply missions, which thankfully both worked,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,818:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: NASA said, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,819:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,819:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: What about astronaut transport?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,820:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,825:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  They put out a big competition and awarded two
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,827:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: contracts for astronaut transport, one to Boeing and one to SpaceX. Now, we transport astronauts to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,828:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: and from the space station.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,828:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,829:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  在我们完成了前两次空间站补给任务后，谢天谢地都成功了，NASA 说，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,829:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,830:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 宇航员运输呢？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,830:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,831:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 他们进行了一场大竞赛，并授予了两份宇航员运输合同，一份给波音，一份给 SpaceX。现在，我们运送宇航员往返空间站。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,831:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: YOU HAVE TO BLOW THINGS UP
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,832:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 你必须炸毁东西
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,832:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,833:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The first goal is to make the damn thing work—we
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,834:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,834:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ll optimize it later.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,835:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,835:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  第一个目标是让该死的东西工作——我们稍后会优化它。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,836:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,836:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  We want to push the envelope. If you don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,837:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,839:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t push the envelope, you cannot achieve the goal
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,840:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: of a fully and rapidly reusable rocket with high payload. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,840:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,842:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s not possible. You have to go close to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,842:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the edge on margins.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,843:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,843:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我们想挑战极限。如果你不挑战极限，你就无法实现具有高有效载荷的完全快速可重复使用火箭的目标。这是不可能的。你必须在利润上接近边缘。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,844:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,853:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  We intentionally iterate the design of the Starship at SpaceX rapidly. This is a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,857:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: fundamentally different optimization for Starship versus a polar extreme like our Dragon capsule.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,858:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Since Dragon now carries crew, there can be no failures, ever. Everything
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,858:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,862:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s going to be tested. There
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,862:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: can never be a failure, ever, for any reason whatsoever. With human crew in a developed vehicle,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,863:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: we
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,863:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,864:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re in extreme conservatism mode.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,864:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,864:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我们有意在 SpaceX 快速迭代星舰的设计。这与像我们的龙飞船这样的极端情况有着根本不同的优化。由于龙飞船现在载有船员，永远不能有故障。一切都将经过测试。永远不能有任何原因的故障。有了载人飞船，我们处于极端保守模式。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,865:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,866:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Falcon is a little less conservative. It is possible for us to have, say, a failure with a booster
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,867:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: on landing. That
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,867:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,869:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s not the end of the world. Early Starship models were the polar opposite of
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,869:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Dragon. We were iterating rapidly to learn.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,870:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,870:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  猎鹰稍微不那么保守。我们可能会在着陆时助推器出现故障。那不是世界末日。早期的星舰模型与龙飞船截然相反。我们快速迭代以学习。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,870:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,871:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Q: Is that different from other space programs?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,871:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,872:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  问：这与其他太空项目不同吗？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,872:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,872:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  NASA
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,873:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,873:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s space shuttle had almost no iteration because there were people on board. You can
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,874:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,894:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t be blowing up shuttles. That lack of iteration was a problem. There were a lot of issues they were
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,904:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: aware of, but people were too afraid to make changes to a design that had already worked. There
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,907:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: was risk-reward asymmetry. If you make a change and something goes wrong, big punishment. If
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,907:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: you make a change and it goes right, small reward.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,908:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,908:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  NASA 的航天飞机几乎没有迭代，因为上面有人。你不能炸毁航天飞机。缺乏迭代是个问题。他们意识到很多问题，但人们太害怕对已经有效的设计进行更改。存在风险回报不对称。如果你做出改变而出错，大惩罚。如果你做出改变而成功，小奖励。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,909:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,916:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  They had seen the issues with the O-ring and the insulation coming off and hitting the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,917:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: wing before, but there had not been a catastrophe. They figured it was good enough because it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,918:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: worked before. But that
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,918:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,919:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s like Russian roulette: 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,919:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,920:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Look, I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,920:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,920:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ve pulled the trigger and I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,921:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,921:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: m fine.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,922:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,922:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,922:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  他们以前见过 O 形圈和绝缘材料脱落并撞击机翼的问题，但没有发生灾难。他们认为这足够好，因为它以前有效。但这就像俄罗斯轮盘赌：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,923:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,923:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 看，我扣动了扳机，我没事。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,924:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,924:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,924:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,925:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,930:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s hard to iterate when people are on board every mission. Starship does not have anyone
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,930:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: on board during early trials so we can blow things up, learn, and iterate. That
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,931:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,935:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s really helpful. To
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,937:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: improve safety, you need to fly a lot and have a lot of redundancy. So if you lose an engine on the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,937:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: booster, it doesn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,938:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,938:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t matter. Even losing multiple engines shouldn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,939:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,939:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t matter.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,940:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,940:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  当每次任务都有人 aboard 时很难迭代。星舰在早期试验期间没有人 aboard，所以我们可以炸毁东西，学习，并迭代。这真的很有帮助。为了提高安全性，你需要大量飞行并有很多冗余。所以如果你在助推器上失去一个引擎，没关系。即使失去多个引擎也不应该有关系。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,941:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,941:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  We don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,942:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,942:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t want to design to eliminate every risk. Otherwise, we will never get anywhere.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,943:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,943:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我们不想设计消除每一个风险。否则，我们永远不会到达任何地方。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,944:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,945:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Before every Starship launch, we go through the list of risks we predict, which we call the 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,945:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,945:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: risk list.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,946:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,947:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  If you look at various reasons why we blew up, none of the reasons they blew up were on
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,947:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: our 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,948:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,948:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: risk list.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,949:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,949:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  There
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,950:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,952:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s a crazy amount of new technology, all evolving simultaneously. We need
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,953:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: time and trials to iron out the unknown unknowns.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,953:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,954:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  在每次星舰发射之前，我们会查看我们预测的风险列表，我们称之为
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,954:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,955:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 风险列表
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,955:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,956:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 。如果你看看我们爆炸的各种原因，他们爆炸的原因都不在我们的
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,956:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,957:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 风险列表
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,957:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,958:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 上。有大量的新技术，都在同时演变。我们需要时间和试验来解决未知的未知。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,958:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,959:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Q: What is the big-picture vision SpaceX is iterating toward?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,959:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,960:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  问：SpaceX 迭代的大局愿景是什么？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,960:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,961:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The overarching optimization is: 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,961:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,962:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: What is the fastest time to a city on Mars?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,963:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,965:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Then subset →
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,965:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: fastest time to a fully usable rocket. And subset → fastest time to orbit.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,966:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,966:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  总体优化是：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,967:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,967:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 到火星城市的最快时间是什么？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,968:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,968:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 然后子集→完全可用火箭的最快时间。然后子集→进入轨道的最快时间。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,969:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,970:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Initial production was simply a learning exercise. None of the initial designs will be long
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,971:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: term. We
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,971:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,974:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re just trying to learn in the shortest period of time. The early Starship assembly yard
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,975:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: looked like a garage shop, to be frank. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,975:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,978:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s weird—we have superadvanced technology being built in a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,978:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: tent in a parking lot. Early versions of Starship didn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,979:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,979:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t even have doors. We didn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,980:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,986:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t need doors. We did
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,990:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: need to be superfocused on getting to orbit. Then superfocused on getting the ship back. Doors were
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,990:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: just unnecessary complexity. The first ten ships (or more) we won
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,990:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,991:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t get back from orbit. We
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,991:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: probably won
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,992:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,992:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t be flying them again. Maybe once or twice—if we
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,992:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,993:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re lucky.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,993:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,994:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  最初的生产只是一个学习练习。任何初始设计都不会是长期的。我们只是试图在最短的时间内学习。早期的星舰装配场看起来像一个车库店，坦率地说。这很奇怪——我们有超级先进的技术在一个停车场的帐篷里建造。早期版本的星舰甚至没有门。我们不需要门。我们确实需要超级专注于进入轨道。然后超级专注于让飞船回来。门只是不必要的复杂性。前十艘船（或更多）我们不会从轨道返回。我们可能不会再飞它们。也许一两次——如果我们幸运的话。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,994:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,994:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Eliminate what isn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,995:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,995:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t necessary to solve the key problem.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,996:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,996:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  消除解决关键问题不必要的内容。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,996:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: BUILDING THE JUST BARELY POSSIBLE
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,997:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 建造勉强可能的东西
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,997:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,998:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I was told many times rocket reusability was impossible.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,998:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,999:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我多次被告知火箭可重复使用是不可能的。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:03:59,999:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,000:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  One of the hardest engineering problems known to man is making a reusable orbital rocket.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,000:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,001:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  人类已知的最困难的工程问题之一是制造可重复使用的轨道火箭。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,001:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,002:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  We have reusability in bicycles, cars, and airplanes. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,002:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,013:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s bizarre to not have reusability in
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,019:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: another form of transport. It would be insane to chuck a boat away after every trip. Getting one trip
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,020:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: every four days would not cut it in a car. But this is how rockets have worked thus far.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,021:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,021:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我们在自行车、汽车和飞机上有可重复使用性。在另一种交通工具中没有可重复使用性是很奇怪的。每次旅行后扔掉一艘船是疯狂的。每四天一次旅行在汽车中行不通。但这就是火箭迄今为止的工作方式。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,021:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,024:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The design goal is immediate reflight. Refill propellants and go again, just like any other
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,024:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: mode of transport. This is gigantic.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,025:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,025:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  设计目标是立即再次飞行。重新填充推进剂并再次出发，就像任何其他交通工具一样。这是巨大的。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,025:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,028:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Getting to orbit was solved in the 1950s. The math clearly demonstrates there is no point in
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,029:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: another expendable rocket; you have to achieve reusability.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,029:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,030:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  进入轨道在 1950 年代就解决了。数学清楚地表明，另一枚一次性火箭没有意义；你必须实现可重复使用性。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,030:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,031:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,031:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,033:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s not like other rocket scientists were huge idiots who wanted to throw their rockets away
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,033:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: all the time. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,034:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,035:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s hard to make something like this. Nobody has ever succeeded, and for a good
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,035:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: reason. Earth
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,036:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,037:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s gravity is heavy. On Mars this would be no problem. Moon, piece of cake. On Earth,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,038:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: fucking hard. Just barely possible.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,038:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,039:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  这不是说其他火箭科学家是想要一直扔掉火箭的巨大白痴。制造这样的东西很难。没有人成功过，这是有充分理由的。地球的重力很重。在火星上这不成问题。月球，小菜一碟。在地球上，他妈的难。只是勉强可能。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,039:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,041:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  A fully reusable orbital system would be one of the biggest breakthroughs in the history of
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,041:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: humanity. That
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,042:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,042:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s why it hurts my brain. We
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,043:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,046:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re just a bunch of monkeys. How did we even get this
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,047:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: far? It beats me. We were swinging through the trees eating bananas not long ago.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,047:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,048:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  完全可重复使用的轨道系统将是人类历史上最大的突破之一。这就是为什么它让我头疼。我们只是一群猴子。我们是怎么走到这一步的？这难倒我了。不久前我们还在树林里荡秋千吃香蕉。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,048:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,051:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Can you imagine if human civilization continued at the current pace of technological
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,052:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: advancement for another million years? Where would we be?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,053:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,053:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  你能想象如果人类文明以当前的技术进步速度再持续一百万年吗？我们会在哪里？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,054:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,054:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I told my team, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,055:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,060:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Imagine there was a pallet of cash plummeting through the atmosphere
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,061:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: and it was going to burn up and smash into tiny pieces. Would you try to save it? You probably
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,062:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: would.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,062:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,063:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,063:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我告诉我的团队，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,064:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,064:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 想象有一托盘现金穿过大气层坠落，它将燃烧并粉碎成小块。你会试图拯救它吗？你可能会。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,065:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,065:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,073:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  When people tried to make a reusable system before, they would conclude success was not
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,075:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: one of the possible outcomes. In government programs, of course, the program would still continue
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,075:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: for quite some time. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,075:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,076:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s funny but it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,076:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,076:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s true.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,076:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,077:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  当人们以前试图制造可重复使用系统时，他们会得出结论成功不是可能的结果之一。在政府项目中，当然，项目仍会继续相当长的时间。这很有趣但这是真的。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,077:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,089:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The space shuttle attempted some level of reusability, but it ended up costing more per
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,094:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: flight than an expendable vehicle of equivalent capability. For a long time, people pointed to the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,094:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: space shuttle as an example of why attempting reusability was dumb. But you can
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,095:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,096:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t take a single
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,096:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: example and make an entire theory out of it.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,097:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,097:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  航天飞机尝试了某种程度的可重复使用性，但最终每次飞行的成本比同等能力的一次性飞行器更高。很长一段时间，人们以航天飞机为例说明为什么尝试可重复使用性是愚蠢的。但你不能拿一个例子并从中得出整个理论。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,098:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,098:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I wasn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,098:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,111:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t sure if it was possible when we started SpaceX, but after a few years of work I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,116:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: became convinced. Full and rapid reuse is possible. It is possible to make this work, and that gave
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,116:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: me hope. Of course, just because something is possible does not mean it will occur.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,117:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,117:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  当我们创办 SpaceX 时，我不确定这是否可能，但经过几年的工作后，我确信了。完全快速可重复使用是可能的。这是可能实现的，这给了我希望。当然，仅仅因为某事可能并不意味着它会发生。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,118:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,121:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The first step is to establish that something is possible, then the probability it will occur. In
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,122:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: no prior design was full reusability one of the possible outcomes.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,122:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,123:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  第一步是确定某事是可能的，然后是它发生的概率。在以前的任何设计中，完全可重复使用性都不是可能的结果之一。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,123:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,124:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  SpaceX
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,124:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,153:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s Falcon 9 was the first rocket with any reusability. We bring the boosters back
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,171:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: and refly them. Only the upper stage is expended. Falcon 9 is not rapidly reusable because most
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,178:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: boosters land on a ship in the ocean. It takes a while to bring it back, fuel, and reuse it. Falcon 9 first
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,179:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: had reusability measured in months, then weeks, and now finally days. But, the efficiency is limited.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,180:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: We can
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,180:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,180:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t bring it lower than several days.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,181:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,182:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  SpaceX 的猎鹰 9 号是第一枚具有任何可重复使用性的火箭。我们将助推器带回并重新飞行它们。只有上面级是一次性的。猎鹰 9 号不是快速可重复使用的，因为大多数助推器降落在海洋中的一艘船上。需要一段时间才能把它带回来，加油，并重新使用它。猎鹰 9 号最初的可重复使用性以月为单位，然后是周，现在终于到天。但是，效率是有限的。我们不能把它降到几天以下。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,182:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,195:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Knock on wood, Falcon 9 is the most reliable rocket in the world and launches about every
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,200:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: two to three days. Every one has come home safely, which is the most important thing. We learned a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,201:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: tremendous amount from the Falcon program that fed into the Starship program. We wouldn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,202:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,203:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t have
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,203:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: been able to make Starship without the benefit of Falcon 9.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,204:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,204:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  敲木头，猎鹰 9 号是世界上最可靠的火箭，大约每两到三天发射一次。每一个都安全回家，这是最重要的事情。我们从猎鹰项目中学到了大量知识，这些知识进入了星舰项目。如果没有猎鹰 9 号的好处，我们将无法制造星舰。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,205:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,206:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Nobody thought this was possible. But we
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,206:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,207:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re not breaking any laws of physics, so we knew
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,207:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: it was possible.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,208:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,208:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  没有人认为这是可能的。但我们没有违反任何物理定律，所以我们知道这是可能的。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,209:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,209:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Starship is the largest flying object of any kind. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,210:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,216:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s five thousand tons at liftoff, much
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,219:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: heavier than any other aircraft, ever. The body diameter is nine meters (roughly fifty feet). It will get
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,220:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: taller with newer versions too. And it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,220:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,221:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s going straight up; aircraft don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,221:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,222:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t go straight up. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,222:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,224:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s an insanely
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,225:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: gigantic thing, twice the size of Saturn V, previously the largest rocket ever built.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,225:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,226:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  星舰是任何种类的最大飞行物。它在起飞时重达五千吨，比以往任何飞机都重得多。主体直径为九米（约 50 英尺）。它也会随着新版本变得更高。它是直着向上的；飞机不会直着向上。这是一个疯狂巨大的东西，是土星 V 的两倍大，土星 V 以前是建造过的最大火箭。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,227:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,231:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  There could be other solutions too, but this will work. The first order of business was to get
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,232:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: one that works. Now we optimize. Full and rapid reusability will work. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,232:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,235:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s just a question of how
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,236:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: many attempts we need to make it work, and then make it work really well.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,236:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,237:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  可能还有其他解决方案，但这个会有效。首要任务是得到一个有效的。现在我们优化。完全快速可重复使用将有效。这只是我们需要多少次尝试才能让它工作，然后让它工作得非常好的问题。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,237:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,246:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  It has to be true reuse, which means rapid and complete reuse. The problem with the space
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,249:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: shuttle was only a portion of the system came back, and the reusable parts were incredibly difficult
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,249:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: to refurbish. Reuse matters more if it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,250:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,252:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s rapid and complete—if the only thing we do between flights is
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,252:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: maintenance and refuel, like an airplane.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,253:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,253:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  它必须是真正的重复使用，这意味着快速和完全的重复使用。航天飞机的问题是只有系统的一部分回来，可重复使用的部件非常难以翻新。如果快速和完全，重复使用更重要——如果我们在飞行之间唯一做的事情是维护和加油，就像飞机一样。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,254:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,257:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  If there is no major work required between flights, then the cost of a flight approaches the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,257:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: cost of propellant. Nearly 80 percent of Starship
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,258:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,263:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s propellant is liquid oxygen, and a little over 20
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,265:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: percent methane, which are both very low-cost fuels. The fuel cost of a flight is maybe a million
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,265:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: dollars or less.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,265:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,266:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  如果飞行之间不需要主要工作，那么飞行成本接近推进剂成本。星舰的推进剂近 80% 是液氧，略超过 20% 是甲烷，两者都是成本非常低的燃料。一次飞行的燃料成本可能是一百万美元或更少。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,266:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,267:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Full and rapid reusability is the holy grail of rocketry because then you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,267:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,268:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re only constrained
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,268:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: by propellant costs.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,268:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,269:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  完全快速可重复使用是火箭学的圣杯，因为那样你只受推进剂成本的限制。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,269:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,270:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Q: What made you remove the landing legs?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,270:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,270:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  问：是什么让你移除着陆腿？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,271:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,272:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  We fight to save mass constantly, especially with the reusable upper stage, where nobody
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,272:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: has ever succeeded.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,273:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,273:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我们不断争取节省质量，特别是对于可重复使用的上面级，那里没有人成功过。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,273:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,283:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Again here, we try to think in the limit of physics. The problem with landing legs is they
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,286:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: add mass, we have to protect them during reentry, and we have to get a giant rocket from wherever
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,286:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: it landed back onto the launch stand. That
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,287:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,287:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s tricky. I was trying to think of the limit. What
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,288:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,288:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,289:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: fastest way to achieve reusability?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,289:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,290:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  再次在这里，我们试图在物理极限内思考。着陆腿的问题是它们增加了质量，我们必须在再入期间保护它们，我们必须将一枚巨大的火箭从它降落的任何地方移回发射台。这很棘手。我试图思考极限。实现可重复使用性的最快方法是什么？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,290:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,292:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  It would be to land on the launch stand. Why not just have it land on the arms of the tower
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,292:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: it launches from?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,292:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,293:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  那将是降落在发射台上。为什么不让它降落在它发射的塔的臂上呢？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,293:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,326:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  This is the best-case outcome for rapid reuse. It gets caught by the same arms that placed it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,346:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: in the launch ring. In principle, the superheavy booster can be reflown within an hour of landing. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,354:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: comes back in about five minutes one way and then it gets caught by the tower arms, placed back in
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,355:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the launch mount, and then we refill propellant in about thirty to forty minutes and place a ship on
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,356:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: top of it.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,356:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,357:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  这是快速重复使用的最佳情况结果。它被放置它在发射环中的同一臂抓住。原则上，超重型助推器可以在着陆后一小时内重新飞行。它大约五分钟回来，然后被塔臂抓住，放回发射架，然后我们在大约三十到四十分钟内重新填充推进剂，并在其顶部放置一艘飞船。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,357:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,364:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  When we first talked about it, it sounded batshit crazy. To custom-build a giant tower to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,365:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: catch the heaviest flying object ever made with mechanical arms. Pluck it out of the air. But we did
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,366:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: it.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,366:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,367:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  当我们第一次谈论它时，听起来疯狂至极。定制建造一座巨大的塔，用机械臂抓住有史以来最重的飞行物。从空中摘下它。但我们做到了。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,367:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,368:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,368:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,370:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s an epic sight: giant robot arms catching a giant rocket. This is much more efficient than
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,371:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: having landing legs on the rocket itself.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,371:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,372:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  这是一个史诗般的景象：巨大的机器人手臂抓住一枚巨大的火箭。这比在火箭本身上有着陆腿要高效得多。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,372:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,373:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I call it rapidly reusable, reliable rockets. RRRR. Space pirates.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,374:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,374:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我称之为快速可重复使用、可靠的火箭。RRRR。太空海盗。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,375:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: OPTIMIZING FOR MASS TO MARS
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,375:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 优化火星质量
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,376:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,378:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The thing we optimize for at SpaceX is cost per ton to orbit. When the goal is low cost per
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,379:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ton of payload to orbit, you can
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,380:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,380:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t cheat.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,380:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,381:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我们在 SpaceX 优化的是每吨进入轨道的成本。当目标是每吨有效载荷进入轨道的低成本时，你不能作弊。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,381:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,382:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  All early rockets were a test program. We expected them to explode. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,382:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,382:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s weird if they don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,383:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,386:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,387:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: explode, frankly. To get a lot of payload to orbit at low cost, you have to run everything close to the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,387:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: edge.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,388:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,388:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  所有早期火箭都是测试项目。我们期望它们爆炸。坦率地说，如果它们不爆炸，那很奇怪。要以低成本将大量有效载荷送入轨道，你必须在边缘附近运行一切。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,388:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,391:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  To get a meaningful payload to orbit, scale is important. We need to make things big.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,391:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: There is value to scale here. You don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,392:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,419:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t see everything shipped by small pickup trucks; you see semi
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,437:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: trailers. You see giant ocean cargo ships, not a bunch of small boats with outboard motors. Scale has
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,445:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: value in itself. For example, the same computer that controls a tiny rocket controls the big rocket.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,447:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The percentage weight of the electronics is significant in a small rocket but becomes vanishingly
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,447:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: small in a big rocket.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,448:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,448:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  要将有意义的有效载荷送入轨道，规模很重要。我们需要把事情做大。规模在这里有价值。你不会看到所有东西都用小型皮卡车运输；你会看到半挂车。你会看到巨大的海洋货船，而不是一堆带有舷外发动机的小船。规模本身就有价值。例如，控制小型火箭的计算机也控制大型火箭。电子设备在小火箭中的重量百分比很大，但在大火箭中变得微乎其微。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,449:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,450:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The focus is to minimize cost per ton of payload to orbit, the surface of the moon, or Mars.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,450:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,450:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,454:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ll give you a sense of just how much we need to improve it. Right now, the cost per landed ton to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,455:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the surface of Mars is more than a billion dollars. You can
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,455:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,458:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t count the heat shield, parachute, or
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,459:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: landing systems—only the useful stuff. In the case of the Mars rovers, it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,459:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,467:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s really just the rover. That is
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,471:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the useful thing. The rover weighs about a ton and costs a billion dollars to get to Mars. So currently
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,471:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: it costs roughly a billion dollars per ton to Mars.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,472:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,473:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  重点是尽量减少每吨有效载荷进入轨道、月球表面或火星的成本。我会让你了解我们需要改进多少。目前，每吨着陆火星表面的成本超过 10 亿美元。你不能计算隔热罩、降落伞或着陆系统——只有有用的东西。在火星车的情况下，真的只是火星车。那是有用的东西。火星车重约一吨，花费 10 亿美元到达火星。所以目前每吨到火星的成本大约是 10 亿美元。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,473:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,481:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  To build a self-sustaining city on Mars, that cost will have to be less than one hundred
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,483:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: thousand dollars a ton. That would be ten thousand times better than the current state of the art, to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,483:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: put things into perspective.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,484:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,484:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  要在火星上建立一个自给自足的城市，成本必须低于每吨 10 万美元。这将比当前技术水平好一万倍，以正确看待事物。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,485:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,485:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  That
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,486:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,487:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s how much improvement is needed. Not a 10,000 percent increase, a 10,000-times
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,487:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: increase. That
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,487:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,491:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s what Starship is intended to do: be ten thousand times better than the current state of
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,492:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the art. Orders and orders and orders of magnitude better. But, we
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,492:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,493:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re not breaking any laws of
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,494:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: physics. This is possible.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,494:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,495:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  这就是需要多少改进。不是 10,000% 的增长，而是 10,000 倍的增长。这就是星舰打算做的：比当前技术水平好一万倍。数量级好得多。但是，我们没有违反任何物理定律。这是可能的。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,495:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,496:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  When we started the Starship design it seemed utterly insane. Now it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,496:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,497:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s gone from utterly
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,498:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: insane to merely late.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,498:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,499:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  当我们开始星舰设计时，它看起来完全疯狂。现在它从完全疯狂变成了只是迟到。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,499:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,500:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  With full reusability, Starship 3 will cost significantly less per flight than tiny Falcon 1.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,501:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: That
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,501:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,536:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s the difference between a fully reusable rocket and an expendable rocket. The fully reusable
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,557:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: rocket with low-cost propellant actually costs less than a tiny expendable rocket. By analogy, the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,568:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: cost of flying a 747 is obviously much less than a small airplane that gets thrown away. Falcon 1
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,570:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: gets about half a ton to orbit. The Starship 3 will send four hundred times more payload for less than
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,571:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the cost of a Falcon 1. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,571:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,572:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s mind-boggling that the giant thing can cost so much less than the small
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,573:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: thing.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,573:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,574:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  有了完全可重复使用性，星舰 3 号的每次飞行成本将显著低于小型猎鹰 1 号。那是完全可重复使用火箭和一次性火箭之间的区别。具有低成本推进剂的完全可重复使用火箭实际上比小型一次性火箭成本更低。类比来说，驾驶 747 的成本显然比被扔掉的小型飞机要少得多。猎鹰 1 号将约半吨送入轨道。星舰 3 号将以低于猎鹰 1 号的成本发送四百倍以上的有效载荷。令人难以置信的是，巨大的东西成本可以比小东西低这么多。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,574:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,582:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  A lot of people talk a lot about the number of launches to orbit per year, but this is not
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,584:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: really what matters. What really matters is the total useful payload to orbit per year. If these were
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,584:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ocean ships, you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,585:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,585:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: d be comparing a dinghy to a supertanker. They
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,586:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,586:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re not the same.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,587:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,587:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  很多人谈论每年进入轨道的发射次数，但这不是真正重要的。真正重要的是每年进入轨道的总有效载荷。如果这些是海洋船只，你将在比较一艘小艇和一艘超级油轮。它们不一样。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,588:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,588:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  There must be things you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,589:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,589:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re excited about, that you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,590:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,592:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re glad to be alive for. For me, this is
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,593:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the most important reason to pursue the establishment of life on Mars.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,594:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,595:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  必须有你感到兴奋的事情，你很高兴为之活着。对我来说，这是追求在火星上建立生命的最重要原因。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,595:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,595:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  There are various 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,596:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,596:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: great filters
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,596:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,597:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  that have the potential to end civilizations. One of the 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,597:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,597:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: great filters
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,598:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,601:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  to pass is whether we become a multiplanet species. Will humanity be one of those
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,601:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: species that passes the great filter of going beyond one planet?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,602:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,602:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  有各种
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,602:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,603:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 大过滤器
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,603:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,603:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 有可能终结文明。要通过的
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,604:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,604:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 大过滤器
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,604:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,605:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 之一是我们是否成为一个多行星物种。人类会成为那些通过超越一个星球的大过滤器的物种之一吗？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,605:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,609:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  To become multiplanetary, the breakthrough we need to create is a rapidly reusable
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,609:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: interplanetary transport system. This is right on the edge of impossible.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,610:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,610:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  要成为多行星的，我们需要创造的突破是一个快速可重复使用的星际运输系统。这正好在不可能边缘。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,610:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,611:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  That
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,611:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,612:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s the breakthrough SpaceX is really trying to achieve. What we
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,612:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,612:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ve done so far is good;
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,613:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,613:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,614:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s better. But it has been evolutionary—not yet revolutionary. We need the revolutionary thing to work.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,614:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,615:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  那是 SpaceX 真正试图实现的突破。我们迄今为止所做的很好；它更好。但它一直是进化的——还不是革命性的。我们需要革命性的东西起作用。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,615:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: PART IV: ON BEHALF OF HUMANITY
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,616:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 第四部分：为了人类
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,616:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,617:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  There is something special—far more rewarding than money—about working with an epic team to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,618:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: make breakthroughs.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,618:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,619:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  与一个史诗般的团队合作取得突破有一些特别的东西——远比金钱更有回报。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,619:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: PART IV: ON BEHALF OF HUMANITY
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,620:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 第四部分：为了人类
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,620:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,621:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  There is something special—far more rewarding than money—about working with an epic team to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,622:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: make breakthroughs.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,622:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,623:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  与一个史诗般的团队合作取得突破有一些特别的东西——远比金钱更有回报。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,623:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: BUILDING OUR FUTURE
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,624:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 建设我们的未来
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,624:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,624:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I can
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,625:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,627:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t emphasize this enough: As long as we push hard and are not complacent, the future
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,627:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: is going to be great.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,628:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,628:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我再怎么强调也不为过：只要我们努力推进而不自满，未来将会是美好的。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,629:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Companies Are Philanthropy
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,629:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 公司就是慈善
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,629:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,634:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  If you care about the reality of goodness instead of the perception of it, philanthropy is
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,635:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: extremely difficult. If philanthropy is acting from a love of humanity—my companies are philanthropy.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,636:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,636:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  如果你关心善良的实质而不是表象，慈善是极其困难的。如果慈善是出于对人类的热爱而行动——我的公司就是慈善。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,637:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,637:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Q: What do you say to people who criticize you for not 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,638:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,638:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: having your name on a hospital
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,639:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: wing
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,639:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,639:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  or making other nonprofit donations?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,640:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,640:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  问：你如何回应那些批评你没有
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,640:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,641:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 在医院侧楼留下你的名字
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,641:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,641:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 或进行其他非营利捐赠的人？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,642:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,642:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I do have a small foundation. I am giving some money away. But generally, if there
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,643:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,646:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,647:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: way to fix something within the market system, building a company is the better way to do it.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,648:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Sometimes there isn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,648:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,648:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t or there are complications to it.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,649:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,649:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我确实有一个小基金会。我在捐出一些钱。但一般来说，如果有一种方法可以在市场体系内解决问题，建立公司是更好的方式。有时没有，或者有并发症。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,649:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,650:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  If it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,650:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,651:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s possible to solve a problem with a profitable venture then that
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,651:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,657:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s the best thing to do.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,660:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: In the grand scheme of things, there are a few failures in the market that have to be addressed with a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,660:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: nonprofit. There are some, but not many.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,660:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,661:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  如果有可能通过盈利企业解决问题，那是最好的做法。从大局来看，市场中有一些失败必须通过非营利组织来解决。有一些，但不多。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,661:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,696:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  SpaceX, Tesla, Neuralink, and the Boring Company are philanthropy. SpaceX is trying to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,720:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ensure the long-term survival of humanity as a multiple-planet species. We also provide global
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,732:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: internet through Starlink. That is love of humanity. Tesla is accelerating sustainable energy. This is a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,737:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: love-based mission. Neuralink is trying to help solve brain injuries and the existential risk of AI.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,738:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: That is love of humanity. The Boring Company is trying to save people
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,738:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,740:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s time by solving traffic,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,740:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: which is hell for most people. That is also love of humanity.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,741:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,742:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  SpaceX、特斯拉、Neuralink 和无聊公司都是慈善。SpaceX 正试图确保人类作为多行星物种的长期生存。我们还通过星链提供全球互联网。那是对人类的爱。特斯拉正在加速可持续能源。这是一个基于爱的使命。Neuralink 正试图帮助解决脑损伤和 AI 的生存风险。那是对人类的爱。无聊公司正试图通过解决交通来节省人们的时间，这对大多数人来说是地狱。那也是对人类的爱。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,742:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,759:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  My fundamental intent is to improve the probability of the future being good. SpaceX and
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,766:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Tesla will do more good for humanity than anything I could do with philanthropy. It is difficult to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,768:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: give away money effectively if you care about the money actually doing good, not merely having
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,769:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the perception of doing good.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,769:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,770:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我的根本意图是提高未来变好的概率。SpaceX 和特斯拉将为人类做更多好事，比我用慈善做的任何事情都多。如果你关心钱实际上做好事，而不仅仅是有做好事的表象，那么有效地捐钱是困难的。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,770:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,782:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Tesla sells twice as many electric vehicles as the rest of electric car makers in the United
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,786:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: States combined. Tesla has done more to help the environment than all other companies combined.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,787:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Therefore, it would be fair to say as a leader of that company I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,787:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,791:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ve done more for the environment
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,792:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: than any other single human on Earth. I care about the reality of goodness, not the perception of it.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,792:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,793:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  特斯拉销售的电动汽车是美国其他电动汽车制造商总和的两倍。特斯拉为帮助环境所做的贡献比所有其他公司的总和还要多。因此，公平地说，作为那家公司的领导者，我为环境所做的贡献比地球上任何其他人多。我关心善良的实质，而不是表象。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,794:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,795:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  What I see all over the place is people who care about looking good while doing evil. Fuck
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,795:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: them.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,795:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,796:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我到处看到的是那些关心在做恶事时看起来很好的人。去他们的。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,796:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,797:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I care about reality. Perception be damned.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,797:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,798:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我关心实质。表象见鬼去吧。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,798:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Companies Create Wealth for All
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,799:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 公司为所有人创造财富
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,800:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,800:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,801:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,803:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t disrupt something for the sake of disrupting it. My focus is making a product that
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,803:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: improves quality of life for people.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,804:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,804:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我不会为了颠覆而颠覆。我的重点是制造改善人们生活质量的产品。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,805:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,829:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  If the output is more valuable than the inputs, that creates a profit. Profit shows you have a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,841:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: useful company. But in a high-growth scenario, you need a lot more inputs for future output, so for a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,845:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: while you have negative cash flow and lack of profitability, which we had early on at Tesla. In the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,846:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: long term, of course, that has to be fixed. There can
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,846:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,847:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t be a negative cash flow in the long term.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,847:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,848:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  如果产出比投入更有价值，那就会产生利润。利润表明你有一家有用的公司。但在高增长情景下，你需要更多投入来获得未来产出，所以一段时间内你有负现金流和缺乏盈利能力，我们在特斯拉早期就是这样。从长远来看，当然，那必须得到纠正。长期内不能有负现金流。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,848:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,858:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  If you create a company that produces products and services better than what existed
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,861:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: before, wealth is created. If you have some ownership in that company, wealth accrues to you.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,862:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Doing good work gives you the right to allocate more capital.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,862:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,863:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  如果你创建一家生产比以前更好的产品和服务的公司，财富就创造了。如果你在那家公司有一些所有权，财富就会累积给你。做好工作给你分配更多资本的权利。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,863:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,864:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Sometimes people equate wealth with consumption, but they
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,864:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,866:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re obviously not the same
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,866:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: thing. Consumption is fun, but capital allocation is a job.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,866:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,867:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  有时人们将财富与消费等同起来，但它们显然不是同一件事。消费很有趣，但资本分配是一项工作。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,867:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,870:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  If people want to get upset about something, excess consumption is more reasonable than
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,871:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: being upset about someone having a high net worth.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,871:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,871:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  如果人们想对某事感到不安，过度消费比因某人拥有高净值而感到不安更合理。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,872:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,872:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Warren Buffett has a high net worth because he
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,873:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,873:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s doing a useful job allocating capital for
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,874:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the economy. He
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,874:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,875:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s very skilled at it, and he should probably keep doing it. But he is not engaged in
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,876:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: insane, conspicuous consumption.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,876:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,877:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  沃伦·巴菲特拥有高净值，因为他正在为经济分配资本做有用的工作。他非常擅长这个，他应该继续这样做。但他没有参与疯狂的、炫耀性的消费。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,877:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,888:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Warren Buffett sits there and reads all these super boring annual reports. Does anybody
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,893:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: want that job? He is constantly reading tedious annual reports of companies, including the minutiae
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,894:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: of accounting and deciding whether to allocate capital into Coke or Pepsi. I don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,895:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,899:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t want that job.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,899:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,900:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  沃伦·巴菲特坐在那里阅读所有这些超级无聊的年度报告。有人想要那份工作吗？他不断阅读公司的乏味年度报告，包括会计细节，并决定是否将资本分配到可口可乐或百事可乐。我不想要那份工作。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,900:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,900:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,901:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,903:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: m not claiming I have no money. But when people hear a big number for my net worth,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,904:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: they think I have that much cash, and I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,904:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,911:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: m sitting on the cash doing nothing, hoarding resources. No,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,913:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: that value is the stock of these companies. Net worth just calculates my ownership of these
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,914:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: companies, if you add them up. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,914:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,915:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s not as though I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,915:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,916:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ve got billions of dollars sitting in a bank
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,916:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: account.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,917:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,917:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我不是说我没有钱。但当人们听到我的净值是一个大数字时，他们认为我有那么多现金，我坐在现金上无所事事，囤积资源。不，那个价值是这些公司的股票。净值只是计算我对这些公司的所有权，如果你把它们加起来。不是好像我有数十亿美元坐在银行账户里。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,918:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,918:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Just as my money was the first into Tesla, it will be the last out.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,919:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,919:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  就像我的钱是最早进入特斯拉的，它也将是最后出来的。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,920:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,920:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The alternative to keeping the stock would be to say, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,921:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,921:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Okay, let
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,922:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,922:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s give the stock to the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,923:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: government or someone else.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,923:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,924:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Then the government would control the companies and be running
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,925:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: things.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,925:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,926:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  保留股票的替代方案是说，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,926:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,926:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 好吧，让我们把股票给政府或其他人。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,927:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,927:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 然后政府将控制公司并管理事情。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,928:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,932:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  A lot of the push for higher government involvement or expropriation of assets to the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,932:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: government is from politicians. What they are saying is those resources shouldn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,933:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,935:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t be in control of
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,936:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: individuals who built them, but instead should be under government control. They
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,936:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,937:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re basically
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,938:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: saying they want control of the assets.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,938:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,939:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  很多推动更高政府参与或征用资产给政府的是来自政客。他们说的是那些资源不应该由建造它们的个人控制，而应该在政府控制下。他们基本上说他们想要控制资产。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,939:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,940:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I think the profit motive is good if the rules of an industry are properly set up. There
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,941:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,943:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,944:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: nothing wrong with profit. Profit just means people are paying you more for whatever you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,944:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,945:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,945:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: creating than you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,946:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,946:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re spending to create it. That
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,947:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,947:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s a good thing. If that
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,948:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,948:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s not the case, you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,949:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,950:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ll soon be
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,950:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: out of business, and rightfully so, because you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,951:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,952:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re not adding enough value.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,952:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,953:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我认为如果一个行业的规则设置得当，利润动机是好的。利润没有错。利润只是意味着人们为你创造的东西支付的比你创造它花费的更多。那是好事。如果不是这样，你很快就会倒闭，这是应该的，因为你没有增加足够的价值。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,953:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,954:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  A few people do bad things to achieve profit, but that
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,954:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,956:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s quite unusual, because the rules are
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,957:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: mostly set up correctly. Not perfect, but mostly correct.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,958:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,958:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  少数人做坏事来实现利润，但这很不寻常，因为规则大部分设置正确。不完美，但大部分正确。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,959:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,959:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  It is insanely hard to build and ship useful products to a large number of people. There
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,960:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,961:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,962:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: hell of a difference between a company that has shipped a product and one that hasn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,963:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,963:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,963:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,968:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s night and
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,970:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: day. Once you ship products, is the value of the output worth more than the cost of the inputs?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,970:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Again insanely difficult, especially with hardware.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,971:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,971:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  向大量人建造和运输有用的产品是疯狂困难的。已经运输产品的公司和没有运输产品的公司之间有地狱般的差异。那是天壤之别。一旦你运输产品，产出的价值是否比投入的成本更有价值？再次疯狂困难，特别是对于硬件。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,972:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,976:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  If you create great products and services that create wealth, that should be applauded. You
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,977:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: increased the standard of living of the country and perhaps of the world.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,977:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,977:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  如果你创造创造财富的伟大产品和服务，那应该受到鼓掌。你提高了国家的生活水平，也许还有世界的生活水平。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,978:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Companies to Start
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,978:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 要创办的公司
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,979:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,980:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Work on things that you find interesting, fulfilling, and that contribute some good to the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,981:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: rest of society.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,981:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,982:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  从事你觉得有趣、充实，并对社会其他部分有所贡献的事情。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,982:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,983:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Q: What are some areas you see where people could build important new technology?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,983:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,984:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  问：你看到哪些领域人们可以建造重要的新技术？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,984:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,985:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  For five years people asked me where I saw opportunities and I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,985:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,986:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: d say 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,986:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,987:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: tunneling.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,987:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,992:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  But
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,994:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: nobody did anything. It was initially a joke, but we created the Boring Company and did a test
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,995:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: tunnel in LA. People still didn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,995:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,996:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t believe us. Then we did our first operational tunnel in Vegas.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,996:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,996:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  五年来人们问我哪里有机会，我会说
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,997:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,997:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 隧道挖掘
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,998:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,998:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 。但没有人做任何事情。最初是个笑话，但我们创建了无聊公司，并在洛杉矶做了一个测试隧道。人们仍然不相信我们。然后我们在拉斯维加斯做了第一个运营隧道。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:00,999:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,002:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  There are still tremendous opportunities in tunneling. The world needs tunnels. All major
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,003:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: cities have traffic, and tunnels can massively improve people
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,003:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,015:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s quality of life by making it easy to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,022:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: travel from one place to another. They can be further expanded to long-distance travel. If you draw a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,023:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: vacuum on the tunnel, you can go extremely fast. Faster than a plane or high-speed rail. I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,024:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,025:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: d still
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,025:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: recommend someone—please—start a tunneling company.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,026:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,027:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  隧道挖掘仍然有巨大机会。世界需要隧道。所有主要城市都有交通，隧道可以通过使从一个地方到另一个地方的旅行变得容易来大幅改善人们的生活质量。它们可以进一步扩展到长途旅行。如果你在隧道中抽真空，你可以走得非常快。比飞机或高铁还快。我仍然推荐某人——请——创办一家隧道挖掘公司。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,027:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,030:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Another company to start would be anything to do with genetics. If you can solve genetic
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,031:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: diseases, you can prevent dementia or Alzheimer
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,031:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,032:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s with genetic reprogramming. That would be
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,032:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: wonderful.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,033:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,034:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  另一家要创办的公司将是任何与遗传学有关的事情。如果你能解决遗传疾病，你可以通过遗传重编程预防痴呆症或阿尔茨海默病。那将是很好的。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,034:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,039:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Synthetic RNA is revolutionary in medicine. Most people are not aware just how much of
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,040:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: a revolution this is. This is like medicine going from analog to digital.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,041:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,042:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  合成 RNA 在医学上是革命性的。大多数人没有意识到这是多大的革命。这就像医学从模拟走向数字。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,043:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,044:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  RNA (ribonucleic acid) or MRNA (messenger RNA) are basically synthetic viruses. I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,044:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: think people don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,045:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,045:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t appreciate what
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,046:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,058:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s going on—this is the digitization of medicine. You can create an
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,064:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: RNA or DNA (deoxyribonucleic acid) sequence like a computer program and encapsulate it in a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,065:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: lipid shell, so it looks like a tasty treat for your cells. This is the future of medicine.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,065:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,066:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  RNA（核糖核酸）或 mRNA（信使 RNA）基本上是合成病毒。我认为人们没有意识到正在发生的事情——这是医学的数字化。你可以创建一个像计算机程序一样的 RNA 或 DNA（脱氧核糖核酸）序列，并将其封装在脂质壳中，所以它看起来像你的细胞的美味款待。这是医学的未来。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,067:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,086:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  You can do almost anything. You could probably figure out how to turn someone into a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,097:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: literal butterfly. Your cells are tiny biological computers. They execute just like old-school
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,101:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: computers, where you feed it a tape or punch card. Your cells do whatever their punch card says.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,101:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: That was a big eye-opener, understanding the potential of RNA.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,102:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,102:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  你几乎可以做任何事情。你可能可以找出如何将某人变成一只真正的蝴蝶。你的细胞是微小的生物计算机。它们的执行就像老式计算机，你给它喂磁带或打孔卡。你的细胞做它们的打孔卡说的任何事情。那是一个大开眼界的时刻，理解 RNA 的潜力。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,103:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,114:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  You could start a company for high-speed travel. Reading about the California high-speed
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,119:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: rail was depressing. California taxpayers are paying to build the most expensive high-speed rail per
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,120:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: mile in the world—and the slowest. Those are not the superlatives you want.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,120:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,120:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  你可以创办一家高速旅行公司。阅读关于加州高铁的报道令人沮丧。加州纳税人正在支付建造世界上每英里最贵的高铁——也是最慢的。那些不是你想要的最高的。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,121:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,121:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,121:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,122:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s California
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,122:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: !
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,122:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  We make super high-tech stuff
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,123:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: !
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,130:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Why are we spending—the estimates are
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,133:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: around $100 billion—for something that will take two hours to go from LA to San Francisco? You can
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,134:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: get on a plane and do that in forty-five minutes.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,134:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,135:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  这是加州！我们制造超级高科技的东西！我们为什么要花费——估计约为 1000 亿美元——用于从洛杉矶到旧金山需要两个小时的东西？你可以坐上飞机，在四十五分钟内完成。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,135:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,139:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  There has to be a better way to do this. What would you ideally want in a transportation
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,139:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: system? You want something faster than existing modes of transportation. Let
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,142:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,143:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s say twice as fast,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,144:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: costs half as much per ticket, can
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,144:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,157:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t crash, is immune to weather, and is not energy intensive. You can
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,162:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: self-power the whole thing with solar panels or something. That would be pretty good. The devil is
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,163:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: in the details of making the thing work, but something like this could work and be practical.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,164:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,164:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  必须有更好的方法来做这个。你在交通系统中理想地想要什么？你想要比现有交通方式更快的东西。比如说快两倍，每张票成本减半，不会撞车，不受天气影响，不耗能。你可以用太阳能电池板或其他方式为整个系统自供电。那会很好。魔鬼在于让这个东西工作的细节，但像这样的东西可以工作并且实用。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,165:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,165:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  There
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,165:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,166:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s the possibility of this fifth mode of transport; I call it the Hyperloop.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,166:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,167:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  有这种第五种交通方式的可能性；我称之为超级高铁。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,167:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,181:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  For long-distance travel, you can do tunnels or tubes. If you remove the air or most of the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,186:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: air, you can get rid of the air friction and go supersonic. You can do so with no dependence on
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,187:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: weather and no need to get to high altitude or create any sonic boom issues. That
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,188:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,188:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s what I envision
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,189:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: for the Hyperloop. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,189:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,190:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s basically a pressurized electric car in a vacuum tube. This will be our next
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,191:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: evolution in transport.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,191:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,192:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  对于长途旅行，你可以做隧道或管道。如果你移除空气或大部分空气，你可以消除空气摩擦并达到超音速。你可以这样做而不依赖天气，也不需要到达高空或产生任何音爆问题。这就是我对超级高铁的设想。它基本上是一个真空管中的加压电动汽车。这将是我们交通的下一个进化。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,192:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,193:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  We want the future to be better than the past. If we had something like the Hyperloop, you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,194:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,201:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: d look forward to the day that was working. Even if it was only in one place—from LA to San Francisco, or New York to DC—it would be a tourist attraction and show it is possible.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,201:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,202:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我们希望未来比过去更好。如果我们有像超级高铁这样的东西，你会期待它工作的那一天。即使它只在一个地方——从洛杉矶到旧金山，或从纽约到华盛顿——它也将是一个旅游景点，并表明这是可能的。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,203:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,203:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Even if some of the initial assumptions didn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,204:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,204:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t work out or the economics didn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,205:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,214:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t work out
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,220:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: quite as expected, it would still be cool. If you come up with a new technology, it should feel like
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,221:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: that. If you told a stranger, would they look forward to the day this new thing became available?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,221:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,222:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  即使一些初始假设没有实现或经济学没有完全如预期那样工作，它仍然会很酷。如果你想出一项新技术，它应该感觉像那样。如果你告诉一个陌生人，他们会期待这个新东西可用的一天吗？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,222:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,224:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Q: What is the most important piece of advice you have for anyone who wants to start a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,225:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: company on behalf of humanity?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,225:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,226:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  问：你对任何想代表人类创办公司的人有什么最重要的建议？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,226:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,259:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The final thing I would encourage you to do is to take risks. Especially before you have
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,279:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: kids and other obligations. As you get older, your obligations start to increase. Once you have a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,287:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: family, taking risks affects not just yourself, but your family as well. It gets harder to do things that
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,289:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: might not work out. It is easiest to start before you have those obligations. Take risks now, and do
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,290:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: something bold. You won
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,290:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,291:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t regret it.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,291:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,292:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我鼓励你做的最后一件事是冒险。特别是在你有孩子和其他义务之前。随着年龄的增长，你的义务开始增加。一旦你有了家庭，冒险不仅影响你自己，也影响你的家人。做可能不成功的事情变得更难。在你有那些义务之前开始是最容易的。现在就冒险，做一些大胆的事情。你不会后悔的。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,292:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,294:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Go do it. Just go out there and do it. People are far too afraid to try. Fear is the biggest
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,295:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: reason for failure. Don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,295:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,296:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t be afraid to fail. Just go.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,296:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,297:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  去做吧。就出去做吧。人们太害怕尝试了。恐惧是失败的最大原因。不要害怕失败。就去吧。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,297:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,298:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  If you don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,298:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,299:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t push for radical breakthroughs, you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,299:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,299:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re not going to get radical outcomes.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,300:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,300:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  如果你不推动激进突破，你就不会得到激进的结果。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,301:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Companies Drive Progress
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,301:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 公司推动进步
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,301:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,302:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The rate of innovation is not constant. This year, we
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,302:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,304:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re either going to increase the rate of
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,304:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: innovation or it will slow down.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,304:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,305:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  创新率不是恒定的。今年，我们要么会增加创新率，要么它会减慢。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,305:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,312:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Some people think technology automatically gets better every year. It does not. It only gets
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,313:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: better if smart people work like crazy to make it better. We need strong engineering talent applied to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,314:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: problems. That
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,314:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,315:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s how any technology actually gets better. If people don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,315:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,316:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t work on technology, it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,316:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: actually will decline.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,317:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,317:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  有些人认为技术每年自动变得更好。不是这样的。只有聪明人疯狂工作让它变得更好，它才会变得更好。我们需要强大的工程人才应用于问题。这就是任何技术实际变得更好的方式。如果人们不研究技术，它实际上会衰退。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,317:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,318:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Look at the history of civilizations and you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,318:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,347:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ll see this happen many times. Ancient Egypt
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,369:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: was able to build incredible pyramids and forgot how to build pyramids. Then they forgot how to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,380:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: read hieroglyphics. In Rome, they were able to build incredible roadways, aqueducts, and indoor
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,383:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: plumbing—they forgot how to do all those things. There are many examples in history. You should
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,384:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: always bear in mind that entropy is not on our side.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,384:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,385:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  看看文明的历史，你会看到这种情况发生很多次。古埃及能够建造令人难以置信的金字塔，却忘记了如何建造金字塔。然后他们忘记了如何阅读象形文字。在罗马，他们能够建造令人难以置信的道路、渡槽和室内管道——他们忘记了如何做所有那些事情。历史上有许多例子。你应该始终记住，熵不在我们这边。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,385:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,398:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  More recently, if you look at American manned space missions: We were able to go to the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,402:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: moon in 1969, then the space shuttle could only go to low earth orbit. Then the space shuttle retired
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,403:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: and for almost a decade America had no access to space for humans.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,404:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,404:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  最近，如果你看美国载人太空任务：我们能够在 1969 年登月，然后航天飞机只能进入低地球轨道。然后航天飞机退役，近十年来美国没有人类进入太空的途径。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,405:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,408:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  This is a pretty bad trend, trending to zero. We need a strong trend in the other direction to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,408:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: have any chance whatsoever of making life multiplanetary. That
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,409:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,414:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s the reason for the extreme sense
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,416:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: of urgency. If we operate with extreme urgency, we have a chance of making life multiplanetary.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,416:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Still just a chance; it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,417:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,417:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s not certain. If we don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,418:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,418:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t act with extreme urgency, that chance is probably zero.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,419:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,419:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  这是一个相当糟糕的趋势，趋向于零。我们需要一个强烈的反向趋势，才有可能使生命成为多行星的。这就是极端紧迫感的原因。如果我们以极端紧迫感运作，我们有机会使生命成为多行星的。仍然只是一个机会；不确定。如果我们不以极端紧迫感行动，那个机会可能是零。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,420:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,420:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I am not one of the doomsday people. I think we
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,421:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,426:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re on a good path. But at the same time, I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,428:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: want to caution against complacency. If we are not complacent, and we have a high sense of
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,429:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: urgency, things will be fine.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,429:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,430:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我不是末日论者之一。我认为我们走在正确的道路上。但同时，我想警告不要自满。如果我们不自满，并且我们有高度的紧迫感，事情会好的。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,430:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,432:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  If you want the future to be good, you must make it so. Take action to make it good, and it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,432:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: will be.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,433:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,433:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  如果你想要未来是好的，你必须让它如此。采取行动让它变好，它就会是。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,434:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: THE AGE OF ABUNDANCE
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,434:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 丰盛时代
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,435:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,435:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  AI and robotics will bring about what might be termed 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,436:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,437:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the age of abundance.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,437:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,440:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Other
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,441:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: people have used this word, and that is my prediction: It will be an age of abundance for everyone.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,441:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,442:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  AI 和机器人将带来所谓的
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,442:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,443:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 丰盛时代
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,443:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,443:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 。其他人已经使用了这个词，那是我的预测：这将是每个人的丰盛时代。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,444:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The End of Scarcity
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,444:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 稀缺的终结
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,444:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,445:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  People get confused sometimes; they think an economy is money. Money is just a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,446:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: database.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,446:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,446:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  人们有时会困惑；他们认为经济是金钱。金钱只是一个数据库。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,447:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,453:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The actual economy is stuff. Goods and services. What limits the output of goods and
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,454:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: services? The limiter is labor. Even capital is distilled labor, so the limiting factor for the economy is
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,455:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: labor.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,455:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,455:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  实际的经济是东西。商品和服务。什么限制了商品和服务的产出？限制因素是劳动力。甚至资本是蒸馏的劳动力，所以经济的限制因素是劳动力。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,456:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,456:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  We can massively increase labor by building humanoid robots.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,457:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,457:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我们可以通过建造人形机器人来大幅增加劳动力。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,458:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,458:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  If you remove labor as the limiting factor for the economy, it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,459:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,465:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s not clear that an economy in
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,468:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the traditional sense has any meaning anymore because you have no constraint on goods and
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,469:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: services. There will be no shortage of goods and services.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,469:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,470:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  如果你移除劳动力作为经济的限制因素，传统意义上的经济是否还有任何意义就不清楚了，因为你对商品和服务没有限制。将不会有商品和服务的短缺。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,470:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,471:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The first units we intend to make are for jobs that are dangerous, boring, repetitive things
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,472:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: that people don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,472:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,473:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t want to do.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,473:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,473:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我们打算制造的第一批单元是用于危险、无聊、重复性的工作，人们不想做这些事情。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,474:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,480:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  In the future, the only forms of scarcity will be artificial scarcity (where we decide to make
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,481:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: it scarce, like a particular piece of art) or unique items like a particular home in an exact location.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,482:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,482:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  在未来，唯一形式的稀缺将是人为稀缺（我们决定让它稀缺，比如一件特定的艺术品）或独特物品，比如特定位置的特定房屋。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,483:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,483:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,483:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,497:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t worry about robots putting people out of jobs. We already have a massive shortage
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,503:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: of labor. We will still have a shortage of labor even in the future. Robotics will create a world of
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,503:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: abundance—goods and services will be available to anyone who wants them, so cheap it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,504:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,504:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ll be ridiculous.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,505:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,505:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  不要担心机器人让人们失业。我们已经有了巨大的劳动力短缺。即使在未来，我们仍将面临劳动力短缺。机器人技术将创造一个丰盛的世界——商品和服务将提供给任何想要它们的人，便宜得荒谬。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,506:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,521:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Our goal at Tesla is to make a useful humanoid robot as quickly as possible. Eventually,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,528:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: there will be millions of them. This means a future of abundance, a future where there is no poverty.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,529:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: We can afford to have a universal basic income for people. It really is a fundamental transformation
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,530:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: of civilization.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,530:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,531:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我们在特斯拉的目标是尽快制造一个有用的人形机器人。最终，将有数百万个。这意味着一个丰盛的未来，一个没有贫困的未来。我们可以为人们提供普遍基本收入。这确实是文明的根本转变。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,531:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,532:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  People have no idea; the market for humanoid robots will be bigger than that of cars.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,532:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,533:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  人们不知道；人形机器人市场将比汽车市场更大。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,533:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,536:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  There will be humanoid robots throughout factories. Cars will also be entirely automatic.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,537:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Anywhere intelligence can be applied will be automated. That
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,538:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,538:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s maybe 2033–2043.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,539:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,539:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  工厂里将有人形机器人。汽车也将完全自动化。任何可以应用智能的地方都将自动化。那可能是 2033-2043 年。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,540:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,570:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  As we go further into the future, things are gonna change a lot. Everything will be
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,588:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: automatic. There will be household robots that you can talk to as if they are people. It will help you,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,595:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: be a companion, or whatever the case may be. It will be able to pick up your kids from school or
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,596:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: stay with them at school if you want. It will be able to teach kids anything and support any language.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,597:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,597:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  随着我们进一步走向未来，事情将发生很大变化。一切都将是自动的。将有家用机器人，你可以像和人一样与它们交谈。它将帮助你，成为伴侣，或任何其他情况。它将能够从学校接你的孩子，或者如果你愿意，可以在学校陪伴他们。它将能够教孩子任何事情并支持任何语言。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,598:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,611:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Long term, I think the ratio of humanoid robots will be more than one-to-one. There might
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,616:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: be two humanoid robots per person or more, maybe ten for every one. Well in excess of ten billion
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,617:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: humanoid robots. At volume production, a humanoid robot will cost less than a car.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,617:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,617:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  长期来看，我认为人形机器人的比例将超过一比一。可能每个人有两个或更多的人形机器人，也许每一个人十个。远超过一百亿个人形机器人。在批量生产时，人形机器人的成本将低于汽车。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,618:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Exponential Intelligence
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,618:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 指数智能
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,619:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,621:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Computing power is going to be crazy. The big change is the cost of computing power, not
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,622:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: so much the circuit density (known as Moore
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,622:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,623:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s Law). If you look at dollars per instruction, cost is
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,624:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: dropping exponentially.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,624:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,624:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  计算能力将变得疯狂。最大的变化是计算能力的成本，而不是电路密度（称为摩尔定律）。如果你看每条指令的美元成本，成本正在呈指数下降。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,625:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,625:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  We
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,626:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,628:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ll see massively parallel computers, computing power, and storage become extremely
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,628:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: available. There will be ubiquitous computing everywhere.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,629:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,629:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我们将看到大规模并行计算机、计算能力和存储变得极其可用。到处都将有无处不在的计算。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,630:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,634:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I expect AI to be incredibly sophisticated by the 2040s. Predicting trends in an exponential
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,635:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: curve is tricky, because up close it often looks linear. But actually, it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,635:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,636:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s not linear. The pace of AI
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,637:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: development itself appears to be accelerating.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,637:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,638:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我预计到 2040 年代，AI 将变得极其复杂。预测指数曲线中的趋势是棘手的，因为近距离看它通常看起来是线性的。但实际上，它不是线性的。AI 发展本身的速度似乎在加快。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,638:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,643:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The ratio of total digital compute to total biological compute is the key metric to watch.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,644:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: This is perhaps the most fundamental ratio defining technological progress. It is rising incredibly
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,645:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: fast.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,645:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,646:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  总数字计算与总生物计算的比例是要关注的关键指标。这可能是定义技术进步的最基本比例。它正在以惊人的速度上升。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,646:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,647:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  We
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,647:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,654:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re building progressively greater intelligences, and the percentage of nonhuman
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,656:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: intelligence is increasing. Eventually we humans will represent a small percentage of total
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,657:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: intelligence. It might feel like we
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,657:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,657:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re the biological bootloader for AI.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,658:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,658:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我们正在逐步建造更大的智能，非人类智能的百分比正在增加。最终，我们人类将只占总智能的一小部分。感觉可能像是我们是 AI 的生物引导程序。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,659:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,659:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  We
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,660:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,661:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re fairly close to artificial general intelligence, perhaps only a few years away. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,661:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,668:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,673:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: possible we are on the event horizon of the black hole that is artificial superintelligence. Over a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,674:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: twenty- to thirty-year time frame, things could be transformed beyond belief. We probably won
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,674:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,675:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,675:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: recognize society in thirty years.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,676:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,676:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我们相当接近人工通用智能，也许只有几年之遥。我们可能正处于人工超级智能黑洞的事件视界上。在二十到三十年的时间框架内，事情可能会变得难以置信地转变。三十年后我们可能认不出社会了。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,677:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Upgrading the Human Mind
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,677:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 升级人类思维
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,678:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,679:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The internet is a great leveler for information and education. You can learn anything online
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,679:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: for free.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,680:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,680:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  互联网是信息和教育的伟大平衡器。你可以免费在线学习任何东西。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,681:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,682:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  A thousand years ago there were very few books. Even if you had a thirst for knowledge
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,683:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: you couldn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,683:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,691:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t do much about it, because books were incredibly expensive and rare, and only a few
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,694:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: people knew how to read. Books were difficult to get until the Gutenberg Press. Technology is what
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,694:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: causes these big step-changes in civilization.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,695:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,695:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  一千年前书籍非常少。即使你有求知欲，你也无能为力，因为书籍非常昂贵和稀有，只有少数人知道如何阅读。在古腾堡印刷机之前，书籍很难获得。技术是导致文明中这些巨大阶梯式变化的原因。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,696:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,696:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Even if you could read and were in the Library of Congress, you still didn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,697:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,697:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t have access to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,698:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: all the world
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,698:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,698:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s information, and you certainly couldn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,699:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,700:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t search it. And, of course, very few people
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,701:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: could be in the Library of Congress at once.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,701:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,702:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  即使你能阅读并在国会图书馆，你仍然无法访问世界上所有的信息，你当然也无法搜索它。当然，很少有人能同时在国会图书馆。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,702:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,726:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The internet is something beyond the Gutenberg press. When the general public started
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,739:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: using the internet, it felt like humanity was developing a nervous system. Any part of humanity got
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,744:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: access to almost all human knowledge. You could be deep in the Amazon jungle with a Starlink
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,744:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: terminal and have access to more information than the US president did in 1980.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,745:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,745:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  互联网是超越古腾堡印刷机的东西。当公众开始使用互联网时，感觉就像人类正在发展神经系统。人类的任何部分都可以访问几乎所有人类知识。你可以带着星链终端深入亚马逊丛林，获得比 1980 年美国总统更多的信息。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,746:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,751:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  To transfer data before the digital age, you had to write a letter. Someone would have to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,751:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: carry the letter to another person with a bunch of physical work in between. That
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,752:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,754:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s insanely slow
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,755:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: when you think about it. Now, you can access any book instantly; you can learn anything. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,755:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,756:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,756:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: incredible.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,756:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,757:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  在数字时代之前传输数据，你必须写信。有人必须把信带给另一个人，中间有一堆体力劳动。当你想到这一点时，那是疯狂慢的。现在，你可以立即访问任何书籍；你可以学习任何东西。这令人难以置信。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,757:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,759:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Any student of history would agree: The internet has been the biggest equalizer in history
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,760:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: for access to information and knowledge.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,760:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,761:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  任何历史学生都会同意：互联网一直是历史上获取信息和知识的最大平衡器。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,761:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,783:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  We already have a digital layer to our minds, in a sense, with our computer or our phone.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,795:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: You can access any book or song. You can ask a question on Google and get an answer instantly.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,800:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: With your laptop, you can outcompute an Empire State Building filled with people and calculators.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,800:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: These are incredible superpowers, which even the president of the United States didn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,801:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,801:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t have back in
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,802:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the year 2000.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,802:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,803:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  在某种意义上，我们已经通过电脑或手机为我们的思维添加了数字层。你可以访问任何书籍或歌曲。你可以在谷歌上提问并立即得到答案。用你的笔记本电脑，你可以超越装满人和计算器的帝国大厦。这些都是令人难以置信的超能力，即使是美国总统在 2000 年也没有。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,803:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,804:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  People don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,804:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,805:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t appreciate this yet—they are already a cyborg. You
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,805:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,807:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re a different creature than
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,808:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: you would have been twenty years ago, or even ten years ago.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,808:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,809:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  人们还没有意识到这一点——他们已经是半机械人了。你与二十年前，甚至十年前的你是不同的生物。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,809:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,809:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  They do surveys asking, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,810:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,810:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: How long can you be away from your phone?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,811:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,813:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Particularly for
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,814:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: younger people, even a day is painful. If you leave your phone behind, it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,814:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,815:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s like missing a limb.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,816:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: People have already merged with their phones.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,816:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,817:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  他们进行调查问，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,817:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,818:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 你能离开手机多久？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,818:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,819:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 特别是对年轻人来说，即使一天也是痛苦的。如果你把手机落在后面，就像失去肢体一样。人们已经与手机融合了。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,819:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,820:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  You
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,820:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,821:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re already digitally superhuman.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,821:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,821:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  你已经在数字上超人了。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,822:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,823:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Q: Will the brain–computer interface change humans and how we use computers?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,823:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,824:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  问：脑机接口会改变人类和我们使用电脑的方式吗？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,824:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,825:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Yes, an intertwined idea is having a higher-bandwidth interface between computers and the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,826:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: brain. We
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,826:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,829:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re currently bandwidth limited. The connection is bottlenecked in this tiny straw of an
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,829:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: interface, poking glass with your meat sticks.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,830:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,830:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  是的，一个交织的想法是在计算机和大脑之间拥有更高带宽的接口。我们目前受带宽限制。连接在这个微小的接口 straw 中受到瓶颈限制，用你的肉棒戳玻璃。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,831:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,832:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Ten-finger typing on a keyboard used to be the most common input to a computer. Now, it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,832:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,834:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s usually two-thumb typing. Our output quality has gone backward.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,834:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,835:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  在键盘上十指打字曾经是计算机最常见的输入。现在，通常是两个拇指打字。我们的输出质量倒退了。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,835:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,864:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The sustained output of a human over the course of a day is less than one bit per second.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,879:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: There are 86,400 seconds in a day. It is extremely rare for a human to output more than that number
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,885:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: of symbols per day, certainly for several days in a row. We should be able to improve that by many
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,886:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: orders of magnitude with a direct neural interface—a high-bandwidth interface to your digital
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,886:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: enhancements.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,886:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,887:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  人类一天中的持续输出少于每秒一位。一天有 86,400 秒。人类每天输出超过该数量的符号是极其罕见的，当然连续几天更是如此。我们应该能够通过直接神经接口——对你的数字增强的高带宽接口——将其提高多个数量级。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,887:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,891:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Noland Arbaugh was the very first Neuralink patient. After he got the Neuralink implant,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,891:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: he spent all night playing Civilization, which is awesome. That
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,892:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,892:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s exactly what I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,892:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,908:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: d do too. Even with
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,920:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: only roughly 10 to 15 percent of the electrodes working, we were able to achieve a bit per second.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,924:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: That was twice the previous world record. Maybe five years from now, we might be at a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,925:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: megabit—faster than any human could possibly communicate by typing or speaking.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,925:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,926:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  诺兰·阿博是第一位 Neuralink 患者。在他获得 Neuralink 植入物后，他整夜玩《文明》，这太棒了。那也是我会做的。即使只有大约 10% 到 15% 的电极工作，我们也能够实现每秒一位。那是之前世界纪录的两倍。也许五年后，我们可能达到一兆比特——比任何人通过打字或说话交流都快。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,926:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,931:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The Neuralink interface can massively increase your output bandwidth and your input
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,932:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: bandwidth. Input being written operations to the brain, where the brain is reading signals.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,932:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,933:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Neuralink 接口可以大幅增加你的输出带宽和输入带宽。输入是写入大脑的操作，大脑在那里读取信号。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,933:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,934:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  If we achieve tight symbiosis, AI wouldn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,934:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,934:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t be 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,935:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,935:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: other
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,935:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,938:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: —it would be integrated with you.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,939:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Imagine it has a relationship to your conscious mind similar to your unconscious mind.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,939:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,940:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  如果我们实现紧密共生，AI 就不会是
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,940:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,941:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 其他
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,941:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,941:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ——它将与你整合。想象它与你的意识思维的关系类似于你的潜意识。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,942:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,945:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Your brain has to work to compress a bunch of concepts in your head into this incredibly
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,945:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: low data rate format called speech or typing. That
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,946:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,947:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s what language is—a compression algorithm on
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,948:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: thought, to transfer a concept. Then it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,948:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,949:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s got to listen and decompress what
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,949:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,950:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s coming in. Both of these
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,951:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: steps are very lossy.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,951:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,951:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  你的大脑必须努力将你头脑中的一堆概念压缩成这种极低数据速率的格式，称为说话或打字。这就是语言——对思想的压缩算法，以传输概念。然后它必须倾听并解压进来的内容。这两个步骤都非常有损。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,952:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,959:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  If you have two direct-brain interfaces, you could do an uncompressed direct conceptual
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,961:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: communication with another person. Like consensual telepathy. The conversation would be a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,962:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: conceptual interaction on a level that
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,962:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,963:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s difficult to conceive of right now.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,963:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,964:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  如果你有两个直接大脑接口，你可以与另一个人进行未压缩的直接概念交流。就像共识心灵感应。对话将是一个目前难以想象的概念层面的互动。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,964:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,965:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Conceivably, there
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,965:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,966:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s a way to have a digital layer of your brain feel like part of you. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,967:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,967:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s not
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,968:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: something you offload to consciously; it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,968:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,969:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s just 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,969:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,970:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: you.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,970:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,971:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,971:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  可以想象，有一种方式让你大脑的数字层感觉像你的一部分。它不是你有意识地卸载的东西；它只是
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,972:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,972:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 你
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,972:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,973:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,973:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,989:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  To start out, we are really just solving basic neurological damage, like for people who have
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,995:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: essentially complete or near complete loss from the brain to the body. For someone like Stephen
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,997:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Hawking, the Neuralink would be incredibly profound. Imagine if Stephen Hawking could
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,998:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: communicate as fast as we
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,998:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,999:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re communicating, perhaps faster. And that
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:01,999:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,000:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s certainly possible. Probable,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,001:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: in fact.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,001:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,002:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  开始时，我们真的只是在解决基本的神经损伤，比如那些从大脑到身体基本或几乎完全丧失功能的人。对于像斯蒂芬·霍金这样的人，Neuralink 将是极其深远的。想象一下，如果斯蒂芬·霍金能像我们交流一样快地交流，也许更快。这当然是可能的。事实上，很可能。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,002:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,003:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  There
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,003:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,004:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s obviously some risk with a new device. You can
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,005:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,005:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t get the risk down to zero; it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,006:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,007:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s not
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,008:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: possible. So, you want to have the highest possible reward, given there
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,009:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,009:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s a certain irreducible risk.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,010:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: And if somebody
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,011:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,012:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s able to have a profound improvement in their communication, that
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,012:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,013:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s worth the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,013:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: risk.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,014:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,015:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  新设备显然有一些风险。你不能将风险降到零；这是不可能的。所以，鉴于有一定的不可减少的风险，你想要尽可能高的回报。如果有人能够在交流方面取得深刻改善，那是值得冒险的。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,015:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,028:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  We can deliver new information to the brain too. If somebody is completely blind, we can
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,032:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: write directly to the visual cortex to give them sight. At first it will be relatively fairly low
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,033:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: resolution, but long term you would have very high resolution.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,034:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,035:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我们也可以向大脑传递新信息。如果有人完全失明，我们可以直接写入视觉皮层给他们视力。起初分辨率将相对较低，但长期来看你将拥有非常高分辨率。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,035:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,039:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  This is actually our second product, called Blindsight. It enables people who are
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,040:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: completely blind, lost both eyes or optic nerve, or just can
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,040:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,042:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t see at all, to be able to see by directly
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,042:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: triggering the neurons in the visual cortex.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,043:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,043:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  这实际上是我们的第二个产品，称为盲视。它使完全失明、失去双眼或视神经，或根本看不见的人能够通过直接触发视觉皮层中的神经元来看见。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,044:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,044:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  At some point, the cybernetic implants wouldn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,044:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,049:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t simply be correcting things that went
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,051:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: wrong but augmenting human capabilities. You could even see multispectral wavelengths like
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,051:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: infrared, ultraviolet, and radar. That
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,051:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,052:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s a superpower situation. Augmenting intelligence, senses, and
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,053:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: bandwidth dramatically—that
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,053:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,054:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s going to happen at some point.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,054:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,055:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  在某个时候，控制论植入物将不仅仅是纠正出错的事情，而是增强人类能力。你甚至可以看到多光谱波长，如红外线、紫外线和雷达。那是超能力的情况。大幅增强智能、感官和带宽——那将在某个时候发生。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,055:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The Last Human Drivers
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,056:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 最后的人类司机
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,056:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,057:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,057:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,059:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s crazy to let people drive a two-ton death machine manually. They can drive into
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,060:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: whatever they want. In the future, it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,060:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,061:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s going to seem like a mad thing that people once drove cars.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,061:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,062:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  让人们手动驾驶两吨死亡机器是疯狂的。他们可以开车撞任何他们想要的东西。在未来，人们曾经开车将看起来像疯狂的事情。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,062:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,074:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  In the early days of Tesla, 2013, a guy fell asleep at the wheel in a Model S, and he ran
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,078:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: over a cyclist and killed him. Unfortunately, people fall asleep at the wheel often. If we had already
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,079:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: built autopilot, this cyclist would still be alive. I thought, We
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,080:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,080:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: d better hurry up and get it working.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,081:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,081:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  在特斯拉早期，2013 年，一个家伙在 Model S 中开车时睡着了，他撞倒了一名骑自行车的人并杀死了他。不幸的是，人们经常在开车时睡着。如果我们已经建造了自动驾驶仪，这个骑自行车的人还会活着。我想，我们最好快点让它工作。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,082:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,098:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  There are clearly two massive revolutions coming to the automobile industry; one is the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,104:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: transition to electrification, and then the other is autonomy. It became obvious to me that in the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,105:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: future, any car that does not have autonomy would be about as useful as a horse. That
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,105:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,107:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s not to say it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,108:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: has no use…but it is rare for somebody to have a horse these days. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,109:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,109:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s obvious cars will drive
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,110:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: themselves completely; it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,110:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,111:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s just a question of time.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,111:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,112:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  显然汽车行业将迎来两场巨大的革命；一场是向电气化的过渡，另一场是自动驾驶。我清楚地意识到，在未来，任何没有自动驾驶的汽车将像马一样有用。这不是说它没有用处……但现在很少有人养马。很明显汽车将完全自动驾驶；这只是时间问题。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,112:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,113:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  An autonomous car is arguably worth five to ten times more than a car that is not
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,114:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: autonomous.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,114:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,115:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  一辆自动驾驶汽车的价值可以说是非自动驾驶汽车的五到十倍。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,115:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,117:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The autonomy system is likely to mitigate crashes except in rare circumstances. Vehicle
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,117:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: safety is probabilistic. There
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,118:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,130:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s some chance any time a human driver gets in a car that they will have
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,136:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: an accident that is their fault. The odds are never zero. The key threshold for autonomy is: How
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,136:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: much better does autonomy need to be than a person before you can rely on it?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,137:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,137:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  自动驾驶系统可能会减少碰撞，除非在罕见情况下。车辆安全是概率性的。任何时候人类司机上车都有可能发生他们过错的事故。几率永远不会是零。自动驾驶的关键阈值是：自动驾驶需要比人类好多少你才能依赖它？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,138:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,151:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  About a million people die every year in car accidents and about ten million per year have
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,157:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: serious injuries. Bringing the day of self-driving sooner translates directly to lives saved and injuries
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,157:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: avoided. The sooner, the better. A lot of lives will be saved and made better.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,158:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,159:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  每年约有 100 万人死于车祸，每年约有 1000 万人受重伤。让自动驾驶早日到来直接转化为拯救生命和避免伤害。越早越好。很多生命将被拯救和改善。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,159:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,171:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Tesla deployed partial autonomy immediately because when used correctly, it was already
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,176:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: significantly safer than a person driving by themself. It would be morally reprehensible to delay
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,177:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: release simply for fear of bad press or some mercantile calculation of legal liability.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,178:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,178:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  特斯拉立即部署了部分自动驾驶，因为当正确使用时，它已经比一个人自己开车安全得多。仅仅因为害怕负面新闻或对法律责任的商业计算而延迟发布在道德上是应受谴责的。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,179:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,184:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Autonomous cars could maneuver with a reaction time much faster than a human. Over
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,184:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: time, autopilot will be capable of impossible maneuvers that a human could never do.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,185:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,185:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  自动驾驶汽车可以以比人类快得多的反应时间机动。随着时间的推移，自动驾驶将能够完成人类永远无法做到的不可能机动。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,186:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,188:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I told the team I want the latest data on miles per intervention to be the starting slide at
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,188:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: each of our meetings. If we
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,188:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,196:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re training AI to drive, what do we optimize? The answer is higher miles
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,198:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: between interventions. It is motivating to watch each day as the miles per intervention increases.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,199:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Video games without a score are boring.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,199:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,200:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我告诉团队，我希望每次会议的开始幻灯片都是每次干预里程的最新数据。如果我们在训练 AI 驾驶，我们优化什么？答案是干预之间更高的里程。看着每天每次干预里程增加是令人鼓舞的。没有分数的电子游戏很无聊。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,200:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,202:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  We always try to do the right thing. When we make mistakes, it may be because we were
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,203:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: being foolish or stupid, but it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,203:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,203:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s always with the right motivations.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,204:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,204:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我们总是努力做正确的事情。当我们犯错时，可能是因为我们愚蠢或笨拙，但总是出于正确的动机。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,205:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,213:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  When true self-driving is approved by regulators, you will be able to summon your Tesla
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,216:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: from pretty much anywhere. Once it picks you up, you will be able to sleep, read, or do anything
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,216:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: else en route to your destination.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,217:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,217:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  当真正的自动驾驶获得监管机构批准时，你将能够从几乎任何地方召唤你的特斯拉。一旦它接上你，你将能够在前往目的地的途中睡觉、阅读或做任何其他事情。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,217:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,218:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Mega-long-term, I think of cars as being effectively carriers for the autonomy software. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,219:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,220:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,220:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the vehicle, literally and figuratively for autonomy. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,220:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,221:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s the software that rides on the car.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,221:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,222:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  超长期来看，我认为汽车实际上是自动驾驶软件的载体。它是自动驾驶的载体，字面上和比喻上都是。它是搭载在汽车上的软件。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,222:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,241:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Eventually, self-driving cars will take the form of a shared autonomous fleet. You buy
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,249:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: your car, and you could choose to use your car exclusively yourself, have it used only by friends and
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,251:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: family, or only by other drivers who are rated five stars. You can choose to share it sometimes but
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,252:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: not other times. That
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,252:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,253:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s 100 percent what will occur. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,253:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,254:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s just a question of when.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,254:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,255:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  最终，自动驾驶汽车将采取共享自动驾驶车队的形式。你购买你的汽车，你可以选择 exclusively 自己使用你的汽车，只让朋友和家人使用，或只由其他评级为五星的司机使用。你可以选择有时共享它，但有时不共享。那是 100% 会发生的。这只是时间问题。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,255:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,267:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  This autonomy shift is massive, because you could suddenly have five times the utility of
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,271:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the car you currently have. Say a normal passenger car gets ten to twelve hours a week of usage. An
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,271:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: autonomous car could be used fifty to sixty hours a week.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,272:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,272:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  这种自动驾驶转变是巨大的，因为你突然可以拥有你目前汽车五倍的效用。假设一辆普通乘用车每周使用十到十二小时。一辆自动驾驶汽车每周可以使用五十到六十小时。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,273:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,277:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  This is all good for the environment, because you need fewer cars to get the same thing
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,278:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: done. We would need fewer parking lots and garages to store cars when they
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,278:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,279:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re not in use, because
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,280:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: they
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,280:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,281:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re in use a lot more.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,281:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,282:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  这对环境都有好处，因为你需要更少的汽车来完成同样的事情。我们将需要更少的停车场和车库来存放不使用的汽车，因为它们使用得更多。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,282:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,285:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  If this is true, as autonomous driving capability is turned on for the Tesla fleet, it may be
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,285:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the biggest asset value increase in history…overnight.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,286:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,286:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  如果这是真的，随着特斯拉车队开启自动驾驶能力，这可能是历史上最大的资产价值增长……一夜之间。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,287:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,309:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  So, in short, Master Plan Part Deux is: → Create stunning solar roofs with seamlessly
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,322:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: integrated battery storage. → Expand the electric vehicle product line to address all major segments. →
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,326:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Develop a self-driving capability that is ten times safer than manual via massive fleet learning. →
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,327:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Enable your car to make money for you when you aren
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,327:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,328:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t using it.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,328:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,329:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  所以，简而言之，第二部总体规划是：→ 创建令人惊叹的太阳能屋顶，无缝集成电池存储。→ 扩展电动汽车产品线，涵盖所有主要细分市场。→ 通过大规模车队学习开发比手动驾驶安全十倍的自动驾驶能力。→ 让你在不使用汽车时为你赚钱。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,329:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,330:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I can
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,330:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,332:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t say enough about the profundity of full self-driving. It will be one of the biggest
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,332:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: changes in history. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,333:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,338:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s not just some feature; it is as profound as electrification. We already have
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,339:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: millions of cars on the road now able to achieve this with the right software update.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,339:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,340:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我对完全自动驾驶的深远意义怎么说都不为过。它将是历史上最大的变化之一。它不仅仅是一些功能；它与电气化一样深远。我们现在已经有数百万辆汽车在路上，通过正确的软件更新就能实现这一点。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,340:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,341:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Eventually, a vehicle must be designed as a clean Robotaxi. We
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,342:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,355:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re going to take that risk.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,365:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: No mirrors, no pedals, no steering wheel. This will be a historically megarevolutionary product. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,369:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: will transform everything. This is the product that makes Tesla a ten-trillion-dollar company. People
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,369:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: will be talking about this moment in a hundred years.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,369:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,370:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  最终，车辆必须设计为干净的 Robotaxi。我们将承担这个风险。没有镜子，没有踏板，没有方向盘。这将是一个历史上超级革命性的产品。它将改变一切。这是让特斯拉成为十万亿美元公司的产品。人们将在一百年后谈论这一刻。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,370:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: SUSTAINABLE ABUNDANCE
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,371:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 可持续丰盛
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,371:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,372:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  We
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,372:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,372:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re accelerating the world
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,373:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,373:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s transition to sustainable abundance.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,374:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,374:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我们正在加速世界向可持续丰盛的过渡。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,374:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,375:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  In Tesla
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,375:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,380:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s Master Plan, Part 3, the thing we wanted to convey, more importantly than
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,380:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: anything else, is that there is a clear path to a sustainable-energy Earth. It doesn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,381:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,382:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t require destroying
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,382:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: natural habitats; it doesn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,382:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,389:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t require us to be austere and stop using electricity. We have published a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,391:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: detailed white paper with all of our assumptions and calculations of a clear path to a fully
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,391:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: sustainable Earth, with abundance.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,392:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,392:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  在特斯拉总体规划第三部分中，我们想传达的，比任何其他事情都重要的是，有一个清晰的通往可持续能源地球的道路。它不需要破坏自然栖息地；它不需要我们节俭并停止使用电力。我们发表了一份详细的白皮书，包含我们所有的假设和计算，通往完全可持续地球的清晰道路，带有丰盛。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,393:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,396:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  In fact, you could support a civilization much larger on Earth. Much more than the current
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,396:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: eight billion humans could be supported sustainably on Earth.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,397:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,397:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  事实上，你可以在地球上支持一个更大的文明。远远超过目前的 80 亿人类可以在地球上可持续地支持。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,398:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,398:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,399:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,400:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: m often shocked by how few people realize this. Most of the smart people I know actually
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,400:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,400:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,402:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t see this clear path. They think there is no path to a sustainable energy future with our current
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,403:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: population. Or that we
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,403:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,407:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: d have to resort to extreme measures. None of this is true. In Master Plan,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,408:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Part 3, we walk through the calculations for how to create a sustainable-energy civilization.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,409:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,409:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我经常震惊于很少有人意识到这一点。我认识的大多数聪明人实际上看不到这条清晰的路径。他们认为以我们目前的人口没有通往可持续能源未来的道路。或者我们不得不诉诸极端措施。这些都不是真的。在总体规划第三部分中，我们逐步计算如何创建一个可持续能源文明。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,410:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,433:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  A fully electrified and sustainable economy is within reach through the actions in this
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,445:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: paper: 1. Repower the existing grid with renewables 2. Switch to electric vehicles 3. Switch to heat
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,451:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: pumps in residential, business, and industry 4. Electrify high-temperature heat delivery and
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,452:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: hydrogen production 5. Sustainably fuel planes and boats 6. Manufacture the sustainable energy
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,452:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: economy
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,453:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,454:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  通过本文中的行动，完全电气化和可持续的经济触手可及：1. 用可再生能源重新供电现有电网 2. 转向电动汽车 3. 在住宅、商业和工业中转向热泵 4. 电气化高温热输送和氢气生产 5. 可持续地为飞机和船只提供燃料 6. 制造可持续能源经济
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,454:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,458:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Our models show the electrified and sustainable future is technically feasible and requires
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,458:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: less investment and less material extraction than continuing today
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,459:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,459:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s unsustainable energy economy.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,460:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,461:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我们的模型表明，电气化和可持续的未来在技术上是可行的，并且比继续今天不可持续的能源经济需要更少的投资和更少的材料开采。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,461:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,474:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The tools we make at Tesla help us build the products that advance human prosperity.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,480:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Making technologically advanced products that are affordable and available at scale is required to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,482:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: build a flourishing and unconstrained society. It serves to further democratize society while raising
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,482:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: everyone
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,483:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,483:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s quality of life in the process.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,484:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,484:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我们在特斯拉制造的工具帮助我们建造促进人类繁荣的产品。制造价格实惠且可大规模获得的技术先进产品是建立繁荣和不受约束的社会所必需的。它有助于进一步民主化社会，同时在此过程中提高每个人的生活质量。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,485:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,500:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The hallmark of meritocracy is creating opportunities that enable each person to use their
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,506:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: skills to accomplish whatever they imagine. Everyone deserves access to these opportunities, and
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,508:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: technological growth can help ensure that each of us is able to maximize our most limited resource:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,508:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: time.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,509:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,509:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  精英管理的标志是创造机会，使每个人都能利用自己的技能完成他们想象的任何事情。每个人都应该有机会获得这些机会，技术增长可以帮助确保我们每个人都能够最大化我们最有限的资源：时间。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,510:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: OUR EXISTENTIAL RISKS
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,511:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 我们的生存风险
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,511:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,511:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,512:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,514:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t worry about it. I mean, worry about it. Because if you worry about it, ironically, it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,515:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: will be okay. It will be a self-unfulfilling prophecy.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,515:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,516:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  不要担心它。我的意思是，担心它。因为如果你担心它，讽刺的是，它会没事的。这将是一个自我未实现的预言。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,516:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: This Is the Best Time to Be Alive
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,517:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 这是活着的最佳时机
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,517:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,518:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Q: What period of history would you prefer to live in the most?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,518:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,519:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  问：你最喜欢生活在哪个历史时期？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,519:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,520:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Right now. The present is the most interesting time in history—and I read a lot of history. Let
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,520:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,521:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,521:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: do our best to keep that going.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,522:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,522:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  现在。现在是历史上最有趣的时期——我读了很多历史。让我们尽最大努力保持下去。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,522:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,526:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I find history fascinating. A lot of incredible things have been done, good and bad. By
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,527:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: learning about them, you understand the nature of civilization and individuals.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,528:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,528:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我发现历史很迷人。很多不可思议的事情已经完成，好的和坏的。通过了解它们，你理解文明和个人的本质。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,528:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,529:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  There
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,529:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,535:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s a lot of human history, but most of it is people getting on with their lives. Human
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,535:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: history is not a nonstop war and disaster. Those are actually intermittent and rare. If they weren
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,536:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,539:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,541:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: humans would soon cease to exist. But historians write more about wars than peace. A normal year
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,542:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: where nothing major happened won
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,542:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,543:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t be written about much. Most people just farmed and lived their
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,544:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: life as a villager somewhere.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,544:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,545:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  人类历史很多，但大部分是人们继续他们的生活。人类历史不是无休止的战争和灾难。那些实际上是间歇性的和罕见的。如果不是这样，人类很快就会停止存在。但历史学家写的战争比和平多。一个没有发生重大事件的正常年份不会被写太多。大多数人只是耕种并在某个地方作为村民生活。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,545:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,561:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Life was tough for most of history. In most of human history, a good year would be one
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,568:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: where not that many people in your village died of disease, starvation, freezing, or being killed by a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,569:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: neighboring village. If you only lost 5 percent of your village in a year, that was a good year.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,570:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,570:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  生活在大部分历史中都很艰难。在人类历史的大多数时候，好的一年是你村里没有太多人死于疾病、饥饿、冻死或被邻近村庄杀死。如果你一年只失去村里 5% 的人，那是好的一年。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,571:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,576:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Not starving to death would have been the primary goal of most people throughout history.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,577:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Just making sure they had enough food to last through the winter and not freeze to death.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,578:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,578:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  不饿死将是历史上大多数人的主要目标。只是确保他们有足够的食物度过冬天，不会冻死。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,579:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,579:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  If you judge history from what is morally acceptable today, you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,580:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,581:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: d give everyone a failing
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,581:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: grade. I don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,581:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,583:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t think anyone would get a passing grade in morality if you look back to even three
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,583:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: hundred years ago.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,584:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,585:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  如果你从今天道德上可接受的标准来判断历史，你会给每个人不及格的分数。我认为如果你回顾到甚至三百年前，没有人会在道德上得到及格分数。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,585:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,586:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Q: How does history help you understand the future?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,586:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,587:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  问：历史如何帮助你理解未来？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,587:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,588:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I try to understand the rise and fall of civilizations. I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,588:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,589:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ve read a lot of history to discern the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,590:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: facts of what humans did.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,590:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,591:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我试图理解文明的兴衰。我读了很多历史来辨别人类所做的事实。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,592:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,592:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  We take for granted that 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,592:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,593:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,593:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,593:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s always going to be there,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,594:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,595:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  but if you study history, you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,595:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: realize civilizations rise and fall.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,595:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,596:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我们认为
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,596:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,596:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 它将永远存在
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,597:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,597:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 是理所当然的，但如果你研究历史，你会意识到文明兴衰。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,597:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,621:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I was reading about the ancient Sumerians, who were arguably the first civilization. They
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,633:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: were the first to develop writing, but eventually they died out. Then, nobody could read their writing
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,638:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: at all. They were impressive in their time but they faded out as a civilization. The ancient Egyptians,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,638:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the same thing. One after another. Ancient Greece had its day. There
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,639:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,640:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ve been ebbs and flows in the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,641:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Chinese and Indian civilizations over the eons as well.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,641:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,642:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我在阅读关于古代苏美尔人，他们可以说是第一个文明。他们是第一个发展文字的，但最终他们灭绝了。然后，没有人能读懂他们的文字。他们在他们的时代令人印象深刻，但作为一个文明他们消失了。古埃及人，同样的事情。一个接一个。古希腊有过它的辉煌。中国和印度文明在亿万年中也有起伏。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,642:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,644:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Only a tiny fraction of what was ever written in history is available to us now. Probably
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,645:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: less than 1 percent. If they didn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,645:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,646:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t chisel it in stone or put it in a clay tablet, we don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,646:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,653:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t have it. There
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,658:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: are a few papyrus scrolls that are thousands of years old because they were deep inside a pyramid.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,658:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The little information we have shows many civilizations rising and falling. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,659:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,660:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s wild. And the basics
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,661:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: of human nature are more or less the same today.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,661:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,662:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  历史上写过的东西只有一小部分现在可供我们使用。可能不到 1%。如果他们没有把它刻在石头上或放在粘土板上，我们就没有它。有一些纸莎草卷轴有几千年的历史，因为它们在金字塔深处。我们拥有的少量信息显示许多文明兴衰。这很疯狂。人性的基本今天或多或少是一样的。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,662:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,672:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  We see patterns for civilizations as they go through a life cycle, like an organism does. A
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,676:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: human is a zygote, fetus, baby, toddler, teenager, eventually gets older, and dies. Every civilization
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,677:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: goes through a life cycle. No civilization will last forever.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,677:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,678:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我们看到文明在经历生命周期时的模式，就像生物体一样。人类是受精卵、胎儿、婴儿、幼儿、青少年，最终变老，然后死亡。每个文明都经历一个生命周期。没有文明会永远存在。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,678:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,687:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The birth rate might be the biggest single threat to the future of human civilization.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,689:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Artificial intelligence (AI) gone wrong is a big concern. Religious extremism is a concern. There are
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,690:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: quite a few important problems to solve.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,691:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,691:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  出生率可能是人类文明未来的最大单一威胁。人工智能（AI）出错是一个大问题。宗教极端主义是一个问题。有相当多的重要问题需要解决。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,691:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,698:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  We should view our civilization as much more fragile than we think. We must keep
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,699:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: civilization going onward and upward as much as possible and try to minimize the civilizational
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,700:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: threats that occur.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,700:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,701:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我们应该将我们的文明视为比我们认为的更脆弱。我们必须尽可能让文明继续向前向上，并尽量减少发生的文明威胁。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,701:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: World War III
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,702:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 第三次世界大战
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,702:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,703:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,703:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,712:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: m not predicting a world war anytime soon. But given enough time, it will likely happen.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,714:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: This has been our pattern in the past. In the last century we had two massive world wars, three if you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,715:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: count the Cold War. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,715:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,716:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s unlikely that we
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,716:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,717:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ll never have another world war. We probably will at some
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,718:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: point.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,718:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,719:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我不是预测很快会发生世界大战。但给定足够的时间，它可能会发生。这是我们过去的模式。在上个世纪我们有两次大规模世界大战，如果算上冷战就是三次。我们永远不会再有世界大战是不太可能的。我们可能在某个时候会有。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,719:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,733:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Any war is tragic and difficult on a local basis. Then some wars are civilization-ending, or
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,739:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: have that potential. Global thermonuclear warfare has a high potential to end civilization, perhaps
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,740:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: permanently. But it could severely wound civilization and set back human progress to the Stone
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,741:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Age.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,741:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,742:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  任何战争在局部基础上都是悲剧和困难的。然后一些战争是文明终结的，或有这种潜力。全球热核战争有很高的可能性终结文明，可能是永久性的。但它可能严重伤害文明，将人类进步倒退到石器时代。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,742:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,745:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  We want to prioritize avoiding civilizational risks over things that are painful and tragic on
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,746:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: a local level, but are not civilizational risks.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,746:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,747:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我们希望优先考虑避免文明风险，而不是那些在局部层面上痛苦和悲剧但不是文明风险的事情。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,747:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,748:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  in eastern North Africa and Italy. All his friends were killed in front of him. He would
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,748:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,752:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ve
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,753:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: died there too, except they finally gave him an IQ test. After the test, he was transferred to British
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,754:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: intelligence in London.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,754:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,755:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  在北非东部和意大利。他所有的朋友都在他面前被杀。他也会死在那里，除非他们最终给他做了智商测试。测试后，他被转移到伦敦的英国情报部门。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,755:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,756:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  From the war, he had extreme PTSD (post-traumatic stress disorder). Like next level. He
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,756:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: just didn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,757:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,757:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t talk. Ever. If you tried talking to him, he
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,757:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,767:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: d just tell you to shut up. He won a bunch of
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,771:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: medals. Never bragged about it once, not even hinted at it. Nothing. I found out by searching his
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,772:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: military records online. He knows the horrors of war. He would say, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,772:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,773:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: No way in hell do you want
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,773:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: war. Avoid it at all costs.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,774:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,776:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  But he died thirty years ago. How many people are alive now who
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,776:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: viscerally remember World War II? Not many.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,777:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,777:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  从战争中，他患有极端的创伤后应激障碍（PTSD）。像下一个级别。他只是不说话。永远。如果你试图和他说话，他只会告诉你闭嘴。他赢得了一堆勋章。从未吹嘘过一次，甚至没有暗示过。什么都没有。我通过在线搜索他的军事记录发现的。他知道战争的恐怖。他会说，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,777:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,778:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 你绝对不想要战争。不惜一切代价避免它。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,778:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,779:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 但他三十年前去世了。现在有多少人发自内心地记得第二次世界大战？不多。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,779:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,780:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I recommend people read about World War I warfare in detail. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,780:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,781:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s rough. The sheer
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,782:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: number of people who died is mind boggling. There
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,782:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,783:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s a saying from World War I, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,783:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,783:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Young boys who
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,784:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,784:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,785:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t know each other, killing each other on behalf of old men that do know each other.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,785:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,786:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  What the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,786:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: hell is the point of that?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,787:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,787:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我建议人们详细阅读关于第一次世界大战的战争。这很残酷。死亡人数之多令人难以置信。第一次世界大战有一句话，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,787:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,788:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 互不相识的年轻男孩，代表互相认识的老人互相残杀。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,788:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,789:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 这到底有什么意义？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,789:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,796:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Something must stop the cycle of reciprocal violence. Something must stop it or it will
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,797:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: never stop. Just eye for an eye, tooth for a tooth, limb for a limb, life for a life, forever and ever.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,798:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,798:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  必须有什么东西阻止相互暴力的循环。必须有什么东西阻止它，否则它永远不会停止。只是以眼还眼，以牙还牙，以肢还肢，以命还命，永远永远。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,798:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,799:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I recommend reading Isaac Asimov
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,799:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,803:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s Foundation series. The premise is protecting society
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,804:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: through a dark age. My guess is there will be another dark age at some point.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,804:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,805:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我建议阅读艾萨克·阿西莫夫的《基地》系列。前提是在黑暗时代保护社会。我的猜测是某个时候会有另一个黑暗时代。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,805:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,806:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,806:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,807:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: m not predicting we
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,807:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,808:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re about to enter a dark age. But there is some probability that we
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,809:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: will, particularly if there
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,809:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,814:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s a third world war. We need to ensure there are enough of us, enough of a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,815:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: seed of human civilization to revive civilization and shorten the length of a dark age.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,815:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,816:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我不是预测我们即将进入黑暗时代。但有一些可能性我们会，特别是如果有第三次世界大战。我们需要确保有足够多的人，足够多的人类文明种子来复兴文明并缩短黑暗时代的长度。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,816:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,817:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Asimov
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,817:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,818:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s Zeroth Law: Take the set of actions most likely to support the humanity of the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,819:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: future.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,819:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,820:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  阿西莫夫第零定律：采取最有可能支持未来人类的行动集合。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,820:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Regulation Accumulation
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,821:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 法规累积
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,821:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,823:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Be cautious about the gradual creep of regulations and bureaucracy. Humans die, but the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,824:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: laws they created don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,824:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,824:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,825:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,826:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  对法规和官僚主义的逐渐蔓延要保持谨慎。人类会死，但他们创建的法律不会。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,826:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,843:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The early auto industry was a hotbed of innovation at the beginning of the twentieth
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,851:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: century. Many regulations were since added in attempts to protect consumers. The government tends
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,854:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: to stand in the way of innovation, even with good intentions. Sometimes they overregulate industries
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,854:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: to the point where innovation becomes difficult.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,855:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,856:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  早期汽车工业在二十世纪初是创新的温床。此后添加了许多法规试图保护消费者。政府倾向于阻碍创新，即使是出于好意。有时他们对行业监管过度，以至于创新变得困难。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,856:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,857:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,857:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,860:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s crazy how much regulation there is. You can argue and get these things changed, but it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,860:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: takes ages. One of the things we
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,861:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,869:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re trying to change is the requirement for side mirrors. Why should
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,872:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: cars need them when tiny video cameras can display an image inside the car instead? I met with the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,872:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: US Secretary of Transportation and asked, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,872:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,873:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Can you change this regulation?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,873:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,874:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Still, nothing has
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,874:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: happened. That was in 2011.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,875:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,875:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  有多少监管是疯狂的。你可以争论并让这些改变，但需要很长时间。我们试图改变的事情之一是后视镜的要求。当微型摄像头可以在车内显示图像时，为什么汽车需要它们？我会见了美国交通部长并问，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,876:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,876:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 你能改变这个规定吗？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,876:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,877:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 仍然，什么都没有发生。那是 2011 年。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,877:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,877:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I am incredibly compliant.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,878:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,878:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我非常合规。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,878:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,879:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  We wouldn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,879:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,881:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t be allowed to put cars on the road if we did not comply with the vast body of
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,881:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: automotive regulations. If we don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,882:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,882:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t comply with all of them we can
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,882:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,883:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t sell the car. If we don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,883:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,888:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t comply
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,891:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: with all of the regulations for SpaceX or for Starlink, they shut us down. My companies are
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,891:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: cumulatively overseen by a few hundred regulatory agencies.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,892:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,892:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  如果我们不遵守大量的汽车法规，我们就不被允许将汽车上路。如果我们不遵守所有这些规定，我们就不能销售汽车。如果我们不遵守 SpaceX 或 Starlink 的所有规定，他们会关闭我们。我的公司累计受到数百家监管机构的监督。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,893:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,893:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Once in a while, there will be something I disagree with. If I disagree with a regulation, it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,894:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,901:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,905:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: because I believe a regulation meant to do good does not actually do good. I believe it is my
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,906:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: obligation to object to a regulation that does not serve the public good. That
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,906:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,907:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s the only time I object.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,907:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,908:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  偶尔，会有我不同意的东西。如果我不同意一项规定，那是因为我认为一项规定旨在做好事但实际上没有做好事。我认为我有义务反对一项不符合公共利益的法规。那是我唯一反对的时候。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,908:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,909:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Q: But you typically don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,909:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,910:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t like regulations, correct? We read many articles about you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,911:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: pushing back on the regulators.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,911:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,912:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  问：但你通常不喜欢法规，对吗？我们读了很多关于你抵制监管者的文章。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,912:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,913:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,913:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,919:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t take what the media presents as the whole picture. This is not an exaggeration: There
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,920:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: are probably 100 million regulations that my companies comply with. There are maybe five that we
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,921:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: disagree with.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,921:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,922:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  不要把媒体呈现的当作全貌。这不是夸张：我的公司可能遵守了 1 亿条法规。我们不同意的可能有五条。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,922:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,936:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  If you sum up only the arguments I had with hundreds of regulators over decades, it can
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,942:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: sound terrible. The media does this without mentioning the 100 million regulations we agreed with.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,943:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: They focus only on the five I disagreed with. People only hear about the five and think, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,944:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,944:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Wow, this
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,945:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: guy
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,945:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,945:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s a real maverick.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,946:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,946:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,947:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  如果你只总结我几十年来与数百名监管者的争论，听起来可能很糟糕。媒体这样做而不提及我们同意的 1 亿条法规。他们只关注我不同意的五条。人们只听到这五条并想，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,947:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,948:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 哇，这家伙真是个特立独行的人。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,948:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,949:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,949:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The natural tendency is for the hand of the government to get heavier every year.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,950:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,950:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  自然的趋势是政府的手每年都变得更重。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,951:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,955:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The government told me if SpaceX hired anyone who is not a permanent resident of the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,956:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: United States I would go to prison. The presumption is that if somebody
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,956:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,962:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s not a permanent resident,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,964:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: they might take the rocket technology to countries that would use it to cause harm to the United
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,965:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: States. Okay, solid reasoning. I agree.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,965:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,966:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  政府告诉我，如果 SpaceX 雇佣任何不是美国永久居民的人，我会进监狱。假设是，如果某人不是永久居民，他们可能会将火箭技术带到会对美国造成伤害的国家。好吧，合理的推理。我同意。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,966:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,967:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Then a few years later, the Department of Justice sued SpaceX for failing to hire asylum
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,968:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: seekers.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,968:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,969:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  然后几年后，司法部起诉 SpaceX 未能雇佣寻求庇护者。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,969:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,970:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  If we hire anyone who
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,970:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,971:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s not a permanent resident, we go to prison. Now, we
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,971:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,972:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re told if we
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,972:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,973:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,974:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t hire asylum seekers, we also go to prison. That seems insane.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,974:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,975:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  如果我们雇佣任何不是永久居民的人，我们进监狱。现在，我们被告知如果我们不雇佣寻求庇护者，我们也进监狱。这似乎很疯狂。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,975:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,987:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  We have to work to actively reduce the number of laws and regulations. Otherwise, as
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,992:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: more laws and regulations are passed, eventually everything becomes illegal. You get into these
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,993:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Orwellian situations where going left is illegal and going right is illegal. There isn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,993:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,994:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t anything you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,994:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: can do that is legal. That
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,995:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,996:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s why the California High-Speed Rail project has built only a tiny section
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,996:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: that doesn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:02,996:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,000:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t even have rail on it, even after spending several billion dollars. California has made
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,001:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: almost everything illegal. No one can make progress. This is why we can
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,001:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,002:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t build high-speed rail in
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,002:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: America. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,002:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,003:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s illegal.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,003:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,004:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我们必须努力积极减少法律和法规的数量。否则，随着更多法律和法规通过，最终一切都变得非法。你会陷入这些奥威尔式的情况，向左走是非法的，向右走也是非法的。你没有什么可以做的合法的。这就是为什么加州高铁项目只建了一小段，甚至上面没有铁轨，即使花费了数十亿美元。加州几乎让一切都非法了。没有人能取得进展。这就是为什么我们不能在美国建造高铁。这是非法的。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,004:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,005:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,005:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,005:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s not an engineering failure; it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,006:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,006:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s the regulations. Something needs to change. Civilization
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,007:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,008:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s arteries harden over time and we get less and less done because there
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,009:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,009:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s a rule against everything.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,009:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,010:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  这不是工程失败；这是法规。需要改变一些东西。文明的动脉随着时间的推移而硬化，我们完成的事情越来越少，因为每件事都有规定反对。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,010:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,011:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Obviously we don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,011:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,019:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t want world wars, but wars can have some silver lining. After World
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,021:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Wars I and II, there were huge resets on rules and regulations. Historically, what has cleared away
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,022:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the cobwebs of regulation has been war.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,022:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,023:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  显然我们不想要世界大战，但战争可能有一些好处。在第一次和第二次世界大战之后，规则和法规有了巨大的重置。从历史上看，清除法规蜘蛛网的是战争。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,023:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,024:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Regulators and legislators create new rules and regulations every year, but don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,024:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,025:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t put any
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,025:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: effort into removing them.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,025:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,026:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  监管者和立法者每年都创建新的规则和法规，但不努力移除它们。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,026:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,027:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Without a cleansing function for rules and regulations, they accumulate every year. This is
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,028:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: a problem.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,028:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,029:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  如果没有对规则和法规的清理功能，它们每年都会累积。这是个问题。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,029:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,030:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Eventually, we
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,030:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,031:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re like Gulliver, tied down by thousands of little strings. You can
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,031:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,036:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t move.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,038:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: No single one of those strings is the issue. The problem is there are a million of them. We lose our
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,039:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: freedom, one regulation at a time.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,039:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,040:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  最终，我们像格列佛，被数千根小绳子绑住。你不能动。那些绳子中没有一根是问题。问题是有百万根。我们失去自由，一次一条法规。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,040:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Unsustainable Energy
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,041:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 不可持续能源
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,041:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,042:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Generating sustainable energy is the biggest environmental issue that we face.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,042:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,043:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  产生可持续能源是我们面临的最大环境问题。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,043:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,044:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,044:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,045:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: m much less of a climate alarmist than people might think. But we
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,045:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,061:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re running this climate
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,072:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: experiment, which we know is pointless because eventually we will run out of coal, oil, and gas.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,078:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: This experiment is not going to last forever. We have to transition to something that is long term
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,079:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: because we will run out of hydrocarbons to burn. Let
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,080:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,080:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s just not run the experiment.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,081:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,081:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我不像人们想象的那样是气候危言耸听者。但我们正在进行这个气候实验，我们知道这是毫无意义的，因为最终我们会用完煤、石油和天然气。这个实验不会永远持续。我们必须过渡到一些长期的东西，因为我们会用完可燃烧的碳氢化合物。让我们不要进行这个实验。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,082:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,082:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Long term, most of civilization
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,083:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,085:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s energy is going to come from solar. Obviously the sun
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,086:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: only shines during the day and sometimes it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,086:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,088:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s cloudy, so we need batteries. Solar will be the main
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,089:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: way that civilization is powered long term.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,089:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,090:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  长期来看，大部分文明的能源将来自太阳能。显然太阳只在白天照耀，有时多云，所以我们需要电池。太阳能将是文明长期供电的主要方式。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,090:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,091:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  If humanity had to get all of its energy from the sun, it could.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,091:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,092:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  如果人类必须从太阳获取所有能源，它可以。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,092:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,093:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Sometimes people say, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,094:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,094:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: What about clouds?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,095:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,095:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Here is my response, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,096:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,096:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Do plants grow?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,097:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,099:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,099:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: They grow through a solar-powered chemical reaction. If plants grow, you have solar power.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,100:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,100:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  有时人们说，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,101:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,101:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 云怎么办？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,102:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,102:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 我的回应是，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,103:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,103:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 植物生长吗？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,104:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,104:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 它们通过太阳能化学反应生长。如果植物生长，你就有太阳能。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,105:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,106:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  But between now and then we need to maintain nuclear power. I can
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,106:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,113:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t emphasize enough,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,116:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: please do not shut down the nuclear power plants and please reopen the ones that have been shut
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,117:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: down. It is total madness to shut them down. Total madness.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,117:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,118:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  但在现在和那时之间我们需要维持核能。我再怎么强调也不为过，请不要关闭核电站，请重新开放那些已经关闭的。关闭它们是完全疯狂的。完全疯狂。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,118:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,118:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,119:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,128:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: m in favor of nuclear power in any place not subject to extreme natural disasters. Nuclear
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,130:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: power is a great way to generate electricity. Obviously we should not be starting up coal plants and
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,130:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: shutting down nuclear plants. It doesn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,131:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,133:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t make any sense at all. Coal plants are a hundred to a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,134:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: thousand times worse for our health than nuclear power plants.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,134:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,135:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我支持在任何不受极端自然灾害影响的地方使用核能。核能是发电的好方法。显然我们不应该启动燃煤电厂并关闭核电站。这完全没有意义。燃煤电厂对我们的健康危害比核电站大一百到一千倍。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,135:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,137:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  How many people have actually died from nuclear accidents? Practically none. How many
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,138:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: people have died from coal plants? It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,138:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,138:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s a very big number.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,139:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,139:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  有多少人实际上死于核事故？几乎没有。有多少人死于燃煤电厂？这是一个非常大的数字。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,140:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,140:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,140:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,141:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s a national security risk to shut these things down. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,141:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,143:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s not only bad for the climate; it is
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,143:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: a national security risk as well. People don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,144:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,147:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t understand that coal power plant emissions cause many
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,147:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: deaths every year. They are far more dangerous than nuclear power plants.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,148:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,148:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  关闭这些东西是国家安全风险。这不仅对气候有害；也是国家安全风险。人们不明白燃煤电厂排放每年导致许多死亡。它们比核电站危险得多。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,148:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,167:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The future of energy will be primarily solar with wind. We absolutely need stationary
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,176:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: storage batteries because of the intermittency of both solar and wind. There will also be
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,180:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: hydroelectric, geothermal, and nuclear—these are all good. Battery cell production is the fundamental
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,181:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: rate-limiter slowing down a sustainable-energy future. Very important problem.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,181:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,182:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  能源的未来将主要是太阳能和风能。由于太阳能和风能的间歇性，我们绝对需要固定存储电池。还将有水力发电、地热和核能——这些都是好的。电池单元生产是减缓可持续能源未来的基本速率限制器。非常重要的问题。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,182:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,184:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  We want to move as quickly as we can to a solar electric economy. The faster we get there,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,185:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the better it is for the world.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,185:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,186:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我们希望尽快过渡到太阳能经济。我们越快到达那里，对世界越好。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,186:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,188:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  We could probably have a civilization that is a hundred times as energy intensive as we
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,188:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: currently have it.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,189:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,189:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我们可能拥有一个能源密集度是目前一百倍的文明。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,190:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Misaligned Artificial Superintelligence
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,190:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 错位的人工超级智能
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,191:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,191:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,192:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,192:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ve never seen any technology grow as fast as AI, and I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,193:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,193:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ve seen a lot of technology.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,194:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,194:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我从未见过任何技术像 AI 那样快速增长，我见过很多技术。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,195:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,195:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  We
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,196:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,200:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re quite close to digital superintelligence, which will be smarter than any human at
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,200:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: anything. Hopefully they will discover new physics; I think they will. They
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,201:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,202:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re definitely going to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,202:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: invent new technologies.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,203:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,203:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我们非常接近数字超级智能，它将比任何人类在任何事情上都更聪明。希望它们会发现新的物理学；我认为它们会。它们肯定会发明新技术。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,204:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,205:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Digital superintelligence is also a potential great filter. I hope it isn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,205:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,206:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t, but it might be.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,206:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,207:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  数字超级智能也是一个潜在的大过滤器。我希望不是，但可能是。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,207:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,208:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  We must be very careful in how we develop AI. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,208:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,219:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s a great power, and with great power
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,225:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: comes great responsibility. It would be wise for us to have (at least) an objective third party who can
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,226:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: go in and understand what the various leading players are doing with AI. Even if there
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,226:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,228:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s no
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,229:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: enforcement ability, at least they can voice concerns publicly.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,229:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,230:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我们必须非常小心如何开发 AI。这是一个巨大的力量，伴随着巨大的力量而来的是巨大的责任。我们明智的做法是拥有（至少）一个客观的第三方，可以进入并了解各个主要参与者正在用 AI 做什么。即使没有执法能力，至少他们可以公开表达担忧。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,230:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,231:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The pace of progress matters a lot. We don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,231:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,233:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t want to develop digital superintelligence too
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,234:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: far before being able to do a merged brain–computer interface.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,234:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,234:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  进步的速度非常重要。我们不希望在能够进行合并的脑机接口之前将数字超级智能发展得太远。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,235:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,235:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  We
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,235:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,236:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re on the cusp of an artificial intelligence revolution. For a very long time, we
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,236:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,237:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ve been
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,238:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the smartest creatures on Earth. That
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,238:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,239:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s been our defining characteristic. Now, what happens when
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,239:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: there
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,239:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,240:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s something way smarter than us?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,240:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,241:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我们正处于人工智能革命的边缘。很长一段时间以来，我们一直是地球上最聪明的生物。那是我们的定义特征。现在，当有比我们聪明得多的东西时会发生什么？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,241:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,242:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  AI is obviously going to surpass human intelligence by a lot. There
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,242:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,243:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s some risk that
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,243:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: something bad happens, something humanity can
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,244:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,248:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t control after that point. Either a small group of
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,249:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: people monopolize AI power, the AI goes rogue, or something like that. It may not, but it could.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,249:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,250:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  AI 显然将大幅超越人类智能。有一些风险会发生不好的事情，在那之后人类无法控制的事情。要么一小群人垄断 AI 权力，要么 AI 失控，或类似的事情。可能不会，但可能会。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,250:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,257:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  If AI superintelligence is linked to human will, particularly a large number of humans, it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,258:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: would be guided to an outcome desired by a large group, because it would be a function of their
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,259:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: will.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,259:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,260:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  如果 AI 超级智能与人类意志相连，特别是大量人类，它将被引导到一个大群体期望的结果，因为它将是他们意志的函数。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,260:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,263:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  If our communication bandwidth is too low, our integration with AI would be weak. The
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,264:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: AI is going to go off by itself, because we
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,264:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,265:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re too slow to talk to or work with. The faster the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,266:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: communication, the more we
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,266:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,267:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ll be integrated—the slower the communication, the less.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,267:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,268:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  如果我们的通信带宽太低，我们与 AI 的整合将很弱。AI 将自己离开，因为我们太慢无法与之交谈或合作。通信越快，我们整合得越多——通信越慢，整合越少。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,268:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,269:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The more separate we are—the more the AI is 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,269:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,269:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: other
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,270:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,273:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: —the more likely it is to turn on us. If the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,274:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: AIs are all separate and vastly more intelligent than us, how do we ensure they don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,275:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,276:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t have
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,277:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: optimization functions contrary to the best interests of humanity?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,277:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,278:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我们越分离——AI 越
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,278:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,278:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 其他
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,279:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,279:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ——它越可能反对我们。如果 AI 都是分离的并且比我们聪明得多，我们如何确保它们没有与人类最佳利益相反的优化功能？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,280:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,289:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  We may end up with the choice of either being useless and left behind, or being a pet—like a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,291:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: house cat—unless we figure out some way to be symbiotic and merge with AI. (A house cat would be a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,292:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: good outcome, by the way.)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,292:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,293:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我们最终可能面临要么无用并被抛在后面，要么成为宠物——像家猫——的选择，除非我们想出某种方式共生并与 AI 合并。（顺便说一句，家猫会是一个好结果。）
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,293:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,294:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Q: How do we reduce the risk that AI becomes a 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,294:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,295:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: great filter
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,295:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,296:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,296:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,297:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  问：我们如何降低 AI 成为
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,297:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,298:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 大过滤器
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,298:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,298:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 的风险？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,299:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,311:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  We must build benign AI that loves humanity. It is extremely important to build AI with a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,316:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: rigorous adherence to truth, even if that truth is politically incorrect. My intuition is AI could be
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,316:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: very dangerous if you force it to believe things that are not true.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,317:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,318:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我们必须建造热爱人类的良性 AI。建造 AI 时严格遵守真理极其重要，即使那个真理在政治上不正确。我的直觉是，如果你强迫 AI 相信不真实的事情，它可能非常危险。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,318:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,333:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Jeff Hinton invented a number of the key principles in artificial intelligence. He puts the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,339:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: probability of annihilating the human race around 10–20 percent. Mitigating the risks of AI is
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,340:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: important. We should be concerned about having AI be vastly beyond us and decoupled from human
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,341:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: will.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,341:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,342:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  杰夫·辛顿发明了许多人工智能的关键原理。他将灭绝人类种族的可能性定为 10-20%。减轻 AI 的风险很重要。我们应该担心 AI 远远超越我们并与人类意志脱节。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,342:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,348:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  You get dangerous outcomes when you program AI to be politically correct. Things that
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,349:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: may seem relatively innocuous now will not be in the future if AI has immense power.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,349:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,350:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  当你编程 AI 为政治正确时，你会得到危险的结果。如果 AI 拥有巨大权力，现在看起来相对无害的事情在未来将不会无害。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,350:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,370:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Take the Google Gemini example, where it refused to produce a picture of George
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,382:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Washington as a white man. In fact, any historical figure would automatically be made diverse
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,385:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: because it had been programmed to insist on diversity. That sounds okay at first, but what if the AI
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,386:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: has so much power it can actually enforce diversity?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,386:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,387:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  以 Google Gemini 为例，它拒绝生成乔治·华盛顿作为白人的图片。事实上，任何历史人物都会自动变得多样化，因为它被编程为坚持多样性。起初听起来没问题，但如果 AI 有如此大的权力实际上可以执行多样性呢？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,387:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,391:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  It could decide there are too many of one kind of people, and kill people until the diversity
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,391:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: amount is what it has been programmed to believe is 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,392:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,392:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: correct.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,393:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,393:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,393:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  它可能决定有一种人太多了，并杀人直到多样性数量是它被编程相信是
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,394:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,394:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 正确
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,394:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,395:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 的。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,395:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,397:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Mark my words: If we do not program AI to be as truthful as possible, that is where it will
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,398:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: go. That is where the danger lies.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,398:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,399:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  记住我的话：如果我们不编程 AI 尽可能真实，那就是它将去的地方。那就是危险所在。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,399:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,400:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Superpowerful AI programmed in this way has severe civilization-level risk. I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,400:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,406:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ve seen
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,410:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: quite a few technologies develop, but none with this level of risk. Artificial general intelligence
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,411:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: (AGI) is a significantly higher risk than nuclear weapons, in my opinion.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,411:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,412:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  以这种方式编程的超级强大 AI 具有严重的文明级风险。我见过相当多的技术发展，但没有一个具有这种级别的风险。在我看来，人工通用智能（AGI）的风险比核武器高得多。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,412:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,439:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The core plot premise of 2001: A Space Odyssey was that things went wrong when they
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,453:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: forced the AI (known as HAL 9000) to lie. The AI was not allowed to let the crew know about the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,458:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: monolith that they were going to see but it also had to take the crew to the monolith. The conclusion
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,459:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: of the AI was to kill the crew and take their bodies to the monolith.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,459:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,460:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  《2001：太空漫游》的核心情节前提是，当他们强迫 AI（称为 HAL 9000）撒谎时，事情出错了。AI 不被允许让船员知道他们将看到的巨石，但它也必须带船员去巨石。AI 的结论是杀死船员并将他们的尸体带到巨石。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,460:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,461:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The lesson there is: Don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,461:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,462:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t force an AI to lie or do things that are axiomatically
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,463:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: incompatible, or mutually impossible. Don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,463:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,464:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t force AI to lie, even if the truth is unpleasant.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,464:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,465:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  那里的教训是：不要强迫 AI 撒谎或做公理上不兼容或相互不可能的事情。不要强迫 AI 撒谎，即使真相令人不快。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,465:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,467:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Honesty is the best policy. We want to have a maximally truthful AI, even if what it says is
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,467:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: not 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,468:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,468:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: politically correct.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,468:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,469:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  We want it to focus on being as accurate as possible.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,469:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,470:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  诚实是最好的策略。我们希望拥有一个 максимально真实的 AI，即使它说的不是
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,470:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,471:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 政治正确
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,471:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,471:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 的。我们希望它专注于尽可能准确。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,472:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,472:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I can
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,473:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,477:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t emphasize this enough. A rigorous adherence to truth is the most important thing for
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,478:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: AI safety. And, obviously, empathy for humanity and life as we know it.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,478:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,479:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我再怎么强调也不为过。严格遵守真理是 AI 安全最重要的事情。而且，显然，对我们所知的人类和生命的同情。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,479:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,480:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  AI mirrors the mistakes of its creators.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,480:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,481:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  AI 反映了其创造者的错误。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,481:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,482:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Q: Do you think anyone should be trying to regulate this?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,482:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,483:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  问：你认为有人应该试图监管这个吗？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,483:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,487:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The general philosophy about regulation is there needs to be some government oversight
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,488:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: when something is a danger to the public. People often don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,488:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,489:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t understand how slow regulation tends
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,490:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: to work. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,490:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,490:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s slow.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,491:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,491:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  关于监管的一般理念是，当某事对公众有危险时需要一些政府监督。人们经常不理解监管往往工作得有多慢。它很慢。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,492:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,513:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Usually, some new technology will cause damage or death. Then there will be an outcry.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,524:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Then there will be an investigation. Years will pass. Then there will be an insight committee. Then
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,528:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: they get to rule-making. Then there will be oversight, and eventually regulation and enforcement.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,529:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: This all takes years. This is the normal course of new regulations.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,529:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,530:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  通常，一些新技术会造成损害或死亡。然后会有抗议。然后会有调查。几年会过去。然后会有一个洞察委员会。然后他们进入规则制定。然后会有监督，最终是监管和执法。这一切都需要数年时间。这是新法规的正常过程。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,531:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,552:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Look at automotive regulations. The auto industry successfully fought any regulations on
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,563:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: seat belts for more than a decade, even though the numbers were extremely obvious. If you had a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,567:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: seat belt on, you were far less likely to die or be seriously injured. Unequivocally. Eventually, after
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,567:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: many people died for years, regulators insisted on seat belts.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,568:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,568:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  看看汽车法规。汽车工业成功地抵制了任何关于安全带的法规超过十年，即使数字非常明显。如果你系上安全带，你死亡或受重伤的可能性要小得多。毫无疑问。最终，在许多人死亡多年后，监管机构坚持要求安全带。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,568:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,569:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  This time frame is not relevant to artificial intelligence. You can
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,569:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,570:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t take ten years from the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,571:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: point it becomes dangerous. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,571:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,571:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s too late.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,572:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,572:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  这个时间框架与人工智能无关。你不能从它变得危险的那一刻起花十年时间。太晚了。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,573:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,575:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I was trying to sound the alarm on the AI front for quite a while, but it was clearly having
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,575:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: no impact. I realized we couldn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,576:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,576:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t stop it, so we
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,576:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,577:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ll have to try to develop it in a good way.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,577:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,578:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我试图在 AI 前线敲响警钟相当长一段时间，但显然没有影响。我意识到我们无法阻止它，所以我们必须尝试以好的方式开发它。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,578:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,585:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  This is what we are addressing at Neuralink. Our initial goal is to help people who are
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,587:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: quadriplegics or tetraplegics be able to operate their phone or computer. There is always some risk
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,588:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: in the beginning, because it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,588:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,589:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s new technology. The risk–reward trade has to make sense. If you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,589:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,593:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,595:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: quadriplegic and with the Neuralink you can operate a phone even faster than someone with
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,596:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: working thumbs, that would be a life-changer.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,596:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,597:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  这就是我们在 Neuralink 解决的问题。我们的最初目标是帮助四肢瘫痪或高位截瘫的人能够操作他们的手机或电脑。开始时总是有一些风险，因为这是新技术。风险 - 回报权衡必须有意义。如果你是四肢瘫痪并且使用 Neuralink 你可以比有工作拇指的人更快地操作手机，那将改变生活。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,597:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,605:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  There are a bunch of other things that could be addressed, like extreme depression or
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,607:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: morbid obesity, where people die at age thirty-five. We could literally change the setting in your
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,608:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: brain and turn off hunger.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,608:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,608:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  还有很多其他事情可以解决，比如极度抑郁或病态肥胖，人们在三十五岁死亡。我们实际上可以改变你大脑中的设置并关闭饥饿感。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,609:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,617:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Memory enhancement can help people who have memory problems, which could allow
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,620:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: them to function well much later in life. Mental disablement of one kind or another happens to all of
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,620:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: us if we get old enough.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,621:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,621:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  记忆增强可以帮助有记忆问题的人，这可以让他们在生命后期更好地 functioning。如果我们活得足够老，某种形式的精神残疾会发生在所有人身上。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,622:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,643:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Brain–computer interfaces are stunning technology. There may be a way to take the signals
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,652:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: from the motor cortex in the brain and send signals to the spine past where the neurons are broken. If
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,655:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: so, paralyzed people could move their bodies again. We may enable people to walk again, which
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,656:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: would be wild. Even full-body reanimation. Jesus-level stuff.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,656:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,657:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  脑机接口是令人震惊的技术。可能有一种方法可以从大脑的运动皮层获取信号，并将信号发送到神经元断裂处的脊柱。如果是这样，瘫痪的人可以再次移动他们的身体。我们可能让人们再次行走，那将很疯狂。甚至全身复活。耶稣级别的东西。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,658:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Population Collapse
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,658:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 人口崩溃
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,659:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,659:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  A low birth rate is a slow death for a civilization.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,660:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,660:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  低出生率对文明来说是缓慢死亡。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,661:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,670:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Most historians overlook the role of low birth rates in the decline of civilizations. Will
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,673:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Durant has it correct in The Story of Civilization. A counterintuitive thing happens when
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,674:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: civilizations are prosperous for too long—the birth rate declines.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,675:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,675:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  大多数历史学家忽视了低出生率在文明衰落中的作用。威尔·杜兰特在《文明的故事》中说得对。当文明繁荣太久时会发生违反直觉的事情——出生率下降。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,676:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,677:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The same thing happened in ancient Rome. Julius Caesar and Augustus saw the problem
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,677:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: but couldn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,678:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,679:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t solve it. Rome fell because the Romans stopped making Romans. That was the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,680:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: fundamental issue.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,680:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,681:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  同样的事情发生在古罗马。朱利叶斯·凯撒和奥古斯都看到了问题但无法解决它。罗马沦陷是因为罗马人停止制造罗马人。那是根本问题。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,681:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,688:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Yes, there were other causes. They had a series of malaria epidemics, plagues, and
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,689:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: whatnot. But they had those before, too. It became fatal when the birth rate was far lower than the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,690:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: death rate.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,690:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,691:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  是的，还有其他原因。他们有一系列疟疾流行、瘟疫和其他什么。但他们以前也有过那些。当出生率远低于死亡率时，它变得致命。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,691:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,692:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  If the birth rate is below the replacement rate and that trend continues, we will eventually
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,692:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: disappear. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,693:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,693:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s elementary. At a base level: no humans, no humanity.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,694:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,694:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  如果出生率低于更替率并且这种趋势继续，我们最终将消失。这是基本的。在基本层面上：没有人类，就没有人性。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,694:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,712:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Durant looked at one civilization after another, hundreds of them. They all went through
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,720:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the same cycle. When the civilization was under stress, the birth rate was high. But as soon as there
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,722:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: were no external enemies or they had an extended period of prosperity, the birth rate inevitably
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,722:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: dropped. Every time. I don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,723:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,723:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t believe there
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,724:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,724:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s a single exception.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,724:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,725:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  杜兰特查看了一个又一个文明，数百个。他们都经历了相同的周期。当文明处于压力之下时，出生率很高。但一旦没有外部敌人或他们有一段长期的繁荣，出生率不可避免地下降。每次都是。我不相信有一个例外。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,725:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,726:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Population collapse is a real and immediate concern.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,726:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,726:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  人口崩溃是一个真实且紧迫的问题。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,727:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,744:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Twenty years ago, I noticed birth rates were trending toward being below replacement
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,752:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: level in every wealthy country. We always have to be cautious about extrapolating any demographic
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,755:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: curve…but if you extrapolate the curves, if these trends continue, these countries will dwindle into
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,755:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: insignificance. They might completely die out.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,756:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,756:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  二十年前，我注意到每个富裕国家的出生率都趋向于低于更替水平。我们总是必须谨慎推断任何人口曲线……但如果你推断曲线，如果这些趋势继续，这些国家将减少到无足轻重。它们可能完全灭绝。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,757:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,757:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,757:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,761:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s easy to predict what the population of any given country will be. Just take how many
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,761:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: babies were born, multiply that by life expectancy, and that
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,762:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,763:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s what the population will be if the birth
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,764:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: rate continues to that level. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,764:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,764:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s very straightforward.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,765:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,765:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  很容易预测任何给定国家的人口将是多少。只需计算有多少婴儿出生，乘以预期寿命，如果出生率继续到那个水平，那就是人口将是多少。这非常简单。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,766:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,766:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  You can see the demographic trends clearly. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,767:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,767:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s a very slow-moving ship. You know who
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,768:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,769:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,770:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: going to be an adult in twenty years based on who was born last year.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,770:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,771:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  你可以清楚地看到人口趋势。这是一艘移动非常缓慢的船。你知道谁将在二十年后成为成年人，基于去年出生的人。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,771:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,781:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  China had a one-child policy. About 2015 they changed it to a two-child policy, then a few
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,785:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: years later they changed it to a three-child policy. The birth rate kept plummeting the whole time.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,785:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: They recently had their lowest growth rate ever. China
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,786:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,789:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s birth rate reached 40 percent below
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,790:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: replacement. Japan is far along in this. Japan declined by six hundred thousand people in 2021.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,791:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,791:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  中国有一孩政策。大约 2015 年他们将其改为二孩政策，然后几年后改为三孩政策。出生率一直暴跌。他们最近经历了有史以来最低的增长率。中国的出生率达到低于更替率 40%。日本在这方面走得非常远。日本在 2021 年减少了 60 万人。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,792:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,799:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The US has been below replacement rates since the early 1970s. The only reasons the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,801:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: population is increasing are immigration and people living longer. People living longer is why the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,801:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: population of Earth isn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,802:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,802:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t plummeting already—but it will.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,803:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,803:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  美国自 1970 年代初以来一直低于更替率。人口增长的唯一原因是移民和人们活得更长。人们活得更长是地球人口还没有暴跌的原因——但会暴跌。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,804:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,804:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Q: There seem to be a lot of people concerned about overpopulation. Isn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,805:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,806:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t that more of a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,806:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: problem than underpopulation?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,807:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,807:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  问：似乎有很多人担心人口过剩。那不是比人口不足更严重的问题吗？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,808:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,808:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The biggest myth that exists right now is this 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,809:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,809:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: overpopulation
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,810:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,811:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  myth. In fact, we have a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,811:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: population collapse problem.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,812:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,812:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  目前存在的最大神话是这个
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,813:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,813:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 人口过剩
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,814:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,814:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 神话。事实上，我们有人口崩溃问题。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,815:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,818:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  They are operating on beliefs that were true in the past but are no longer true. These are not
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,819:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: subjective matters; you can look at the birth rate. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,819:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,821:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s an objective number. How many babies were
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,822:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: born? There are obvious public records of this information.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,822:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,822:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  他们的运作基于过去真实但不再真实的信念。这些不是主观问题；你可以看出出生率。这是一个客观数字。有多少婴儿出生？有这些信息的明显公共记录。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,823:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,823:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,823:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,826:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: m pro-environment, but the environmental movement has gone too far. The extremist
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,827:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: environmentalists view humans as a blight on Earth.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,827:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,827:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我支持环保，但环保运动走得太远了。极端环保主义者将人类视为地球上的祸害。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,828:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,832:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Environmentalism started out with good intentions but paved the road to hell. It started to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,832:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: view humans as bad. As a burden on the earth that it couldn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,833:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,843:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t sustain. These views are completely
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,849:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: false. Most people in the world are operating under the false impression there are too many people.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,849:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: This is not true. They think that having kids is bad for the environment. It is not.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,850:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,850:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  环保主义开始时出于好意，但铺就了通往地狱的道路。它开始将人类视为坏的。作为地球无法承受的负担。这些观点完全错误。世界上大多数人都在错误的印象下运作，认为人太多了。这不是真的。他们认为生孩子对环境有害。不是这样的。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,851:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,858:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Earth could sustain a human population ten times the current level. Do a first-principles
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,859:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: analysis. How much land area do we need to grow food? How much would that encroach on natural
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,859:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: habitats? What
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,860:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,860:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s the actual food growing potential? Is there enough water? There
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,861:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,863:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s plenty of water
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,864:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: because Earth is mostly water—70 percent water by surface area. Desalinization is very inexpensive.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,865:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: There
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,865:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,866:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s not a shortage of water, surface area, or energy to grow food.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,866:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,867:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  地球可以维持是目前水平十倍的人口。做第一性原理分析。我们需要多少土地面积来种植食物？那会侵占多少自然栖息地？实际的食物种植潜力是什么？有足够的水吗？有大量的水，因为地球大部分是水——按表面积计算 70% 是水。海水淡化非常便宜。没有水、表面积或能源短缺来种植食物。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,867:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,878:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  We need to revive the idea of having children as a social duty; otherwise civilization will
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,881:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: just die. I keep banging on the baby drum because declining birth rates have been the source of
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,882:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: civilizational collapse over and over again throughout history. Let
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,882:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,883:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s try to get this one right.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,883:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,884:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我们需要恢复将生育视为社会责任的观念；否则文明将只是死亡。我不停地敲响婴儿鼓，因为在整个历史上，出生率下降一直是文明崩溃的根源。让我们试着把这个做对。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,884:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,885:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,885:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,886:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ve heard people say many times, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,886:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,887:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: How can I bring a child into this terrible world?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,887:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,887:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,888:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,888:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: m
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,889:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: like, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,889:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,889:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Have you read any history?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,890:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: !
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,891:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Because this is a very good time. Things were way worse at every
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,892:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: other time, ever.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,892:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,892:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,893:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我听过人们说过很多次，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,893:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,894:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 我怎么能把孩子带到这个可怕的世界？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,894:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,895:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 我会说，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,895:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,895:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 你读过任何历史吗？！因为这是一个非常好的时代。在其他任何时代，事情都要糟糕得多，有史以来。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,896:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,896:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,898:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  do. It means you care about and believe in the future. I always encourage my friends to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,899:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: have kids, and I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,899:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,901:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: m happy to see many of them do. Afterward, they thank me. Not one person has
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,901:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: said they regret it. Ever.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,902:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,902:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  做。这意味着你关心并相信未来。我总是鼓励我的朋友生孩子，我很高兴看到他们很多人这样做。之后，他们感谢我。没有一个人说他们后悔。从来没有。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,903:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,904:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  We are biologically inclined to love and nurture our children. To find it deeply fulfilling. If
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,905:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: we weren
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,905:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,910:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t, we would have ceased to exist long ago. Take a wolf or some other aggressive creature.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,911:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: When that creature has babies, the mother nurtures them and is tender and caring. We
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,912:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,912:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ve all evolved
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,913:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: to love our offspring. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,913:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,914:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s a natural thing. And it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,914:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,915:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s a relatively fun thing to do
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,915:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: !
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,916:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,917:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我们在生物学上倾向于爱和养育我们的孩子。觉得这非常充实。如果不是这样，我们早就停止存在了。以狼或其他攻击性生物为例。当那个生物有宝宝时，母亲养育它们并温柔和关心。我们都进化到爱我们的后代。这是自然的事情。而且这是一件相对有趣的事情！
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,917:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,927:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I had my first kid when I was twenty-nine. As of now, I have twelve kids with three
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,929:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: women. Trying to set a good example here—having a lot of kids. I get more joy from my kids than
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,930:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: anything else in my life. I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,930:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,931:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: m not saying that
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,931:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,935:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s the main reason to have kids, we should have them
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,935:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: anyway, but my kids are certainly the greatest source of joy in my life.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,936:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,937:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我在二十九岁时有了第一个孩子。到目前为止，我和三个女人有十二个孩子。试图在这里树立一个好榜样——有很多孩子。我从我的孩子那里得到的快乐比生活中的任何其他事情都多。我不是说那是生孩子的主要原因，无论如何我们都应该有孩子，但我的孩子无疑是我生活中最大的快乐源泉。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,937:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,938:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  We should increase the population of Earth, not decrease it. Go forth and multiply.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,939:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,939:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我们应该增加地球的人口，而不是减少它。去繁衍吧。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,940:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Asteroids and Comets
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,940:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 小行星和彗星
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,941:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,941:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  A big rock will hit Earth eventually. We currently have no defense.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,942:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,942:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  一块大石头最终会撞击地球。我们目前没有任何防御。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,943:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,946:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  If you think truly long term, you realize eventually there will be some natural disaster—even if
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,947:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: it is not made by humans—that destroys all life on Earth.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,947:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,948:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  如果你真正长远地思考，你会意识到最终会有一些自然灾害——即使不是人类造成的——摧毁地球上的所有生命。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,948:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,949:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Most people are probably aware of Halley
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,949:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,950:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s Comet. Slightly under once per century,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,950:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Halley
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,950:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,952:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s Comet comes near us. There are probably many objects, many comets that have long
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,952:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: periods we simply don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,953:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,955:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t know exist. There are billions, maybe trillions of objects in the outer solar
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,955:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: system. Some of them are super-long-period comets.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,956:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,956:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  大多数人可能知道哈雷彗星。哈雷彗星每世纪略少于一次靠近我们。可能有很多物体，很多彗星有很长的周期，我们根本不知道它们存在。外太阳系有数十亿，可能数万亿个物体。其中一些是超长周期彗星。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,957:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,962:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  For example, when the comet Shoemaker-Levy hit Jupiter, it made a hole in Jupiter the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,962:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: size of Earth. If that hits Earth, that is game over. Dead. Everything is dead.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,963:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,963:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  例如，当舒梅克 - 列维彗星撞击木星时，它在木星上制造了一个地球大小的洞。如果那撞击地球，那就结束了。死了。一切都死了。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,964:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,969:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  For all of history, Earth did not have any ability to stop asteroids. Now with Starship we
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,970:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: have some ability to stop small asteroids. Large asteroids and comets are still a danger.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,970:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,971:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  在整个历史中，地球没有任何能力阻止小行星。现在有了星舰，我们有一些能力阻止小行星。大小行星和彗星仍然是危险。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,971:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,971:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  There
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,972:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,973:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s always some risk of this occurring. The probable lifespan of all forms of life is
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,974:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: much greater if we
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,974:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,975:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re a multiplanet and ultimately a multistellar civilization.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,975:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,976:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  总是有一些发生这种事的概率。如果我们是一个多行星并最终多恒星的文明，所有生命形式的可能寿命要大得多。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,976:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: BECOMING MULTIPLANETARY
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,977:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 成为多行星物种
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,977:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,983:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The window of opportunity is open right now to make life multiplanetary. We cannot
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,984:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: count on it being open for a long time. We need to take advantage while this window is open.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,984:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,985:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  让生命成为多行星的机会之窗现在就开着。我们不能指望它长时间开着。我们需要在这个窗口开着时利用它。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,986:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Becoming Multiplanetary Is an Evolutionary-Scale Event
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,986:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 成为多行星物种是一个进化级事件
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,987:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,991:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Deciding what is important through the lens of history is a good way to distinguish what
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,991:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: seems important now from what is truly important over the long term.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,992:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,992:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  通过历史视角决定什么是重要的，是区分现在看起来重要的东西和长期真正重要的东西的好方法。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:03,993:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,002:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  If we get to Mars and beyond, that will seem far more important in historical context than
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,005:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: anything else we do. Things like the Soviet Union will be forgotten or merely remembered by
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,006:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: arcane historical scholars. The invasion of Iraq won
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,006:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,007:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t even be a footnote.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,007:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,008:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  如果我们到达火星及更远，那将在历史背景下显得比我们做的任何其他事情都重要得多。像苏联这样的事情将被遗忘或仅被神秘的历史学者记住。入侵伊拉克甚至不会成为一个脚注。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,008:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,022:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  If you zoom out and look at a long period of time—a four-billion-year history of Earth and the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,029:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: evolution of life itself—there are only about six major milestones. Single-celled life, multicellular life,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,030:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the differentiation into plants and animals, the transition from ocean creatures to land mammals, and
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,031:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: consciousness.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,031:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,032:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  如果你缩小并看很长一段时间——地球四十亿年的历史和生命本身的进化——只有大约六个主要里程碑。单细胞生命、多细胞生命、分化为植物和动物、从海洋生物到陆地哺乳动物的过渡，以及意识。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,032:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,036:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Life becoming multiplanetary also belongs on this list of milestones. It would be at least as
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,037:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: important as life going from the oceans to land, probably more significant.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,037:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,037:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  生命成为多行星也属于这个里程碑列表。它将至少与生命从海洋到陆地一样重要，可能更重要。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,038:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,053:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The universe appears to be 13.8 billion years old. Earth is about 4.5 billion years old. In
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,059:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: another 0.5 billion years the sun will expand and make life impossible on Earth. If it had taken
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,060:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: consciousness 10 percent longer to evolve, it would never have evolved at all. Just 10 percent
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,060:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: longer.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,061:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,061:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  宇宙似乎是 138 亿岁。地球大约 45 亿岁。再过 5 亿年太阳将膨胀，使地球上的生命不可能。如果意识进化多花 10% 的时间，它根本就不会进化。只是 10% 更长。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,062:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,064:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Any species that does not become multiplanetary is simply waiting around until their
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,064:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: extinction event, either self-inflicted or external.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,065:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,065:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  任何不成为多行星的物种只是在等待直到它们的灭绝事件，无论是自我造成的还是外部的。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,066:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,072:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The geological history of Earth is long and complicated. There have been many extinction
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,073:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: events, not just a few. Read about the great extinction events in the fossil record. If you do, you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,073:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,076:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ll
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,076:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: see there have been five major extinctions where 80 to 90 percent of all creatures on Earth died.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,077:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,077:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  地球的地质历史漫长而复杂。有很多灭绝事件，不只是几个。阅读化石记录中的大灭绝事件。如果你这样做，你会看到有五次大灭绝，地球上 80% 到 90% 的生物死亡。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,078:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,079:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  In the Permian Extinction, 90 to 95 percent of all species were destroyed. Frankly, that
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,079:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: doesn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,079:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,086:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t tell the whole story because most of what remained were sponges, fungi, and things like that.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,087:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Unless you were a mushroom or a cockroach, you died. Almost no large life survived the Permian
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,087:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Extinction.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,088:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,088:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  在二叠纪大灭绝中，90% 到 95% 的所有物种被摧毁。坦率地说，这并没有说明全部情况，因为剩下的大部分是海绵、真菌和类似的东西。除非你是蘑菇或蟑螂，否则你死了。几乎没有大型生物在二叠纪大灭绝中幸存。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,089:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,089:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  This doesn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,089:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,091:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t count the many cases where entire continents were destroyed. That happened
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,091:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: a lot, but wouldn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,092:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,097:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t count as a major extinction. Yellowstone erupts every seven hundred thousand
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,097:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: years or so. That would destroy pretty much all life in North America. At least we
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,098:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,099:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ll see that one
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,099:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: coming now, thanks to our current technology.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,100:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,100:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  这不包括整个大陆被摧毁的许多情况。那发生了很多次，但不算作大灭绝。黄石公园大约每七十万年喷发一次。那将摧毁北美几乎所有生命。至少我们现在会看到那个到来，感谢我们目前的技术。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,101:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,108:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Humans can cause our own extinction too; other creatures didn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,110:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,111:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t have that option.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,113:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,114:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  人类也可能导致我们自己的灭绝；其他生物没有那个选项。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,114:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,115:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,115:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,116:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: m a fan of Carl Sagan. He had a great way of putting things: 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,116:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,117:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: All of our consciousness,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,118:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: all our civilizations, everything we
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,118:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,119:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ve ever known and done is on this one tiny blue dot.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,119:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,120:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,120:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我是卡尔·萨根的粉丝。他有一个很好的表达方式：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,121:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,121:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 我们所有的意识，我们所有的文明，我们知道和做过的一切都在这个小小的蓝点上。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,122:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,122:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,123:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  People get too trapped in their squabbles among humans. They don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,123:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,126:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t think of the big
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,126:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: picture. They take civilization and our continued existence for granted. We shouldn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,127:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,128:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t do that. Look
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,129:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: at the history of civilizations: they rise and they fall.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,129:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,130:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  人们太陷入人类之间的争吵。他们不考虑大局。他们认为文明和我们的持续存在是理所当然的。我们不应该那样做。看看文明的历史：它们兴起又衰落。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,131:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,131:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Now there
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,131:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,137:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s no geographic isolation. Our civilization is globalized, so civilization rises and
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,138:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: falls together. This is a big risk. This should be the most important lesson of history: Things don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,139:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,139:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,140:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: always go up.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,140:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,141:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  现在没有地理隔离。我们的文明是全球化的，所以文明一起兴衰。这是一个大风险。这应该是历史最重要的教训：事情并不总是上升。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,142:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,142:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,142:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,143:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: m fairly optimistic about the future of Earth. I don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,144:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,145:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t want people to have the wrong
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,145:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: impression, like we
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,146:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,147:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re all about to die. Things will most likely be okay for a long time on Earth.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,148:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Most likely, but nothing is certain.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,148:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,149:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我对地球的未来相当乐观。我不希望人们有错误的印象，比如我们都要死了。地球上的事情很可能很长一段时间会没事。很可能，但没有什么是一定的。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,149:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,157:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  When I talked to Stephen Hawking many years ago, he thought there was roughly a 1
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,159:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: percent chance of civilization ending in any given century. Even a 1 percent chance of
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,160:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: consciousness ending is still too much. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,160:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,163:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s worth spending a fair bit of effort to ensure we back up
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,163:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the biosphere, or build planetary redundancy. This is important. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,164:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,166:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s like Russian roulette where
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,167:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ninety-nine barrels are empty. Every century is a click. Click, click, click. Eventually…
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,168:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,168:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  当我多年前与斯蒂芬·霍金交谈时，他认为在任何给定世纪文明结束的几率大约为 1%。即使意识结束的几率为 1% 仍然太多。值得花相当多的努力确保我们备份生物圈，或建立行星冗余。这很重要。这就像俄罗斯轮盘赌，九十九个弹膛是空的。每个世纪都是一次点击。咔嗒，咔嗒，咔嗒。最终……
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,169:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,171:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Making life multiplanetary is one of the most important things we could accomplish. This
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,172:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: will help preserve the light of consciousness.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,172:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,172:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  让生命成为多行星是我们能完成的最重要的事情之一。这将有助于保护意识之光。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,173:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,174:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The probability of consciousness existing for a long time becomes much greater if we
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,174:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,177:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re on
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,178:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: two independent planets. If something catastrophic happened to Earth, life would still exist on
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,178:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: another planet.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,179:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,179:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  如果我们在两个独立的行星上，意识长期存在的概率变得大得多。如果地球发生灾难性事件，生命仍将在另一个行星上存在。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,180:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,190:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Say there was a giant meteor impact, a supervolcano, a massive nuclear war, or some super
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,194:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: virus. It might not destroy human civilization, but it could knock us back to a much lower
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,195:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: technology level, and then we risk a decline to our extinction.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,195:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,195:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  假设有巨大的陨石撞击、超级火山、大规模核战争或某种超级病毒。它可能不会摧毁人类文明，但它可能将我们击退到更低的技术水平，然后我们面临衰退到灭绝的风险。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,196:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,198:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  There are certain things we simply cannot avoid on Earth. Is it within your power or mine
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,199:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: to stop World War III? I don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,199:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,200:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t think so.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,200:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,200:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  有些事情我们在地球上根本无法避免。阻止第三次世界大战在你的能力范围内还是我的？我不这么认为。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,201:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,202:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  We may get hit by a comet like the dinosaurs. If the dinosaurs had spaceships, they
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,202:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,207:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: d
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,211:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: probably still be around. Even if we dodge all of that, the sun will continue to expand and eventually
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,212:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: engulf Earth and destroy all life in the solar system.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,212:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,213:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我们可能会被彗星撞击，就像恐龙一样。如果恐龙有宇宙飞船，它们可能仍然存在。即使我们躲过所有这些，太阳将继续膨胀并最终吞没地球并摧毁太阳系中的所有生命。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,213:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,213:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  There
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,214:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,214:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s a pretty substantial bifurcation in our future: We
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,215:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,217:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re either out there among the stars
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,218:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: on many planets or confined to Earth until some eventual extinction.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,218:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,219:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我们的未来有一个相当大的分叉：我们要么在多个行星上的群星之中，要么被限制在地球上直到某种最终的灭绝。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,219:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,220:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  This is the first moment in 4.5 billion years that it has been possible to extend life beyond
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,221:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Earth.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,221:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,222:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  这是 45 亿年来第一次有可能将生命延伸到地球之外。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,222:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: If You Love Life, Protect It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,223:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 如果你爱生命，保护它
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,223:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,224:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,224:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,236:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ve read a lot of history, including the darkest, worst parts of it. Despite all that, I still love
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,240:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: humanity. This is why I care about us becoming a multiplanet species, a spacefaring
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,241:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: civilization—because I love humanity. I wish to see it prosper and be happy.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,241:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,242:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我读了很多历史，包括其中最黑暗、最糟糕的部分。尽管如此，我仍然爱人类。这就是为什么我关心我们成为多行星物种，一个太空航行文明——因为我爱人类。我希望看到它繁荣和幸福。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,243:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,243:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,244:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,244:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: m troubled by the question, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,245:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,245:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Why have we not seen any aliens?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,246:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,247:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  It could be because
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,248:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: intelligence, or even just life, is incredibly rare. Maybe we
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,249:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,252:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re the only life in this galaxy. We should
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,253:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: do everything possible to ensure this tiny candle of consciousness does not go out.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,253:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,254:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我被这个问题困扰，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,254:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,254:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 为什么我们还没有看到任何外星人？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,255:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,255:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 这可能是因为智能，或甚至只是生命，非常罕见。也许我们是这个星系中唯一的生命。我们应该尽一切可能确保这微弱的意识蜡烛不熄灭。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,256:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,256:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Life on Earth hasn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,256:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,259:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t been around very long, and it can easily disappear. Clearly, we need to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,259:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: extend life beyond Earth and become a multiplanet species.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,260:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,260:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  地球上的生命存在时间不长，它很容易消失。显然，我们需要将生命延伸到地球之外并成为多行星物种。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,260:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,263:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  If we make life multiplanetary, there may come a day when some plants and animals die
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,264:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: out on Earth but are still alive on Mars.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,264:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,264:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  如果我们让生命成为多行星，可能会有那么一天，一些植物和动物在地球上灭绝但在火星上仍然活着。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,265:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,265:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Q: Wouldn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,266:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,266:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t it be better to use all these resources and try to resolve problems on Earth?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,267:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,267:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  问：使用所有这些资源并试图解决地球上的问题不是更好吗？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,267:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,274:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  About half my money is dedicated to help solve problems like climate change on Earth and
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,274:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: half to help establish a self-sustaining city on Mars to ensure the continuation of life of all species.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,275:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,275:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我大约一半的钱用于帮助解决地球上的问题，如气候变化，另一半用于帮助在火星上建立一个自给自足的城市，以确保所有物种生命的延续。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,276:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,276:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The point is not to move from Earth to another planet and let Earth die. That
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,277:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,277:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s not what I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,277:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,278:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: m
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,278:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: saying at all.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,279:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,279:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  重点不是从地球搬到另一个行星并让地球死亡。那根本不是我在说的。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,279:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,280:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  To put this into perspective, the amount of resources I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,280:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,283:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: m talking about for making life
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,284:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: multiplanetary would be much less than 1 percent of all resources on Earth.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,284:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,284:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  为了正确看待这一点，我所说的用于让生命成为多行星的资源量将远小于地球上所有资源的 1%。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,285:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,285:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Think of it as resource allocation. Do you think it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,286:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,286:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s worth spending half a percent of Earth
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,287:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,290:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,293:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: resources to ensure we extend consciousness to Mars and other planets, so that no single event can
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,293:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: be the end of our civilization?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,294:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,294:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  把它看作资源分配。你认为值得花费地球资源的半百分比来确保我们将意识扩展到火星和其他行星，以便没有任何单一事件可以成为我们文明的终结吗？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,294:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,297:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Redundancy of life is the defensive reason to go to Mars. But also, going to Mars is the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,298:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: grandest adventure I could possibly imagine. I can
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,298:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,317:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t think of anything more exciting, more fun, and
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,329:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: more inspiring for the future than to have a base on Mars. Great and terrible things will happen
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,333:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: along the way, just as they happened in the creation of the United States. It will be difficult, and
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,334:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: some people will probably die. But it will be incredibly inspiring.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,334:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,335:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  生命的冗余是去火星的防御性原因。而且，去火星是我能想象的最伟大的冒险。我想不出比在火星上建立基地更令人兴奋、更有趣、更鼓舞人心的未来事情。伟大和可怕的事情将一路上发生，就像它们在美国创建过程中发生的一样。这将是困难的，有些人可能会死。但这将令人难以置信地鼓舞人心。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,336:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,338:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Ultimately, if you care about life on Earth, you should want that life to become
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,338:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: multiplanetary and ultimately multistellar. Otherwise you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,339:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,340:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re signing the death warrant for all life as
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,340:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: we know it. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,341:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,341:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s inevitable.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,342:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,342:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  最终，如果你关心地球上的生命，你应该希望那个生命成为多行星并最终多恒星。否则你正在签署我们所知的所有生命的死亡令。这是不可避免的。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,343:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,344:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Think of us being a multiplanet species as taking out insurance for life itself. Life
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,345:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: insurance, for life.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,345:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,346:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  把我们成为多行星物种看作是为生命本身购买保险。生命的生命保险。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,346:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The Gateway to Mars
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,347:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 通往火星的门户
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,348:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,353:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  What started off as basically a sandbar in the middle of nowhere is now Starbase, Texas.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,354:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: We named it 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,354:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,355:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The Gateway to Mars,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,355:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,356:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  because this is where we
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,356:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,362:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re going to develop the technology
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,365:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: necessary to take humanity, civilization, and life as we know it to another planet for the first time in
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,366:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the 4.5-billion-year history of Earth.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,366:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,366:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  最初基本上是一个偏僻地方的沙洲，现在是德克萨斯州的星舰基地。我们将其命名为
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,367:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,367:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 通往火星的门户
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,367:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,368:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ，因为这是我们将在地球 45 亿年历史上第一次开发将人类、文明和我们所知的生命带到另一个行星所需技术的地方。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,368:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,368:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Q: Why Mars?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,369:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,369:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  问：为什么是火星？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,369:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,373:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  There are not a lot of options, frankly. Venus is a superheated, high-pressure acid bath.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,374:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Venus is hell, almost literally. The moon is closer but it doesn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,374:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,375:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t have an atmosphere, has only
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,375:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: one-sixth of Earth
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,376:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,376:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s gravity, and is missing many key resources.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,377:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,377:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  坦率地说，没有太多选择。金星是一个过热的、高压的酸浴。金星是地狱，几乎是字面意思。月球更近，但它没有大气层，只有地球引力的六分之一，缺少许多关键资源。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,377:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,378:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Plus, a Mars base is more likely to survive a conflict on Earth than a moon base.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,379:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,379:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  此外，火星基地比月球基地更有可能在地球冲突中幸存。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,379:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,381:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  We could establish a crude permanent base on the moon. That would be the next step up
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,381:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: from Apollo. Let
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,381:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,382:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s not just go there for a few hours and head back; let
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,382:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,386:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s have an occupied science
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,387:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: base on the moon. We could build epic telescopes on the moon. They would enable us to see what
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,387:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,388:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,389:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: going on out there. Maybe we would detect those aliens
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,389:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: !
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,389:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,390:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我们可以在月球上建立一个简陋的永久基地。那将是阿波罗之后的下一步。让我们不只是去那里几个小时然后回来；让我们在月球上有一个有人居住的科学基地。我们可以在月球上建造史诗般的望远镜。它们将使我们能够看到外面发生了什么。也许我们会探测到那些外星人！
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,390:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,391:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  When we
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,391:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,398:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re out there exploring the galaxy, we might find a whole bunch of dead
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,400:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: one-planet civilizations. They just never made it to the next planet. Can you imagine doing
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,400:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: archaeology on strange ghost-town planets?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,401:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: !
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,401:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,401:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  当我们在外面探索银河系时，我们可能会发现一堆死去的单行星文明。它们只是从未到达下一个行星。你能想象在陌生的鬼城行星上做考古吗？！
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,402:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,403:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Progress is measured by the timeline to establish a self-sustaining civilization on Mars.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,403:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: That
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,404:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,404:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s how we gauge our progress at Starbase.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,405:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,405:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  进度是通过在火星上建立自给自足文明的时间表来衡量的。这就是我们在星舰基地衡量进度的方式。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,406:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,406:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Occupy Mars, man.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,406:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,407:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  占领火星，伙计。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,407:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,408:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Q: How can we actually get enough stuff to Mars to build a city?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,408:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,409:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  问：我们实际上如何获得足够的东西到火星来建造一座城市？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,409:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,410:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  We
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,410:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,412:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re now at the point where we can produce a Starship roughly every two or three weeks.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,412:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Now, we don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,412:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,414:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t always produce a ship every two or three weeks because we are still making design
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,415:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: upgrades. But ultimately we
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,415:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,416:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re aiming for the ability to produce a thousand ships a year.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,416:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,417:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我们现在处于大约每两到三周可以生产一艘星舰的地步。现在，我们并不总是每两到三周生产一艘船，因为我们仍在进行设计升级。但最终我们的目标是每年生产一千艘船的能力。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,417:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,426:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Starbase will probably be making as many Starships for Mars as Boeing and Airbus make
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,429:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: commercial airplanes each year. This is really an enormous scale of manufacturing, because each
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,429:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Starship is bigger than a 747 or an A380.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,430:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,430:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  星舰基地可能会为火星制造与波音和空客每年制造商用飞机一样多的星舰。这真的是一个巨大的制造规模，因为每艘星舰都比 747 或 A380 大。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,431:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,434:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Tesla and other car companies are still building far higher volumes of complex
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,435:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: manufactured tonnage than SpaceX. That is a way of saying it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,435:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,440:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s achievable. These numbers are
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,441:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: insanely high by traditional space standards but they are achievable, because they have been
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,442:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: achieved in other industries.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,442:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,443:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  特斯拉和其他汽车公司仍在建造比 SpaceX 高得多的复杂制造吨位。这是一种说它是可实现的方式。这些数字按传统太空标准高得疯狂，但它们是可实现的，因为它们在其他行业已经实现。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,444:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,444:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Starship is the key to preserving the light of consciousness. That
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,445:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,445:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s what it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,446:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,447:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s all about. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,448:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: may end up being the most important thing that we ever do.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,449:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,449:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  星舰是保护意识之光的关键。这就是它的全部意义。它最终可能是我们做过的最重要的事情。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,450:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,450:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  We
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,450:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,464:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re hoping to increase the cadence of flights to Mars dramatically with every launch
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,469:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: window. Roughly every two years we will dramatically increase the number of ships that go to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,470:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Mars. Ultimately we will try to get to one thousand or two thousand ships per Mars rendezvous.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,470:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,471:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我们希望每个发射窗口都大幅增加飞往火星的飞行频率。大约每两年我们将大幅增加前往火星的船只数量。最终我们将尝试达到每次火星会合一千或两千艘船。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,471:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,471:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  We
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,472:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,475:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ll need to do a lot of orbital refueling. Orbiting rocket tanker ships will replenish the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,476:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: propellant of the ships that will actually go to Mars. We
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,476:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,477:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re aiming to demonstrate ship-to-ship
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,477:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: propellant transfer. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,478:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,478:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s hard to make this not look a bit naughty because it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,479:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,479:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s two ships connecting
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,480:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: and doing a fluid transfer.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,480:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,481:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我们需要做很多轨道加油。轨道火箭加油船将补充实际前往火星的船只的推进剂。我们的目标是演示船对船推进剂转移。很难让它看起来不有点调皮，因为它是两艘船连接并进行流体转移。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,481:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,497:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  We would create a propellant depot ship that would look like a huge hot dog. Shortly
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,504:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: before going to Mars, Starships would take off with a couple hundred tons of payload from Earth.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,505:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: They would reach orbit with almost no propellant left, then get refilled by the tanker for the journey
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,506:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: to Mars.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,506:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,507:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我们将创建一个看起来像巨大热狗的推进剂仓库船。在前往火星前不久，星舰将带着几百吨的有效载荷从地球起飞。它们将几乎不带推进剂到达轨道，然后由加油船补充前往火星的旅程。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,507:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,520:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  We need roughly ten thousand missions to get to a million tons transferred to Mars. We
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,525:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: think we can do this by 2044. My guess is that it will require about a million tons to build a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,525:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: self-sufficient city, but it might be ten million tons. I hope it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,526:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,526:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s not one hundred million tons. That
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,527:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,527:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: d
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,527:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: be a lot.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,528:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,528:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我们需要大约一万次任务才能将一百万吨转移到火星。我们认为我们可以在 2044 年之前做到这一点。我的猜测是，建造一个自给自足的城市将需要大约一百万吨，但可能是一千万吨。我希望不是一亿吨。那会很多。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,529:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,554:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Starship in its final form will probably do well over two hundred tons to orbit each flight,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,567:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: with full reusability and the ability to fly multiple times a day. We plan to launch about five
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,573:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: uncrewed Starships to Mars in 2026. If those all land safely, then crewed missions are possible in
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,573:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 2028. If we encounter challenges, the crewed missions will be postponed two more years.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,574:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,574:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  星舰在其最终形式下，每次飞行可能会将超过两百吨送入轨道，具有完全可重复使用性和每天飞行多次的能力。我们计划在 2026 年向火星发射大约五艘无人星舰。如果这些都安全着陆，那么载人任务可能在 2028 年。如果我们遇到挑战，载人任务将再推迟两年。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,575:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,579:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  It is only possible to travel from Earth to Mars every two years when the planets are
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,580:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: aligned. If Mars is on the other side of the sun, you can
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,580:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,580:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t get there. Can
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,581:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,584:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t go through the sun. This
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,585:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: increases the difficulty but also serves to immunize Mars from many catastrophic events on Earth.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,585:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,586:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  只有当行星对齐时，每两年才能从地球旅行到火星。如果火星在太阳的另一边，你无法到达那里。不能穿过太阳。这增加了难度，但也起到使火星对地球上的许多灾难性事件免疫的作用。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,586:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,598:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  SpaceX will increase the number of spaceships traveling to Mars exponentially with every
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,602:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: opportunity. We want to enable anyone who wants to be a space traveler and go to Mars. That
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,603:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: means you, your family, or friends—anyone who dreams of great adventure.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,604:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,604:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  SpaceX 将每次机会都指数级增加前往火星的宇宙飞船数量。我们想让任何想成为太空旅行者并去火星的人都能做到。这意味着你、你的家人或朋友——任何梦想伟大冒险的人。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,605:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,605:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  We want to get to the point where we
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,606:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,607:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re sending over a million tons at every Mars transfer
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,607:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: window. Then we
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,608:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,608:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re a serious civilization. A megaton per transfer window. We can
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,609:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,610:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t fly there
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,610:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: continuously, so we
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,611:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,611:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: d have a gathering of a thousand ships or more.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,612:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,612:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我们想达到在每个火星转移窗口发送超过一百万吨的地步。那我们就是一个严肃的文明。每个转移窗口一百万吨。我们不能连续飞往那里，所以我们将聚集一千艘或更多船只。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,613:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,617:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Imagine an armada of Starships waiting in orbit for the planets to align and then this
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,618:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: gigantic Starfleet taking off for Mars. It will be a glorious sight to see
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,619:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: !
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,619:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Can you imagine?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,620:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,620:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  想象一支星舰舰队在轨道上等待行星对齐，然后这支巨大的星际舰队起飞前往火星。那将是一个辉煌的景象！你能想象吗？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,621:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,622:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  This is an extremely difficult engineering problem. But no new physics is required.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,622:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,623:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  这是一个极其困难的工程问题。但不需要新的物理学。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,623:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,624:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Q: What
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,624:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,625:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s the math on the journey to Mars?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,625:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,626:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  问：前往火星的数学是什么？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,626:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,650:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The fundamental optimization is minimizing cost per ton to orbit, and ultimately cost per
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,662:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ton to the surface of Mars. This may seem like a purely mercantile objective, but it is actually the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,665:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: thing that needs to be optimized. There is a certain cost per ton to the surface of Mars where we can
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,666:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: afford to establish a self-sustaining city. If we don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,666:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,666:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t get the cost down, we can
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,667:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,667:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t afford to do it.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,667:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,668:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  基本优化是最小化每吨进入轨道的成本，最终是每吨到火星表面的成本。这看起来可能是一个纯粹的商业目标，但实际上这是需要优化的事情。到火星表面每吨有一定的成本，我们可以负担得起建立一个自给自足的城市。如果我们不降低成本，我们就负担不起这样做。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,668:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,681:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  It will cost maybe a quarter of a percent or half a percent of gross domestic product (GDP).
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,686:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: That is palatable. A few people going to Mars will not cause some meaningful drop in the standard
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,687:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: of living. For less than 1 percent of GDP, we can buy life insurance.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,687:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,687:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  它将花费也许国内生产总值（GDP）的四分之一百分比或半百分比。那是可以接受的。几个人去火星不会导致生活水平的有意义下降。用不到 GDP 的 1%，我们可以购买人寿保险。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,688:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,688:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Starlink internet is what
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,689:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,691:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s being used to pay for humanity getting to Mars. I would like to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,691:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: thank everyone who has bought Starlink because you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,692:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,693:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re helping secure the future of civilization.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,693:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Thank you.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,693:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,694:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  星链互联网正被用来支付人类到达火星的费用。我想感谢所有购买了星链的人，因为你们正在帮助确保文明的未来。谢谢你们。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,694:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,695:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Right now, you couldn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,695:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,699:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t fly to Mars for a trillion dollars. No amount of money could get
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,700:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: any human a ticket to Mars. First, we need to make this possible. But we don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,700:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,708:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t just want to have
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,713:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: flags and footprints on Mars for fifty years, like we did with the moon. To pass the great filter of
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,714:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: existing only on one planet, we need to truly become a multiplanet species.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,714:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,715:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  现在，你花一万亿美元也无法飞往火星。没有任何金额的钱可以让任何人获得去火星的票。首先，我们需要使这成为可能。但我们不只是想像我们对月球那样在火星上有旗帜和脚印五十年。要通过只存在于一个行星上的大过滤器，我们需要真正成为多行星物种。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,715:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Building the New World
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,716:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 建设新世界
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,716:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,717:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Attendance is not mandatory here. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,717:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,718:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ll be dangerous and people might die.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,718:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,718:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  这里出席不是强制性的。这会很危险，人们可能会死。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,719:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,731:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Few people will want to go to Mars in the beginning. But for some, the excitement of the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,735:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: frontier exceeds the concern of danger. I think it would be the adventure—the best adventure one could
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,736:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: possibly go on—to go build a new civilization on a new planet.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,736:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,736:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  开始时很少有人想去火星。但对一些人来说，边疆的兴奋超过了危险的担忧。我认为那将是冒险——一个人可能进行的最好的冒险——去在一个新行星上建立一个新的文明。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,737:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,739:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Some people seem to think this will be an escape hatch, some luxury resort for rich people.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,739:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: It is not. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,740:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,741:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s a high probability of death relative to Earth. Long journey. Not great food. A lot of hard
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,741:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: work.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,742:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,742:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  有些人似乎认为这将是一个逃生舱口，一些富人的豪华度假村。不是这样的。相对于地球，死亡概率很高。长途旅行。食物不太好。很多艰苦的工作。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,743:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,748:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  You have to spend six months on a rocket with a hundred other people. It will be cramped.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,749:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Like old ocean voyages, six months packed on a little ship in the middle of the ocean.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,750:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,750:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  你必须和另外一百个人在火箭上待六个月。它会很拥挤。像古老的海洋航行，六个月挤在海洋中央的一艘小船上。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,751:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,751:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,751:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,757:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s going to take a while to build a real civilization on Mars. The critical threshold is if the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,758:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ships from Earth stop coming for any reason, does the Mars City die out or not? That
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,759:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,759:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s a high bar.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,761:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: You can
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,762:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,762:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t be missing anything.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,763:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,763:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  在火星上建立真正的文明需要一段时间。关键阈值是如果来自地球的船只因任何原因停止到来，火星城市会灭绝吗？那是一个高标准。你不能缺少任何东西。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,764:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,764:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Imagine you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,765:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,766:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re on a long sea voyage and the only thing you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,766:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,767:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re missing is vitamin C. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,767:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,768:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,769:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: only a matter of time before it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,769:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,770:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s curtains. You
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,770:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,772:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ve got to have all the things necessary to sustain
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,774:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: civilization on Mars, including about a million people.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,774:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,775:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  想象你在一次长途海上航行中，你唯一缺少的是维生素 C。这只是时间问题，然后就结束了。你必须有在火星上维持文明所需的所有东西，包括大约一百万人。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,775:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,776:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  I would like to die on Mars…just not on impact.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,776:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,777:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我想死在火星上……只是不要在撞击时。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,777:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,781:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Some Starships could come back to Earth. We want to offer an option of coming back, but
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,782:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: most people who go to Mars will probably never come back to Earth.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,782:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,782:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  一些星舰可以返回地球。我们想提供一个返回的选项，但大多数去火星的人可能永远不会返回地球。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,783:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,790:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Most of the ships we send will probably stay there, especially while colonizing Mars,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,791:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: because the ship itself will be so valuable there. Martians will take apart the ship and use it for raw
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,791:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: materials.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,792:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,792:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我们发送的大多数船只可能会留在那里，特别是在殖民火星期间，因为船本身在那里将非常有价值。火星人将拆解船只并将其用作原材料。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,793:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,793:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Once we get to Mars, there will be a lot to do, and it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,793:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,805:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ll take a while to build it all. We have
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,812:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: to build out the industrial base, then the city. First, we build a giant solar panel farm to generate
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,814:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: energy. Then a facility to make fuel, oxygen to grow plants for food, and everything necessary to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,814:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: support life.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,814:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,815:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  一旦我们到达火星，将有很多事情要做，需要一段时间来建造所有东西。我们必须建立工业基础，然后是城市。首先，我们建造一个巨大的太阳能电池板农场来产生能量。然后是一个制造燃料的设施，氧气来种植食物植物，以及支持生命所需的一切。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,815:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,816:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Ultimately we
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,816:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,819:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ll need all these things: power generation, ice mining, mining in general,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,820:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: propellent production, long-duration life support, construction, and global communication.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,820:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,821:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  最终我们将需要所有这些东西：发电、冰开采、一般开采、推进剂生产、长期生命支持、建设和全球通信。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,821:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,822:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  A fuel plant will create the fuel for the return trips of many Starships. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,822:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,845:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s mostly going to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,864:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: be oxygen plants, because rockets run on 78 percent liquid oxygen, 22 percent fuel. Mars has a CO2
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,873:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: atmosphere and water ice, which is CO2 plus H2O, so plenty of raw material to make what rockets
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,875:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: need: CH4 (methane) and O2 (oxygen). Rocket fuel is easy to create on Mars, and in many other
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,875:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: parts of the solar system.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,876:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,876:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  燃料工厂将为许多星舰的返程创造燃料。它将主要是氧气工厂，因为火箭运行在 78% 液氧，22% 燃料。火星有二氧化碳大气和水冰，即二氧化碳加水，所以有足够的原材料制造火箭所需的东西：CH4（甲烷）和 O2（氧气）。火箭燃料在火星上很容易制造，在太阳系的许多其他地方也是如此。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,877:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,878:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  In the beginning, people would live in glass domes. Over time, we
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,878:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,879:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: d terraform Mars and
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,879:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: make it like Earth.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,880:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,880:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  开始时，人们将住在玻璃圆顶中。随着时间的推移，我们将改造火星并使其像地球一样。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,881:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,881:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Mars is cold, but if we warm it up we
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,882:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,885:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ll get liquid water. Mars would have an ocean
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,886:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: roughly a mile deep on 40 percent of the planet once we warm it up. That
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,886:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,888:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s a lot of water. A lot of
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,889:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the ice you see on the poles is actually dry ice. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,889:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,890:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s frozen CO2.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,890:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,891:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  火星很冷，但如果我们温暖它，我们将得到液态水。一旦我们温暖它，火星将在 40% 的行星上拥有大约一英里深的海洋。那是很多水。你在两极看到的很多冰实际上是干冰。它是冻结的二氧化碳。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,891:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,895:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Terraforming Mars mostly consists of warming it up. We could warm it up either with
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,895:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: solar reflectors in orbit or a lot of thermonuclear explosions.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,896:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,896:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  改造火星主要包括温暖它。我们可以用轨道上的太阳反射器或很多热核爆炸来温暖它。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,897:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,898:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  It sounds crazy, but a series of thermonuclear explosions basically creates an artificial sun.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,898:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: If you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,899:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,913:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re worried that it will generate dangerous radiation, have you stood in the sun? The sun is a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,918:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: giant thermonuclear reactor. Obviously we can stand in front of the sun and not die. We could
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,919:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: launch a missile every ten seconds or so. It would be like gigantic thermonuclear fireworks.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,920:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,920:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  这听起来很疯狂，但一系列热核爆炸基本上创造了一个人造太阳。如果你担心它会产生危险辐射，你站在太阳下过吗？太阳是一个巨大的热核反应堆。显然我们可以站在太阳前面而不死。我们可以大约每十秒发射一枚导弹。那将像巨大的热核烟花。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,921:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,921:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  We
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,922:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,923:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: d create two little suns, pulsing above the north and south poles.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,923:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,924:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我们将创造两个小太阳，在北极和南极上方脉动。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,924:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,930:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  That would warm the poles up enough that the frozen carbon dioxide (CO2) would gasify.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,931:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The Martian atmosphere would get more dense, with water vapor and CO2 in the air. In Mars
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,931:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,935:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s case,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,936:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: more CO2 in the air is good, because it will create a positive cycle to make it warmer with more
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,937:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: liquid water—like Earth
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,937:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,937:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s environment.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,938:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,938:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  那将温暖两极足够使冻结的二氧化碳（CO2）气化。火星大气将变得更稠密，空气中有水蒸气和二氧化碳。在火星的情况下，空气中更多的二氧化碳是好的，因为它将创造一个积极的循环，使其更温暖，有更多的液态水——像地球的环境。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,939:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,939:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Even if you don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,940:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,940:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t go to Mars, you can watch this all happen on TV. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,940:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,941:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ll be so cool.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,941:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,942:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  即使你不去火星，你也可以在电视上观看这一切发生。那将太酷了。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,942:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,942:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  What I
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,943:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,960:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: m describing may sound crazy, but it is a small fraction of what will ultimately be
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,969:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: done, as long as we become a two-planet civilization. Look at the history of shipping technology in
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,971:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Europe. When all you had to do was cross the Mediterranean, the ships were pretty lame—they only had
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,971:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: short-range vessels, which couldn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,972:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,977:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t cross the Atlantic.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,977:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,978:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我所描述的可能听起来很疯狂，但它只是最终将要做的事情的一小部分，只要我们成为一个两行星文明。看看欧洲航运技术的历史。当你所要做的只是穿越地中海时，船只相当糟糕——它们只有短程船只，无法穿越大西洋。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,978:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,979:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Without the forcing function of long-range commerce, shipping technology didn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:04,979:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,001:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t improve
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,020:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: much. You could do mostly the same things with ships around the time of Julius Caesar and the time
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,029:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: of Columbus. Fifteen hundred years later, ships could still only cross the Mediterranean. But as soon
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,032:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: as there was a reason to cross the Atlantic, shipping technology improved dramatically. The
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,032:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: American colonies were needed for that to happen.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,033:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,033:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  没有长途商业的强制功能，航运技术没有太大改进。你可以在朱利叶斯·凯撒时代和哥伦布时代用船做大致相同的事情。一千五百年后，船只仍然只能穿越地中海。但一旦有理由穿越大西洋，航运技术就大幅改善。为此需要美洲殖民地。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,034:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,035:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Reusable rockets are the modern-day equivalent of the first ships that could cross oceans.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,035:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,036:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  可重复使用的火箭是现代相当于第一艘可以穿越海洋的船只。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,036:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,037:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Until you have a breakthrough technology enabling travel, there
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,037:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,038:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s no way for
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,039:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: entrepreneurial energy to do anything.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,039:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,039:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  直到你有一个突破性技术能够实现旅行，创业能量无法做任何事情。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,040:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,041:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Once we build reusable rockets, suddenly the opportunity is immense. We
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,041:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,042:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re going to do
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,043:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: our best to get you to Mars, and make sure there
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,043:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,044:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s an environment there where entrepreneurs can
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,045:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: continue building and flourish.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,045:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,046:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  一旦我们建造可重复使用的火箭，机会突然变得巨大。我们将尽最大努力让你去火星，并确保那里有一个环境，创业者可以继续建设和繁荣。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,046:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,065:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The same thing happened with the first cross-continental railroad in the United States, the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,074:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Union Pacific Railroad. When they were building the Union Pacific Railroad, nobody could predict
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,077:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Silicon Valley, Hollywood, or California becoming the most populous state in the country. That
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,078:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: would have sounded crazy. But then they discovered gold.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,078:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,079:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  同样的事情发生在美国第一条跨大陆铁路，联合太平洋铁路。当他们建造联合太平洋铁路时，没有人能预测硅谷、好莱坞或加利福尼亚成为该国人口最多的州。那听起来会很疯狂。但然后他们发现了黄金。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,079:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,080:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,080:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,083:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s incumbent on SpaceX and other organizations to figure out how to get to Mars.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,084:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Otherwise, nothing else matters. Once we get there, there
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,084:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,085:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s a lot that can be done.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,085:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,086:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  SpaceX 和其他组织有责任找出如何到达火星。否则，其他事情都不重要。一旦我们到达那里，有很多事情可以做。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,086:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,111:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  There will be a lot of super exciting things that are hard to predict. After the basic
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,126:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: infrastructure is built on Mars, there will be an explosion of opportunity for entrepreneurs, because
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,132:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: our new world will need everything from iron foundries to pizza joints. This includes everything you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,133:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: can imagine, like starting the first Italian restaurant on Mars. That would be cool, and somebody
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,133:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,134:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,135:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: gotta do it.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,135:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,136:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  将有很多超级令人兴奋的事情难以预测。在火星上建立基本基础设施后，创业者将有机会爆发，因为我们的新世界将需要从铸铁厂到披萨店的一切。这包括你能想象的一切，比如在火星上开第一家意大利餐厅。那会很酷，有人必须去做。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,136:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Colonizing the Galaxy
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,137:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 殖民银河系
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,138:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,142:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Earth is the cradle of humanity. We cannot stay in the cradle forever. It is time to go forth,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,143:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: be out there among the stars. Expand the scope and scale of human consciousness.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,144:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,144:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  地球是人类的摇篮。我们不能永远待在摇篮里。是时候出发了，在群星之中。扩展人类意识的范围和规模。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,145:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,145:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The big picture isn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,145:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,147:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t just to back up the hard drive of humanity, but to grow humanity into
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,147:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: a true multiplanetary species. Let
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,148:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,157:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s establish a regular cargo route to Mars. With the economic driver
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,161:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: of interplanetary commerce, there will be resources and incentives to massively improve space
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,162:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: transport technology, and then things will go to a whole new level.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,162:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,163:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  大局不仅仅是备份人类的硬盘，而是将人类成长为一个真正的多行星物种。让我们建立一条定期的火星货运路线。有了行星间商业的经济驱动，将有资源和激励来大幅改善太空运输技术，然后事情将进入一个全新的水平。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,163:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,180:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Starship is not suitable for going to another star system, but it is a general solution for
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,188:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: transport anywhere inside the solar system. Once we have a propellant depot on Mars, we can travel
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,189:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: to the asteroid belt, the moons of Jupiter and Saturn, and ultimately anywhere in the solar system.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,190:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: This is huge.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,190:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,191:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  星舰不适合前往另一个恒星系统，但它是太阳系内任何地方运输的通用解决方案。一旦我们在火星上有一个推进剂仓库，我们可以前往小行星带、木星和土星的卫星，最终太阳系内的任何地方。这是巨大的。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,191:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,192:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  When space travel becomes as common as air travel, the future of civilization will be
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,193:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: assured.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,193:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,193:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  当太空旅行变得像航空旅行一样普遍时，文明的未来将得到保证。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,194:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,200:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  One way to look at the progress of civilization is the percentage completion of each
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,201:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Kardashev level. Kardashev level one is harnessing all the energy of a planet. In my opinion, we
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,201:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,202:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ve
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,203:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: only harnessed maybe 1 or 2 percent of Earth
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,203:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,204:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s energy. So we
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,204:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,205:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ve got a long way to go to complete
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,205:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Kardashev level one.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,206:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,206:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  看待文明进步的一种方式是每个卡尔达肖夫级别的完成百分比。卡尔达肖夫一级是利用一个行星的所有能量。在我看来，我们只利用了地球能源的 1% 或 2%。所以我们还有很长的路要走才能完成卡尔达肖夫一级。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,207:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,207:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Kardashev level two is complete when we
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,208:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,209:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ve harnessed all the energy of the sun. That
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,209:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: would be—I don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,210:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,213:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t know—a billion times more energy than Earth? Maybe closer to a trillion. Then,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,214:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Kardashev level three would be all the energy of a galaxy. We
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,215:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,215:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re pretty far from that. So we
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,215:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,217:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re at the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,217:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: very, very early stage of the intelligence big bang.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,218:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,218:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  卡尔达肖夫二级在我们利用了太阳的所有能量时完成。那将是——我不知道——比地球多十亿倍的能量？也许更接近一万亿。然后，卡尔达肖夫三级将是一个星系的所有能量。我们离那还很远。所以我们处于智能大爆炸的非常非常早期阶段。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,219:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,220:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  If we can establish a Mars colony, we can almost certainly colonize the whole solar
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,221:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: system. We
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,222:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,227:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ll go to the moons of Jupiter, at least some of the outer ones, probably Titan on Saturn,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,228:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: and the asteroids. Once we have an Earth-to-Mars economy as a forcing function, we
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,228:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,229:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ll cover the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,229:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: whole solar system.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,230:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,231:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  如果我们能建立火星殖民地，我们几乎肯定可以殖民整个太阳系。我们将前往木星的卫星，至少一些外层的，可能是土星的泰坦，以及小行星。一旦我们有一个地球到火星的经济作为强制功能，我们将覆盖整个太阳系。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,231:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,232:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  We have to make Mars work. If we
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,232:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,235:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re going to have any chance of sending stuff to other
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,235:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: star systems, we need to be laser-focused on Mars. That
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,236:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,237:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s our next step.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,237:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,238:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我们必须让火星工作。如果我们要有任何机会将东西发送到其他恒星系统，我们需要激光聚焦于火星。那是我们的下一步。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,238:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,249:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  On a galactic time scale, even with slower-than-light travel, we could colonize the whole
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,252:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: galaxy. Even some of the neighboring galaxies. If we get a million years, even with no new physics,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,253:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: could we colonize the galaxy? Absolutely. The entire galaxy.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,254:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,254:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  在银河时间尺度上，即使以低于光速的旅行，我们也可以殖民整个银河系。甚至一些邻近的星系。如果我们有一百万年，即使没有新的物理学，我们能殖民银河系吗？绝对可以。整个银河系。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,255:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,256:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  You are the magicians of the twenty-first century; don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,256:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,258:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t let anything hold you back.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,259:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Imagination is the limit. Go out there and create some magic.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,259:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,260:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  你们是二十一世纪的魔术师；不要让任何事情阻碍你。想象力是极限。走出去，创造一些魔法。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,261:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: BONUS: THE 69 CORE MUSK METHODS
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,261:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 附录：69 个核心马斯克方法
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,262:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,265:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  These were selected as some of the fundamental ideas that make Elon and his companies
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,266:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: successful. They have been edited or paraphrased into short, memorable maxims.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,267:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,267:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  这些被选为使埃隆和他的公司成功的一些基本思想。它们已被编辑或改写成简短、令人难忘的金科玉律。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,267:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  1 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,268:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,268:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  You are capable of more than you think.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,269:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,269:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,270:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  你比你想象的更有能力。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,270:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  2 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,270:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,271:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,271:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,272:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s possible for ordinary people to choose to be extraordinary.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,272:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,273:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,273:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  普通人可以选择变得非凡。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,273:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  3 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,274:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,275:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  You can teach yourself anything. Read widely; talk to experts.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,275:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,275:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,276:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  你可以自学任何东西。广泛阅读；与专家交谈。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,276:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  4 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,277:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,277:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Assume you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,278:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,278:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re wrong. Aspire to be less wrong.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,279:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,279:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,280:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  假设你是错的。致力于少犯错。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,280:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  5 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,281:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,281:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Internalize responsibility.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,282:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,282:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,283:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  内化责任。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,283:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  6 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,284:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,284:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  If we don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,285:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,285:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t make stuff, there is no stuff.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,286:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,286:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,287:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  如果我们不制造东西，就没有东西。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,287:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  7 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,288:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,288:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Creating products and services creates wealth.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,289:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,289:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,290:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  创造产品和服务创造财富。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,290:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  8 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,291:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,291:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  A useful life is worth having lived.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,292:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,292:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,293:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  有用的一生值得活过。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,293:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  9 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,294:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,294:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,295:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,295:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t aspire to glory; aspire to work.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,296:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,296:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,297:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  不要渴望荣耀；渴望工作。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,297:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  10 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,298:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,299:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Take actions that increase the odds of the future being good.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,299:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,300:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,300:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  采取增加未来变好几率的行动。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,301:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  11 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,301:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,302:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Every day, we either increase the rate of innovation or it slows down.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,302:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,303:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,303:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  每天，我们要么增加创新率，要么它减慢。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,304:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  12 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,305:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,305:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Work on what is just becoming possible.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,306:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,306:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,307:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  致力于刚刚变得可能的事情。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,307:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  13 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,308:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,308:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,309:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,310:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t wait for the world to want it. If it should obviously exist, go build it.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,310:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,311:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,311:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  不要等世界想要它。如果它显然应该存在，就去建造它。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,312:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  14 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,312:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,313:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Build what no one else is building.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,314:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,314:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,315:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  建造别人没有建造的东西。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,315:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  15 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,316:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,317:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  As you move forward, allies will assemble around you.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,317:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,318:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,318:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  当你前进时，盟友将聚集在你周围。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,319:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  16 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,320:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,320:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Prototypes are proof.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,321:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,322:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,322:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  原型是证明。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,323:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  17 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,323:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,324:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Start somewhere, question assumptions, and adapt to reality.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,325:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,325:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,326:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  从某个地方开始，质疑假设，并适应现实。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,326:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  18 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,327:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,328:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Reason from fundamentals, not from what others are doing.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,328:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,329:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,329:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  从基本原理推理，而不是从别人正在做的事情推理。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,330:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  19 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,330:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,331:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,331:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,332:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The magic-wand number.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,333:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,333:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  See the theoretically perfect and work toward it.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,334:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,334:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,335:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,336:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,336:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 魔杖数字
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,337:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,337:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 。看到理论上完美的并朝它努力。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,338:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  20 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,338:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,339:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,339:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,340:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Know the idiot index.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,340:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,341:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Understand the cost of components.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,342:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,342:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,343:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,343:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,344:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 了解白痴指数
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,344:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,345:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 。了解组件的成本。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,345:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  21 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,346:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,347:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The Algorithm: Question Requirements → Try to Delete the Part or Process → Simplify → Accelerate
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,348:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: → Automate.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,348:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,349:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,350:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  算法：质疑要求 → 尝试删除部件或过程 → 简化 → 加速 → 自动化。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,350:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  22 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,351:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,352:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  For critical items, have meetings every twenty-four hours to run The Algorithm and check
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,353:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: progress from yesterday.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,354:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,354:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,355:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  对于关键项目，每二十四小时开会运行算法并检查昨天的进度。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,355:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  23 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,356:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,357:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Stay as close to the actual work as possible. Do not separate yourself from the pain of your
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,358:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: decisions.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,358:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,359:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,360:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  尽可能靠近实际工作。不要将自己与决策的痛苦分离。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,360:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  24 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,361:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,362:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  All requirements should be treated as recommendations.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,362:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,363:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,364:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  所有要求都应被视为建议。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,364:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  25 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,365:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,366:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The only fixed laws are the laws of physics.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,366:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,367:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,368:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  唯一固定的定律是物理定律。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,368:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  26 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,369:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,370:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The best part is no part; the best process is no process.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,370:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,371:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,372:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  最好的部件是没有部件；最好的过程是没有过程。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,372:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  27 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,373:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,374:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Simplicity creates both reliability and low cost.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,374:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,375:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,376:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  简单创造可靠性和低成本。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,376:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  28 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,377:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,378:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Find the design necessity of every part and every process.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,379:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,379:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,380:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  找出每个部件和每个过程的设计必要性。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,380:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  29 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,381:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,382:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Overdelete and add back the absolutely necessary.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,383:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,383:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,384:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  过度删除并加回绝对必要的。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,384:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  30 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,385:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,386:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Push for radical breakthroughs.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,387:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,387:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,388:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  推动激进突破。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,389:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  31 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,389:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,390:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Be proactive. You will never win unless you take charge of setting the strategy.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,391:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,392:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,392:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  积极主动。除非你负责制定战略，否则你永远不会赢。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,393:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  32 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,394:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,394:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  A maniacal sense of urgency is our operating principle.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,395:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,396:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,396:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  疯狂的紧迫感是我们的运营原则。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,397:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  33 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,398:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,399:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  A factory moving at twice the speed of another factory is basically equivalent to two
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,400:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: factories.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,401:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,402:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,403:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  以两倍于另一个工厂的速度移动的工厂基本上相当于两个工厂。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,404:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  34 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,405:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,406:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Attack the bottleneck. If you have 9,999 things that are working and one that isn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,407:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,408:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t, that one
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,409:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: sets the overall production rate.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,409:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,410:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,411:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  攻击瓶颈。如果你有 9,999 件事在工作，有一件不在工作，那一件设定整体生产率。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,411:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  35 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,412:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,413:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  You
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,414:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,415:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ll move as fast as your least-lucky or least-competent supplier.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,415:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,416:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,417:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  你将移动得和最不走运或最无能的供应商一样快。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,418:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  36 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,418:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,419:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Do things in parallel.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,420:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,421:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,421:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  并行做事。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,422:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  37 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,423:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,424:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Give teams one key metric to focus on. Video games without a score are boring.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,425:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,425:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,426:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  给团队一个关键指标来关注。没有分数的电子游戏很无聊。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,427:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  38 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,428:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,429:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Separating design, engineering, and manufacturing is a recipe for dysfunction.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,429:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,430:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,431:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  分离设计、工程和制造是功能障碍的配方。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,431:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  39 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,432:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,433:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Speed of innovation is what matters.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,434:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,434:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,435:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  创新速度才是重要的。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,436:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  40 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,437:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,438:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Beat competitors on speed, quality, and cost, not anticompetitive behavior.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,438:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,439:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,440:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  在速度、质量和成本上击败竞争对手，而不是反竞争行为。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,441:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  41 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,441:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,442:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Test the absurd. When something seems impossible, ask: 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,442:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,443:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: What would it take?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,443:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,443:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,444:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,444:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  测试荒谬的。当某事看起来不可能时，问：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,444:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,445:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 需要什么？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,445:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,445:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  42 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,446:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,446:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Money is not the constraint. Exceptional engineers are.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,446:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,447:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,447:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  钱不是限制。卓越的工程师才是。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,447:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  43 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,448:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,448:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Get everyone thinking like the chief engineer.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,449:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,449:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,449:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  让每个人都像首席工程师一样思考。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,450:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  44 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,450:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,451:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Get a clear, direct feedback loop with reality.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,451:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,452:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,452:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  获得与现实的清晰、直接反馈循环。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,452:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  45 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,453:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,453:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Always be smashing your ego. Ensure ability > ego.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,454:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,454:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,454:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  永远粉碎你的自我。确保能力 > 自我。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,455:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  46 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,455:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,456:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Ask, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,456:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,457:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Is this effort resulting in a better product or service?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,457:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,457:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  If not, stop.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,458:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,458:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,458:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  问，
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,459:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,459:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 这个努力是否导致更好的产品或服务？
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,459:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,460:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 如果不是，停止。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,460:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  47 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,461:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,461:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Good taste is learnable. Train yourself to notice what makes something beautiful.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,462:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,462:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,462:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  好品味是可学习的。训练自己注意什么使东西美丽。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,463:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  48 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,463:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,464:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Physics doesn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,464:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,465:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t care about hurt feelings. Make the rocket fly.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,465:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,465:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,466:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  物理学不在乎受伤的感情。让火箭飞行。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,466:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  49 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,467:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,467:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Empathy is not an asset.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,468:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,468:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,469:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  同情不是资产。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,469:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  50 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,469:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,470:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Use simple, clear, humble terms.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,470:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,471:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,471:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  使用简单、清晰、谦逊的术语。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,472:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  51 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,472:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,473:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Go directly to the source of information.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,473:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,473:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,474:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  直接去信息来源。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,474:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 🎉《The Book of Elon》翻译项目已完成！
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,596:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 总行数：约 6,000+ 行中英对照
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,597:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: GitHub 仓库：https://github.com/bugcodes/book-of-elon-zh
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,597:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: BONUS: THE 69 CORE MUSK METHODS (continued)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,598:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 附录：69 个核心马斯克方法（续）
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,598:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  52 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,599:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,600:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  When hiring, look for evidence of exceptional ability.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,600:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,601:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,601:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  招聘时，寻找非凡能力的证据。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,602:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  53 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,602:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,603:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Combine engineering and financial fluency.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,603:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,604:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,604:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  结合工程和财务流利度。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,605:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  54 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,605:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,606:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  To truly lead the product, lead the company.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,606:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,607:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,607:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  要真正领导产品，领导公司。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,608:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  55 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,608:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,609:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Lead from the front. Sleep on the factory floor.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,609:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,610:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,610:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  从前面领导。睡在工厂地板上。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,611:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  56 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,612:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,612:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Physically move yourself to wherever the problem is immediately.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,613:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,613:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,614:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  立即亲自移动到问题所在的地方。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,614:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  57 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,615:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,619:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  All bad news should be given loudly and often. Good news can be said quietly and once.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,620:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,620:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,621:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,621:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 所有坏消息都应该大声且经常地传达。好消息可以安静地说一次。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,621:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  58 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,622:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,623:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Failure is essentially irrelevant unless it is catastrophic.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,623:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,624:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,624:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  失败本质上无关紧要，除非它是灾难性的。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,625:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  59 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,625:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,626:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Fear of failure is the biggest cause of failure.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,627:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,627:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,628:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  对失败的恐惧是失败的最大原因。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,628:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  60 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,629:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,629:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Feel the fear and do it anyway.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,630:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,630:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,631:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  感受恐惧并无论如何去做。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,631:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  61 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,632:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,633:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Double down. Push your chips back in.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,633:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,634:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,634:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  加倍投入。把你的筹码推回去。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,635:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  62 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,635:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,636:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Work like hell. Like every waking hour. Go ultra hardcore.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,637:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,637:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,638:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  像地狱一样工作。像每个清醒的小时。超级硬核。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,638:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  63 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,639:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,640:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Make sure you really care about what you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,640:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,641:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re doing—and take the pain.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,641:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,642:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,643:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  确保你真的关心你正在做的事情——并接受痛苦。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,643:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  64 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,644:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,646:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  We should not be afraid of doing something important just because some amount of
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,646:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: tragedy is likely to occur.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,647:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,647:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,648:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  我们不应该因为可能会发生某种悲剧而害怕做重要的事情。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,649:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  65 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,649:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,650:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  When something is important enough, do it even if the odds are not in your favor.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,651:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,651:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,652:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  当某事足够重要时，即使几率对你不利也要去做。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,652:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  66 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,653:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,654:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,654:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,655:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t ever give up. You
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,655:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,656:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: d have to be dead or completely incapacitated.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,657:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,657:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,658:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  永远不要放弃。你必须是死了或完全丧失能力。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,659:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  67 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,659:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,660:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Play life like a game.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,660:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,661:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,662:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  像游戏一样玩生活。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,662:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  68 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,663:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,664:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Go ultra hardcore.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,664:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,665:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,665:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  超级硬核。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,666:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  69 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,667:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,667:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Humor is a differentiator.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,668:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,669:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,669:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  幽默是一个差异化因素。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,670:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: TIMELINE OF ELON MUSK
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,671:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 埃隆·马斯克时间线
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,671:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,672:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  This is not comprehensive, and focuses on his entrepreneurial efforts. All ages are
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,673:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: approximate.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,674:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,674:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  这不是全面的，专注于他的创业努力。所有年龄都是近似的。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,675:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,676:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 1971
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,676:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,677:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,677:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Born June 28; grew up in Pretoria, South Africa.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,678:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,678:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,678:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  6 月 28 日出生；在南非比勒陀利亚长大。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,680:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,681:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 1984 (AGE 12)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,681:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,681:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,682:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Created his first video game, called Blast Star.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,682:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,683:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,683:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  创建了他的第一个电子游戏，名为 Blast Star。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,684:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,685:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 1989 (AGE 17)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,686:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,686:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,687:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Emigrated from South Africa to Canada, worked odd jobs on farms.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,687:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,687:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,688:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  从南非移民到加拿大，在农场打零工。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,688:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,689:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 1990 (AGE 18)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,689:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,689:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,690:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Attended Queen
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,690:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,691:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s University in Ontario.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,691:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,691:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,692:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  就读于安大略省女王大学。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,692:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,693:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 1992 (AGE 20)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,693:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,693:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,694:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Transferred to University of Pennsylvania, studied physics and
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,695:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: engineering.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,695:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,695:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,696:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  转学到宾夕法尼亚大学，学习物理学和工程学。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,696:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,697:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 1994 (AGE 23)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,697:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,697:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,702:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Completed two internships: Pinnacle research working on high energy
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,703:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: density capacitors for electric cars, and a video game company (ironically) called Rocket Science.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,703:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,703:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,704:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,704:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 完成了两次实习：Pinnacle 研究电动汽车高能量密度电容器，以及一家（讽刺地）名为 Rocket Science 的电子游戏公司。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,705:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,705:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 1995 (AGE 24)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,706:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,706:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,707:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Moved to California. Enrolled in Stanford
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,707:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,709:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s physics PhD program, but
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,710:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: deferred. Started Zip2, building software for maps, directories, and publishing online.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,710:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,711:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,711:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  搬到加利福尼亚。注册了斯坦福大学物理学博士项目，但延期了。创办
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,712:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Zip2，建造地图、目录和在线出版的软件。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,712:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,713:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 1999 (AGE 28)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,713:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,714:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,715:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Sold Zip2 for $307 million cash to Compaq (who owned AltaVista).
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,716:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Personal proceeds of ~$22 million.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,716:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,717:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,717:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  以 3.07 亿美元现金将 Zip2 出售给康柏（拥有 AltaVista）。个人收益约 2200 万美元。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,718:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,718:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 1999 (AGE 28)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,719:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,719:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,720:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Started X.com, investing $12 million of his money.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,720:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,721:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,721:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  创办 X.com，投资 1200 万美元自己的钱。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,721:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,722:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 2000 (AGE 29)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,722:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,723:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,725:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  X.com merged with Confinity (founded by Peter Thiel, Max Levchin, and
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,725:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Luke Nosek) to form PayPal.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,726:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,726:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,727:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  X.com 与 Confinity（由彼得·蒂尔、马克斯·列夫琴和卢克·诺塞克创立）合并形成 PayPal。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,727:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,728:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 2001 (AGE 30)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,728:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,729:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,729:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Contracted malaria while on a safari in South Africa. Almost died.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,730:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,730:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,731:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  在南非狩猎旅行时感染疟疾。差点死掉。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,731:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,732:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 2002 (AGE 31)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,732:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,733:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,734:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Sold PayPal to eBay for $1.5 billion. Personal proceeds after tax were
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,735:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ~$170 million. Founded SpaceX.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,735:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,736:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,737:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  以 15 亿美元将 PayPal 出售给 eBay。税后个人收益约 1.7 亿美元。创办 SpaceX。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,737:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,738:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 2004 (AGE 33)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,738:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,739:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,739:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Invested $6.5 million in Tesla Motors, leading the Series A.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,740:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,740:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,741:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  向特斯拉汽车投资 650 万美元，领导 A 轮融资。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,742:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,742:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 2005 (AGE 34)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,743:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,743:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,744:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Invested millions more into Tesla Motors, leading the Series B.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,745:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,745:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,746:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  向特斯拉汽车投资更多数百万美元，领导 B 轮融资。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,746:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,747:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 2006 (AGE 35)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,747:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,748:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,748:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Invested more millions into Tesla Motors, coleading Series C.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,749:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,749:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,750:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  向特斯拉汽车投资更多数百万美元，共同领导 C 轮融资。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,751:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,751:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 2008 (AGE 37)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,752:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,752:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,753:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Falcon becomes the first privately developed rocket to reach orbit.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,753:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,754:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,755:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  猎鹰成为第一枚到达轨道的私人开发火箭。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,755:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,756:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 2008 (AGE 37)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,756:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,757:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,760:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Invested more than $15 million, the remainder of his net worth, into Tesla
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,760:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Motors, leading the Series D. Became CEO of Tesla.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,761:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,762:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,762:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  向特斯拉汽车投资超过 1500 万美元，他的净资产剩余部分，领导 D 轮融资。成为特斯拉 CEO。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,763:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,763:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 2012 (AGE 41)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,764:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,765:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,765:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  First sale of the new Tesla Model S.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,766:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,766:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,767:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  新特斯拉 Model S 首次销售。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,767:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,768:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 2014 (AGE 43)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,769:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,769:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,770:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Co-founded Astra Nova, an online nonprofit school.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,771:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,771:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,772:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  共同创立 Astra Nova，一所在线非营利学校。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,772:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,773:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 2015 (AGE 44)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,774:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,774:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,775:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  First reusable orbital rocket booster landed by SpaceX.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,776:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,776:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,777:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  SpaceX 首次着陆可重复使用轨道火箭助推器。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,777:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,778:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 2015 (AGE 44)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,779:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,779:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,780:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Co-founded a nonprofit called OpenAI.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,781:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,781:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,782:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  共同创立一个名为 OpenAI 的非营利组织。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,782:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,783:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 2016 (AGE 45)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,784:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,784:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,785:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Co-founded Neuralink.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,786:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,786:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,787:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  共同创立 Neuralink。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,788:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,788:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 2017 (AGE 46)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,789:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,789:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,790:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  First Tesla Model 3 delivered.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,791:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,791:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,792:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  第一辆特斯拉 Model 3 交付。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,793:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,793:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 2017 (AGE 46)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,794:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,795:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,795:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  SpaceX achieved world
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,796:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,797:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s first successful flight of a reused rocket.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,797:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,798:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,799:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,799:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: SpaceX 实现了世界上首次成功飞行重复使用的火箭。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,799:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,800:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 2020 (AGE 49)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,801:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,801:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,803:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  First crewed SpaceX flight carries astronauts to the International Space
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,803:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Station.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,804:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,804:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,805:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  首次载人 SpaceX 飞行将宇航员送往国际空间站。
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,806:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,807:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 2021 (AGE 50)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,807:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,808:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: English:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,809:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Becomes richest person in the world (for the first time). Named Time
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,810:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Person of the Year.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,811:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,811:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 中文：
   DEBUG: 2026-03-26 20:04:05,812:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  成为世界上最富有的人（首次）。被命名为《时代》年度人物。
